column2: wave=1:message=&5[Crysta] &fWelcome to the prettiest underground arena you will ever see! Today we have a challenger from somewhere trying to make a name for themselves, let's see how they fare.
column3: wave=1:message=&5[Crysta] &fWelcome to the prettiest underground arena you will ever see! Today we have a challenger from somewhere trying to make a name for themselves, let's see how they fare.

column2: wave=2:message=&5[Crysta] &fSeems like they were not willing to break. Ok, how about something else then!
column3: wave=2:message=&5[Crysta] &fSeems like they were not willing to break. Ok, how about something else then!

column2: wave=3:message=&5[Crysta] &fWhat if they were fighting some slowers, that should slow them down!
column3: wave=3:message=&5[Crysta] &fWhat if they were fighting some slowers, that should slow them down!

column2: wave=4:message=&5[Crysta] &fEvery time I see a dog I go blind. Well not really, it is just a hint.
column3: wave=4:message=&5[Crysta] &fEvery time I see a dog I go blind. Well not really, it is just a hint.

column2: wave=5:message=&5[Crysta] &fI heard that this particular monster if quite fond of arrows.
column3: wave=5:message=&5[Crysta] &fI heard that this particular monster if quite fond of arrows.

column2: wave=6:message=&5[Crysta] &fA healthy mix of monsters is what makes the challenge a challenge.
column3: wave=6:message=&5[Crysta] &fA healthy mix of monsters is what makes the challenge a challenge.

column2: wave=7:message=&5[Crysta] &fPurple crystals promote good health and well-being but they do not help against really angry dogs and skeletons.
column3: wave=7:message=&5[Crysta] &fPurple crystals promote good health and well-being but they do not help against really angry dogs and skeletons.

column2: wave=8:message=&5[Crysta] &fWe do have a lot of angry dogs in storage actually. Or are these wolves...
column3: wave=8:message=&5[Crysta] &fWe do have a lot of angry dogs in storage actually. Or are these wolves...

column2: wave=9:message=&5[Crysta] &fJust when you thought you were getting out they pull you right back in.
column3: wave=9:message=&5[Crysta] &fJust when you thought you were getting out they pull you right back in.

column2: wave=10:message=&5[Crysta] &fFor this next wave our brave challengers will be taking on a living balloon! Exciting!
column3: wave=10:message=&5[Crysta] &fFor this next wave our brave challengers will be taking on a living balloon! Exciting!

column2: wave=11:message=&5[Crysta] &fHot tip. Stay out of the hearts unless you like to get hurt.
column3: wave=11:message=&5[Crysta] &fHot tip. Stay out of the hearts unless you like to get hurt.

column2: wave=12:message=&5[Crysta] &fMore of those wolf-dog things coming right up, oh and some pullers too!
column3: wave=12:message=&5[Crysta] &fMore of those wolf-dog things coming right up, oh and some pullers too!

column2: wave=13:message=&5[Crysta] &fI think that my favorite combination of monsters probably is, blinder, breaker and puller.
column3: wave=13:message=&5[Crysta] &fI think that my favorite combination of monsters probably is, blinder, breaker and puller.

column2: wave=14:message=&5[Crysta] &fYou should SLOW down and enjoy the view. Try not to die though.
column3: wave=14:message=&5[Crysta] &fYou should SLOW down and enjoy the view. Try not to die though.

column2: wave=15:message=&5[Crysta] &fThis particular monster is very unstable and just teleports to its targets at random, how annoying.
column3: wave=15:message=&5[Crysta] &fThis particular monster is very unstable and just teleports to its targets at random, how annoying.

column2: wave=16:message=&5[Crysta] &fOK. Stuff is starting to get interesting now.
column3: wave=16:message=&5[Crysta] &fOK. Las cosas se están poniendo interesantes ahora.

column2: wave=17:message=&5[Crysta] &fYou know what always brightens up my day? Woof-woofs and lots of arrows!
column3: wave=17:message=&5[Crysta] &fYou know what always brightens up my day? Woof-woofs and lots of arrows!

column2: wave=18:message=&5[Crysta] &fI hope you brought a lot of potions of anti-blindness with you.
column3: wave=18:message=&5[Crysta] &fI hope you brought a lot of potions of anti-blindness with you.

column2: wave=19:message=&5[Crysta] &fIs it fun when the monsters die and they pull you back?
column3: wave=19:message=&5[Crysta] &fIs it fun when the monsters die and they pull you back?

column2: wave=20:message=&5[Crysta] &fI heard that this hag was so powerful that we had to cast a spell on it to make it weaker. The more you know.
column3: wave=20:message=&5[Crysta] &fI heard that this hag was so powerful that we had to cast a spell on it to make it weaker. The more you know.

column2: wave=21:message=&5[Crysta] &fI heard that quartz crystals can make you more of a punctual person, is that true?
column3: wave=21:message=&5[Crysta] &fI heard that quartz crystals can make you more of a punctual person, is that true?

column2: wave=22:message=&5[Crysta] &fReally? More of these blinders, how many of these do we have. Sheesh.
column3: wave=22:message=&5[Crysta] &fReally? More of these blinders, how many of these do we have. Sheesh.

column2: wave=23:message=&5[Crysta] &fThe pain-makers seem pretty harmless but I assure you that they are a great threat!
column3: wave=23:message=&5[Crysta] &fThe pain-makers seem pretty harmless but I assure you that they are a great threat!

column2: wave=24:message=&5[Crysta] &fAre you ready for the next wave? I mean not this one, but the one after. You know the one with the boss?
column3: wave=24:message=&5[Crysta] &fAre you ready for the next wave? I mean not this one, but the one after. You know the one with the boss?

column2: wave=25:message=&5[Crysta] &fWait, what... Is that a cow?
wave=26:message=&5[Crysta] &fAnd another moo bites the dust. Next up we got some breakers and you guessed it, more blinders!
column3: wave=26:message=&5[Crysta] &fAnd another moo bites the dust. Next up we got some breakers and you guessed it, more blinders!

column2: wave=27:message=&5[Crysta] &fWhat are these? These are not supposed to be in the arena.
column3: wave=27:message=&5[Crysta] &fWhat are these? These are not supposed to be in the arena.

column2: wave=28:message=&5[Crysta] &fI can describe the entire next encounter using only one word. WOOF!
column3: wave=28:message=&5[Crysta] &fI can describe the entire next encounter using only one word. WOOF!

column2: wave=30:message=&5[Crysta] &fMake sure that you do not get hit by this one or you are gonna regret it.
column3: wave=30:message=&5[Crysta] &fMake sure that you do not get hit by this one or you are gonna regret it.

column2: wave=31:message=&5[Crysta] &fDid you know that 67% of participants do not make it through this next wave?
column3: wave=31:message=&5[Crysta] &fDid you know that 67% of participants do not make it through this next wave?

column2: wave=32:message=&5[Crysta] &fWe got a healthy mix of all sorts of nasties for this one.
column3: wave=32:message=&5[Crysta] &fWe got a healthy mix of all sorts of nasties for this one.

column2: wave=33:message=&5[Crysta] &fNext up it is your favorite monster duo! Guess which ones.
column3: wave=33:message=&5[Crysta] &fNext up it is your favorite monster duo! Guess which ones.

column2: wave=34:message=&5[Crysta] &fWhat does a pain-maker even do anyway?
column3: wave=34:message=&5[Crysta] &f¿Qué hace un creador de dolor de todos modos?

column2: wave=35:message=&5[Crysta] &fWhatever you do, do not get launched into space.
column3: wave=35:message=&5[Crysta] &fHagas lo que hagas, no salgas disparado al espacio.

column2: wave=36:message=&5[Crysta] &fIs being blinded a bad thing when you're in combat?
column3: wave=36:message=&5[Crysta] &f¿Es malo quedarse ciego cuando estás en combate?

column2: wave=38:message=&7You hear barking noises coming from the speakers.
column3: wave=38:message=&7Oyes ladridos provenientes de los altavoces.

column2: wave=39:message=&5[Crysta] &fUhh, sorry about that last one. I might have lost control.
column3: wave=39:message=&5[Crysta] &fUhh, sorry about that last one. I might have lost control.

column3: wave=40:message=&5[Crysta] &fI heard that Calcium really likes getting close to people.

column2: wave=41:message=&5[Crysta] &fPullers again? Really? Why do we have so many of those, sheesh!
column3: wave=41:message=&5[Crysta] &fPullers again? Really? Why do we have so many of those, sheesh!

column2: wave=43:message=&5[Crysta] &fThis next wave is looking pretty rough. Good luck!

column3: wave=46:message=&5[Crysta] &fEstas oleadas se están poniendo realmente desagradables.

column2: wave=47:message=&5[Crysta] &fWhen in doubt just go back to the basics!
column3: wave=47:message=&5[Crysta] &f¡En caso de duda, vuelve a lo básico!

column3: wave=49:message=&5[Crysta] &fWe are just gonna throw everything we have in the arena now.

column3: Hey there! Quite the location, isn't it? Wonderful land, and right in the center, a beautiful manor! Alright, yes... in its current state it might not look like it.

column2: But that's where vision comes in, you see! A grand opportunity to restore the land, fix up the manor, and flip it for a tidy profit!
column3: But that's where vision comes in, you see! A grand opportunity to restore the land, fix up the manor, and flip it for a tidy profit!

column2: Of course, there is the small matter of trouble, undead, ghosts, cursed objects lurking about. But really, if it weren’t for all that 'trouble', this place wouldn't even be up for grabs. So in a way, fortune smiles on us!?
column3: Of course, there is the small matter of trouble, undead, ghosts, cursed objects lurking about. But really, if it weren’t for all that 'trouble', this place wouldn't even be up for grabs. So in a way, fortune smiles on us!?

column3: And you, you look like the adventuring sort. Sword at your side, shield on your back. The strong and capable type who could clear out a few pesky undead, hm? This is a once-in-a-lifetime opportunity.

column2: The place needs to be properly cleansed. I’m fairly certain I saw furniture shifting around in there, not to mention the usual undead wandering about. Such a shame too, valuable antiques like that could have raised the selling price considerably.

column2: From the cracks in the walls, I could tell there are greater threats inside as well; a large, nasty ghost, certainly not like the silly sheet-ghosts we’ve dealt with, and a monstrous, man-eating jello taking up residence.

column2: &e[Alaric]&f Go... find her... release her from her torment... and bring me the crest. It is all that remains of her.
column3: &e[Alaric]&f Go... find her... release her from her torment... and bring me the crest. It is all that remains of her.

column2: &7&oWhat a horrible fate. Let's help out this poor ghost.
column3: &7&oWhat a horrible fate. Let's help out this poor ghost.

column2: &e[Alaric]&f Ah… the crest… you’ve done it. Lady Hale can finally rest… and so can I, a little. You’ve earned a reward… but… there is still one more thing I need your help with… if you are willing.
column3: &e[Alaric]&f Ah… the crest… you’ve done it. Lady Hale can finally rest… and so can I, a little. You’ve earned a reward… but… there is still one more thing I need your help with… if you are willing.

column2: &7&oI am sure I have enough time to help them out again.
column3: &7&oI am sure I have enough time to help them out again.

column2: Ah... a visitor... after all these years... Do you feel it? That strange warmth that lingers here... not right, is it?
column3: Ah... a visitor... after all these years... Do you feel it? That strange warmth that lingers here... not right, is it?

column2: This manor... it used to be grand. The envy of every noble nearby. We had wealth, comfort... and yet it wasn’t enough. The Holloway Family... always showing off.
column3: This manor... it used to be grand. The envy of every noble nearby. We had wealth, comfort... and yet it wasn’t enough. The Holloway Family... always showing off.

column2: When they got their new heating system... I couldn’t let them outshine me. So I had one built... magical, alive with power. At first... it was wonderful. The air shimmered, the walls hummed... people whispered about our brilliance.
column3: When they got their new heating system... I couldn’t let them outshine me. So I had one built... magical, alive with power. At first... it was wonderful. The air shimmered, the walls hummed... people whispered about our brilliance.

column2: But then... it went wrong. The warmth... it grew... it watched. Floors creaked on their own. Chairs moved. Whispers in the vents... laughter from the cellar. I told everyone it was nothing... pride made me blind.
column3: But then... it went wrong. The warmth... it grew... it watched. Floors creaked on their own. Chairs moved. Whispers in the vents... laughter from the cellar. I told everyone it was nothing... pride made me blind.

column2: Too late... the furnace took over. The house... it devoured us. My wife... Lady Hale... she lingers on as a phantom, twisted by the same curse. She guards something precious... her crest.
column3: Too late... the furnace took over. The house... it devoured us. My wife... Lady Hale... she lingers on as a phantom, twisted by the same curse. She guards something precious... her crest.

column2: &e[Alaric]&f Do not worry about the others... the lost wanderers... Focus on what is mine... so that our family... can finally rest. Go now... The house watches...
column3: &e[Alaric]&f Do not worry about the others... the lost wanderers... Focus on what is mine... so that our family... can finally rest. Go now... The house watches...

column2: &7&oI need to slay the &c&oOoze and gather bones from the &c&oSkeletons that wander the manor and its surroundings.
column3: &7&oI need to slay the &c&oOoze and gather bones from the &c&oSkeletons that wander the manor and its surroundings.

column2: &a[Alaric]&f You have done it... all my family... finally at rest. You have freed them from decades of unrest, and in doing so, lifted a great weight from this house... and from me.
column3: &a[Alaric]&f You have done it... all my family... finally at rest. You have freed them from decades of unrest, and in doing so, lifted a great weight from this house... and from me.

column2: The bones that linger here... some belong to my family... others... strangers, foolish adventurers, treasure-seekers, or those who thought they could purge evil from this house. They tried... and failed... and now they wander as skeletons, lost to time.
column3: The bones that linger here... some belong to my family... others... strangers, foolish adventurers, treasure-seekers, or those who thought they could purge evil from this house. They tried... and failed... and now they wander as skeletons, lost to time.

column2: What I ask of you... is to gather my family’s bones. They are scattered, hidden among the others... silent victims of this curse. Only when they are together... only then... can they finally rest.
column3: What I ask of you... is to gather my family’s bones. They are scattered, hidden among the others... silent victims of this curse. Only when they are together... only then... can they finally rest.

column2: But it will not be easy... There is one who guards some of them... a foul creature, an ooze... a horrible thing that swallowed some of the bones long ago.
column3: But it will not be easy... There is one who guards some of them... a foul creature, an ooze... a horrible thing that swallowed some of the bones long ago.

column2: It slithers through the manor, and its hunger binds what it has consumed. You... you must put an end to it. Free the bones from its grasp...
column3: It slithers through the manor, and its hunger binds what it has consumed. You... you must put an end to it. Free the bones from its grasp...

column2: &d[Salty Jack]&f Aye, if ye be willin', might ye be so kind as to kick some pirate arse while yer on yer way? And make sure to send that lyin' scurvy dog &cRedbeard&f to the sea for me!
column3: &d[Jack el Salado]&f Aye, si estás dispuesto, ¿serías tan amable de patear algunos culos piratas mientras estás en camino? ¡Y asegúrate de enviar a ese perro sarnoso y mentiroso de &cBarbarroja&f al mar por mí!

column2: &7&oIt's time to head East. Have to make sure to stop by &cRedbeard's&f ship and ensure that he and his crew become well acquainted with the blade of my sword before I meet with the &dFormer Pirate&f crew member.
column3: &7&oEs hora de dirigirse al Este. Tengo que asegurarme de pasar por el barco de &cBarbarroja&f y asegurarme de que él y su tripulación se familiaricen bien con la hoja de mi espada antes de reunirme con el miembro de la tripulación &dAntiguo Pirata&f.

column2: &d[Freezing Buccaneer]&f So, ye came here to tell me 'bout a crew of former pirates that's lookin' fer the likes of me, eh? What be their game, and what mischief be they plannin'? As a former pirate meself, I be always keen on hearin' 'bout a good adventure! Tell me more, matey!
column3: &d[Bucanero Gélido]&f Así que viniste aquí a contarme sobre una tripulación de antiguos piratas que buscan a gente como yo, ¿eh? ¿Cuál es su juego y qué travesuras planean? Como antiguo pirata que soy, ¡siempre estoy deseando escuchar sobre una buena aventura! ¡Cuéntame más, compañero!

column2: &7&oSeems like &dFreezing Buccaneer&f has a new quest for me.
column3: &7&oParece que &dBucanero Gélido&f tiene una nueva misión para mí.

column2: Ahoy there, matey! You look like a reliable sort.
We're a band of former pirates, see. Tired of the backstabbin' and betrayals.
column3: We're a band of former pirates, see. Tired of the backstabbin' and betrayals.

column2: There was supposed to be a grand coalition of three crews, but it all went to Davy Jones' locker.
column3: There was supposed to be a grand coalition of three crews, but it all went to Davy Jones' locker.

column2: Greed got the better of 'em, and we ended up with nothin' but broken promises and empty pockets.
column3: Greed got the better of 'em, and we ended up with nothin' but broken promises and empty pockets.

column2: So, we decided to chart our own course. Found a few good lads and lasses who felt the same way.
column3: So, we decided to chart our own course. Found a few good lads and lasses who felt the same way.

column2: But there's more crew we heard of, quit under similar circumstances.
column3: But there's more crew we heard of, quit under similar circumstances.

column2: They were located east of here last we heard. Figured you could get over there and see if they're interested in joinin' us.
column3: They were located east of here last we heard. Figured you could get over there and see if they're interested in joinin' us.

column2: We're buildin' somethin' new here, somethin' honorable. What d'ya say, you in?
column3: Estamos construyendo algo nuevo aquí, algo honorable. ¿Qué dices, te apuntas?

column2: &d[Freezing Buccaneer]&f Arr, sorry to trouble ye, but could I ask one last favor? Would ye mind clearin' out some of these great big fed bears so I can navigate without gettin' me legs chewed off?
column3: &d[Bucanero Gélido]&f Arr, siento molestarte, ¿pero podría pedirte un último favor? ¿Te importaría despejar algunos de estos grandes osos bien alimentados para que pueda navegar sin que me arranquen las piernas a mordiscos?

column2: &7&oIt's time to head North. First, I've got to slay some bears, After that, I'll deal with &fWhitebeard&f and his crew, and finally, I'll meet up with the former pirate crew member, &dPeg Leg Keg&f. That should cover everything.
column3: &7&oEs hora de dirigirse al Norte. Primero, tengo que matar algunos osos, después de eso, me encargaré de &fBarba Blanca&f y su tripulación, y finalmente, me reuniré con el miembro de la antigua tripulación pirata, &dBarril Pata de Palo&f. Eso debería cubrirlo todo.

column2: &d[Peg Leg Keg]&f Ahoy there, matey! Bless yer heart fer findin' me. hic I been wanderin' these parts fer longer than I care t'remember. Now that ye're here, I reckon there's a bit o' a favor I need t'ask. hic Ye see, there's a wee bit o' trouble brewin' that I could use yer help with.
column3: &d[Barril Pata de Palo]&f ¡Ahoy, compañero! Bendito seas por encontrarme. hic He estado vagando por estos lares más tiempo del que quiero recordar. Ahora que estás aquí, creo que hay un pequeño favor que necesito pedirte. hic Verás, hay un pequeño problema gestándose con el que podría usar tu ayuda.

column2: &7&oI should hear what &dPeg Leg Keg&f has to say.
column3: &7&oDebería escuchar lo que &dBarril Pata de Palo&f tiene que decir.

column2: Avast! Thanks for findin' me, matey. Thought I'd be shark bait by now.
column3: ¡Avante! Gracias por encontrarme, compañero. Pensé que ya sería cebo de tiburón.

column2: Heard about &dSalty Jack&c and his crew. Good to know there's still some honor left in this world.
column3: Heard about &dSalty Jack&c and his crew. Good to know there's still some honor left in this world.

column2: Say, you wouldn't happen to be sailin' south, would ye? There be another lad what left the coalition.
column3: Say, you wouldn't happen to be sailin' south, would ye? There be another lad what left the coalition.

column2: Goes by the name &dPeg Leg Keg&f. Last I saw him, he was on some ice sheet.
column3: Goes by the name &dPeg Leg Keg&f. Last I saw him, he was on some ice sheet.

column2: While you're at it... could ye do me a favor?  That blasted &fWhitebeard&f, he... he's the reason my parrot Polly's gone to the great beyond.
column3: While you're at it... could ye do me a favor?  That blasted &fWhitebeard&f, he... he's the reason my parrot Polly's gone to the great beyond.

column2: If you see any o' his scallywags, give 'em a taste o' yer steel. And if ye find &fWhitebeard&f himself, make 'im pay for what he did!
column3: If you see any o' his scallywags, give 'em a taste o' yer steel. And if ye find &fWhitebeard&f himself, make 'im pay for what he did!

column2: &d[Peg Leg Keg]&f The &cBlackbeard's&f ship be the great big one in the middle, ye can’t miss it with its size and its golden rear! Give ’em a taste of hell, matey!
column3: &d[Barril Pata de Palo]&f El barco de &cBarbanegra&f es el grande que está en el medio, ¡no puedes perderlo con su tamaño y su popa dorada! ¡Dales una probada del infierno, compañero!

column2: &7&oIt's time to head to &cBlackbeard's&f ship and make sure to take care of the crew and &cBleackbeard&f himself for good!
column3: &7&oEs hora de dirigirse al barco de &cBarbanegra&f y asegurarse de encargarse de la tripulación y del propio &cBarbanegra&f para siempre.

column2: &d[Salty Jack]&f Back already, lad? We hear tell ye found the crew that needed ye. They spun tales of yer grand deeds and the crooked pirates ye’ve put to the sword. But if ye don’t mind, there be one last thing I’d like yer ear to catch.
column3: &d[Jack el Salado]&f ¿Ya de vuelta, muchacho? Oímos decir que encontraste a la tripulación que te necesitaba. Contaron historias de tus grandes hazañas y de los piratas deshonestos a los que pasaste por la espada. Pero si no te importa, hay una última cosa que me gustaría que escucharas.

column2: &7&oHmm, seems like &dSalty Jack&f might have one last quest for me.
column3: &7&oHmm, parece que &dJack el Salado&f podría tener una última misión para mí.

column2: Shiver me timbers!  You found me!  Thought I was destined to wander these frozen wastes forever.
column3: Shiver me timbers!  You found me!  Thought I was destined to wander these frozen wastes forever.

column2: &dSalty Jack&f, eh?  A good man, leadin' an honorable crew. I'll be sure to join 'em soon.
column3: &dJack el Salado&f, ¿eh? Un buen hombre, liderando una tripulación honorable. Me aseguraré de unirme a ellos pronto.

column2: But before I go... there's a score I need settled. That blackhearted fiend, &cBlackbeard&f, and his whole rotten crew!
column3: But before I go... there's a score I need settled. That blackhearted fiend, &cBlackbeard&f, and his whole rotten crew!

column2: They plundered my ship, stole me treasure, and left me for dead!  They deserve to be  feedin' the fishes!
column3: They plundered my ship, stole me treasure, and left me for dead!  They deserve to be  feedin' the fishes!

column2: Do what ya gotta do, matey. Send &cBlackbeard&f and his lot to the depths. Make 'em pay for their crimes!
column3: Do what ya gotta do, matey. Send &cBlackbeard&f and his lot to the depths. Make 'em pay for their crimes!

column2: Once the deed is done, head back to &dSalty Jack&f.  Tell him &dPeg Leg Keg's&f on his way... with a tale o' vengeance!
column3: Once the deed is done, head back to &dSalty Jack&f.  Tell him &dPeg Leg Keg's&f on his way... with a tale o' vengeance!

column2: &d[Salty Jack]&f Head East, towards the tallest, most treacherous peak.  Find the mage's tomb, claim the treasure... and become a legend yourself!
column3: &d[Salty Jack]&f Dirígete al Este, hacia el pico más alto y traicionero. Encuentra la tumba del mago, reclama el tesoro... ¡y conviértete tú mismo en una leyenda!

column2: &7&oI have a really bad feeling about this. I should prepare before heading there.
column3: &7&oTengo un muy mal presentimiento sobre esto. Debería prepararme antes de ir allí.

column2: &d[Salty Jack]&f Ah, ye be back! That can only mean one thing: ye got the treasure! Do tell, were the stories true? Was he there? Ah, never mind, best not to delve into such unnatural tales. As promised, here’s yer half of the treasure!
column3: &d[Salty Jack]&f ¡Ah, has vuelto! Eso solo puede significar una cosa: ¡conseguiste el tesoro! Dime, ¿eran ciertas las historias? ¿Estaba él allí? Ah, no importa, mejor no indagar en tales cuentos antinaturales. ¡Como prometí, aquí tienes tu mitad del tesoro!

column2: &7&oWhat kind of medallion turns someone into a powerful goat...
column3: &7&oQué clase de medallón convierte a alguien en una cabra poderosa...

column2: Avast, matey! Ye've done us a right turn, findin' those lost souls and dealin' with those treacherous captains.
column3: Avast, matey! Ye've done us a right turn, findin' those lost souls and dealin' with those treacherous captains.

column2: The brotherhood's stronger for it. But I've seen the fire in yer eyes, the way ye handle a blade... Ye're meant for greater things.
column3: The brotherhood's stronger for it. But I've seen the fire in yer eyes, the way ye handle a blade... Ye're meant for greater things.

column2: I've heard tell of an old legend, a tale passed down through generations of sea dogs.
column3: I've heard tell of an old legend, a tale passed down through generations of sea dogs.

column2: They say there was once a powerful pirate mage, a master of the arcane arts, sailed these very waters.
column3: They say there was once a powerful pirate mage, a master of the arcane arts, sailed these very waters.

column2: When his time came, he was buried atop a towering ice peak, his vast treasure entombed alongside him.
column3: When his time came, he was buried atop a towering ice peak, his vast treasure entombed alongside him.

column2: Some whisper that his spirit still lingers, guardin' his loot with icy wrath. A risky venture, to be sure...
column3: Some whisper that his spirit still lingers, guardin' his loot with icy wrath. A risky venture, to be sure...

column2: But the rewards... unimaginable riches, enough to make even a king jealous. 50/50 split, matey. What d'ya say?
column3: But the rewards... unimaginable riches, enough to make even a king jealous. 50/50 split, matey. What d'ya say?

column2: They are filled with cursed magic, driven by the vampires to do their bidding.
column3: Están llenos de magia maldita, impulsados por los vampiros para cumplir sus órdenes.

column2: And the &cDrained Husks&f... those poor souls... they're nothing but empty shells, used as tools by the vampires.
column3: And the &cDrained Husks&f... those poor souls... they're nothing but empty shells, used as tools by the vampires.

column2: There is also a personal request I would like to make... There are several &cEnraged Spirits&f roaming about.
column3: There is also a personal request I would like to make... There are several &cEnraged Spirits&f roaming about.

column2: Among them, one carries my beloved family's &eNecklace&f... my family member... they're gone, taken by the vampires. I need you to recover it for me...
column3: Among them, one carries my beloved family's &eNecklace&f... my family member... they're gone, taken by the vampires. I need you to recover it for me...

column2: &e[Jessamyn] &fYou were sent by another survivor? I thought I was the only one left alive...
column3: &e[Jessamyn] &f¿Fuiste enviado por otro superviviente? Creí que era la única que quedaba viva...

column2: &e[Kamil] &fThank you again for your help. May the light watch over you on your journey.
column3: &e[Kamil] &fGracias de nuevo por tu ayuda. Que la luz te acompañe en tu viaje.

column2: &7&oI should head out to the building located to the West and slay any creatures on the way there.
column3: &7&oDebería dirigirme al edificio situado al Oeste y matar cualquier criatura en el camino.

column2: I saw a flicker... a faint light, coming from a building.
column3: Vi un parpadeo... una luz tenue, viniendo de un edificio.

column2: There might be someone else out there, another survivor.
column3: Podría haber alguien más ahí fuera, otro superviviente.

column2: I need you to investigate, but be careful...
column3: Necesito que investigues, pero ten cuidado...

column2: Those creatures still roam the village. Clear any threats you come across.
column3: Esas criaturas aún deambulan por la aldea. Elimina cualquier amenaza que encuentres.

column2: Make the area a safer place, even if it is just for a little bit.
column3: Haz la zona un lugar más seguro, aunque sea solo por un poco.

column2: &e[Jessamyn] &cKain&f should be somewhere to the East, near our old house...
column3: &e[Jessamyn] &cKain&f debería estar en algún lugar al Este, cerca de nuestra vieja casa...

column2: &7&oTime to go locate &c&oKain&7&o and bring back the &e&oCrossbow&7&o. He should be somewhere to the East near a ruined building.
column3: &7&oHora de ir a localizar a &c&oKain&7&o y traer de vuelta la &e&oBallesta&7&o. Debería estar en algún lugar al Este cerca de un edificio en ruinas.

column2: &e[Jessamyn] &fYou have put my brother to rest? Thank you...
column3: &e[Jessamyn] &f¿Has puesto a mi hermano a descansar? Gracias...

column2: &e[Jessamyn] &fThe &eCrossbow&f... it seems to be broken, but I think I can repair it. I was always good with my hands.
column3: &e[Jessamyn] &fLa &eBallesta&f... parece estar rota, pero creo que puedo repararla. Siempre fui buena con mis manos.

column2: &7&oI should talk to &e&oJessamyn&7&o and see if there is anything I can do help her repair the bow.
column3: &7&oDebería hablar con &e&oJessamyn&7&o y ver si hay algo que pueda hacer para ayudarla a reparar la ballesta.

column2: I've been hiding, trying to survive.
The vampires, they took everything. My brother, Kain, he was the bravest of us all.
column3: The vampires, they took everything. My brother, Kain, he was the bravest of us all.

column2: He fought to protect me, to keep me safe. He sent me away, told me to hide.
column3: He fought to protect me, to keep me safe. He sent me away, told me to hide.

column2: But the vampires, they turned him into one of them. A powerful, monstrous creature.
column3: Pero los vampiros, lo convirtieron en uno de ellos. Una criatura poderosa y monstruosa.

column2: I need you to put him to rest. To end his suffering. He would want that, and I can't bear the thought of him roaming free.
column3: I need you to put him to rest. To end his suffering. He would want that, and I can't bear the thought of him roaming free.

column2: Kain used to be a skilled hunter. He had a &eCrossbow&f, a powerful weapon, it could help you fight the vampires, I need you to retrieve it.
column3: Kain used to be a skilled hunter. He had a &eCrossbow&f, a powerful weapon, it could help you fight the vampires, I need you to retrieve it.

column2: &e[Jessamyn] &fGo on ahead, I will go look for the enchanted wood while you go into the manor.
column3: &e[Jessamyn] &fAdelante, iré a buscar la madera encantada mientras tú entras en la mansión.

column2: &7&oI need to enter &d&oThe Vampire Manor&7&o and find some &e&oString&7&o that could be used to repair the &e&oCrossbow&7&o.
column3: &7&oNecesito entrar en &d&oLa Mansión Vampírica&7&o y encontrar alguna &e&oCuerda&7&o que pueda usarse para reparar la &e&oBallesta&7&o.

column2: &7&oI should also use this chance to slay some of the evil creatures that reside there.
column3: &7&oTambién debería aprovechar esta oportunidad para matar a algunas de las criaturas malvadas que residen allí.

column2: &e[Jessamyn] &fYou are back! I hope you made those fiends suffer! Did you find a replacement string?
column3: &e[Jessamyn] &f¡Has vuelto! ¡Espero que hayas hecho sufrir a esos demonios! ¿Encontraste una cuerda de reemplazo?

column2: &e[Jessamyn] &fAhhh, yes. This will do! We are just missing a catalyst now...
column3: &e[Jessamyn] &fAhhh, sí. ¡Esto servirá! Ahora solo nos falta un catalizador...

column2: This is no ordinary &eCrossbow&f, it needs special materials to repair. I know where to find enchanted wood for the handle, but we need a new string.
column3: This is no ordinary &eCrossbow&f, it needs special materials to repair. I know where to find enchanted wood for the handle, but we need a new string.

column2: I believe &dThe Vampire Manor&f might have something suitable.
column3: Creo que &dLa Mansión Vampírica&f podría tener algo adecuado.

column2: Go into the manor, find something that can replace the string.
column3: Entra en la mansión, encuentra algo que pueda reemplazar la cuerda.

column2: And while you're at it, deal with the monsters inside. Those creatures have no right to live after what they did to our village, to my family. No mercy for those fiends!
column3: And while you're at it, deal with the monsters inside. Those creatures have no right to live after what they did to our village, to my family. No mercy for those fiends!

column2: &e[Jessamyn] &fThis is our chance to reclaim the village, to avenge our lost loved ones. We cannot fail!
column3: &e[Jessamyn] &fEsta es nuestra oportunidad de reclamar la aldea, de vengar a nuestros seres queridos perdidos. ¡No podemos fallar!

column2: &7&oI need to head into &d&oThe Vampire Manor&7&o, slay any vampires I find there and retrieve &c&oThe Vampire King's&e&o Heart&7&o.
column3: &7&oNecesito dirigirme a &d&oLa Mansión Vampírica&7&o, matar a cualquier vampiro que encuentre allí y recuperar el &c&oCorazón&7&o &e&odel Rey Vampiro&7&o.

column2: &e[Jessamyn] &fYou did it! You've vanquished the king and his vile servants! My family, no... the entire village can finally rest.
column3: &e[Jessamyn] &f¡Lo hiciste! ¡Has vencido al rey y a sus viles sirvientes! Mi familia, no... toda la aldea finalmente puede descansar.

column2: &e[Jessamyn] &fThe heart was the last piece I needed to repair the &eCrossbow&f. It's ready for you to use against any other vampires you may encounter. Thank you for everything, goodbye.
column3: &e[Jessamyn] &fEl corazón era la última pieza que necesitaba para reparar la &eBallesta&f. Está lista para que la uses contra cualquier otro vampiro que puedas encontrar. Gracias por todo, adiós.

column2: &7&oI don't think this place will ever be able to recover to its former beauty. But at least the vampires will not be able to hurt anyone else.
column3: &7&oNo creo que este lugar pueda recuperar alguna vez su antigua belleza. Pero al menos los vampiros no podrán hacer daño a nadie más.

column2: This is it, the final push! We can cleanse this land of the vampires, for good.
column3: This is it, the final push! We can cleanse this land of the vampires, for good.

column2: To restore the &eCrossbow&f to its full power, we need a catalyst, a source of powerful magic.
column3: To restore the &eCrossbow&f to its full power, we need a catalyst, a source of powerful magic.

column2: &cThe Vampire King&f, who holds dominion over this manor, is a potent magical being.  His &eHeart&f would be the perfect catalyst!
column3: &cEl Rey Vampiro&f, quien tiene dominio sobre esta mansión, es un ser mágico potente. ¡Su &eCorazón&f sería el catalizador perfecto!

column2: But first, we must end their reign of terror. The powerful vampires are the source of their strength. Destroy them, and the lesser ones they turned will wither and die.
column3: But first, we must end their reign of terror. The powerful vampires are the source of their strength. Destroy them, and the lesser ones they turned will wither and die.

column2: Go into the manor, eliminate every vampire within. Make them pay for their horrible deeds. Then, retrieve the king's &eHeart&f.
column3: Go into the manor, eliminate every vampire within. Make them pay for their horrible deeds. Then, retrieve the king's &eHeart&f.

column2: &cForged in the fires of a thousand sunsets.
column3: &cForjado en los fuegos de mil atardeceres.

column2: &cWhispers of ancient battles echo in its string.
column3: &cSusurros de batallas antiguas resuenan en su cuerda.

column2: &cWrought from the fangs of a fallen fiend.
column3: &cForjada de los colmillos de un demonio caído.

column2: &cNo vampire can withstand its deadly embrace.
column3: &cNingún vampiro puede resistir su abrazo mortal.
&cReforjada por una hermana con el corazón roto.

column2: &cits bloody string hums with the night.
column3: &csu cuerda sangrienta zumba con la noche.

column2: &cA stolen echo of the vampire king's
&cpower, beats with a final, chilling rhythm.
column3: &csu poder, late con un ritmo final y escalofriante.

column2: &aYou can use this rod to catch amazing fish!
column3: &aYou can use this rod to catch amazing fish!

column2: &dMr. Choppington thrives in gathering and growth.
column3: &dMr. Choppington thrives in gathering and growth.

column2: &7This blade carries the strength of ancient roots.
column3: &7This blade carries the strength of ancient roots.

column2: &7Though fragile in form, its power is undeniable.
column3: &7Though fragile in form, its power is undeniable.

column2: &2The God of Mischief has had enough fun for today!
column3: &2The God of Mischief has had enough fun for today!

column2: &cThe God of Mischief has blessed us with his presence!
column3: &cThe God of Mischief has blessed us with his presence!

column2: &8Boots that once walked the branches of Yggdrasil.
column3: &8Boots that once walked the branches of Yggdrasil.

column2: &8Greaves touched by the fires of Muspelheim.
column3: &8Greaves touched by the fires of Muspelheim.

column2: Loki is just the best god!
column3: Loki is just the best god!

column2: We shall see each other again!
column3: We shall see each other again!

column2: It is a joy to see you!
column3: It is a joy to see you!

column2: Do you have any exciting news?
column3: Do you have any exciting news?

column2: Loki is totally the best god!
column3: Loki is totally the best god!

column2: Light of the day with you!
column3: Light of the day with you!

column2: Such a beautiful day, look at that sun!
column3: Such a beautiful day, look at that sun!

column2: &bYou feel light on your toes, almost as if the ground
column3: &bYou feel light on your toes, almost as if the ground

column2: &6A glimmer of cunning dances across its surface,
column3: &6A glimmer of cunning dances across its surface,

column2: &2Every step you take seems a little quicker,
column3: &2Every step you take seems a little quicker,

column2: What is even going on here.
column3: What is even going on here.

column2: &6[Rune]&fYou wouldn’t mind cutting down a few of those pesky creatures on your way, would you? &eIngrid, the Wise Woman &flives just a short walk from here, up in that fancy house on the hill.
column3: &6[Rune]&fYou wouldn’t mind cutting down a few of those pesky creatures on your way, would you? &eIngrid, the Wise Woman &flives just a short walk from here, up in that fancy house on the hill.

column2: &7&oI need to be careful, these creatures aren’t like anything I’ve faced before.
column3: &7&oI need to be careful, these creatures aren’t like anything I’ve faced before.

column2: &6[Ingrid]&fSo Rune sent you. Those creatures you met, they are not here by chance. And the villagers trance... it reeks of a trickster’s hand. I may know who is behind it, aye.
column3: &6[Ingrid]&fSo Rune sent you. Those creatures you met, they are not here by chance. And the villagers trance... it reeks of a trickster’s hand. I may know who is behind it, aye.

column2: Oh, Praise Odin! Am I glad to see some adventurers!
column3: Oh, Praise Odin! Am I glad to see some adventurers!

column2: Something’s off in town. Strange little beasts running about they're not hurting anyone, just pulling pranks, making a mess of things.
column3: Something’s off in town. Strange little beasts running about they're not hurting anyone, just pulling pranks, making a mess of things.

column2: The livestock won’t settle, and tools go missing as if the ground itself swallowed them. And the villagers... half of them just wander around muttering nonsense, like they’re half-asleep.
column3: The livestock won’t settle, and tools go missing as if the ground itself swallowed them. And the villagers... half of them just wander around muttering nonsense, like they’re half-asleep.

column2: Gives me chills to look at them too long. I can’t make sense of it, but the &eWise Woman &fmight. She always knows more than she lets on. Go find her, maybe she can tell you what in Hel’s name is going on.
column3: Gives me chills to look at them too long. I can’t make sense of it, but the &eWise Woman &fmight. She always knows more than she lets on. Go find her, maybe she can tell you what in Hel’s name is going on.

column2: &aAn intricate device with many gears and
column3: &aAn intricate device with many gears and

column2: &agolden inlays, centered around a large crystal.
column3: &agolden inlays, centered around a large crystal.

column2: I feel like this prank went too far.
column3: I feel like this prank went too far.

column2: Only one god could be behind this mess...
column3: Only one god could be behind this mess...

column2: &6[Ingrid]&fFeel free to clear some of these beasts while you head towards the cave, I really do not need any more of them coming to my house and stealing my valuable property.
column3: &6[Ingrid]&fFeel free to clear some of these beasts while you head towards the cave, I really do not need any more of them coming to my house and stealing my valuable property.

column2: &6[Ingrid]&fYou can reach the cave by going behind the hill and following the river to the east.
column3: &6[Ingrid]&fYou can reach the cave by going behind the hill and following the river to the east.

column2: &6[Ingrid]&fOnce you have the device, bring it to &eTor-Olav&f, a man of strong body and mind. I doubt Loki's charm spell could have swayed him, and he has more than enough brawn to operate the device.
column3: &6[Ingrid]&fOnce you have the device, bring it to &eTor-Olav&f, a man of strong body and mind. I doubt Loki's charm spell could have swayed him, and he has more than enough brawn to operate the device.

column2: &7&oAn Ice Giant, never fought one of those before, I mean how big could it be...
column3: &7&oAn Ice Giant, never fought one of those before, I mean how big could it be...

column2: &6[Tor-Olav]&fYou want me to operate this device? Alright, but first... we need to talk. I need an explanation of everything that’s happened.
column3: &6[Tor-Olav]&fYou want me to operate this device? Alright, but first... we need to talk. I need an explanation of everything that’s happened.

column2: So Rune sent you, then... Good, we need help. The villagers are dazed, mumbling nonsense as if caught in some strange trance, and mischievous beasts run through the town causing chaos.
column3: So Rune sent you, then... Good, we need help. The villagers are dazed, mumbling nonsense as if caught in some strange trance, and mischievous beasts run through the town causing chaos.

column2: That enormous tree growing in the center… a seed of Yggdrasil... it is unnatural, and it seems tied to these disturbances.
column3: That enormous tree growing in the center… a seed of Yggdrasil... it is unnatural, and it seems tied to these disturbances.

column2: Only a god could have such power to cause all of this in so short a time. There is only one god I can think of who might be behind it, the god of mischief himself, Loki.
column3: Only a god could have such power to cause all of this in so short a time. There is only one god I can think of who might be behind it, the god of mischief himself, Loki.

column2: But he is not a god of evil, his pranks and tricks usually have a reason. And I think I know what might be going on.
column3: But he is not a god of evil, his pranks and tricks usually have a reason. And I think I know what might be going on.

column2: You see, an unnatural cold has been creeping across the village for some time, threatening crops and wells. If left unchecked, it would have been the end of this village and its people.
column3: You see, an unnatural cold has been creeping across the village for some time, threatening crops and wells. If left unchecked, it would have been the end of this village and its people.

column2: But now, the cold does not bite as before, it feels fresh and natural, as if some being of immense power, perhaps a god, has stopped it at its root.
column3: But now, the cold does not bite as before, it feels fresh and natural, as if some being of immense power, perhaps a god, has stopped it at its root.

column2: The chaos and the strange creatures, however, I suspect... that may be Loki’s idea of repayment, his amusement for saving us.
column3: The chaos and the strange creatures, however, I suspect... that may be Loki’s idea of repayment, his amusement for saving us.

column2: There is a device that measures the cold, but a harpy stole it and brought it to an ice giant hiding in a nearby cave. I cannot operate the device myself anymore, my hands are too old to manage it.
column3: There is a device that measures the cold, but a harpy stole it and brought it to an ice giant hiding in a nearby cave. I cannot operate the device myself anymore, my hands are too old to manage it.

column2: I need you to slay the beasts, defeat the ice giant, and bring the device back.
column3: I need you to slay the beasts, defeat the ice giant, and bring the device back.

column2: Once another can read it, we will know if the frost has truly been stopped and confirm that Loki’s intervention saved the village. Everything else is just his playful payment.
column3: Once another can read it, we will know if the frost has truly been stopped and confirm that Loki’s intervention saved the village. Everything else is just his playful payment.

column2: Well, I guess this could have been a lot worse.
column3: Well, I guess this could have been a lot worse.

column2: &6[Tor-Olav]&f Ha! That’s the spirit! Head east to the arena and show that Wyrm what for before it burns the place to cinders.
column3: &6[Tor-Olav]&f Ha! That’s the spirit! Head east to the arena and show that Wyrm what for before it burns the place to cinders.

column2: &6[Tor-Olav]&f And hey, if you spot any of those little beasties skulking about on your way, knock a few down. Never hurts to give the village some peace and quiet while you’re at it.
column3: &6[Tor-Olav]&f And hey, if you spot any of those little beasties skulking about on your way, knock a few down. Never hurts to give the village some peace and quiet while you’re at it.

column2: &7&oGrabbing some fire protection before I fight the Wyrm might be a good idea.
column3: &7&oGrabbing some fire protection before I fight the Wyrm might be a good idea.

column2: &6[Tor-Olav]&f Ha! Well struck, my friend! That Wyrm won’t be scorching our fine arena any time soon thanks to you.
column3: &6[Tor-Olav]&f Ha! Well struck, my friend! That Wyrm won’t be scorching our fine arena any time soon thanks to you.

column2: &6[Tor-Olav]&f Some might ask why I didn’t take care of it myself but, truth be told, if I went swinging in there, we’d have no arena left standing!
column3: &6[Tor-Olav]&f Some might ask why I didn’t take care of it myself but, truth be told, if I went swinging in there, we’d have no arena left standing!

column2: &6[Tor-Olav]&f Now, rest a moment and catch your breath. We’ll need to talk again soon, there’s still a god left to deal with, and I’ll need your strength once more.
column3: &6[Tor-Olav]&f Now, rest a moment and catch your breath. We’ll need to talk again soon, there’s still a god left to deal with, and I’ll need your strength once more.

column2: &7&oI should speak to &eTor-Olav again to hear what more he has to say.
column3: &7&oI should speak to &eTor-Olav again to hear what more he has to say.

column2: Ho! So you’re the one &eIngrid &fsent. Aye, we’ve talked it all through, and I get the whole story now. Quite the mess you’ve been wrapped up in, eh?
column3: Ho! So you’re the one &eIngrid &fsent. Aye, we’ve talked it all through, and I get the whole story now. Quite the mess you’ve been wrapped up in, eh?

column2: Here, hand me that fancy contraption. I may not look the part, but these big mitts can turn a gear or two.
column3: Here, hand me that fancy contraption. I may not look the part, but these big mitts can turn a gear or two.

column2: &oHe fumbles a bit, then the Frost-Sense Crystal hums and glows. &fHa! Look at that! Ingrid was right! No more chill creeping over the village. Whatever was causing the biting cold, sure is gone now!
column3: &oHe fumbles a bit, then the Frost-Sense Crystal hums and glows. &fHa! Look at that! Ingrid was right! No more chill creeping over the village. Whatever was causing the biting cold, sure is gone now!

column2: I guess Loki truly did come to aid us after all, though his way of taking payment is... troublesome.
column3: I guess Loki truly did come to aid us after all, though his way of taking payment is... troublesome.

column2: But don’t think you’re getting a break just yet. There’s a new fire to put out, quite literally!
column3: But don’t think you’re getting a break just yet. There’s a new fire to put out, quite literally!

column2: The arena down east is being rebuilt, prettier than a bride’s dress on midsummer’s day. But a Wyrm has taken residence of the place, and if we let it sit, it’ll roast the timber, stone, and cloth to ashes before we ever see the first fight.
column3: The arena down east is being rebuilt, prettier than a bride’s dress on midsummer’s day. But a Wyrm has taken residence of the place, and if we let it sit, it’ll roast the timber, stone, and cloth to ashes before we ever see the first fight.

column2: So! Grab your weapons, head to the arena, and give that scaly torch lighter a proper thrashing.
column3: So! Grab your weapons, head to the arena, and give that scaly torch lighter a proper thrashing.

column2: &6[Tor-Olav]&f Right then, hero, the door at the base of the great tree will carry you up to Loki’s perch. Mind yourself, the path is crawling with foul beasts and tricks meant to trip you. Keep strong, and give Loki a fight worth remembering!
column3: &6[Tor-Olav]&f Right then, hero, the door at the base of the great tree will carry you up to Loki’s perch. Mind yourself, the path is crawling with foul beasts and tricks meant to trip you. Keep strong, and give Loki a fight worth remembering!

column2: &7&oTime to face a god... I should make sure I am ready before I fight Loki.
column3: &7&oTime to face a god... I should make sure I am ready before I fight Loki.

column2: &6[Tor-Olav]&f Back already, eh? You faced Loki himself, toppled him in battle, only to find it was another of his tricks, ha! Just like the old fox to play both sides of the board.
column3: &6[Tor-Olav]&f Back already, eh? You faced Loki himself, toppled him in battle, only to find it was another of his tricks, ha! Just like the old fox to play both sides of the board.

column2: &6[Tor-Olav]&f So then, the pranks are over, the cold has lifted, and the wyrm won’t be burning down our arena anytime soon. The village can finally breathe easy again, thanks to you. A mighty feat, one for songs and feasts both!
column3: &6[Tor-Olav]&f So then, the pranks are over, the cold has lifted, and the wyrm won’t be burning down our arena anytime soon. The village can finally breathe easy again, thanks to you. A mighty feat, one for songs and feasts both!

column2: &6[Tor-Olav]&f As for me, I’ll keep raising my cup to Loki, trickster though he is, for he’s been my patron and helped me through many a scrape. But today, it’s you the people will raise their cups to. Rest well, hero, the village is safe, and all know who we have to thank.
column3: &6[Tor-Olav]&f As for me, I’ll keep raising my cup to Loki, trickster though he is, for he’s been my patron and helped me through many a scrape. But today, it’s you the people will raise their cups to. Rest well, hero, the village is safe, and all know who we have to thank.

column2: &7&oThat was quite exhausting... but kind of fun.
column3: &7&oEso fue bastante agotador... pero algo divertido.

column2: Ah, you’ve done more for this village than most ever dream, friend. And now, it’s time we stop dancing around and face the mischief maker himself.
column3: Ah, you’ve done more for this village than most ever dream, friend. And now, it’s time we stop dancing around and face the mischief maker himself.

column2: You’ve seen that great tree in the heart of the village, aye? At its base lies a door, not carved by any craftsman’s hand, but shaped by trickery and old magic. Step through it, and you’ll find your way to Loki’s perch at the very top.
column3: You’ve seen that great tree in the heart of the village, aye? At its base lies a door, not carved by any craftsman’s hand, but shaped by trickery and old magic. Step through it, and you’ll find your way to Loki’s perch at the very top.

column2: Now, I should be there at your side... but here’s the truth I’ve long kept close, Loki is my patron. He has guided my hand in battle, turned the tide when all hope seemed lost, and lent me strength when my own failed.
column3: Now, I should be there at your side... but here’s the truth I’ve long kept close, Loki is my patron. He has guided my hand in battle, turned the tide when all hope seemed lost, and lent me strength when my own failed.

column2: You might wonder why I’d bend the knee to such a trickster, but I’ve always been one for a good jest, a clever prank, a laugh in the face of trouble... until the time comes to swing steel, of course!
column3: You might wonder why I’d bend the knee to such a trickster, but I’ve always been one for a good jest, a clever prank, a laugh in the face of trouble... until the time comes to swing steel, of course!

column2: But now... now his games cut too deep, and the village suffers for it. I cannot raise my hand against him not after all he’s given me. That task falls to you, brave one.
column3: But now... now his games cut too deep, and the village suffers for it. I cannot raise my hand against him not after all he’s given me. That task falls to you, brave one.

column2: So go. Step through that door, climb to his stage at the crown of the tree, and face Loki himself. Tell him his cruel prank ends here.
column3: So go. Step through that door, climb to his stage at the crown of the tree, and face Loki himself. Tell him his cruel prank ends here.

column2: &e[Heidi]&f Ah, thank you! If you want to help, take the path right behind me. Follow it through the district and you’ll find the dwarves causing all the ruckus and a few mischievous beasties along the way. Clear them out, and maybe I’ll finally get some well earned sleep!
column3: &e[Heidi]&f Ah, thank you! If you want to help, take the path right behind me. Follow it through the district and you’ll find the dwarves causing all the ruckus and a few mischievous beasties along the way. Clear them out, and maybe I’ll finally get some well earned sleep!

column2: &7&oI should be careful, these dwarves are not like the other creatures in this village.
column3: &7&oI should be careful, these dwarves are not like the other creatures in this village.

column2: &e[Heidi]&f Ah, finally some peace! Thank you for dealing with those nuisances, I can finally rest properly. You’ve done the district and me a great service!
column3: &e[Heidi]&f Ah, finally some peace! Thank you for dealing with those nuisances, I can finally rest properly. You’ve done the district and me a great service!

column2: &7&oTo be honest, they were quite loud...
column3: &7&oTo be honest, they were quite loud...

column2: By the gods, I haven’t had a proper wink of sleep in days! First I stayed up too long tending to business, and then, bam! My district was overrun with beasties and dwarves banging their shields like madmen.
column3: By the gods, I haven’t had a proper wink of sleep in days! First I stayed up too long tending to business, and then, bam! My district was overrun with beasties and dwarves banging their shields like madmen.

column2: I panicked at first, thought the village was in real peril, but turns out the creatures are more nuisance than danger. Still, I can’t catch a wink when those armored oafs keep slamming about! I’ve tried sleeping elsewhere, but nothing matches my bed. My bed or no sleep at all!
column3: I panicked at first, thought the village was in real peril, but turns out the creatures are more nuisance than danger. Still, I can’t catch a wink when those armored oafs keep slamming about! I’ve tried sleeping elsewhere, but nothing matches my bed. My bed or no sleep at all!

column2: Please, drive out the creatures and especially those noisy dwarves. If you can give me back my peace and quiet, I’ll finally get the rest I need, and you’ll be a hero to my poor, weary head.
column3: Please, drive out the creatures and especially those noisy dwarves. If you can give me back my peace and quiet, I’ll finally get the rest I need, and you’ll be a hero to my poor, weary head.

column2: wave=1:message=&8[Zuma] &fAnother day in the arena and another sacrifice. But do not worry we play it fair here! Should they survive all 50 waves they get to keep their life and soul. Alright, time to get started.
column3: wave=1:message=&8[Zuma] &fAnother day in the arena and another sacrifice. But do not worry we play it fair here! Should they survive all 50 waves they get to keep their life and soul. Alright, time to get started.

column2: wave=2:message=&8[Zuma] &fI hope you brought some carrots, cause it's only gonna get worse from now on. Or better?...
column3: wave=2:message=&8[Zuma] &fI hope you brought some carrots, cause it's only gonna get worse from now on. Or better?...

column2: wave=3:message=&8[Zuma] &fOh yeah? Well, what if the enemies had some more OOMPH to them!
column3: wave=3:message=&8[Zuma] &fOh yeah? Well, what if the enemies had some more OOMPH to them!

column2: wave=4:message=&8[Zuma] &fI must say, I have never seen anyone dispatch bunnies and dusty bones so efficiently! They really must be fighting for their life!
column3: wave=4:message=&8[Zuma] &fI must say, I have never seen anyone dispatch bunnies and dusty bones so efficiently! They really must be fighting for their life!

column2: wave=5:message=&8[Zuma] &fI ordered a tractor but they sent me this instead. Why do I need a tractor? NONE OF YOUR BUSINESS! Get plowed!
column3: wave=5:message=&8[Zuma] &fI ordered a tractor but they sent me this instead. Why do I need a tractor? NONE OF YOUR BUSINESS! Get plowed!

column2: wave=6:message=&8[Zuma] &fStill got a lot of hoppers and skellz to spare. Here are some more!
column3: wave=6:message=&8[Zuma] &fStill got a lot of hoppers and skellz to spare. Here are some more!

column2: wave=7:message=&8[Zuma] &fI think they are actually trying, so cute...I mean BRAVE...
column3: wave=7:message=&8[Zuma] &fI think they are actually trying, so cute...I mean BRAVE...

column2: wave=8:message=&8[Zuma] &fDid you know that 5 in 10 sacrifices were clearing all 50 waves. This is one of the main reasons why we decided to significantly increase the amount of hoppers.
column3: wave=8:message=&8[Zuma] &fDid you know that 5 in 10 sacrifices were clearing all 50 waves. This is one of the main reasons why we decided to significantly increase the amount of hoppers.

column2: wave=9:message=&8[Zuma] &fHey, these were supposed to be skellz only. I guess a bunny from the previous wave stuck around.
column3: wave=9:message=&8[Zuma] &fHey, these were supposed to be skellz only. I guess a bunny from the previous wave stuck around.

column2: wave=10:message=&8[Zuma] &fWhat happens when you leave a bunch of toxic concoctions locked up in a crate? You get some &2Jello &fthat's what.
column3: wave=10:message=&8[Zuma] &fWhat happens when you leave a bunch of toxic concoctions locked up in a crate? You get some &2Jello &fthat's what.

column2: wave=11:message=&8[Zuma] &fWell seems like someone got all jelly about the &2Jello &fhe he he. Okay, okay. Back to the usual!
column3: wave=11:message=&8[Zuma] &fWell seems like someone got all jelly about the &2Jello &fhe he he. Okay, okay. Back to the usual!

column2: wave=12:message=&8[Zuma] &fWhat does the audience demand? &cMORE&f hoppers and skellz, that's what!
column3: wave=12:message=&8[Zuma] &fWhat does the audience demand? &cMORE&f hoppers and skellz, that's what!

column2: wave=13:message=&8[Zuma] &fOh, seems we are on wave 13. Such an unlucky number...
column3: wave=13:message=&8[Zuma] &fOh, seems we are on wave 13. Such an unlucky number...

column2: wave=14:message=&8[Zuma] &fI think the hoppers were a bit too pushy if you know what I mean.
column3: wave=14:message=&8[Zuma] &fI think the hoppers were a bit too pushy if you know what I mean.

column2: wave=15:message=&8[Zuma] &fAnd now for something completely else! The worlds first sneaky and backstabby spider, everyone welcome &cMrs. Webbers&f to the arena!
column3: wave=15:message=&8[Zuma] &fAnd now for something completely else! The worlds first sneaky and backstabby spider, everyone welcome &cMrs. Webbers&f to the arena!

column2: wave=16:message=&8[Zuma] &fWell glad you made it out of that web. Because, next we got some really...uhh...what's wrong with these...
column3: wave=16:message=&8[Zuma] &fWell glad you made it out of that web. Because, next we got some really...uhh...what's wrong with these...

column2: wave=17:message=&8[Zuma] &fAlright, alright. How about some &cTOTALLY JUICED&f enemies next. Don't let the bun-buns send you flying!
column3: wave=17:message=&8[Zuma] &fAlright, alright. How about some &cTOTALLY JUICED&f enemies next. Don't let the bun-buns send you flying!

column2: wave=18:message=&8[Zuma] &fNext we got &cBig Chungus&f, uhhh actually, it's just well fed hoppers. Nevermind...
column3: wave=18:message=&8[Zuma] &fNext we got &cBig Chungus&f, uhhh actually, it's just well fed hoppers. Nevermind...

column2: wave=19:message=&8[Zuma] &fAre you ready to face off, FLAMIN, HOT, SKELETONS! Actually, they kinda just set things on fire...
column3: wave=19:message=&8[Zuma] &fAre you ready to face off, FLAMIN, HOT, SKELETONS! Actually, they kinda just set things on fire...

column2: wave=20:message=&8[Zuma] &fThe arenas coolest skeleton, &bChiller&f, is ready for a fight. Double the bow, double the pow! I hope you brought your winter gear, cause it's about to get cold.
column3: wave=20:message=&8[Zuma] &fThe arenas coolest skeleton, &bChiller&f, is ready for a fight. Double the bow, double the pow! I hope you brought your winter gear, cause it's about to get cold.

column2: wave=21:message=&8[Zuma] &fWell that was a pretty...chill fight. Boo, me? No, boo you!
column3: wave=21:message=&8[Zuma] &fWell that was a pretty...chill fight. Boo, me? No, boo you!

column2: wave=22:message=&8[Zuma] &fIs it just me, or are these fights getting a bit more, high stake?
column3: wave=22:message=&8[Zuma] &fIs it just me, or are these fights getting a bit more, high stake?

column2: wave=23:message=&8[Zuma] &fI have a feeling the next set of enemies might have a couple of tricks up their sleeves!
column3: wave=23:message=&8[Zuma] &fI have a feeling the next set of enemies might have a couple of tricks up their sleeves!

column2: wave=24:message=&8[Zuma] &fThunder and lightning, very very frightening. Oh, don't worry. It's just foreshadowing.
column3: wave=24:message=&8[Zuma] &fThunder and lightning, very very frightening. Oh, don't worry. It's just foreshadowing.

column2: wave=25:message=&8[Zuma] &fAnd the crowd is completely abuzz at the chance of seeing the great &eArena Shocker, Bob&f in action!
column3: wave=25:message=&8[Zuma] &fAnd the crowd is completely abuzz at the chance of seeing the great &eArena Shocker, Bob&f in action!

column2: wave=26:message=&8[Zuma] &fThat was electrifying, back to hoppers and skellz. If the boss fights are meals then the regular fights are pure snacks.
column3: wave=26:message=&8[Zuma] &fThat was electrifying, back to hoppers and skellz. If the boss fights are meals then the regular fights are pure snacks.

column2: wave=27:message=&8[Zuma] &fWould be a real shame if the enemies just kept getting stronger and stronger...
column3: wave=27:message=&8[Zuma] &fWould be a real shame if the enemies just kept getting stronger and stronger...

column2: wave=28:message=&8[Zuma] &fDid you know that we are the largest carrot consumer in the entire region. If you wonder why, you're about to find out.
column3: wave=28:message=&8[Zuma] &fDid you know that we are the largest carrot consumer in the entire region. If you wonder why, you're about to find out.

column2: wave=29:message=&8[Zuma] &fWould be a real shame if somebody allowed the skellz to shoot tracking fire-arrows!
column3: wave=29:message=&8[Zuma] &fWould be a real shame if somebody allowed the skellz to shoot tracking fire-arrows!

column2: wave=30:message=&8[Zuma] &fWell the sacrifice candidate seems to be doing well, let's see how they fair against some &dFOUL MAGIC&f!
column3: wave=30:message=&8[Zuma] &fWell the sacrifice candidate seems to be doing well, let's see how they fair against some &dFOUL MAGIC&f!

column2: wave=31:message=&8[Zuma] &fYikes, so much for magic. Nothing seems to be able to stop this mighty fighter!
column3: wave=31:message=&8[Zuma] &fYikes, so much for magic. Nothing seems to be able to stop this mighty fighter!

column2: wave=32:message=&8[Zuma] &fThe crowd is going wild, but will their cheers be able to carry the sacrifice candidate all the way through?
column3: wave=32:message=&8[Zuma] &fThe crowd is going wild, but will their cheers be able to carry the sacrifice candidate all the way through?

column2: wave=33:message=&8[Zuma] &fOkay, let's mix up &cPOISON&f and &eFIRE&f and see what happens.
column3: wave=33:message=&8[Zuma] &fOkay, let's mix up &cPOISON&f and &eFIRE&f and see what happens.

column2: wave=34:message=&8[Zuma] &fIs it wrong that I sometimes cheer for the wrong side? I mean sometimes I want the sacrifice candidate to win, is that so wrong?
column3: wave=34:message=&8[Zuma] &fIs it wrong that I sometimes cheer for the wrong side? I mean sometimes I want the sacrifice candidate to win, is that so wrong?

column2: wave=35:message=&8[Zuma] &fAll I see is &5PURPLE&f. Look at the crowd go wild, they know what this means!
column3: wave=35:message=&8[Zuma] &fAll I see is &5PURPLE&f. Look at the crowd go wild, they know what this means!

column2: wave=36:message=&8[Zuma] &fWOW! What a performance! Can we get some applause both for the sacrifice candidate and &5Clarice&f!

column3: &7&oDebería ir a buscar el amuleto y demostrar que soy digno.

column2: &a[Men-na]&f Well, seems like I was wrong about you. You have my respect now. Feel free to stand next to me on top of this hill as much you like.

&7&oAhora, lo soy. El maestro de la colina.

column2: Just because you managed to climb this hill.

column2: Doesn't mean you're a better climber than me, you know.

column2: You like to think so highly of yourself, don't you.
column3: Te gusta pensar muy bien de ti mismo, ¿verdad?

column2: Well you are certainly not a good enough of a climber to retrieve the &eHill &eTrinket&f I placed on a hill somewhere in this land.

column2: If you want my respect come back to me with the trinket in hand.

column2: &a[Nu]&f Even if you do everything I say, I still might not give up all of my coin.

column2: But I would never give it up so easily.
column3: Pero nunca las cedería tan fácilmente.

column2: If you want all my coin. Then you will have to work for it.

column2: &7&oI guess I should just consider it as experience...
There is a very good reason why I am wearing this outfit.
column3: Hay una muy buena razón por la que llevo este atuendo.

column2: I thought it would be a good idea to disguise myself as a monster before heading into the sewers.
column3: I thought it would be a good idea to disguise myself as a monster before heading into the sewers.

column2: Surely the monsters would not attack me if I looked like one of them.
column3: Seguramente los monstruos no me atacarían si me pareciera a uno de ellos.

column2: But, uhhh. Thinking about it now. I am not so sure.
column3: Pero, uhhh. Pensándolo ahora. No estoy tan seguro.

column2: You wouldn't mind helping me out would you?
column3: No te importaría echarme una mano, ¿verdad?

column2: It is usually found within the sewer waters. I only need four of them.
column3: Normalmente se encuentra en las aguas de las cloacas. Solo necesito cuatro.

column2: &a[Neb-oo]&f Why are you staring at me? Go collect S-C-R-A-P!
column3: &a[Neb-oo]&f ¿Por qué me miras? ¡Ve a recoger C-H-A-T-A-R-R-A!

column2: &7&oI have many things I want to say right now but I should focus on collecting &e&oScrap&7&o from &c&oLesser Sentinels&7&o.
column3: &7&oTengo muchas cosas que quiero decir ahora mismo, pero debería centrarme en recolectar &e&oChatarra&7&o de los &c&oCentinelas Menores&7&o.

column2: &a[Neb-oo]&f What took you song long! Since you were so slow, I will only be paying out 20 percent of the original reward!
column3: &a[Neb-oo]&f ¡Qué te tomó tanto tiempo! ¡Como fuiste tan lento, solo pagaré el 20 por ciento de la recompensa original!
&7&oBueno, me alegra que esto haya terminado...

column2: You there! Yeah, you! You seem like you have nothing better to do but work for me.
column3: You there! Yeah, you! You seem like you have nothing better to do but work for me.

column2: Ok, listen. See all these sentinels that are patrolling this area.
column3: Ok, escucha. Mira todos estos centinelas que están patrullando esta área.

column2: I need you to slay them and bring me back any equipment &eScrap&f you manage to find on them.
column3: I need you to slay them and bring me back any equipment &eScrap&f you manage to find on them.

column2: Listen! When I say &eScrap&f, I mean it!
ONLY &eScrap&f! No other whole pieces of equipment or gear, got that?
column3: ¡SOLO &eChatarra&f! Ninguna otra pieza completa de equipo o armadura, ¿entendido?

column2: You seem pretty simple minded, so let me be clear O-N-L-Y S-C-R-A-P.
column3: Pareces bastante simple, así que déjame ser claro S-O-L-O C-H-A-T-A-R-R-A.
&1Nacido de la chatarra. Hecho para proteger.

column2: &a[Sokari]&f Kill them all. For every single one you slay I shall pay ten coin!
column3: &a[Sokari]&f Mátalos a todos. ¡Por cada uno que mates, pagaré diez monedas!

column2: &7&o&Why do I feel like I am being made fun of...
column3: &7&o&Por qué siento que se están burlando de mí...

column2: &a[Sokari]&f Oh, my brave warrior! You are so strong and mighty! Killing those scary, oh so scary haulers for little old me. As promised, your reward!
column3: &a[Sokari]&f ¡Oh, mi valiente guerrero! ¡Eres tan fuerte y poderoso! Matando a esos aterradores, oh tan aterradores cargadores para esta viejecita. ¡Como prometí, tu recompensa!

column2: Why am I up here? Well, just look at them down there.
column3: ¿Por qué estoy aquí arriba? Bueno, solo míralos ahí abajo.

column2: Shambling about neither alive or dead. Such creepy haulers!
column3: Deambulan sin estar vivos ni muertos. ¡Qué cargadores tan espeluznantes!

column2: Such fearsome haulers! Oh, how could I ever go down there with those scary things walking around.
column3: Such fearsome haulers! Oh, how could I ever go down there with those scary things walking around.

column2: If only there was a brave warrior who could free me from such fear.
column3: Si tan solo hubiera un guerrero valiente que pudiera liberarme de tal miedo.

column2: I wish every single one of them would be gone.
column3: Desearía que cada uno de ellos desapareciera.

column2: &a[Sua]&f About 10 flowers will do. They will look so lovely in my little home.
column3: &a[Sua]&f Unas 10 flores bastarán. Se verán tan preciosas en mi pequeña casa.

column2: &7&oI have a weird feeling about this one.
&a[Sua]&f There they are! Aren't they so pretty! This will really make my day, thank you.
column3: &a[Sua]&f ¡Ahí están! ¡No son tan bonitas! Esto realmente alegrará mi día, gracias.

column2: Such a pretty day requires pretty flowers.
column3: Un día tan bonito requiere flores bonitas.

column2: Would you, kind stranger, mind brightening up this citizens day.
column3: ¿Te importaría, amable extraño, alegrar el día de este ciudadano?

column2: I would just need you to go pick some flowers for me.
column3: Solo necesitaría que fueras a recoger algunas flores para mí.

column2: Nothing a tough adventurer like you won't be able to handle.
column3: Nada que un aventurero duro como tú no pueda manejar.

column2: &eThe outer facing side of this shield

column3: &a[Nofre-ka-u]&f ¿Y bien? Parece que tenemos un trato. Te estaré esperando aquí con una buena bolsa de monedas en la mano.

column3: &7&oDebería ir a matar seres &9&oVampíricos&7&o. Y traer de vuelta 20 &e&oColmillos Humanoides&7&o.

column3: &a[Nofre-ka-u]&f ¡Los 20 están en perfecto estado, excelente! Bien hecho, aquí tienes tu bolsa de monedas.

column2: &7&oI wonder if I could become a dentist in the future...
column3: &7&oMe pregunto si podría convertirme en dentista en el futuro...

column3: ¿No estarás por casualidad entrando en este fabuloso &dObservatorio&f?

column2: I came here to collect some valuable ingredients.
column3: Vine aquí para recolectar algunos ingredientes valiosos.

column2: But if I could outsource this job to you, then that would be excellent.
column3: Pero si pudiera subcontratar este trabajo a ti, sería excelente.

column2: If you're interested, I would need you to bring me back 20 &eHumanoid &eFangs&f.
column3: Si estás interesado, necesitaría que me trajeras 20 &eColmillos &eHumanoides&f.

column3: &a[Kasmut]&f Si pudiera desear tres cosas maravillosas. Sin duda sería una &ePerla Brillante&f, una &eConcha Arcoíris&f y de las profundidades de los océanos más profundos un &eCristal de Sal&f.

column3: &a[Kasmut]&f ¡Oh, sí! Todo lo que mi corazón deseaba. Deberías considerar unirte a mí si alguna vez te aburres de la aventura. ¡Solo piensa en todas las curiosidades que podríamos coleccionar!

column3: Oh, are you a fellow diver? Did not expect to see anyone else down here in the depths.

column2: Bring me three and I will make sure to compensate you well for your hard work and time.
