column2: &a[Cheres]&f Your first task shall be to go to the following locations and siphon energy that has collected there. The energy quantities are so dense that they have a mind of their own. Do not be surprised if it attacks back. Take these viles, the energy will be drawn into them after you disperse it.
column3: &a[Cheres]&f Tu primera tarea será ir a las siguientes ubicaciones y extraer la energía que se ha acumulado allí. Las cantidades de energía son tan densas que tienen mente propia. No te sorprendas si ataca. Toma estos viales, la energía será atraída hacia ellos después de que la disperses.

column2: &7&oI need to go to the indicated locations and disperse the &c&oSoul Energies&7&o. I should &9&ostrike the exact location&7&o to make the energy more visible.
column3: &7&oNecesito ir a las ubicaciones indicadas y dispersar las &c&oEnergías del Alma&7&o. Debería &9&ogolpear la ubicación exacta&7&o para hacer la energía más visible.

column2: &a[Cheres]&f Well done. I will take the viles now. Shall we move on to the next task?
column3: &a[Cheres]&f Bien hecho. Tomaré los viales ahora. ¿Pasamos a la siguiente tarea?

column2: &7&oMore work awaits I better check with &a&oCheres&7&o for more details.
column3: &7&oMás trabajo me espera, mejor consulto con &a&oCheres&7&o para más detalles.

column2: Quite interesting what is happening in this land, don't you think?
column3: Bastante interesante lo que está pasando en esta tierra, ¿no crees?

column2: I would say these are excellent conditions to be gathering rarities.
column3: Diría que estas son excelentes condiciones para recolectar rarezas.

column2: I was about to go do it myself, but I see a capable warrior standing in front of me and my purse is full of coins.
column3: I was about to go do it myself, but I see a capable warrior standing in front of me and my purse is full of coins.

column2: So what say you, I have several requests so this should be a good opportunity for you to earn some coin.
column3: So what say you, I have several requests so this should be a good opportunity for you to earn some coin.

column2: &a[Cheres]&f Remember, the blood has to be near the source of the curse.
column3: &a[Cheres]&f Recuerda, la sangre tiene que estar cerca de la fuente de la maldición.

column2: &7&oHmm, I wonder if the &c&oPharaoh's Sentinels&7&o are close enough to the source.
column3: &7&oHmm, me pregunto si los &c&oCentinelas del Faraón&7&o están lo suficientemente cerca de la fuente.

column2: &a[Cheres]&f Hand me the discs. As expected another job well done.
column3: &a[Cheres]&f Dame los discos. Como era de esperar, otro trabajo bien hecho.

column2: &7&oSeems like there is more work for me.
column3: &7&oParece que hay más trabajo para mí.

column2: Next I need you to go collect some blood for me.
column3: Luego necesito que vayas a recolectar algo de sangre para mí.

column2: Not just any blood, it has to be near the source of the curse.
column3: No cualquier sangre, tiene que estar cerca de la fuente de la maldición.

column2: And even then only certain blood will do.
column3: E incluso entonces, solo cierta sangre servirá.

column2: Do not worry, I have some items that will make this easy for you. Take these stone discs.
column3: Do not worry, I have some items that will make this easy for you. Take these stone discs.

column2: Hold one of the discs near an open wound and if the blood is the correct type that I seek, it will flow onto the disc by itself.
column3: Hold one of the discs near an open wound and if the blood is the correct type that I seek, it will flow onto the disc by itself.

column2: &a[Cheres]&f Here another one of my tools. This lantern will collect the vitae or essence of the unwelcome guests when you slay them. They have hidden themselves well, so finding them might not be as easy as it looks.
column3: &a[Cheres]&f Aquí tienes otra de mis herramientas. Esta linterna recolectará la vitae o esencia de los invitados no deseados cuando los mates. Se han escondido bien, así que encontrarlos podría no ser tan fácil como parece.

column2: &7&oI need to find the location where these so called unwelcome guests have settled.
column3: &7&oNecesito encontrar la ubicación donde se han asentado estos supuestos invitados no deseados.

column2: &a[Cheres]&f The lantern please. I hope it did not take you too long to find them.
column3: &a[Cheres]&f La linterna, por favor. Espero que no te haya tomado demasiado tiempo encontrarlos.

column2: &7&oWhat were &d&oNether&7&o creatures doing all the way here...
Seems like the people of this land did not notice unwelcome guests settling down in their domain.
column3: Seems like the people of this land did not notice unwelcome guests settling down in their domain.

column2: I guess they might be a bit preoccupied with other things right now.
column3: Supongo que podrían estar un poco preocupados con otras cosas en este momento.

column2: Don't think they would mind us evicting these new settlers and collecting their essence...
column3: Don't think they would mind us evicting these new settlers and collecting their essence...

column2: &a[Cheres]&f The creature is deep in the ocean. It has escaped to a place where no fish swim and no plants grow...
column3: &a[Cheres]&f La criatura está en lo profundo del océano. Ha escapado a un lugar donde no nadan peces ni crecen plantas...

column2: &7&oSeems like I should prepare for a long swim.
column3: &7&oParece que debería prepararme para un largo nado.

column2: &a[Cheres]&f Excellent. That was the last contract. I no longer need your services, farewell mortal.
column3: &a[Cheres]&f Excelente. Ese fue el último contrato. Ya no necesito tus servicios, adiós mortal.

column2: This will be your last task.
The curse has corrupted a being to such an extent that it has twisted its soul into something unknown.
column3: The curse has corrupted a being to such an extent that it has twisted its soul into something unknown.

column2: I would like a sample of this soul.
column3: Me gustaría una muestra de esta alma.

column2: Well, when I say sample I actually mean the entirety of it.
column3: Bueno, cuando digo muestra, en realidad me refiero a su totalidad.

column2: Do not worry about how you will capture the soul.
column3: No te preocupes por cómo capturarás el alma.

column2: You just need to release it from its corporal shell.
column3: Solo necesitas liberarla de su caparazón corporal.

column2: I will make sure it finds it's way here once it has been released.
column3: Me aseguraré de que encuentre su camino hasta aquí una vez que haya sido liberada.

column2: &7that has taken the shape of a crossbow.

A dull blade can\nnever strike\ndown a fiend.

column2: &a[Abubakar] &fAll of a sudden all these monsters started appearing and people started going mad. Please help!
column3: &a[Abubakar] &fDe repente, todos estos monstruos empezaron a aparecer y la gente empezó a enloquecer. ¡Por favor, ayuda!

column2: &7&oI should hear what else &a&oAbubakar&7&o has to say.
column3: &7&oDebería escuchar qué más tiene que decir &a&oAbubakar&7&o.

column2: &a[Captain Squalus]&f Well don't just stand around, go!
column3: &a[Capitán Squalus]&f Bueno, no te quedes ahí parado, ¡ve!

column2: I hope this doesn't turn into another week long ordeal...
column3: Espero que esto no se convierta en otra prueba de una semana...

column2: &7&oI should go talk to the crowd at the &d&oDessa Docks&7&o.
column3: &7&oDebería ir a hablar con la multitud en los &d&oMuelles de Dessa&7&o.

column2: &a[Abubakar]&f We are worried about our friends.
&7&oSeems like Abubakar has more to say...
column3: &7&oParece que Abubakar tiene más que decir...

column2: Well so much for just stopping here for supplies.
column3: Bueno, hasta aquí llegamos con solo parar por suministros.

column2: I guess our journey is on hold until we figure out
column3: Supongo que nuestro viaje está en espera hasta que descubramos

column2: what's going on here and get our supplies.
column3: qué está pasando aquí y consigamos nuestros suministros.

column2: Seems like that crowd wants to board the ship.
column3: Parece que esa multitud quiere abordar el barco.

column2: Go talk to them and find out what is happening.
column3: Ve a hablar con ellos y averigua qué está pasando.

column2: &a[Nefer] &fOh, you came to rescue us? We never gave up hope!
&a[Aseskafankh] &fIn light of the deteriorating safety conditions downstairs, it was a unanimous decision that we seek refuge up here...
column3: &a[Aseskafankh] &fEn vista de las condiciones de seguridad deterioradas abajo, fue una decisión unánime que buscáramos refugio aquí arriba...

column2: &a[Monifa] &fWe were able to construct a rudimentary barricade using the bookshelves, though we were uncertain of its durability in the long run...
column3: &a[Monifa] &fPudimos construir una barricada rudimentaria usando las estanterías, aunque no estábamos seguros de su durabilidad a largo plazo...

column2: &a[Keknum]&f I will send a detachment of our guards behind you. Once you have found the survivors the guards will take care of the rest.
column3: &a[Keknum]&f Enviaré un destacamento de nuestros guardias detrás de ti. Una vez que hayas encontrado a los supervivientes, los guardias se encargarán del resto.

column2: &7&oI better get going, every second counts.
column3: &7&oSerá mejor que me ponga en marcha, cada segundo cuenta.

column2: &a[Keknum]&f Greetings soldier, I see that you have performed admirably once again. The guards have been dispatched to retrieve the survivors, and your contribution has been instrumental in their rescue. Your efforts today have helped to save several lives, and I offer my sincere commendations for a job well done.
column3: &a[Keknum]&f Saludos soldado, veo que has actuado admirablemente una vez más. Los guardias han sido enviados para recuperar a los supervivientes, y tu contribución ha sido fundamental en su rescate. Tus esfuerzos de hoy han ayudado a salvar varias vidas, y ofrezco mis sinceras felicitaciones por un trabajo bien hecho.

column2: I got a another mission for you if you're up for it.
column3: Tengo otra misión para ti si estás dispuesto.

column2: When we were at the &dLibrary&f we could not rescue everyone.
column3: Cuando estuvimos en la &dBiblioteca&f no pudimos rescatar a todos.

column2: I want you to go there and escort back any survivors before it's too late.
column3: I want you to go there and escort back any survivors before it's too late.

column2: I am not sure where they could be hiding, but my guess would be somewhere safe.
column3: I am not sure where they could be hiding, but my guess would be somewhere safe.

column2: Somewhere where the monsters wouldn't be able to find them.
column3: En algún lugar donde los monstruos no pudieran encontrarlos.

column2: &a[Keknum]&f Do not underestimate the keeper, according to the librarians the keeper would have had years of training in magic and hexes. The book you're looking for is called &eGrimoire &eHvit&f. Be careful.
column3: &a[Keknum]&f No subestimes al guardián, según los bibliotecarios el guardián habría tenido años de entrenamiento en magia y maleficios. El libro que buscas se llama &eGrimorio &eHvit&f. Ten cuidado.

column2: &7&oI should locate the &c&oKnowledge Keeper&7&o and retrieve &e&oGrimoire Hvit&7&o.
column3: &7&oDebería localizar al &c&oGuardián del Conocimiento&7&o y recuperar el &e&oGrimorio Hvit&7&o.

column2: &a[Keknum]&f Thank you! With this book we should be able to come closer to the answers we seek about our current situation.
column3: &a[Keknum]&f ¡Gracias! Con este libro deberíamos poder acercarnos a las respuestas que buscamos sobre nuestra situación actual.

column2: The librarians that we managed to rescue had some important information to share.
column3: Los bibliotecarios que logramos rescatar tenían información importante que compartir.

column2: They are pretty certain that a certain book has valuable information on what is happening to our city.
column3: They are pretty certain that a certain book has valuable information on what is happening to our city.

column2: The book is kept by the &cKnowledge Keeper&f at all times.
column3: El libro es guardado por el &cGuardián del Conocimiento&f en todo momento.

column2: They say that when all this happened the keeper was not at the library but at home.
column3: They say that when all this happened the keeper was not at the library but at home.

column2: Apparently his house has a blue lantern hanging above the entrance.
column3: Aparentemente, su casa tiene una linterna azul colgando sobre la entrada.

column2: Hopefully that should make it easier for you to locate the building.
column3: Con suerte, eso debería facilitarte la localización del edificio.

column2: I doubt that the keeper managed to avoid the curse, considering the state of the city.
column3: I doubt that the keeper managed to avoid the curse, considering the state of the city.

column2: So if I was you I would prepare for a fight.
column3: Así que si yo fuera tú, me prepararía para una pelea.

column2: &a[Onouris] &fWelcome to Zanerun...or whats left of it.
column3: &a[Onouris] &fBienvenido a Zanerun... o lo que queda de él.

column2: &a[Keknum]&f I can say with confidence that &dZanerun&f is in good hands now. &dZanerun&f is located directly north from here. Godspeed friend!
column3: &a[Keknum]&f Puedo decir con confianza que &dZanerun&f está en buenas manos ahora. &dZanerun&f se encuentra directamente al norte de aquí. ¡Buena suerte amigo!

column2: &7&oTime to make my way over to &d&oZanerun&7&o.
&a[Onouris]&f What sends you our way in these horrible times, traveler?
column3: &a[Onouris]&f ¿Qué te trae por aquí en estos tiempos horribles, viajero?

column2: &7&oI should explain why I have come here.
column3: &7&oDebería explicar por qué he venido aquí.

column2: Thanks to you and the book you retrieved we were able to finally conclude that our current situation is a product of a powerful curse.
column3: Thanks to you and the book you retrieved we were able to finally conclude that our current situation is a product of a powerful curse.

column2: With some more research we were also able to conclude that the most likely origin of the curse would be the &dPyramid&f.
column3: With some more research we were also able to conclude that the most likely origin of the curse would be the &dPyramid&f.

column2: Though we were not able to ascertain why or what triggered the curse.
column3: Aunque no pudimos determinar por qué o qué desencadenó la maldición.

column2: There would be no natural reason for the curse to occur since our burials are always performed properly.
column3: There would be no natural reason for the curse to occur since our burials are always performed properly.

column2: I would like to send you off to &dZanerun&f next.
column3: Me gustaría enviarte a &dZanerun&f a continuación.

column2: You should share with them the information you have acquired.
column3: Deberías compartir con ellos la información que has adquirido.

column2: Maybe you will be able to find more information about the curse there.
column3: Quizás puedas encontrar más información sobre la maldición allí.

column2: With your help we have managed to seize control of the city so there is no need to worry about us.
column3: With your help we have managed to seize control of the city so there is no need to worry about us.

column2: It was an honor working with you.
&a[Uah-abra]&f You have arrived just in time!
&a[Onouris]&f I really thought I was going to die here, guess I shouldn't have given up hope so easily.
column3: &a[Onouris]&f Realmente pensé que iba a morir aquí, supongo que no debería haber perdido la esperanza tan fácilmente.

column2: &7&oI should go to the house where all the survivors are hiding out.
column3: &7&oDebería ir a la casa donde se esconden todos los supervivientes.

column2: &a[Uah-abra]&f We are so glad that you have come to help. Don't think we would have lasted much longer...
column3: &a[Uah-abra]&f Estamos muy contentos de que hayas venido a ayudar. No creo que hubiéramos durado mucho más...

column2: &7&oI should see what I can do to help.
column3: &7&oDebería ver qué puedo hacer para ayudar.

column2: Just because there are monsters around does not mean I will stop doing my job of greeting newcomers to our town!
column3: Just because there are monsters around does not mean I will stop doing my job of greeting newcomers to our town!

column2: It will take more than just some monsters to stop me.
column3: Hará falta más que solo algunos monstruos para detenerme.

column2: If you came here to help then you should head to this building.
column3: Si viniste a ayudar, entonces deberías dirigirte a este edificio.

column2: All the survivors have gathered there.
column3: Todos los supervivientes se han reunido allí.

column2: We have lost a lot of people, and many guards have perished trying to save as many as they could.
column3: We have lost a lot of people, and many guards have perished trying to save as many as they could.

column2: Go now, I am glad someone finally came to help.
column3: Ve ahora, me alegra que alguien finalmente haya venido a ayudar.

column2: &a[Uah-abra]&f Before you head off I just wanted to say that we really appreciate you doing this for us.
column3: &a[Uah-abra]&f Antes de que te vayas, solo quería decir que realmente apreciamos que hagas esto por nosotros.

column2: &7&oI should head out into town and slay any monsters I come across.
column3: &7&oDebería salir al pueblo y matar a cualquier monstruo que encuentre.

column2: &a[Uah-abra]&f I have never seen anyone cut down fiends so efficiently. Clearly there is more to you than meets the eye. Now that the danger is gone we have plenty of time to discuss whatever it is that you wanted to talk about.
column3: &a[Uah-abra]&f Nunca he visto a nadie acabar con demonios tan eficientemente. Claramente hay más en ti de lo que parece. Ahora que el peligro ha pasado, tenemos tiempo de sobra para discutir lo que sea que querías hablar.

column2: &7&oI need to talk to &a&oUah-abra&7&o about the curse.
We were expecting our own people to come to our to aid, but honestly we should be thankful anybody came at all.
column3: We were expecting our own people to come to our to aid, but honestly we should be thankful anybody came at all.

column2: As you can see we are in no shape to be out there fighting these things.
column3: Como puedes ver, no estamos en condiciones de salir a luchar contra estas cosas.

column2: The wounded guards that are here, are all that is left of our defenses.
column3: Los guardias heridos que están aquí son todo lo que queda de nuestras defensas.

column2: Before we continue our discussion you should head out there and finish off the remaining monsters.
column3: Before we continue our discussion you should head out there and finish off the remaining monsters.

column2: We gave them one hell of a beating but in the end there was just no end to them.
column3: Les dimos una paliza infernal, pero al final simplemente no tenían fin.

column2: Slaying the remaining monsters should give us enough time to heal and recover our forces.
column3: Slaying the remaining monsters should give us enough time to heal and recover our forces.

column2: &a[Uah-abra]&f As I mentioned before, that area is infested with monsters. Do not let your guard down.
column3: &a[Uah-abra]&f Como mencioné antes, esa zona está infestada de monstruos. No bajes la guardia.

column2: &7&oI should head for the archives at the east side of &d&oZanerun&7&o.
column3: &7&oDebería dirigirme a los archivos en el lado este de &d&oZanerun&7&o.

column2: &a[Uah-abra]&f Did you find anything of use?
&7&oI should tell &a&oUah-abra&7&o what I managed to find.
column3: &7&oDebería decirle a &a&oUah-abra&7&o lo que logré encontrar.

column2: So you say this event was caused by a powerful curse that originated from the &dPyramid&f.
column3: So you say this event was caused by a powerful curse that originated from the &dPyramid&f.

column2: Hmm. Unfortunately none of us in here hold any knowledge that might help you.
column3: Hmm. Unfortunately none of us in here hold any knowledge that might help you.

column2: There was an old scribe who would have been able to help you, but I am sure they have fallen to the curse
column3: There was an old scribe who would have been able to help you, but I am sure they have fallen to the curse

column2: .The east side of &dZanerun&f was hit the hardest with the curse.
column3: El lado este de &dZanerun&f fue el más afectado por la maldición.

column2: And that's where the scribe and the archives were.
column3: Y ahí es donde estaban el escriba y los archivos.

column2: Your best shot would be to go to the archives and see if you can find anything of use there.
column3: Your best shot would be to go to the archives and see if you can find anything of use there.

column2: If there is any information on this curse it would be there.
column3: Si hay alguna información sobre esta maldición, estaría allí.

column2: &a[Uah-abra]&f Take heed when going up there, there a lot of monsters about. And we aren't even sure what the curse might have done to the cultists...
column3: &a[Uah-abra]&f Ten cuidado al subir allí, hay muchos monstruos. Y ni siquiera estamos seguros de lo que la maldición podría haberles hecho a los cultistas...

column2: &7&oHow would a cult from &d&oZanerun&7&o be able to cause all of this? I should go to their lair and investigate.
column3: &7&o¿Cómo podría un culto de &d&oZanerun&7&o ser capaz de causar todo esto? Debería ir a su guarida e investigar.

column2: A note, let me see it. Hmm, a &eVoid Bell&f. There is information about it in the archives you brought back. Apparently it is a powerful artifact of the undead from the &dNether&f dimension...
column3: A note, let me see it. Hmm, a &eVoid Bell&f. There is information about it in the archives you brought back. Apparently it is a powerful artifact of the undead from the &dNether&f dimension...

column2: &7&oSeems like &a&oUah-abra&7&o might have another quest for me.
column3: &7&oParece que &a&oUah-abra&7&o podría tener otra misión para mí.

column2: We have looked through the archives you brought back.
column3: Hemos revisado los archivos que trajiste.

column2: There is a lot referencing to a local cult.
column3: Hay muchas referencias a un culto local.

column2: They were supposed to be looked into but there where always other priorities.
column3: Se suponía que debían ser investigados, pero siempre había otras prioridades.

column2: Apparently the cult was centered around the ideology that a great cleansing will come and rid this land of those blind to the truth.
column3: Apparently the cult was centered around the ideology that a great cleansing will come and rid this land of those blind to the truth.

column2: Sounds like a bunch of mad rambling to me, darn it!
column3: Me suena a un montón de divagaciones locas, ¡maldita sea!

column2: That's the problem with having underpaid guards, they do not have time to look into all reports.
column3: That's the problem with having underpaid guards, they do not have time to look into all reports.

column2: We should have requested aid from the other settlements and had this cult taken care of long before they managed to grow in strength.
column3: We should have requested aid from the other settlements and had this cult taken care of long before they managed to grow in strength.

column2: I am pretty certain that the cult is behind all of this, but we still need proof.
column3: I am pretty certain that the cult is behind all of this, but we still need proof.

column2: Their base is located up the stairs in the heart of the mountain.
column3: Su base se encuentra subiendo las escaleras en el corazón de la montaña.

column2: Go there and see if our suspicions are correct.
column3: Ve allí y mira si nuestras sospechas son correctas.

column2: &2[Tau]&f Not a step closer fiend, I WILL stab you!
column3: &2[Tau]&f ¡Ni un paso más demonio, TE APUÑALARÉ!

column2: &a[Uah-abra]&f I am not sure what to say. What you have done for us, I mean we wouldn't even be here if you did not come to &dZanerun&f. I wish you good luck on your journey and investigation. I hope you manage to stop this foul curse. If you ever need anything in the future, you come to us. We owe you a great debt!
column3: &a[Uah-abra]&f No estoy seguro de qué decir. Lo que has hecho por nosotros, quiero decir, ni siquiera estaríamos aquí si no hubieras venido a &dZanerun&f. Te deseo buena suerte en tu viaje e investigación. Espero que logres detener esta vil maldición. Si alguna vez necesitas algo en el futuro, ven a nosotros. ¡Te debemos una gran deuda!

column2: &7&oZanerun seems to be a safer place now. I should head for the &d&oAdministrative Palace&7&o and find out how we can stop this curse.
column3: &7&oZanerun parece ser un lugar más seguro ahora. Debería dirigirme al &d&oPalacio Administrativo&7&o y averiguar cómo podemos detener esta maldición.

column2: &a[Tau]&f Oh, my! Am I glad that you're one of the living!
column3: &a[Tau]&f ¡Oh, Dios mío! ¡Qué alegría que seas uno de los vivos!

column2: I think that next you should leave for the &dAdministrative &dPalace&f, it is located between &dKhesusiris&f and &dTappesheh&f.
column3: I think that next you should leave for the &dAdministrative &dPalace&f, it is located between &dKhesusiris&f and &dTappesheh&f.

column2: I really hope that the &aAdvisor&f is still alive, if anyone knows anything about this &eVoid &eBell&f, it would be them.
column3: I really hope that the &aAdvisor&f is still alive, if anyone knows anything about this &eVoid &eBell&f, it would be them.

column2: &a[Tau]&f The &cPharaoh&f is at all times surrounded by two &cGuardians&f, but last time I saw them they were in pretty bad shape, so they shouldn't pose much of a threat...
column3: &a[Tau]&f El &cFaraón&f está en todo momento rodeado por dos &cGuardianes&f, pero la última vez que los vi estaban en bastante mal estado, so they shouldn't pose much of a threat...

column2: &7&oI need to find the &c&oPharaoh&7&o and his &c&oGaurdians&7&o and eliminate them.
column3: &7&oNecesito encontrar al &c&oFaraón&7&o y a sus &c&oGuardianes&7&o y eliminarlos.

column2: &a[Tau]&f Woah! What was all that noise! Oh, sorry. Now that our former ruler has been laid to rest we have time to discuss the &eVoid Bell&f.
column3: &a[Tau]&f ¡Vaya! ¡Qué fue todo ese ruido! Oh, lo siento. Ahora que nuestro antiguo gobernante ha sido puesto a descansar, tenemos tiempo para discutir la &eCampana del Vacío&f.

column2: &7&oTime to hear what &a&oTau&7&o knows about the &e&oVoid Bell&f.
column3: &7&oEs hora de escuchar lo que &a&oTau&7&o sabe sobre la &e&oCampana del Vacío&f.

column2: Hmm, you certainly have uncovered a lot. I do know what the &eVoid &eBell&f is.
column3: Hmm, ciertamente has descubierto mucho. Sí sé qué es la &eCampana &edel Vacío&f.

column2: But if you don't mind before we discuss it, I have a request. What I am gonna ask you to do is pretty grim, but it must be done.
column3: But if you don't mind before we discuss it, I have a request. What I am gonna ask you to do is pretty grim, but it must be done.

column2: I am afraid that our current &cPharaoh&f has succumbed to the curse.
column3: Me temo que nuestro actual &cFaraón&f ha sucumbido a la maldición.

column2: We cannot allow our once great ruler to shamble around as thoughtless fiend. You know what must be done...
column3: We cannot allow our once great ruler to shamble around as thoughtless fiend. You know what must be done...

column2: Also the passage to &dTappesheh&f has been sealed off by our former &cAdmin&f &cWarden&f as you can see.
column3: Also the passage to &dTappesheh&f has been sealed off by our former &cAdmin&f &cWarden&f as you can see.

column2: You will have to slay them if you wish to reopen the passage. Heh, I say 'him' as if they are still human...
column3: You will have to slay them if you wish to reopen the passage. Heh, I say 'him' as if they are still human...

column2: &2[Khalid]&f You better have a good reason for bothering me.
column3: &2[Khalid]&f Será mejor que tengas una buena razón para molestarme.

column2: &a[Tau]&f You need to go to &dTappesheh&f and inform them of what has happened. The only way to reach the &dPyramid&f is through &dTappesheh&f. The only way to end this curse now is to slay the source of it, our former Pharaoh that was buried there.
column3: &a[Tau]&f Necesitas ir a &dTappesheh&f e informarles de lo que ha sucedido. La única forma de llegar a la &dPyramid&f es a través de &dTappesheh&f. La única forma de acabar con esta maldición ahora es matar a su origen, nuestro antiguo Faraón que fue enterrado allí.

column2: &7&oI should head for &d&oTappesheh&7&o and find out how to access the &d&oPyramid&7&o.
column3: &7&oDebería dirigirme a &d&oTappesheh&7&o y averiguar cómo acceder a la &d&oPyramid&7&o.

column2: &a[Khalid]&f If you have come with important information, then I would like to hear it. Sorry for being rude earlier, but we are a bit stressed out these days...
column3: &a[Khalid]&f Si has venido con información importante, me gustaría escucharla. Siento haber sido grosero antes, pero estamos un poco estresados estos días...

column2: &7&oI need to disclose my findings to &a&oKhalid&7&o.
About the bell, you better sit down for this one. A long time ago we sent an expedition to the &dNether&f.
column3: About the bell, you better sit down for this one. A long time ago we sent an expedition to the &dNether&f.

column2: Only a few soldiers survived to tell the story. Their mission was to explore a region in the &dNether&f and report back.
column3: Only a few soldiers survived to tell the story. Their mission was to explore a region in the &dNether&f and report back.

column2: But yet they kept going deeper and deeper, as if something was calling to them.
column3: Pero aun así seguían yendo más y más profundo, como si algo los estuviera llamando.

column2: They discovered a large underground temple deep within the &dNether&f.
column3: Descubrieron un gran templo subterráneo en lo profundo del &dNether&f.

column2: And at the heart of the temple a small bell suspended in the air.
column3: Y en el corazón del templo, una pequeña campana suspendida en el aire.

column2: The bell was retrieved by the expedition, removed from its resting place. The expedition started its long journey back home.
column3: The bell was retrieved by the expedition, removed from its resting place. The expedition started its long journey back home.

column2: Right before reaching the exit portal they were attacked by a large force of fiends. Many expedition soldiers fell during this fight.
column3: Right before reaching the exit portal they were attacked by a large force of fiends. Many expedition soldiers fell during this fight.

column2: The commander as if under a spell took out the bell from its pouch. His glazed eyes peering at the dead, the hand holding the bell moved. The bell swung back and forth releasing a cacophony of sounds.
column3: The commander as if under a spell took out the bell from its pouch. His glazed eyes peering at the dead, the hand holding the bell moved. The bell swung back and forth releasing a cacophony of sounds.

column2: The dead rose back to life, but, changed, different, monstrous. And just soon after, the bell vanished from the commanders hand.
column3: The dead rose back to life, but, changed, different, monstrous. And just soon after, the bell vanished from the commanders hand.

column2: The living had to fight off the undead. And those who survived rushed back to the portal fearing for their lives.
column3: The living had to fight off the undead. And those who survived rushed back to the portal fearing for their lives.

column2: The cult must have ventured into the &dNether&f and retrieved the bell.
column3: El culto debe haberse aventurado en el &dNether&f y recuperado la campana.

column2: Then they used it in the pyramid raising our former ruler and twisting them into a powerful fiend who cursed this land...
column3: Then they used it in the pyramid raising our former ruler and twisting them into a powerful fiend who cursed this land...

column2: &a[Tiumautef]&fWho are you? What are you doing here?
&a[Abubakar]&f I hope they are still alive. Please hurry!
column3: &a[Abubakar]&f Espero que sigan vivos. ¡Por favor, date prisa!

column2: &7&oI should go look for any survivors and slay some of these foul creatures.
column3: &7&oDebería ir a buscar supervivientes y matar a algunas de estas asquerosas criaturas.

column2: &a[Tiumautef]&f Friends at the dock sent you? Oh, thank goodness.
column3: &a[Tiumautef]&f ¿Te enviaron amigos del muelle? Oh, gracias a Dios.

column2: We are so glad you came here to help. Can we talk?
column3: Estamos muy contentos de que hayas venido a ayudar. ¿Podemos hablar?

column2: &7&oI should hear what &a&oTimuautef&7&o has to say.
column3: &7&oDebería escuchar lo que &a&oTimuautef&7&o tiene que decir.

column2: We came from the &dDessa Plaza&f. There was a chance to escape, so we took it.
column3: Vinimos de la &dDessa Plaza&f. Había una oportunidad de escapar, así que la tomamos.

column2: We ran towards the &dDocks&f hoping we could get on a boat and escape to safety.
column3: We ran towards the &dDocks&f hoping we could get on a boat and escape to safety.

column2: There are plenty of people who are still in danger.
column3: Hay mucha gente que todavía está en peligro.

column2: Could you please go there and save them.
We are so lucky to have bumped into such a brave warrior as yourself. It must have been destiny!
column3: We are so lucky to have bumped into such a brave warrior as yourself. It must have been destiny!

column2: &a[Khalid]&f We would like you to handle the &cSentingels&f and the &cSnipers&f, we will take care of the rest.
column3: &a[Khalid]&f Nos gustaría que te encargaras de los &cSentinels&f y los &cSnipers&f, nosotros nos ocuparemos del resto.

column2: &7&oI should clear the nearby area of &c&oSentinels&7&o and &c&oSnipers&7&o.
column3: &7&oDebería despejar el área cercana de &c&oSentinels&7&o y &c&oSnipers&7&o.

column2: &a[Khalid]&f That should do it. We can now secure the bank entrance. There is plenty of work left, if you would like to help us further.
column3: &a[Khalid]&f Eso debería bastar. Ahora podemos asegurar la entrada del banco. Queda mucho trabajo, si quieres ayudarnos más.

column2: &7&oI should talk to &c&oKhalid&7&o to continue my quest.
column3: &7&oDebería hablar con &c&oKhalid&7&o para continuar mi misión.

column2: Well must be our lucky break finally! If what you say is true we will assist you as best as we can.
column3: Well must be our lucky break finally! If what you say is true we will assist you as best as we can.

column2: Hmm, the entrance to the &dPyramid&f is located near the &dHarbor&f.
column3: Hmm, la entrada a la &dPyramid&f se encuentra cerca del &dHarbor&f.

column2: I am not sure how anyone would get in there, the old entrance has been sealed and it has been remodeled into a bank.
column3: I am not sure how anyone would get in there, the old entrance has been sealed and it has been remodeled into a bank.

column2: If you could help us secure this position we would be able to assist you with securing a route towards the bank.
column3: If you could help us secure this position we would be able to assist you with securing a route towards the bank.

column2: &2[Neb-pu]&f You haven't come here to eat me right?
column3: &2[Neb-pu]&f No has venido aquí a comerme, ¿verdad?

column2: &a[Khalid]&f Before you head off, I wanted to thank you for updating us with this vital information. We can now focus on reclaiming the cursed areas while you go deal with the source of it all.
column3: &a[Khalid]&f Antes de que te vayas, quería agradecerte por actualizarnos con esta información vital. Ahora podemos concentrarnos en recuperar las áreas malditas mientras tú te encargas de la fuente de todo.

column2: &a[Neb-pu]&f Finally someone came to rescue me. A way to enter the &dPyramid&f?
column3: &a[Neb-pu]&f Finalmente alguien vino a rescatarme. ¿Una forma de entrar en la &dPyramid&f?

column2: &7&oI need to talk to Neb-pu about a way to enter the &d&oPyramid&7&o.
column3: &7&oNecesito hablar con Neb-pu sobre una forma de entrar en la &d&oPyramid&7&o.

column2: The way to the bank should be clear now. The only thing still in your way would be the &cPharaoh's&f &cSentinels&f.
column3: The way to the bank should be clear now. The only thing still in your way would be the &cPharaoh's&f &cSentinels&f.

column2: As you can imagine this curse has affected them to so they only understand violence and bloodshed now.
column3: As you can imagine this curse has affected them to so they only understand violence and bloodshed now.

column2: Hopefully there is still someone left alive at the bank or we are gonna have to get real creative about entering the &dPyramid&f.
column3: Hopefully there is still someone left alive at the bank or we are gonna have to get real creative about entering the &dPyramid&f.

column2: &7&oI need to slay all the &c&oMoneychangers&7&o so I can get into the vault and retrieve the key for the iron door from &c&oThe Foundry&7&o.
column3: &7&oNecesito matar a todos los &c&oMoneychangers&7&o para poder entrar en la bóveda y recuperar la llave de la puerta de hierro de &c&oThe Foundry&7&o.

column2: &a[Neb-pu]&fGreat! You should be able to go through the iron door now. Once again, thank you for saving me! I will head to that camp you mentioned. Goodbye!
column3: &a[Neb-pu]&f¡Genial! Ahora deberías poder pasar por la puerta de hierro. ¡Una vez más, gracias por salvarme! Iré a ese campamento que mencionaste. ¡Adiós!

column2: &7&oI should go through the iron door and see what I can find.
column3: &7&oDebería pasar por la puerta de hierro y ver qué encuentro.

column2: Getting into the &dPyramid&f should be easy seeing as a bunch of cultists broke in and blew their way into the inner corridor.
column3: Getting into the &dPyramid&f should be easy seeing as a bunch of cultists broke in and blew their way into the inner corridor.

column2: The only issue is that the iron door that leads to the inner corridor got locked during all this commotion.
column3: The only issue is that the iron door that leads to the inner corridor got locked during all this commotion.

column2: To get the key to the door you need to slay &cThe Foundry&f that is located within the vault.
column3: To get the key to the door you need to slay &cThe Foundry&f that is located within the vault.

column2: And to get into the vault you need all the &cMoneychangers&f to let you in.
column3: And to get into the vault you need all the &cMoneychangers&f to let you in.

column2: They all have lost their mind, they are nothing but monsters now. If you want to get into the vault you will have to kill them.
column3: They all have lost their mind, they are nothing but monsters now. If you want to get into the vault you will have to kill them.

column2: &7&oTime to end this curse. I should go into the pyramid and slay &c&oThe Keepers&7&o so I can reach &c&oThe Pharaoh&7&o.
column3: &7&oHora de acabar con esta maldición. Debería entrar en la pirámide y matar a &c&oThe Keepers&7&o para poder llegar a &c&oThe Pharaoh&7&o.

column2: &a[Khalid]&f You did it! The curse has been lifted, you are a true hero! We must prepare a grand feast in your honor. We will make sure to invite your friends from the boat too.
column3: &a[Khalid]&f ¡Lo hiciste! La maldición se ha levantado, ¡eres un verdadero héroe! Debemos preparar un gran festín en tu honor. Nos aseguraremos de invitar también a tus amigos del barco.

column2: &7&oI am so hungry I could eat a creeper.
column3: &7&oTengo tanta hambre que podría comerme un creeper.

column2: We have done our deed. The Void Bell has been rung...
column3: Hemos cumplido nuestra tarea. La Campana del Vacío ha sonado...

column2: Whoever you are, you're way too late...
column3: Quienquiera que seas, llegas demasiado tarde...

column2: The keepers will not let anyone reach the Pharaoh he-he-he.
column3: Los guardianes no dejarán que nadie llegue al Faraón je-je-je.

column2: &a[Tiumautef]&f I can see you that you can take care of yourself.
But still, please be careful. These things know no limits, they don't stop wailing at you no matter how much you damage them...
column3: But still, please be careful. These things know no limits, they don't stop wailing at you no matter how much you damage them...

column2: &7&oI should deal with the nearby monsters and then report back.
column3: &7&oDebería encargarme de los monstruos cercanos y luego informar.

column2: &a[Tiumautef]&f Well that was quite a display of skill. I guess I was worried about you for no reason.
column3: &a[Tiumautef]&f Bueno, eso fue una gran demostración de habilidad. Supongo que me preocupé por ti sin razón.

column2: It would be great if you could help us deal with further issues.
column3: Sería genial si pudieras ayudarnos a lidiar con más problemas.

column2: &7&oSeems like there is more to do around here, I should have a chat with the locals.
column3: &7&oParece que hay más cosas que hacer por aquí, debería charlar con los locales.

column2: We thought we were done for! To be honest I thought that running towards the &dDock&f would be a suicide mission.
column3: We thought we were done for! To be honest I thought that running towards the &dDock&f would be a suicide mission.

column2: Well I am glad that I was wrong. You say you're here to help?
column3: Bueno, me alegro de haberme equivocado. ¿Dices que estás aquí para ayudar?

column2: You can start by killing all these...creatures, they used to be people like us but something awful must have happened since they're nothing but mindless monsters now.
column3: You can start by killing all these...creatures, they used to be people like us but something awful must have happened since they're nothing but mindless monsters now.

column2: Come back to me after you're done, there will be plenty of other tasks to do after you help us clear out the monsters.
column3: Come back to me after you're done, there will be plenty of other tasks to do after you help us clear out the monsters.

column2: &a[Sesochris]&f Do we need help? No, we are OK actually. The golem stops anything that tries to attack us. You should go check on the guard outpost, there is a lot of noise coming from there...
column3: &a[Sesochris]&f ¿Necesitamos ayuda? No, en realidad estamos bien. El golem detiene cualquier cosa que intente atacarnos. Deberías ir a revisar el puesto de guardia, hay mucho ruido viniendo de allí...

column2: &a[Tiumautef]&f Thank you for everything once more! And you watch yourself you hear! There are only so many good people in the world, don't die on us!
column3: &a[Tiumautef]&f ¡Gracias por todo una vez más! ¡Y cuídate, oíste! Solo hay un número limitado de buenas personas en el mundo, ¡no te mueras!

column2: &7&oI should head further into town and look for survivors or anybody else that I can help.
column3: &7&oDebería adentrarme más en la ciudad y buscar supervivientes o cualquier otra persona a la que pueda ayudar.

column2: &a[Nailah]&f I am sorry, but, what are you doing here?
Friend, if you would like to help us further then you should head deeper into town and look for any other survivors that you can help.
column3: Friend, if you would like to help us further then you should head deeper into town and look for any other survivors that you can help.

column2: If it was this bad over here, I cannot even imagine how bad it must be in the town itself.
column3: If it was this bad over here, I cannot even imagine how bad it must be in the town itself.

column2: We had golems patrolling the streets but they can only regenerate so many times before they break down...
column3: We had golems patrolling the streets but they can only regenerate so many times before they break down...

column2: &a[Nailah]&f Don't let your guard down while in there. I have lost many guards in there already...
column3: &a[Nailah]&f No bajes la guardia ahí dentro. Ya he perdido muchos guardias allí...

column2: Before passing away one of my guards reported that the &9Noisy Ones&f are weak to projectiles.
column3: Before passing away one of my guards reported that the &9Noisy Ones&f are weak to projectiles.

column2: &7&oTime to enter the &d&oObservatory&7&o and kill any monsters I come across.
column3: &7&oHora de entrar en el &d&oObservatory&7&o y matar a cualquier monstruo que encuentre.

column2: &a[Nailah]&f Hah! Well you have my respect and trust now, traveler. There are more things to be done around here if you are interested?
column3: &a[Nailah]&f ¡Ja! Bueno, ahora tienes mi respeto y confianza, viajero. ¿Hay más cosas que hacer por aquí si te interesa?

column2: You have come to help? Who the heck are you?
Sorry, but I have a hard time believing some random traveler decided to show up here to help.
column3: Sorry, but I have a hard time believing some random traveler decided to show up here to help.

column2: You know what, the situation here is critical so if you truly mean what you say then prove yourself.
column3: You know what, the situation here is critical so if you truly mean what you say then prove yourself.

column2: We can handle the outbreak in the town.
column3: Podemos controlar el brote en la ciudad.

column2: Our main concern is all the creeps coming from the &dObservatory&f.
column3: Nuestra principal preocupación son todos los bichos que vienen del &dObservatory&f.

column2: I don't know what's going on in there, but if the attacks continue we will be done for.
column3: I don't know what's going on in there, but if the attacks continue we will be done for.

column2: Go in there and if you see anything that looks like it's about to crack your skull and slurp up the insides.
column3: Go in there and if you see anything that looks like it's about to crack your skull and slurp up the insides.

column2: You put it down! Got that? Good! And don't come back here without proof!
column3: ¡Acaba con él! ¿Entendido? ¡Bien! ¡Y no vuelvas aquí sin pruebas!

column2: &6[Bastpaduse] &fYou look like reinforcements. Please tell me you are reinforcements...
column3: &6[Bastpaduse] &fPareces refuerzos. Por favor, dime que eres refuerzos...

column2: &a[Nailah]&f It was damn good working with you, you're a fine fighter. Until next time. And don't let all the praise get to your head.
column3: &a[Nailah]&f Fue genial trabajar contigo, eres un buen luchador. Hasta la próxima. Y no dejes que todos los elogios se te suban a la cabeza.

column2: &a[Bastpaduse]&f You came from &dDessa&f to help out? Well I have no clue who you are but I sure as heck ain't gonna pass up on your offer!
column3: &a[Bastpaduse]&f ¿Viniste de &dDessa&f para ayudar? Bueno, no tengo ni idea de quién eres, ¡pero seguro que no voy a rechazar tu oferta!

column2: &7&oI should talk to &a&oBastpaduse&7&o and see how I can help out.
column3: &7&oDebería hablar con &a&oBastpaduse&7&o y ver cómo puedo ayudar.

column2: I wish I could keep you around here.
But I see that you're willing to help.
column3: Pero veo que estás dispuesto a ayudar.

column2: And it would be wrong of me to be selfish.
column3: Y estaría mal de mi parte ser egoísta.

column2: I am sure &dKhesusiris&f needs your help more than we do now.
column3: Estoy seguro de que &dKhesusiris&f necesita tu ayuda más que nosotros ahora.

column2: Hopefully they have more answers to what is going on right now than we do.
column3: Hopefully they have more answers to what is going on right now than we do.

column2: &a[Bastpaduse] &fTry to not get surrounded, they are not much to take on by themselves but they can be dangerous when there are several of them.
column3: &a[Bastpaduse] &fIntenta no rodearte, no son mucho por sí solos, pero pueden ser peligrosos cuando hay varios de ellos.

column2: &7&oI should slay the &c&oTwisted Dead&7&o and any other creatures near the entrance.
column3: &7&oDebería matar a los &c&oTwisted Dead&7&o y a cualquier otra criatura cerca de la entrada.

column2: &a[Bastpaduse]&f If you would like to continue the fight, I can give you coordinates to our officer.
column3: &a[Bastpaduse]&f Si quieres continuar la lucha, puedo darte las coordenadas de nuestro oficial.

column2: &7&oI should talk to &a&oBastpaduse&7&o to continue my quest.
column3: &7&oDebería hablar con &a&oBastpaduse&7&o para continuar mi misión.

column2: Thanks for helping out with the monsters.
column3: Gracias por ayudar con los monstruos.

column2: We thought we were done for, I wish the rest of our group had made it...
column3: Pensamos que estábamos perdidos, ojalá el resto de nuestro grupo lo hubiera logrado...

column2: But enough of that. We are unable to retreat since the city entrance is overrun by &cTwisted &cDead&f.
column3: But enough of that. We are unable to retreat since the city entrance is overrun by &cTwisted &cDead&f.

column2: Could you help us take them down, so we can rendezvous with the rest of the guards within the city?
column3: Could you help us take them down, so we can rendezvous with the rest of the guards within the city?

column2: &a[Bastpaduse] &fWe will try and meetup with some other guards nearby. Good luck!
column3: &a[Bastpaduse] &fIntentaremos reunirnos con otros guardias cercanos. ¡Buena suerte!

column2: &7&oI should head for the center of the city and look for &a&oOfficer Keknum&7&o.
column3: &7&oDebería dirigirme al centro de la ciudad y buscar al &a&oOficial Keknum&7&o.

column2: &7&oI should have a talk with &a&oOfficer Keknum&7&o.
You want to talk to &aOfficer Keknum&f.
When our patrol group left they were still in the center of the city and I doubt they moved location.
column3: When our patrol group left they were still in the center of the city and I doubt they moved location.

column2: Be careful on your way there.
column3: Ten cuidado en tu camino hacia allí.

column2: There were more of us patrolling the streets at the start.
column3: Éramos más patrullando las calles al principio.

column2: But, there are far less of us now...
&a[Keknum] &fGo scour the city for the bracelet. I really hope you are able to retrieve it.
column3: &a[Keknum] &fVe a rastrear la ciudad en busca de la pulsera. Realmente espero que puedas recuperarla.

column2: &7&oI need to go find the &e&oGolem Control Bracelet&7&o.
column3: &7&oNecesito ir a buscar la &e&oPulsera de Control de Golems&7&o.

column2: &a[Keknum]&f Hah! There it is! And it is still functioning, excellent! Time to get those golems to work.
column3: &a[Keknum]&f ¡Ja! ¡Ahí está! Y todavía funciona, ¡excelente! Es hora de poner a trabajar a esos golems.

column2: &7&oI wonder if &a&oKenum&7&o has more quests for me.
column3: &7&oMe pregunto si &a&oKenum&7&o tiene más misiones para mí.

column2: Well now that you have explained yourself.
column3: Bueno, ahora que te has explicado.

column2: We could indeed use some help.
column3: De hecho, podríamos usar algo de ayuda.

column2: Most importantly I would need you to go retrieve my &eGolem &eControl &eBracelet&f.
column3: Most importantly I would need you to go retrieve my &eGolem &eControl &eBracelet&f.

column2: As we were rushing to secure this location and set up camp, the straps holding the bracelet must have snapped.
column3: As we were rushing to secure this location and set up camp, the straps holding the bracelet must have snapped.

column2: By the time I noticed, we were already here.
column3: Cuando me di cuenta, ya estábamos aquí.

column2: SoI am not sure where exactly the bracelet had fallen off.
column3: Así que no estoy seguro de dónde exactamente se cayó la pulsera.

column2: I need that bracelet. Without it I cannot assign new tasks to the golems.
column3: Necesito esa pulsera. Sin ella no puedo asignar nuevas tareas a los golems.

column2: And we need those golems if we are to make it out of this alive.
column3: Y necesitamos esos golems si queremos salir vivos de esto.
&bLa pesca con lanza es mi pasatiempo.

column2: &8Out of the shadow comes a light
column3: &8Fuera de la sombra aparece una luz

column2: &8whose robes are dull gray, marred by fight.
column3: &8cuyas túnicas son de un gris apagado, estropeadas por la lucha.

column2: &8Of ice and snow, of fire and heat.
column3: &8De hielo y nieve, de fuego y calor.
&8Las hachas rebotan pero las espadas derrotan.
&8Cuidado con el camino que tienes adelante

column2: &fof the bookshelf that holds the best.
column3: &fde la estanteria que contiene lo mejor.
&fpor el uso de sombras y marionetas

column2: &ehide their secrets up rather than down.
column3: &ocultar sus secretos hacia arriba y no hacia abajo.
&bLa armadura del sentry es demasiado resistente

column2: &bwielding a sword, your fight will be rough.
column3: &busar una espada, tu lucha será dificil.

column2: &6for from gold your damage shall abound.
column3: A partir del oro tu daño desaparecerá.
&6Las paredes de los faraones están llenas

column2: &6From the southwest corner of the room with blue windows
column3: &6Desde la esquina suroeste de la habitación con ventanas azules

column2: &3There is a louse of unusual size.
&3Its on the prowl, behold its prize.
column3: &3Está al acecho, he aquí su premio.

column2: &3all you have to do is swim around.
column3: &3Todo lo que tienes que hacer es nadar.

column2: &3then down the right tunnel you must go.
column3: &3luego debes seguir por el túnel de la derecha.
&3La maldad acecha donde se drenan las aguas

column2: &3Be ever watchful, they'll eat your brain!
&3You must open 3 gates guarded by creatures
&32 pages will guide you, do not strain.
column3: &32 páginas te guiarán, no te esfuerces.

column2: &cDozens of weapons have struck the beast
column3: &cDocenas de armas han golpeado a la bestia

column2: &cIt fears not the bite of stone, gold or diamonds in the least
column3: &cNo teme al mordisco de la piedra, el oro o los diamantes en lo más mínimo

column2: &cIf the warlock you seek to slight,
&cThe second floor shall test your might,
column3: &cEl segundo piso pondrá a prueba tu fuerza,

column2: &cDown the spire and into the cave
column3: &cAbajo de la aguja y dentro de la cueva

column2: &cBeware of those returned from the grave,
column3: &cCuidado con los que regresan de la tumba,
&cMata al maestro por lo que anhelas.

column2: &cthe other where books can be read!
column3: &cel otro donde los libros pueden ser leídos!
&4Atrae todos los proyectiles hacia sí mismo.
&4Atrae todos los proyectiles hacia sí mismo.
&4Atrae todos los proyectiles hacia sí mismo.
&ede la que fue la ciudad dorada

column2: &fThe final dungeon of the Oasis adventure!
column3: &8[EM] &7¡Has llegado al Polo Norte! &f¿Has sido travieso este año?
&8[EM] &7Vuelve a visitarnos. &f¡Hay muchos dulces y golosinas para la próxima vez!

column2: &a[Tau]&f Keep an eye out for anything unusual on your way there.
column3: &a[Tau]&f Mantén los ojos abiertos por si ves algo inusual en tu camino.

column2: &7&oI need to find out what has happened to the &d&oLighthouse&7&o.
column3: &7&oNecesito averiguar qué le ha pasado al &d&oFaro&7&o.
&a[Odion]&f ¡Por favor, mata a estas horribles bestias!

column2: Since you already are offering your help. I would like to ask you to find out what is going on with the &dLighthouse&f.
column3: Since you already are offering your help. I would like to ask you to find out what is going on with the &dLighthouse&f.

column2: Since this all started, the lights at the &dLighthouse&f have gone out.
column3: Desde que todo esto comenzó, las luces del &dFaro&f se han apagado.

column2: This is a big issue, the lights need to be on at all times.
column3: Este es un gran problema, las luces deben estar encendidas en todo momento.

column2: You should head that way and see if you can find out what has happened.
column3: Deberías dirigirte hacia allí y ver si puedes averiguar qué ha sucedido.

column2: &a[Odion]&f There are so many of them!
&7&oI should slay the &c&oCrocgators&7&o that are circling the boat.
column3: &7&oDebería matar a los &c&oCrocgators&7&o que están rodeando el bote.

column2: &a[Odion]&f Oh, thank goodness! I express my gratitude for your help. Now excuse me, but I really must go talk to the advisor at once.
column3: &a[Odion]&f ¡Oh, gracias a Dios! Expreso mi gratitud por tu ayuda. Ahora discúlpame, pero realmente debo ir a hablar con el consejero de inmediato.

column2: &7&oI should probably explain that the advisor sent me...
column3: &7&oProbablemente debería explicar que el consejero me envió...

column2: Please, strong warrior. Kill these water beasts.
column3: Por favor, fuerte guerrero. Mata a estas bestias acuáticas.

column2: I was on my way from the &dLighthouse&f when these creatures attacked me and the boat flipped over.
column3: I was on my way from the &dLighthouse&f when these creatures attacked me and the boat flipped over.

column2: I have an important message for the advisor. It is very important that you slay these beasts so I can continue my journey.
column3: I have an important message for the advisor. It is very important that you slay these beasts so I can continue my journey.

column2: &2[Azibo]&f Yes, do I know you? The advisor sent you, excellent!
column3: &2[Azibo]&f Sí, ¿te conozco? ¡El consejero te envió, excelente!

column2: &a[Odion]&f Be sure to mention that they need to come get me. I will be waiting at the nearest shore.
column3: &a[Odion]&f Asegúrate de mencionar que necesitan venir a buscarme. Estaré esperando en la orilla más cercana.

column2: &a[Azibo]&f Yeah, sure. I can explain what happened. While we talk I will send &aUsi&f to go fetch our river friend.
column3: &a[Azibo]&f Sí, claro. Puedo explicar lo que pasó. Mientras hablamos, enviaré a &aUsi&f a buscar a nuestro amigo del río.

column2: &7&oI should hear what happened at the &d&oLighthouse&7&o.
column3: &7&oDebería escuchar lo que pasó en el &d&oFaro&7&o.

column2: Oh! So the advisor was already aware that something is wrong.
column3: ¡Oh! Así que el consejero ya sabía que algo andaba mal.

column2: Yes, he was correct. We have totally lost control of the &dLighthouse&f.
column3: Sí, tenía razón. Hemos perdido totalmente el control del &dFaro&f.

column2: It has become infested with monsters and something has altered the light.
column3: Se ha infestado de monstruos y algo ha alterado la luz.

column2: You should go there and talk to my coworkers, they will tell you more.
column3: Deberías ir allí y hablar con mis compañeros de trabajo, ellos te contarán más.

column2: I need to take a breather now, all of this has been a bit too much for me...
column3: Necesito tomar un respiro ahora, todo esto ha sido un poco demasiado para mí...

column2: &a[Azibo]&f Return to me once you have found the &eKeychain&f and the &eControl Crystals&f.
column3: &a[Azibo]&f Regresa a mí una vez que hayas encontrado el &eLlavero&f y los &eCristales de Control&f.

column2: &7&oI am sure the monsters in the &d&oLighthouse&7&o have the items on them. I should slay some &c&oSentinels&7&o and &c&oSkeletons&7&o until I find the items.
column3: &7&oEstoy seguro de que los monstruos en el &d&oFaro&7&o tienen los objetos consigo. Debería matar algunos &c&oCentinelas&7&o y &c&oEsqueletos&7&o hasta que encuentre los objetos.

column2: &a[Azibo]&f You found them, very good. We can now restore the light.
column3: &a[Azibo]&f Los encontraste, muy bien. Ahora podemos restaurar la luz.

column2: &7&oSeems like &a&oAzibo&7&o has another quest for me.
column3: &7&oParece que &a&oAzibo&7&o tiene otra misión para mí.

column2: After this curse, as you say, was unleashed. All these monsters started appearing. It wasn't the monsters that were bothering us, I can explain more later.
column3: After this curse, as you say, was unleashed. All these monsters started appearing. It wasn't the monsters that were bothering us, I can explain more later.

column2: I am more concerned about our belongings that we managed to loose while we were fleeing.
column3: I am more concerned about our belongings that we managed to loose while we were fleeing.

column2: We dropped our keys and our control crystals. We have been scouting from afar trying to see if we could spot them.
column3: We dropped our keys and our control crystals. We have been scouting from afar trying to see if we could spot them.

column2: But no luck. I wonder if some of the monsters managed to snag them.
column3: Pero sin suerte. Me pregunto si algunos de los monstruos lograron agarrarlos.

column2: The keys we could manage without, but the crystals, we need those.
column3: Las llaves podríamos manejarlas sin ellas, pero los cristales, esos los necesitamos.

column2: The light is impossible to control without the crystals.
column3: La luz es imposible de controlar sin los cristales.

column2: &a[Azibo]&f We will be right behind you, as soon as you calm the light we will take over and restore the light to it's former shape.
column3: &a[Azibo]&f Estaremos justo detrás de ti, tan pronto como calmes la luz tomaremos el control y restauraremos la luz a su forma anterior.

column2: &7&oI need to climb the &d&oLighthouse&7&o and slay the &c&oBeacon&7&o.
&a[Azibo]&f We are truly grateful. Just a second, I have something for you.
column3: &a[Azibo]&f Estamos realmente agradecidos. Solo un segundo, tengo algo para ti.

column2: Ok, time for me to explain why we actually escaped from the &dLighthouse&f.
column3: Ok, es hora de que explique por qué realmente escapamos del &dFaro&f.

column2: We could have just shut our selves in the &dLighthouse&f, we had enough supplies to last us a while and there was no chance the monsters could reach us up there.
column3: We could have just shut our selves in the &dLighthouse&f, we had enough supplies to last us a while and there was no chance the monsters could reach us up there.

column2: But, you see, the light we use. It's different, magical. The curse must have interacted with the light somehow.
column3: But, you see, the light we use. It's different, magical. The curse must have interacted with the light somehow.

column2: It made the light take form. It became a living &cBeacon&f.
column3: Hizo que la luz tomara forma. Se convirtió en un &cFaro&f viviente.

column2: And not a friendly sort of beacon either. If we hadn't escaped, I am sure we would have been floor decoration by now.
column3: And not a friendly sort of beacon either. If we hadn't escaped, I am sure we would have been floor decoration by now.

column2: If the &cBeacon&f gets defeated I am sure that would reset the light and we would be able to take control of it with our &eControl Crystals&f.
column3: If the &cBeacon&f gets defeated I am sure that would reset the light and we would be able to take control of it with our &eControl Crystals&f.

column2: So, you feel like taking on the &cBeacon&f?
&2[Tau]&f I see that the lighthouse is working once again. I assume you have succeeded in your quest?
column3: &2[Tau]&f Veo que el faro vuelve a funcionar. ¿Supongo que has tenido éxito en tu misión?

column2: &7&oI should go speak to the &a&oAdvisor&7&o and claim my reward.
column3: &7&oDebería ir a hablar con el &a&oConsejero&7&o y reclamar mi recompensa.

column2: &a[Tau]&f Ahh, yes. Let me see the letter. Hmm, there is no doubt that what you have done for us is anything but exceptional.
column3: &a[Tau]&f Ahh, sí. Déjame ver la carta. Hmm, no hay duda de que lo que has hecho por nosotros es excepcional.

column2: On behalf of the people of &dOasis&f I would like to present you with this reward. &eRadiance&f is a unique sword which was crafted from a shell of a curious bug that our troops ran into in the desert.
column3: On behalf of the people of &dOasis&f I would like to present you with this reward. &eRadiance&f is a unique sword which was crafted from a shell of a curious bug that our troops ran into in the desert.

column2: Usually this sword would be reserved for royalty but in such dire times as these it would be more useful in the hands of a capable warrior.
column3: Usually this sword would be reserved for royalty but in such dire times as these it would be more useful in the hands of a capable warrior.

column2: &7&oThis sword, it doesn't feel right. As if it's powers are channeled from a higher being. If I point the sword towards the pyramid, I can see the source of the curse in my mind, it fears this blade...
column3: &7&oEsta espada, no se siente bien. Como si sus poderes fueran canalizados desde un ser superior. Si apunto la espada hacia la pirámide, puedo ver la fuente de la maldición en mi mente, teme esta hoja...

column2: Here take this letter. It describes everything you have done for us here.
column3: Aquí toma esta carta. Describe todo lo que has hecho por nosotros aquí.

column2: With our official seal on there confirming all your deeds. Go and show it to the &aAdvisor&f.
column3: With our official seal on there confirming all your deeds. Go and show it to the &aAdvisor&f.

column2: I am certain you will be rewarded properly!
column3: ¡Estoy seguro de que serás recompensado adecuadamente!
&eEsta espada refleja la luz tan brillantemente

column2: &ethat one might mistake it for a torch.
column3: &eque uno podría confundirla con una antorcha.

column2: &eEven in the darkest of places it's light
column3: &eIncluso en los lugares más oscuros su luz

column2: &fA blade of unknown make and origin.
column3: &fUna hoja de fabricación y origen desconocidos.

column2: &a[Tau]&f You may not see it like this, but this is a very important task.
column3: &a[Tau]&f Puede que no lo veas así, pero esta es una tarea muy importante.

column2: &7&oWell, time to go locate the vermin and eradicate them.
column3: &7&oBueno, es hora de ir a localizar las verminas y erradicarlas.

column2: &a[Tau]&f Fine work! For a job well done you will be well rewarded! 333 coins!
column3: &a[Tau]&f ¡Buen trabajo! ¡Por un trabajo bien hecho serás bien recompensado! ¡333 monedas!

column2: &7&oMakes me wonder what their paper tastes like.
column3: &7&oMe pregunto a qué sabrá su papel.

column2: This might not be right time for such an important task.
column3: Este podría no ser el momento adecuado para una tarea tan importante.

column2: But with all the guards dead and everyone else having turned into vicious monsters.
column3: But with all the guards dead and everyone else having turned into vicious monsters.

column2: There is no one left to defend our glorious palace from it's true threat!
column3: ¡No queda nadie para defender nuestro glorioso palacio de su verdadera amenaza!

column2: There are a lot of important documents inside our palace that we absolutely cannot afford to lose.
column3: There are a lot of important documents inside our palace that we absolutely cannot afford to lose.

column2: But these &cPaper &cVermin&f have been getting inside and nibbling on our important documents like it was premium cheese!
column3: But these &cPaper &cVermin&f have been getting inside and nibbling on our important documents like it was premium cheese!

column2: We cannot allow this to continue!
I need you to go out there and eliminate all vermin that you manage to find!
column3: ¡Necesito que salgas y elimines todas las verminas que logres encontrar!

column2: &eUsed to crack open wooden crates and more...
column3: &eUsada para abrir cajas de madera y más...

column2: &a[Sosche]&f Good luck! Beware of the critters!
&7&oI should dive into the river and look for the &e&oFood&7&o.
column3: &7&oDebería sumergirme en el río y buscar la &e&oComida&7&o.

column2: &a[Sosche]&f You did it! And everything is still in good shape, excellent!
column3: &a[Sosche]&f ¡Lo hiciste! Y todo sigue en buen estado, ¡excelente!

column2: Hail! Thank you for helping us deal with all the monsters.
column3: ¡Salve! Gracias por ayudarnos a lidiar con todos los monstruos.

column2: I thought that the poor crowd at the plaza was done for.
column3: Pensé que la pobre multitud en la plaza estaba acabada.

column2: Would you mind helping me out?
When I was escaping to safety here I dropped my sack of food.
column3: Cuando estaba escapando a un lugar seguro aquí, se me cayó mi saco de comida.

column2: And it drifted down to the bottom of the river. I would have gotten it myself, but some nasty critters got lured out by the food and are now circling the area.
column3: And it drifted down to the bottom of the river. I would have gotten it myself, but some nasty critters got lured out by the food and are now circling the area.

column2: I would really appreciate it if you could go retrieve the &eFood&f. There are a lot of hungry people to feed...
column3: I would really appreciate it if you could go retrieve the &eFood&f. There are a lot of hungry people to feed...

column2: &a[Tu-en-hor]&f Watch yourself those things can be vicious. I would try hunting them with a bow. Best to keep your distance...
column3: &a[Tu-en-hor]&f Ten cuidado, esas cosas pueden ser viciosas. Intentaría cazarlas con un arco. Lo mejor es mantener la distancia...

column2: &7&oTime to go slay some &c&oRabbid Rabbits&7&o and fetch those &e&oSticks&7&0.
column3: &7&oEs hora de ir a matar algunos &c&oConejos Rabiosos&7&o y buscar esos &e&oPalos&7&0.

column2: &a[Tu-en-hor]&f Thank you, so much! But, uhhh...
&7&oSeems like I am not done with this quest yet....
column3: &7&oParece que aún no he terminado con esta misión....

column2: Hey how's it going! So, uhhhh...
Can I ask you for a huge favor? Now that you made this area safe again.
column3: ¿Puedo pedirte un gran favor? Ahora que has vuelto a hacer segura esta zona.

column2: I would like to climb down, but there is a small issue. When I was rushing to climb this fountain, I banged up my knee real good and I can barely move my leg.
column3: I would like to climb down, but there is a small issue. When I was rushing to climb this fountain, I banged up my knee real good and I can barely move my leg.

column2: It would be great if you could get me a ladder.
column3: Sería genial si pudieras conseguirme una escalera.

column2: The only issue is the monsters destroyed all the ladders we had around here.
column3: The only issue is the monsters destroyed all the ladders we had around here.

column2: So if you could go fetch some sticks so we can make a new one.
column3: Así que si pudieras ir a buscar algunos palos para que podamos hacer una nueva.

column2: And not just any sticks, these need to be sturdy high quality sticks.
column3: Y no cualquier palo, estos necesitan ser palos resistentes de alta calidad.

column2: You can go hunt &cRabbid Rabbits&f for the sticks. They carry sticks in their mouths, it's some sort of defense method.
column3: You can go hunt &cRabbid Rabbits&f for the sticks. They carry sticks in their mouths, it's some sort of defense method.

column2: They only pick the best sticks so you will know you got a quality stick if you get it from them.
column3: They only pick the best sticks so you will know you got a quality stick if you get it from them.

column2: &a[Tiumautef] &fYou need me to make a ladder? Yeah, sure. No problem!
column3: &a[Tiumautef] &f¿Necesitas que haga una escalera? Sí, claro. ¡No hay problema!

column2: &a[Tu-en-hor]&f Search the ground around the palm trees carefully, the fiber shouldn't be that hard to find.
column3: &a[Tu-en-hor]&f Busca con cuidado en el suelo alrededor de las palmeras, la fibra no debería ser tan difícil de encontrar.

column2: Oh! Almost forgot! Here, the sticks. Take these to Tiumautef too.
column3: ¡Oh! ¡Casi lo olvido! Aquí, los palos. Llévaselos también a Tiumautef.

column2: &7&oI should search the palm tree surroundings for &e&oPalm Tree Fiber&7&0.
column3: &7&oDebería buscar en los alrededores de las palmeras &e&oFibra de Palmera&7&0.

column2: &a[Tiumautef]&f Don't worry about the rest. Once I have made the ladder I will take it to Tu-en-hor and help him down.
column3: &a[Tiumautef]&f No te preocupes por el resto. Una vez que haya hecho la escalera, se la llevaré a Tu-en-hor y le ayudaré a bajar.

column2: &7&oMaybe we should start stocking ladders on our ship...
column3: &7&oQuizás deberíamos empezar a almacenar escaleras en nuestro barco...

column2: I am very grateful, but there is not much I can do with just these sticks.
column3: Estoy muy agradecido, pero no hay mucho que pueda hacer solo con estos palos.

column2: We will need some string to shape these sticks into an actual ladder.
column3: We will need some string to shape these sticks into an actual ladder.

column2: The palm trees shed a lot of fiber that can be used as string.
column3: Las palmeras sueltan mucha fibra que se puede usar como cuerda.

column2: If you search the surrounding area of a palm tree you should be able to gather enough to make a ladder.
column3: If you search the surrounding area of a palm tree you should be able to gather enough to make a ladder.

column2: After that you can go to &aTiumatef&f and he will help you make a ladder.
column3: Después de eso, puedes ir a &aTiumatef&f y él te ayudará a hacer una escalera.

column2: &a[Tiumautef]&f We need you to clear the wildlife in the river, the palm forest and the sands.
column3: &a[Tiumautef]&f Necesitamos que despejes la fauna en el río, el bosque de palmeras y las arenas.

column2: &a[Tiumautef]&f All done? Very good, we will try and gather as many supplies as we can and take it to your boat as soon as we can.
column3: &a[Tiumautef]&f ¿Todo listo? Muy bien, intentaremos reunir tantos suministros como podamos y los llevaremos a tu barco tan pronto como sea posible.
&7&oAl Capitán le va a encantar esto.

column2: As a thanks for your help we wanted to gather some supplies for you and carry them over to the boat.
column3: As a thanks for your help we wanted to gather some supplies for you and carry them over to the boat.

column2: But the local wildlife is making it quite hard.
column3: Pero la fauna local lo está haciendo bastante difícil.

column2: If it is not to much to ask, could you cull some of their numbers so we can gather the supplies without worrying about getting attacked?
column3: If it is not to much to ask, could you cull some of their numbers so we can gather the supplies without worrying about getting attacked?

column2: &a[Ramla]&f The beasts should be asleep, so you will have the advantage.
column3: &a[Ramla]&f Las bestias deberían estar dormidas, así que tendrás la ventaja.

column2: &a[Ramla]&f On behalf of all of &dDessa&f I would like to express our deepest gratitude. Your kindness knows no bounds.
column3: &a[Ramla]&f En nombre de toda &dDessa&f, me gustaría expresar nuestra más profunda gratitud. Tu amabilidad no conoce límites.

column2: &7&oWhere did those beasts come from anyway.
column3: &7&o¿De dónde vinieron esas bestias de todos modos?

column2: One last request if I may. Since the situation in &dDessa&f is now stabilizing.
column3: One last request if I may. Since the situation in &dDessa&f is now stabilizing.

column2: We need to be able to reach the other settlements, there is one tiny issue with this.
column3: We need to be able to reach the other settlements, there is one tiny issue with this.

column2: There are beasts in this area that have grown fond of the taste of our wooden bridge.
column3: There are beasts in this area that have grown fond of the taste of our wooden bridge.

column2: They like to sneak onto the bridges and nibble on the wood until they pass out.
column3: Les gusta colarse en los puentes y mordisquear la madera hasta que se desmayan.

column2: They are quite large so there is no way around them once they fall asleep.
column3: Son bastante grandes, así que no hay forma de rodearlos una vez que se duermen.

column2: The guards used to keep them away from the bridges but with the current situation the guards were too busy with more important tasks as you can imagine.
column3: The guards used to keep them away from the bridges but with the current situation the guards were too busy with more important tasks as you can imagine.

column2: So feel like clearing some bridges of beasts?
column3: ¿Así que te apetece despejar algunos puentes de bestias?

column2: Oh! There are also some water monsters that are too close to the bridges for safe passage to be possible. Those should be taken care of as well.
column3: Oh! There are also some water monsters that are too close to the bridges for safe passage to be possible. Those should be taken care of as well.

column2: &a[Nailah]&f Make sure you rejuvenate the golem on the hill. That one is top priority. It has been tasked with drawing all the creatures away from town. Make sure it keeps doing it's job. Understood?
column3: &a[Nailah]&f Asegúrate de rejuvenecer el golem de la colina. Ese es la máxima prioridad. Se le ha encomendado la tarea de alejar a todas las criaturas del pueblo. Asegúrate de que siga haciendo su trabajo. ¿Entendido?

column2: &a[Nailah]&f Don't forget, the tool is in the chest behind me.
column3: &a[Nailah]&f No olvides, la herramienta está en el cofre detrás de mí.

column2: &7&oI need to rejuvenate all 5 &a&oDessa Sand Golems&7&o scattered around town.
column3: &7&oNecesito rejuvenecer los 5 &a&oGolems de Arena de Dessa&7&o dispersos por el pueblo.

column2: &a[Nailah]&f I see that all 5 jewels on my command bracelet are showing green. So I assume everything is in order. Another job well done. You are surprisingly skilled.
column3: &a[Nailah]&f Veo que las 5 joyas de mi brazalete de mando están en verde. Así que supongo que todo está en orden. Otro trabajo bien hecho. Eres sorprendentemente hábil.

column2: &7&oWe should get some of these golems for the Adventurer's Guild.
column3: &7&oDeberíamos conseguir algunos de estos golems para el Gremio de Aventureros.

column2: I am sure you saw our golems in the streets on your way here.
column3: Estoy seguro de que viste a nuestros golems en las calles de camino aquí.

column2: Well, they are in critical state because SOMEONE, decided it would be a good idea to change the maintenance interval on these to every 6 months!
column3: Well, they are in critical state because SOMEONE, decided it would be a good idea to change the maintenance interval on these to every 6 months!

column2: I need a brave soul to go out there and rejuvenate them with new smart-sand.
column3: Necesito un alma valiente que salga y los rejuvenezca con arena inteligente nueva.

column2: You can get the tool from the chest behind me.
column3: Puedes conseguir la herramienta del cofre que está detrás de mí.

column2: To use the tool approach a golem and insert the tool inside the golem.
column3: To use the tool approach a golem and insert the tool inside the golem.

column2: Make sure you are only using the tool, if try this with anything else the golem will detect you as a threat and start attacking.
column3: Make sure you are only using the tool, if try this with anything else the golem will detect you as a threat and start attacking.

column2: If done correctly the golem will collapse into a pile of sand. This is normal, after a few minutes the golem will reconstruct itself using the new supply of smart-sand.
column3: If done correctly the golem will collapse into a pile of sand. This is normal, after a few minutes the golem will reconstruct itself using the new supply of smart-sand.

column2: &a[Nailah]&f Make sure you are properly armed before you storm the place. Good luck!
column3: &a[Nailah]&f Asegúrate de estar bien armado antes de asaltar el lugar. ¡Buena suerte!
