column2: &7&oI need to make sure I have the right equipment before I attempt this quest.
column3: &7&oNecesito asegurarme de tener el equipo adecuado antes de intentar esta misión.

column2: &a[Nailah]&f HAHAHA! We could hear the vampire screams from all the way here! Another mission accomplished. If you were a part of our guard you would be getting a medal right now!
column3: &a[Nailah]&f ¡JAJAJA! ¡Podíamos oír los gritos de los vampiros desde aquí! Otra misión cumplida. Si fueras parte de nuestra guardia, ¡estarías recibiendo una medalla ahora mismo!

column2: I am puzzled by the vampires though. Whatever caused all the people to turn into monsters would have nothing to do with the vampires. They must have been there before all of this happened.
column3: I am puzzled by the vampires though. Whatever caused all the people to turn into monsters would have nothing to do with the vampires. They must have been there before all of this happened.

column2: After the current situation is resolved I need to investigate the &dObservatory&f and find out what exactly was going on in there...
column3: After the current situation is resolved I need to investigate the &dObservatory&f and find out what exactly was going on in there...

column2: &7&oMaybe I should have asked the &a&oCaptain&7&o for some garlic.
column3: &7&oQuizás debería haberle pedido algo de ajo al &a&oCapitán&7&o.

column2: Since the &dObservatory&f seems to be filled with creatures, we should clear out the entire area.
column3: Since the &dObservatory&f seems to be filled with creatures, we should clear out the entire area.

column2: We had some scouts sneak in behind you, while you were in there clearing the first floor. One of them managed to return in one piece.
column3: We had some scouts sneak in behind you, while you were in there clearing the first floor. One of them managed to return in one piece.

column2: They scouted the rest of the area and, well. What they found is quite concerning.
column3: Exploraron el resto del área y, bueno. Lo que encontraron es bastante preocupante.

column2: I am sure you ran into some former citizens that got turned into twisted monsters, but there are far worse things in there.
column3: I am sure you ran into some former citizens that got turned into twisted monsters, but there are far worse things in there.

column2: Apparently vampiric creatures were sighted in the deeper areas of the &dObservatory&f.
column3: Apparently vampiric creatures were sighted in the deeper areas of the &dObservatory&f.

column2: These creatures will be the top priority, do not return until you have slain them.
column3: Estas criaturas serán la máxima prioridad, no regreses hasta que las hayas matado.

column2: I assume you are familiar with vampires? Anything &9Wooden and &9Pointy&f should make short work of them. Well, ready to head back there?
column3: I assume you are familiar with vampires? Anything &9Wooden and &9Pointy&f should make short work of them. Well, ready to head back there?

column2: &a[Ramla]&f I know you can handle yourself, but be careful.
column3: &a[Ramla]&f Sé que puedes cuidarte, pero ten cuidado.

column2: &7&oI guess I should go kill them but be respectful about it.
column3: &7&oSupongo que debería ir a matarlos, pero ser respetuoso al respecto.

column2: &a[Ramla]&f Thank you, traveler. I have another favor to ask of you if you're up for it?
column3: &a[Ramla]&f Gracias, viajero. ¿Tengo otro favor que pedirte si estás dispuesto?

column2: Sorry to bother you. But I would really be grateful if you could do us a favor.
column3: Sorry to bother you. But I would really be grateful if you could do us a favor.

column2: This curse or plague or whatever it is has resurrected some of our towns most honored citizens. It is a disrespect to them and everything living that they now wander the town as these awful abominations.
column3: This curse or plague or whatever it is has resurrected some of our towns most honored citizens. It is a disrespect to them and everything living that they now wander the town as these awful abominations.

column2: Please put them back to rest. Let them be at peace once more.
column3: Por favor, devuélvelos al descanso. Que estén en paz una vez más.

column2: &fBut who would carry around a fish.
&fMade to handle the toxic wastes of the sewer.
column3: &fHechos para soportar los residuos tóxicos de la alcantarilla.

column2: &eIt's a fishing rod, from the abyss.
column3: &eEs una caña de pescar, del abismo.

column2: &dYou feel like doing evil every time you use this pickaxe.
column3: &dSientes ganas de hacer el mal cada vez que usas este pico.

column2: &a[Keknum]&f I hope you don't mind getting wet. Unless, you maybe used a fishing rod with a really durable line and a sharp hook...hmmm. Uhh..just ignore that last part, carry on!
column3: &a[Keknum]&f Espero que no te importe mojarte. A menos que, quizás usaste una caña de pescar con una línea realmente duradera y un anzuelo afilado... hmmm. Uhh... ignora esa última parte, ¡continúa!

column2: &7&oTime to go clear the nearby waters of its unwelcome guests.
column3: &7&oHora de ir a despejar las aguas cercanas de sus huéspedes no deseados.

column2: &a[Keknum]&f Sent the floaters back to the depths? Good!
column3: &a[Keknum]&f ¿Enviaste a los flotantes de vuelta a las profundidades? ¡Bien!

column2: &7&oI should have looked for some pearls while I was down there.
column3: &7&oDebería haber buscado algunas perlas mientras estaba allí abajo.

column2: Not only are we dealing with all these monsters in the streets but apparently the waters have become infested with living corpses of people who have drowned in the river.
column3: Not only are we dealing with all these monsters in the streets but apparently the waters have become infested with living corpses of people who have drowned in the river.

column2: If you don't mind I would like to task you with going down to the river and making sure this problem goes away.
column3: If you don't mind I would like to task you with going down to the river and making sure this problem goes away.

column2: We already have enough to do with just trying to hold the city, I don't want to worry about an attack from the river now too.
column3: We already have enough to do with just trying to hold the city, I don't want to worry about an attack from the river now too.

column2: &a[Asim]&f Make sure you clear the gardens of all the foes so we can go there and collect the fruits later.
column3: &a[Asim]&f Asegúrate de despejar los jardines de todos los enemigos para que podamos ir allí y recoger las frutas más tarde.

column2: &7&oKill monsters and fetch &e&oGarden Fruit&7&o, got it.
column3: &7&oMatar monstruos y traer &e&oFruta del Jardín&7&o, entendido.

column2: &a[Asim]&f I could smell the fresh fruits before I even saw you coming back. Many thanks, this will really help inspire the troops and keep them going.
column3: &a[Asim]&f Pude oler las frutas frescas antes incluso de verte regresar. Muchas gracias, esto realmente ayudará a inspirar a las tropas y a mantenerlas en marcha.

column2: &7&oWe should stock up on these after all this is over.
column3: &7&oDeberíamos abastecernos de estas después de que todo esto termine.

column2: Could I bother you with a tiny request?
You see we grow special energy fruits in this city.
column3: Verás, cultivamos frutas energéticas especiales en esta ciudad.

column2: And I was thinking that if we could free the gardens from undesirables, we could have a steady supply for the soldiers.
column3: And I was thinking that if we could free the gardens from undesirables, we could have a steady supply for the soldiers.

column2: It would be a great way to boost morale and make sure the troops have plenty of energy.
column3: It would be a great way to boost morale and make sure the troops have plenty of energy.

column2: Oh and make sure you also bring back some &eGarden &eFruits&f while you're already heading to the &dGardens&f.
column3: Oh and make sure you also bring back some &eGarden &eFruits&f while you're already heading to the &dGardens&f.

column2: &a[Tsiskha]&f Also a group of us did not make it out. &aOfficer Keknum&f was planning to send someone to rescue them, you should speak to him about this, unless you already did.
column3: &a[Tsiskha]&f También un grupo de nosotros no logró salir. El &aOficial Keknum&f planeaba enviar a alguien a rescatarlos, deberías hablar con él sobre esto, a menos que ya lo hayas hecho.

column2: &7&oI should go to the &d&oLibrary&7&o and gather any books that might be useful.
column3: &7&oDebería ir a la &d&oBiblioteca&7&o y recoger cualquier libro que pueda ser útil.

column2: &a[Tsiskha]&f You've proven to be more than just a force of strength and power, as you've returned with books that shed light on the situation and hold vital information for us. Well done! I am truly grateful from the depths of my heart.
column3: &a[Tsiskha]&f Has demostrado ser más que una fuerza de fortaleza y poder, ya que has regresado con libros que arrojan luz sobre la situación y contienen información vital para nosotros. ¡Bien hecho! Estoy verdaderamente agradecida desde lo más profundo de mi corazón.

column2: &7&oI just picked books on undead and curses and took with me the heaviest ones...
column3: &7&oSolo elegí libros sobre no muertos y maldiciones y me llevé los más pesados...

column2: Adventurer! How lucky am I to get attention from such a capable warrior. Or maybe it is not luck but destiny? As you can see the guards managed to help some of us librarians escape the now besieged &dLibrary&f.
column3: Adventurer! How lucky am I to get attention from such a capable warrior. Or maybe it is not luck but destiny? As you can see the guards managed to help some of us librarians escape the now besieged &dLibrary&f.

column2: We would love to help out in any way possible but our expertise lies in the written word and not in sword and shield.
column3: We would love to help out in any way possible but our expertise lies in the written word and not in sword and shield.

column2: But, if a brave warrior such as yourself would lend us a hand in retrieving some books from the library we could research what exactly is going on and provide the guards with valuable information against the fight of these undead or whatever they are. So would you mind helping us out?
column3: But, if a brave warrior such as yourself would lend us a hand in retrieving some books from the library we could research what exactly is going on and provide the guards with valuable information against the fight of these undead or whatever they are. So would you mind helping us out?

column2: &a[Keknum]&f None of our guards use crossbows so if you see a bolt heading your way. You find the source and make sure it never fires another bolt again.
column3: &a[Keknum]&f Ninguno de nuestros guardias usa ballestas, así que si ves un proyectil dirigiéndose hacia ti. Encuentra la fuente y asegúrate de que nunca vuelva a disparar otro proyectil.

column2: &7&oTime to put the &c&oOld Bones&7&o to rest.
column3: &7&oHora de poner a descansar a los &c&oHuesos Viejos&7&o.

column2: &a[Keknum]&f Done already? Good. My guards have taken out the rest of them, so, we should be good on that front.
column3: &a[Keknum]&f ¿Ya terminaste? Bien. Mis guardias se han encargado del resto, así que, deberíamos estar bien en ese frente.

column2: &7&oAnother day and another good deed done.
column3: &7&oOtro día y otra buena acción hecha.

column2: As you probably noticed some of the citizens and the guards decided to take cover on the roof tops.
column3: As you probably noticed some of the citizens and the guards decided to take cover on the roof tops.

column2: I want to make sure that they stay safe up there.
column3: Quiero asegurarme de que permanezcan seguros allí arriba.

column2: My guards have reported that there are monsters out there armed with crossbows. &cOld &cBones&f they call them.
column3: My guards have reported that there are monsters out there armed with crossbows. &cOld &cBones&f they call them.

column2: I want you to go into the streets and dispose of anything that is wielding a crossbow.
column3: I want you to go into the streets and dispose of anything that is wielding a crossbow.

column2: &a[Rak-hor]&f Are you the one they sent? Ok, here is the list of all the nasty things that need to be slain and their locations. Navigating the sewers can be a challenge so patience is key. Good luck!
column3: &a[Rak-hor]&f ¿Eres tú a quien enviaron? Ok, aquí tienes la lista de todas las cosas desagradables que necesitan ser eliminadas y sus ubicaciones. Navegar por las alcantarillas puede ser un desafío, así que la paciencia es clave. ¡Buena suerte!

column2: &a[Rak-hor]&f By the way, you can squeeze through tight spaces if you swim real quick!
column3: &a[Rak-hor]&f Por cierto, ¡puedes pasar por espacios estrechos si nadas muy rápido!

column2: &a[Asim]&f One of our contacts will be waiting in a sewage drain. You should meet up with him first. Here is his location.
column3: &a[Asim]&f Uno de nuestros contactos estará esperando en un desagüe. Deberías reunirte con él primero. Aquí está su ubicación.

column2: &7&oI should meet up with the contact and then see if I can find a way into the &d&oSewers&7&o.
column3: &7&oDebería reunirme con el contacto y luego ver si puedo encontrar una forma de entrar en las &d&oAlcantarillas&7&o.

column2: &a[Asim]&f Good to see you. Now with the sewers cleared there is one less threat for the guards to worry about. Thank you for supporting us!
column3: &a[Asim]&f Me alegra verte. Ahora con las alcantarillas despejadas, hay una amenaza menos de la que los guardias deben preocuparse. ¡Gracias por apoyarnos!

column2: &7&oThey need to make their sewers less complicated...
Friend if we could bother you with a new request.
column3: Amigo, si pudiéramos molestarte con una nueva petición.

column2: Some of us have been scouting the city to help out the guards and we found something quite disturbing.
column3: Some of us have been scouting the city to help out the guards and we found something quite disturbing.

column2: One of the scouts reported finding all sorts of nasty things now roaming the city &dSewers&f.
column3: One of the scouts reported finding all sorts of nasty things now roaming the city &dSewers&f.

column2: What is down there right now is not much of a threat but it might become one if not taken care of.
column3: What is down there right now is not much of a threat but it might become one if not taken care of.

column2: We think there is no need to bother the guards with this task since I am confident that with your aid we can handle this problem.
column3: We think there is no need to bother the guards with this task since I am confident that with your aid we can handle this problem.

column2: We need you to go down into the &dSewers&f with our volunteers and clear some of the nasty things that now inhabit the space.
column3: We need you to go down into the &dSewers&f with our volunteers and clear some of the nasty things that now inhabit the space.

column2: &cA shield made out of a ladder.
&a[Usi]&f Hope you teach them that squatting is not accepted around these parts even if you're just a bunch of monsters.
column3: &a[Usi]&f Espero que les enseñes que okupar no está permitido por aquí, aunque solo seáis un montón de monstruos.

column2: &7&oTime to clear the nearby cabin area and make sure it's safe.
column3: &7&oEs hora de despejar la zona de cabañas cercana y asegurarse de que sea segura.

column2: &a[Usi]&f It is gonna be so good to finally be able to sleep in my own bed again!
column3: &a[Usi]&f ¡Será tan bueno poder dormir finalmente en mi propia cama de nuevo!

column2: If you feel like helping out then I have a task for you. I am sure that you saw all the river cabins on your way here.
column3: If you feel like helping out then I have a task for you. I am sure that you saw all the river cabins on your way here.

column2: Well those used to be our homes before the entire area became populated with undead, the cursed and monsters.
column3: Well those used to be our homes before the entire area became populated with undead, the cursed and monsters.

column2: It would be really awesome if someone brave and mighty such as yourself would solve this matter for us.
column3: It would be really awesome if someone brave and mighty such as yourself would solve this matter for us.

column2: &a[Usi]&f Oh, and if you find anything of value there, it's yours for the keeping.
column3: &a[Usi]&f Oh, y si encuentras algo de valor allí, es tuyo para quedártelo.

column2: &7&oI should head for the nearby &9&oEast Dock&7&o and convince the ship crew to leave.
column3: &7&oDebería dirigirme al &9&oMuelle Este&7&o cercano y convencer a la tripulación del barco de que se vaya.

column2: &a[Usi]&f And that is another problem solved. Thank you, kind sir.
column3: &a[Usi]&f Y ese es otro problema resuelto. Gracias, amable señor.

column2: &7&oI wonder how many more unwelcome guests have managed to find their way into this land during this chaos.
column3: &7&oMe pregunto cuántos invitados no deseados más han logrado encontrar su camino a esta tierra durante este caos.

column2: It seems we have unwelcome guests on our dock. They must have used this chaos to sneak in and dock their ship.
column3: It seems we have unwelcome guests on our dock. They must have used this chaos to sneak in and dock their ship.

column2: We really do not need anymore trouble. Would you go to their ship and use your weapons to convince them to go back to where they came from?
column3: We really do not need anymore trouble. Would you go to their ship and use your weapons to convince them to go back to where they came from?

column2: &a[Usi]&f Make sure you are well prepared before you go out there.
column3: &a[Usi]&f Asegúrate de estar bien preparado antes de salir.

column2: &7&oTime to test my patience and my skill.
column3: &7&oEs hora de poner a prueba mi paciencia y mi habilidad.

column2: &a[Usi]&f Fine work! Here are your coins as promised!
column3: &a[Usi]&f ¡Buen trabajo! ¡Aquí tienes tus monedas como prometido!

column2: Sure is sad to see the &dLighthouse&f infested with these monsters.
column3: Ciertamente es triste ver el &dFaro&f infestado de estos monstruos.

column2: We wanted to let the &dTappesheh&f forces deal with them, but I see that you are here and capable.
column3: We wanted to let the &dTappesheh&f forces deal with them, but I see that you are here and capable.

column2: Up for the task? We will pay good coin for this one, but it will be a daunting task clearing all the monsters.
column3: Up for the task? We will pay good coin for this one, but it will be a daunting task clearing all the monsters.

column2: &dIt is either a bow taken from a pirate.
column3: &dEs un arco tomado de un pirata.

column2: &dOr a bow used to hunt pirates.
column3: &dO un arco usado para cazar piratas.

column2: &eThey will all pay for what they have done!
column3: &e¡Todos pagarán por lo que han hecho!

column2: &dLooks like a trident but it is totally a spear.
column3: &dParece un tridente pero es totalmente una lanza.

column2: &7From the deepest depths it shall poke.
&a[Khalid]&f I am sure that I do not need to point out to you what fiends need to be disposed of. I mean there are so many of them it should be pretty clear...
column3: &a[Khalid]&f Estoy seguro de que no necesito señalarte qué demonios deben ser eliminados. Quiero decir, hay tantos que debería estar bastante claro...

column2: &7&oSeems like I should clear the &d&oHarbor&7&o of &c&oHexed Haulers&7&o and &c&oSkeletal Sharpshooters&7&o. Well better get to it.
column3: &7&oParece que debería despejar el &d&oPuerto&7&o de &c&oTransportadores Embrujados&7&o y &c&oTiradores Esqueléticos&7&o. Bueno, mejor me pongo a ello.

column2: &a[Khalid]&f Welcome back friend. While you were out there fighting the good fight our forces took this chance to do some scouting. We managed to find the reason that was causing us such grief. We should eliminate this threat as soon as possible!
column3: &a[Khalid]&f Bienvenido de nuevo, amigo. Mientras estabas ahí fuera librando la buena batalla, nuestras fuerzas aprovecharon para hacer algo de exploración. Logramos encontrar la razón que nos estaba causando tanto pesar. ¡Deberíamos eliminar esta amenaza lo antes posible!

column2: &7&oI should talk to &a&oKhalid&7&o about this threat.
If you want me to keep you busy, well do I have a task for you my friend.
column3: Si quieres que te mantenga ocupado, bueno, tengo una tarea para ti, amigo mío.

column2: We have been trying to retake the &dHarbor&f to no avail.
column3: Hemos estado intentando retomar el &dPuerto&f sin éxito.

column2: It feels like every time we make any progress, more of those darn monsters just pop up.
column3: It feels like every time we make any progress, more of those darn monsters just pop up.

column2: Your help might just be the edge that we need to secure the &dHarbor&f.
column3: Tu ayuda podría ser justo la ventaja que necesitamos para asegurar el &dPuerto&f.

column2: &a[Khalid]&f We are not sure what it is capable of, so make sure you are well prepared and be ready for anything.
column3: &a[Khalid]&f No estamos seguros de lo que es capaz, así que asegúrate de estar bien preparado y listo para cualquier cosa.

column2: &7&oI should hurry and go slay the &c&oMonumental Monstrosity&7&o before it has a chance to use it's powers.
column3: &7&oDebería darme prisa e ir a matar a la &c&oMonstruosidad Monumental&7&o antes de que tenga la oportunidad de usar sus poderes.

column2: &a[Khalid]&f Well if it isn't our harbor hero! Well done friend, the &dHarbor&f has now been fully secured!
column3: &a[Khalid]&f ¡Vaya, si no es nuestro héroe del puerto! Bien hecho, amigo, ¡el &dPuerto&f ha sido completamente asegurado!

column2: &7&oThat was one heck of a tough balloon fish.
column3: &7&oEse fue un pez globo increíblemente duro.

column2: You won't believe it but we found the source of our woes.
column3: No lo creerás, pero encontramos la fuente de nuestras desgracias.

column2: A foul monster has settled in the &dHarbor&f and has been resurrecting the fiends we were slaying.
column3: A foul monster has settled in the &dHarbor&f and has been resurrecting the fiends we were slaying.

column2: No wonder, we could not make any progress.
column3: Con razón, no podíamos hacer ningún progreso.

column2: It takes it a while to gather it's powers to resurrect the fiends, so we should strike before it has a chance to use it's powers again.
column3: It takes it a while to gather it's powers to resurrect the fiends, so we should strike before it has a chance to use it's powers again.

column2: &a[Nahab]&f I am not sure how you are going to get on top of the &dWarehouse&f. Just a find a way to get up there and make sure that the &cGhost&f never bothers us again.
column3: &a[Nahab]&f No estoy seguro de cómo vas a subir encima del &dAlmacén&f. Solo encuentra una forma de subir y asegúrate de que el &cFantasma&f nunca nos moleste de nuevo.

column2: &7&oGetting on top of the &d&oWarehouse&7&o is going to be a challenge...
column3: &7&oSubir encima del &d&oAlmacén&7&o va a ser un desafío...

column2: &a[Nahab]&f You have managed to slay the &cGhost&f. That is excellent news!
column3: &a[Nahab]&f Has logrado matar al &cFantasma&f. ¡Esa es una excelente noticia!

column2: &7&oThey could have warned me about the &c&oGhosts&7&o unique powers...
column3: &7&oPodrían haberme advertido sobre los poderes únicos de los &c&oFantasma&7&o...

column2: I have something of an odd request.
There might be other higher priorities right now but I was thinking that if we do not deal with this now, there might not be another chance for a while.
column3: There might be other higher priorities right now but I was thinking that if we do not deal with this now, there might not be another chance for a while.

column2: We have a &cGhost&f that is haunting our &dWarehouse&f.
column3: Tenemos un &cFantasma&f que está acechando nuestro &dAlmacén&f.

column2: We have tried dealing with this problem in the past but it would always escape before we could deal the finishing blow.
column3: We have tried dealing with this problem in the past but it would always escape before we could deal the finishing blow.

column2: But some of the guards have reported seeing the &cGhost&f on top of the &dWarehouse&f. This is our chance to get rid of it for good.
column3: But some of the guards have reported seeing the &cGhost&f on top of the &dWarehouse&f. This is our chance to get rid of it for good.

column2: &a[Khalid]&f There are four caches in total spread across the nearby islands. Here, I will write down their exact locations.
column3: &a[Khalid]&f Hay cuatro almacenes en total repartidos por las islas cercanas. Aquí, anotaré sus ubicaciones exactas.

column2: &7&oI should search the nearby islands for &e&oEmergency Caches&7&o.
column3: &7&oDebería buscar en las islas cercanas los &e&oAlmacenes de Emergencia&7&o.

column2: &a[Khalid]&f I see you managed to locate all of the caches! Well done!
column3: &a[Khalid]&f ¡Veo que lograste localizar todos los almacenes! ¡Bien hecho!

column2: &7&oWhy would anyone store such important resources so far away from the city...
column3: &7&o¿Por qué alguien almacenaría recursos tan importantes tan lejos de la ciudad...?

column2: I think it might be time to collect our &eEmergency &eCaches&f.
column3: Creo que podría ser hora de recoger nuestros &eAlmacenes &ede Emergencia&f.

column2: The caches are filled with various resources that will help us continue fighting on.
column3: The caches are filled with various resources that will help us continue fighting on.

column2: I would usually send some troops to fetch it but if you're available I would like to delegate this task to you.
column3: I would usually send some troops to fetch it but if you're available I would like to delegate this task to you.

column2: &6[Keknum]&f The Shining Army is coming? I haven't seen them march since I was a child. We will do our best to prepare!
column3: &6[Keknum]&f ¿El Ejército Brillante se acerca? No los he visto marchar desde que era un niño. ¡Haremos todo lo posible para prepararnos!

column2: &a[Uah-abra]&f Tappesheh will be sending aid you say. Thank you for coming to let us know. This is great news!
column3: &a[Uah-abra]&f Dices que Tappesheh enviará ayuda. Gracias por venir a informarnos. ¡Esta es una gran noticia!

column2: &e[Nailah]&f You know I used to be a part of then Shining Army in my younger days. Hah! This will be one heck of a sight! The forces of Dessa will be ready to join them when they come!
column3: &e[Nailah]&f Sabes, yo solía ser parte del Ejército Brillante en mis días más jóvenes. ¡Ja! ¡Esto será un espectáculo increíble! ¡Las fuerzas de Dessa estarán listas para unirse a ellos cuando lleguen!

column2: &a[Pili]&f They will know the time has come when they see our brilliant sun banner and hear the marching footsteps of our shining army.
column3: &a[Pili]&f Sabrán que ha llegado el momento cuando vean nuestro brillante estandarte del sol y escuchen los pasos marciales de nuestro ejército brillante.

column2: &7&oI need to revisit the settlements of the &d&oOasis&7&o and notify them that the &9&oShining Army of Tappesheh&7&o has not forgotten them.
column3: &7&oNecesito volver a visitar los asentamientos del &d&oOasis&7&o y notificarles que el &9&oEjército Brillante de Tappesheh&7&o no los ha olvidado.

column2: &a[Pili]&f It is good to see you. The mission was a success yes? Very good. I will notify the general. We will see how these fiends will fare when the entire might of the &9Tappesheh Shining Army&f comes crashing down upon them!
column3: &a[Pili]&f Me alegra verte. La misión fue un éxito, ¿verdad? Muy bien. Notificaré al general. ¡Veremos cómo les va a estos demonios cuando toda la fuerza del &9Ejército Brillante de Tappesheh&f caiga sobre ellos!

column2: &7&oI almost feel sorry for the monsters...almost.
column3: &7&oCasi siento pena por los monstruos... casi.

column2: As we near our goal of securing Tappesheh we will start gathering our forces for a push to free the other settlements from this dark force.
column3: As we near our goal of securing Tappesheh we will start gathering our forces for a push to free the other settlements from this dark force.

column2: We are looking for someone to go ahead and notify the settlements to prepare their forces so that they can join in glory when we arrive.
column3: We are looking for someone to go ahead and notify the settlements to prepare their forces so that they can join in glory when we arrive.

column2: We will be handing out a good sum of coin to anyone who volunteers for this mission.
column3: We will be handing out a good sum of coin to anyone who volunteers for this mission.

column2: &a[Nahab]&f It was &9one of the&f &cSalted Grimace's&f that snatched it. The trident you're looking for has engravings on the handle. You can find the &cSalted&f west of the &dHarbor&f, deep in the sea.
column3: &a[Nahab]&f Fue &9uno de los&f &cGestos Salados&f el que lo arrebató. El tridente que buscas tiene grabados en el mango. Puedes encontrar a los &cSalados&f al oeste del &dPuerto&f, en lo profundo del mar.

column2: &7&oI should head west of the &d&oHarbor&7&o and see which one of the &c&oSalted&7o has the &e&oFamily Trident&7&o.
column3: &7&oDebería dirigirme al oeste del &d&oPuerto&7&o y ver cuál de los &c&oSalados&7o tiene el &e&oTridente Familiar&7&o.

column2: &a[Nahab]&f Oh, goodness! I thought I would never see it again!
column3: &a[Nahab]&f ¡Oh, cielos! ¡Pensé que nunca lo volvería a ver!

column2: &7&oWhy not just use fishing nets...or a fishing rod...
column3: &7&o¿Por qué no usar simplemente redes de pesca... o una caña de pescar...?

column2: Kind traveler can I bother you with a personal request?
column3: Amable viajero, ¿puedo molestarte con una petición personal?

column2: I am a hard working fisherman, and when the monsters started appearing one of them stole my &eTrident&f.
column3: I am a hard working fisherman, and when the monsters started appearing one of them stole my &eTrident&f.

column2: And the worse part is, I have no idea which one of them is the one that grabbed my precious &eTrident&f.
column3: And the worse part is, I have no idea which one of them is the one that grabbed my precious &eTrident&f.

column2: It was passed down in our family for generations so it means a lot to me, it is more than just a tool.
column3: It was passed down in our family for generations so it means a lot to me, it is more than just a tool.

column2: &a[Pili]&f It is pretty straight forward, go to the docks, collect the weapons from the containers and then bring them back.
column3: &a[Pili]&f Es bastante sencillo, ve a los muelles, recoge las armas de los contenedores y luego tráelas de vuelta.

column2: &7&oI need to search the &d&oHarbor&7&o docks for weapons containers.
column3: &7&oNecesito buscar en los muelles del &d&oPuerto&7&o contenedores de armas.

column2: &a[Pili]&f That is an excellent haul! These new weapons will be of good use to us.
column3: &a[Pili]&f ¡Esa es una excelente pesca! Estas nuevas armas nos serán de gran utilidad.

column2: I have an interesting mission for you if you want it.
column3: Tengo una misión interesante para ti si la quieres.

column2: Our forces could always use more weapons. And we are quite lucky that the last boat of shipments were weapons.
column3: Our forces could always use more weapons. And we are quite lucky that the last boat of shipments were weapons.

column2: Of course it just so happens that the shipments were delivered to us right before this whole thing so the weapons are still stuck in containers on the &dHarbor&f docks...
column3: Of course it just so happens that the shipments were delivered to us right before this whole thing so the weapons are still stuck in containers on the &dHarbor&f docks...

column2: &a[Nahab]&f The &dWater Tower&f is the tallest structure in all of &dTappesheh&f so it should not be hard for you to locate it.
column3: &a[Nahab]&f La &dTorre de Agua&f es la estructura más alta de todo &dTappesheh&f, por lo que no debería ser difícil para ti localizarla.

column2: &7&oI need to find the &d&oWater Tower&7&o and slay any undead that might poison the water supply.
column3: &7&oNecesito encontrar la &d&oTorre de Agua&7&o y matar a cualquier no muerto que pueda envenenar el suministro de agua.

column2: &a[Nahab]&f So how did it go? Sad to hear about that no workers made it.
column3: &a[Nahab]&f ¿Y cómo fue? Es triste escuchar que ningún trabajador lo logró.

column2: &7&oHaving a fresh water supply is very important in such a large city.
column3: &7&oTener un suministro de agua dulce es muy importante en una ciudad tan grande.

column2: I was worried about our water getting contaminated by the undead.
column3: Me preocupaba que nuestra agua se contaminara por los no muertos.

column2: So I raised the issue with the officer and they agreed that it might become an issue so they sent a unit to go clear any undead that are in or near our water supplies.
column3: So I raised the issue with the officer and they agreed that it might become an issue so they sent a unit to go clear any undead that are in or near our water supplies.

column2: Except that we never considered what might have happened to the water tower workers.
column3: Except that we never considered what might have happened to the water tower workers.

column2: If they turned into monsters as well, then that might be a cause for concern too.
column3: If they turned into monsters as well, then that might be a cause for concern too.

column2: Would you go climb the water tower and make sure that any monsters you encounter are taken care of?
column3: Would you go climb the water tower and make sure that any monsters you encounter are taken care of?

column2: &a[Pili]&f The crops are located North of here. Shouldn't be too hard to find, just look for the golden fields of wheat!
column3: &a[Pili]&f Los cultivos se encuentran al Norte de aquí. No debería ser muy difícil encontrarlos, ¡solo busca los campos dorados de trigo!

column2: &7&oI should locate the crops and harvest some wheat and slay any former &c&oGrovetenders&7&o.
column3: &7&oDebería localizar los cultivos, cosechar algo de trigo y matar a cualquier antiguo &c&oGrovetender&7&o.

column2: &a[Pili]&f This will do. Thank you for taking the time to do this for us.
column3: &a[Pili]&f Esto servirá. Gracias por tomarte el tiempo para hacer esto por nosotros.

column2: &7&oI should probably stop and get some food for myself soon.
column3: &7&oProbablemente debería parar y conseguir algo de comida para mí pronto.

column2: Another hour another mission. We are in need of some wheat so we can feed the troops.
column3: Another hour another mission. We are in need of some wheat so we can feed the troops.

column2: Oh, and not just wheat. We had people tending to the crops and farming for wheat but the curse has turned them into mindless monsters now.
column3: Oh, and not just wheat. We had people tending to the crops and farming for wheat but the curse has turned them into mindless monsters now.

column2: If it's not too much of a bother, would you mind putting the poor souls to rest?
column3: Si no es demasiada molestia, ¿te importaría dar descanso a esas pobres almas?

column2: &a[Uah-abra]&f Reaching the end of the temple will not be easy. Make sure you are well prepared before you venture forth.
column3: &a[Uah-abra]&f Llegar al final del templo no será fácil. Asegúrate de estar bien preparado antes de aventurarte.

column2: &7&oI should go into the temple and find the source of the darkness and eliminate it.
column3: &7&oDebería entrar en el templo, encontrar la fuente de la oscuridad y eliminarla.

column2: &a[Uah-abra]&f Well done! Seems like it will take a while before the darkness disperses from the temple. I know this mustn't have been an easy task, thank you.
column3: &a[Uah-abra]&f ¡Bien hecho! Parece que tomará un tiempo antes de que la oscuridad se disperse del templo. Sé que esta no debe haber sido una tarea fácil, gracias.

column2: &7&oI have never seen anything like that before, it's as if the light itself was being consumed by the darkness...
column3: &7&oNunca antes había visto algo así, es como si la propia luz estuviera siendo consumida por la oscuridad...

column2: There is another issue we would like help with.
column3: Hay otro problema con el que nos gustaría ayuda.

column2: Ever since the curse, as you call it, happened.
column3: Desde que ocurrió la maldición, como tú la llamas.

column2: Our temple has fallen under complete darkness and vile things now roam its halls.
column3: Our temple has fallen under complete darkness and vile things now roam its halls.

column2: There must be something or someone deep in the temple that is causing this to happen.
column3: There must be something or someone deep in the temple that is causing this to happen.

column2: You are the only one we can rely on to disperse this darkness.
column3: Eres el único en quien podemos confiar para dispersar esta oscuridad.

column2: &a[Ua]&f Watch yourself when approaching the nest, the wigglers get very aggressive so I suggest caution.
column3: &a[Ua]&f Ten cuidado al acercarte al nido, los wigglers se vuelven muy agresivos, así que sugiero precaución.

column2: &7&oI should go retrieve the &e&oDeepest Blue&7&o from the wiggler nest.
column3: &7&oDebería ir a recuperar el &e&oAzul Profundo&7&o del nido de wiggler.

column2: &a[Ua]&f Yes! That is it! It will take me some time to prepare it. Thank you, this should help us save those few who are still holding on.
column3: &a[Ua]&f ¡Sí! ¡Eso es! Me tomará algo de tiempo prepararlo. Gracias, esto debería ayudarnos a salvar a los pocos que aún resisten.

column2: &7&oThe world still holds many wonders for us to find it would seem.
column3: &7&oEl mundo aún guarda muchas maravillas para que las encontremos, al parecer.

column2: I could really use your help! As you can see there are a lot of wounded here, we do have bandages and medicine to treat them.
column3: I could really use your help! As you can see there are a lot of wounded here, we do have bandages and medicine to treat them.

column2: But I know of something that is far better, something that will heal their wounds almost instantly.
column3: But I know of something that is far better, something that will heal their wounds almost instantly.

column2: While out diving in the river long before any of this, I came upon a very curious, crystal?
column3: While out diving in the river long before any of this, I came upon a very curious, crystal?

column2: I am not even sure what it was, I have never seen anything like it before.
column3: Ni siquiera estoy seguro de qué era, nunca antes había visto algo así.

column2: I think it is made by the &cHardshell &cWigglers&f, because
column3: Creo que está hecho por los &cHardshell &cWigglers&f, porque

column2: I could only find it in their nests. Such a strange object, it looks and feels like a crystal, yet it is soft and filled with liquid.
column3: I could only find it in their nests. Such a strange object, it looks and feels like a crystal, yet it is soft and filled with liquid.

column2: There is a nest not too far away from here in the nearby river.
column3: Hay un nido no muy lejos de aquí en el río cercano.

column2: Just one will do. Do not worry you will know for sure when you have found one, it's brilliant blue color is striking, hard to miss.
column3: Just one will do. Do not worry you will know for sure when you have found one, it's brilliant blue color is striking, hard to miss.

column2: &a[Ua]&f Oh, I almost forgot to mention the details. The items you're looking for are, a &eLiquid Extractor&f, a &eLiquid Purifier&f, and a &eLiquid Stabilizer&f.
column3: &a[Ua]&f Oh, casi olvido mencionar los detalles. Los objetos que buscas son: un &eExtractor de Líquidos&f, un &ePurificador de Líquidos&f y un &eEstabilizador de Líquidos&f.

column2: &7&oHmm, the regular dead are probably too gone to have snatched these. So I should probably see if the crossbow wielders, the witches and the wizards have the items.
column3: &7&oHmm, los muertos comunes probablemente están demasiado idos como para haberlos arrebatado. Así que probablemente debería ver si los portadores de ballesta, las brujas y los magos tienen los objetos.

column2: &a[Ua]&f You managed to find them! Incredible. To be honest I thought they were gone for good. You have no idea how much I needed these!
column3: &a[Ua]&f ¡Lograste encontrarlos! Increíble. Para ser honesto, pensé que se habían ido para siempre. ¡No tienes idea de cuánto necesitaba esto!

column2: I could use help with a task if you wouldn't mind? Some time ago I managed to sneak past all the monsters to go look for my items that were left behind.
column3: I could use help with a task if you wouldn't mind? Some time ago I managed to sneak past all the monsters to go look for my items that were left behind.

column2: But to my great surprise they were gone. A few hours later I spotted one of those monsters running around with one of my tools!
column3: But to my great surprise they were gone. A few hours later I spotted one of those monsters running around with one of my tools!

column2: I managed to sneak past them but I fear going toe to toe with these fiends is not something I would be capable of.
column3: I managed to sneak past them but I fear going toe to toe with these fiends is not something I would be capable of.

column2: Well I assume you know what that task would be by now. Go slay those foul things and bring me back my items.
column3: Well I assume you know what that task would be by now. Go slay those foul things and bring me back my items.

column2: It is gonna be hard to tell which ones are carrying the items. Come back to me when you managed to collect all of the items.
column3: It is gonna be hard to tell which ones are carrying the items. Come back to me when you managed to collect all of the items.

column2: &a[Merit]&f Look for the &eCoconuts&f on the western side of the town. Follow the river. If you see any wigglers right below the palm tree tops, that's a good sign there are &eCoconuts&f there.
column3: &a[Merit]&f Busca los &eCocos&f en el lado oeste del pueblo. Sigue el río. Si ves algún wiggler justo debajo de las copas de las palmeras, es una buena señal de que hay &eCocos&f allí.

column2: Make sure to only collect the ripe ones, you can see which ones are ripe by looking for oozing coconut juice.
column3: Make sure to only collect the ripe ones, you can see which ones are ripe by looking for oozing coconut juice.

column2: &7&oI should make sure to equip a bow or some other ranged weapon that will let me knock down the ripe &e&oCoconuts&7&o.
column3: &7&oDebería asegurarme de equipar un arco o alguna otra arma a distancia que me permita derribar los &e&oCocos&7&o maduros.

column2: &a[Merit]&f What a haul! This should keep us fed for a while!
column3: &a[Merit]&f ¡Qué botín! ¡Esto debería mantenernos alimentados por un tiempo!

column2: &7&oWell, that was fun. Those wigglers are nasty though.
column3: &7&oBueno, eso fue divertido. Aunque esos wigglers son desagradables.

column2: Hmm, I am worried about our food supplies.
column3: Hmm, estoy preocupado por nuestros suministros de comida.

column2: We have plenty of water but we only have a few meals left before our food supplies reach zero.
column3: We have plenty of water but we only have a few meals left before our food supplies reach zero.

column2: One of us left to procure food some time ago, but they never came back.
column3: Uno de nosotros se fue a conseguir comida hace algún tiempo, pero nunca regresó.

column2: Thankfully our town is surrounded by palm trees. So our food supply is right there, we just need someone who can go out there and gather enough &eCoconuts&f to last us a while. Want to help us out with this dangerous mission?
column3: Thankfully our town is surrounded by palm trees. So our food supply is right there, we just need someone who can go out there and gather enough &eCoconuts&f to last us a while. Want to help us out with this dangerous mission?

column3: &7&oNecesito eliminar a todos los mobs en el este de &d&oZanerun&7&o.

column2: &a[Merit]&f Is it done? They're all dead? Good, wretched fiends...
column3: &a[Merit]&f ¿Está hecho? ¿Están todos muertos? Bien, miserables demonios...

column2: &7&oThe people in this town have suffered enough.
column3: &7&oLa gente de este pueblo ha sufrido suficiente.

column2: I have a request. Is it wrong and selfish of me to send you on a quest where the only reason is revenge?
column3: I have a request. Is it wrong and selfish of me to send you on a quest where the only reason is revenge?

column2: I come from east &dZanerun&f. I had family there, once.
column3: Vengo del este de &dZanerun&f. Tuve familia allí, una vez.

column2: I want all the monsters there dead, I just cannot stand the thought of those things still roaming the streets. I understand if this is not something that you want to do.
column3: I want all the monsters there dead, I just cannot stand the thought of those things still roaming the streets. I understand if this is not something that you want to do.

column2: &a[Ua]&f Me and my friends built that little hut with our own hands. I wonder if I will ever dare go back there now that it is nothing but a grim reminder of the people I have lost...
column3: &a[Ua]&f Mis amigos y yo construimos esa pequeña cabaña con nuestras propias manos. Me pregunto si alguna vez me atreveré a volver allí ahora que no es más que un sombrío recordatorio de las personas que he perdido...

column2: &7&oThe hut is down by the river, shouldn't be hard to find.
column3: &7&oLa cabaña está río abajo, no debería ser difícil de encontrar.

column2:
Prestige Tier and Guild Rank:
Guild Rank determines how good your loot can be, sets your bonus from the Prestige Tier, among other things. The Prestige Tier unlocks extremely powerful rewards, like increased max health, chance to dodge/crit, increased currency rewards and more! You can unlock Guild Ranks and Prestige Tiers at /ag!
⚜ = prestige rank, ✧ = guild rank!
column3:
Prestigio y Rango de Gremio:
El Rango de Gremio determina que tan bueno puede ser el botín, establece tu bonificación de prestigio, entre varias cosas. ¡El Prestigio desbloquea recompensas poderosas, como incrementar tu vida máxima, probabilidad de esquivar/crítico, conseguir más monedas y mucho mas! ¡Puedes desbloquear todo esto en /ag!
⚜ = Prestigio, ✧ = Rango de Hermandad!

column2:
You're not from around these parts,
 are you?
column3:

 are you?

column2: &a[Venator Pabulatus]&f If you can get rid of those pesky &cWolves&f, I will reward you handsomely!
column3: &a[Venator Pabulatus]&f Si puedes deshacerte de esos molestos &cLobos&f, te recompensaré genialmente!

column2: I am getting too old to be dealing with the wild things of these lands...
column3: Me estoy volviendo demasiado viejo para tratar con las cosas salvajes de estas tierras...

column2: &7&oI should go kill the &cWolves&7&o in the den to the Southeast of the village.
column3: &7&oDebería ir a matar a los &cLobos&7&o en su guarida al Sureste de la aldea.

column2: &a[Venator Pabulatus]&f I knew I could count on you!
Thank you for all of your help!
column3: ¡Gracias a todos por toda su ayuda!

column2: Here is your reward as promised.
column3: Aquí está tu recompensa como he prometido.

column2: I heard you were looking to help out around here.
column3: He oído que estabas buscando ayudar por aquí.

column2: There is a &dDen of Wolves&f nearby that is really impeding my foraging for the village!
column3: There is a &dDen of Wolves&f nearby that is really impeding my foraging for the village!

column2: You look strong and mighty. Talk to some \nof the villagers if you want to help us out.
column3: Te ves fuerte y poderoso. Habla con algunos \nde los aldeanos si quieres ayudarnos.

column2: A long time ago there was a beautiful shrine to\nthe southeast, shame what happened to it.
column3: Hace mucho tiempo había un hermoso santuario yendo\nal sudeste, ahora da vergüenza de lo que le sucedió.

column2: The ruins in the southwest are such a horrible place!\n Who would ever go there...
column3: ¡Las ruinas en el sudoeste son un lugar tan horrible!\n ¿Quién iría allí...

column2: Met a powerful mage once,\nthey were able to summon a beautiful ice wall.\nToo bad it would break if they fainted.
column3: Alguna vez se conoció a un mago un poderoso,\nfue capaz de invocar un hermoso muro de hielo.\nLo malo es que si se desmayaba, se rompía.

column2: I heard that a nasty type of\nwolf has settled in the wolf den!
column3: ¡He oído que un tipo desagradable de lobo\nse ha instalado en la cueva de lobo!

column2: It is good to see you!

You're not from around these parts,
 are you?
column3:
You're not from around these parts,
 are you?

column2: Just here to sell\nto the shop-keep.
column3: Solo estoy aquí para venderle\nal tendero.

column2:
Ask not what this village can do for you,
ask what you can do for this village!
column3:
No preguntes qué puede hacer esta aldea por ti,
¡pregunta qué puedes hacer tú por esta aldea!

column2:
You're not from around these parts,
 are you?
column3:
You're not from around these parts,
 are you?

column2: Got nothing to sell, I'm afraid.
column3: No tengo nada que vender, estoy preocupado.

column2: Don't forget to give\nme some scrap too!
I got the tools\nto fix anything!

column2: Hope you are enjoying the map!
&a[Amavit]&f Thank you so much for accepting our request. I hope with all my heart you succeed.
column3: &a[Amavit]&f Muchas gracias por aceptar nuestra solicitud. Espero con todo el corazón que tengas éxito.

column2: &7&oI should go to the &dBasement of the Lighthouse&7&o and put the &cLighthouse Keeper&7&o out of his misery.
column3: &7&oDebería ir al &dSótano del Faro &7&oy poner al &cGuardián del Faro&7&o fuera de su miseria.

column2: &a[Amavit]&f I heard it - so it is done? Did he suff- no, forget it, I don't want to know.
column3: &a[Amavit]&f Lo he oído - así que está hecho? ¿Ha sufri- no, olvídalo, no quiero saberlo.

column2: &fIt seems like the lighthouse started emitting an odd light when you... dealt with the issue. We need to make sure it is not an issue.
column3: &fParece que el faro ha empezado a emitir una luz extraña cuando tú... Te ocupaste del problema. Hemos de asegurarnos de que no se trata de un problema.

column2: &7&oSeems like &aAmavit&7&o has another task for me. I should talk to her.
column3: &7&oParece que &aAmavit&7&o tiene otra tarea para mí. Debería hablar con ella.

column2: Something is deeply wrong with my husband.
column3: Algo está muy mal con mi marido.

column2: He used to be a loving and caring husband and father, but in recent times he has been focusing on documents he found in the basement.
column3: Solía ser un marido amable y padre cariñoso, pero en los últimos tiempos se ha centrado en unos documentos que encontró en el sótano.

column2: He said it was for important research, something that could change the world.
column3: Dijo que era para una investigación importante, algo que podría cambiar el mundo.

column2: I should've told him to stop when I saw how obsessed he was becoming.
column3: Debería haberle dicho que parara cuando vi lo obsesionado que se estaba volviendo.

column2: He did... something... to the lighthouse - and I fear the lighthouse has done something to him, too.
column3: He did... something... to the lighthouse - and I fear the lighthouse has done something to him, too.

column2: It morphed him into some kind of monster. He no longer recognizes us, and has even attacked us when we tried to approach him.
column3: Lo transformó en una especie de monstruo, que ya no nos reconoce e incluso nos ha atacado cuando intentamos acercarnos.

column2: At night, we can't sleep due to the wailing sounds coming from the &dLighthouse's Basement&f.
column3: At night, we can't sleep due to the wailing sounds coming from the &dLighthouse's Basement&f.

column2: He is suffering, and we are powerless to help him.
column3: Está sufriendo, y nosotros somos impotentes para ayudarlo.

column2: I know it's asking a lot, but do you think you could help us?
column3: Sé que es pedir mucho, pero ¿crees que podrías ayudarnos?

column2: &a[Jeeves]&f &2Amavit&f sent you? What's this about a lighthouse? My, what a discovery!\n&fThis will revolutionize my job as a traveling merchant! Here, have these &eScrolls&f - just call me and I'll be there in a jiffy!\n&7&oSeems like &aJeeves&7&o has something for me. I should talk to him.
column3: &a[Jeeves]&f ¿Te envió &2Amavit&f? ¿Qué es esto de un faro? ¡Vaya, qué descubrimiento!\n&f¡Esto revolucionará mi trabajo como mercader ambulante! Aquí, toma estos &ePergaminos&f - solo llámame y estaré allí en un santiamén!\n&7&oParece que &aJeeves&7&o tiene algo para mí. Debería hablar con él.

column2: &a[Amavit]&f Thank you once again, and good luck. Hopefully it's nothing.
column3: &a[Amavit]&f Gracias de nuevo, y buena suerte. Esperemos que no sea nada.

column2: &7&oI should go to the &dTop of the Lighthouse&f, investigate the issue and then report back to &aAmavit's&f father &aJeeves&f in the village.
column3: Debería ir a la &dCima del Faro&f, investigar el problema y luego informar al padre de &aAmavit&f &aJeeves&f en el Pueblo.

column2: &7&oThese scrolls seem mighty useful! I should use the &dLighthouse&7&o to get back to the &dFarmstead&7&o and keep moving.
column3: &7&o¡Estos desplazamientos parecen muy útiles! Debería usar el &dFaro&7&o para volver a &dAlqueria&7&o y seguir moviéndose.

column2: A strange light started being emitted from the &dTop of the Lighthouse&f when you...dealt with the issue.
column3: A strange light started being emitted from the &dTop of the Lighthouse&f when you...dealt with the issue.

column2: My father &aJeeves&f went to the top to check but he has not returned yet.
column3: Mi padre &aJeeves&f fue a la cima para revisar, pero aún no ha regresado.

column2: My heart can not bear to suffer any more, and we already owe you much - but if you could investigate the issue and find my father, I would be eternally grateful.
column3: Mi corazón no puede soportar para sufrir más, y ya se lo debemos mucho, pero si pudiera investigar el asunto y encontrar a mi padre, estaría eternamente agradecido.

column2: Without a lighthouse, how will boats navigate?
column3: Sin un faro, ¿cómo navegarán los barcos?

column2: You seem like you came a long way from here.
column3: Parece que ha venido de muy lejos de aquí.

column2: What dangerous times we live in.

&cSolo la sangre puede complacer esta hoja.

column2: I've got a task for you!

Good thing you're here,
 we need some help!
column3:
Good thing you're here,
 we need some help!

column2: &aLooks like you could reel big fish with these.
column3: &aParece que podrias atrapar peces grandes con estos.

column2: Hope you are enjoying the map!
It's a pine-cone covered in snow.
column3: Es un pino cubierto de nieve.

column2: &a[Belli] Deal with those &cAssassins&f! Remember to use the &eGrappling Arrows&f!.
column3: &a[Belli] ¡Hazte cargo esos &cAsesinos&f! ¡Recuerda usar las &eFlechas de Agarre&f!.

column2: &a[Belli]&f You dealt with those &cAssassins&f? Good! That's one headache dealt with!
column3: &a[Belli]&f ¿Te has ocupado de esos &cAsesinos&f? ¡Bueno! ¡Ese es un dolor de cabeza tratado!

column2: The roofs of &dGladius&f are covered in &cAssassins&f!
Venturing out to the streets is a death sentence. We need to deal with these snipers!
column3: Salir a las calles es una sentencia de muerte. ¡Tenemos que ocuparnos de estos francotiradores!

column2: There are some spots for &eGrappling Arrows&f on the roofs, make good use of them and deal with those snipers!
column3: Hay algunos lugares para las &eFlechas de Agarre&f en los tejados, haz buen uso de ellos y hazte cargo de esos francotiradores!

column2: &a[Belli] &fJust go out there and thin their numbers!
column3: &a[Belli] &f¡Simplemente sal ahí y reduce sus números!

column2: &7&oI go out and clear the streets of &dGladius&7&o.
column3: &7&oSalgo ahí y despejo las calles de &dGladius&7&o.

column2: &a[Belli]&f Look at that, the Gods have provided with a true warrior in our time of need! I have a job for a person like you.
column3: &a[Belli]&f Mira eso, ¡los Dioses han proporcionado un verdadero guerrero en nuestro tiempo de necesidad! Tengo un trabajo para una persona como tú.

column2: &7&oSeems like &aBelli&7&o has a plan for me. I should talk to her..
column3: &7&oParece que &aBelli&7&o tiene un plan para mí. Debería ir a hablar con ella..

column2: I don't need to tell you that the town is being invaded, do I?
column3: No necesito decirte que la ciudad está siendo invadida, ¿verdad?

column2: We are offering a reward to those willing to put a dent in the amount of &cInvaders&f.
column3: Estamos ofreciendo una recompensa a quienes están dispuestos a poner una abolladura en la cantidad de &cInvasores&f.

column2: &fIt is time to take Gladius back!
column3: &8[EM] &3¡Jugador por la borda! &b¡Regresa cuando hayas ganado tus piernas de mar, terrícola!
&8[EM] &7Vuelve a visitarnos. &f¡Hay muchos dulces y golosinas para la próxima vez!
&8[EM] &3¡Ahora abordando el Barco Pirata! &b¡Saquea y pilla a tu gusto!

column2: It's a war zone out there!
column3: ¡Es una zona de guerra por ahí!

column2: Ring the bell to\nend the battle.
column3: Toca la campana para\nterminar la batalla.

column2: ... hence, for the help lended during these most trying
column3: ... por lo tanto, por la ayuda prestada durante estos tiempos tan difíciles

column2: times, Pontis Mille promises to return in kind at Gladius'
column3: veces, Pontis Mille promete devolver de la misma manera en Gladius'

column2: &a[Belli] &fGo &dUpstairs&f and follow the candles! Careful not to fall, the path is treacherous!
column3: &a[Belli] &f¡Ve al &dpiso superior&f y sigue las velas! ¡Cuidado de no caer, el camino es traicionero!

column2: &7&oI should follow the &dCandle Path&7&o and defeat the &cMonk&7&o.
column3: &7&oDebería seguir el &dCamino de Velas&7&o y derrotar al &cMonje&7&o.

column2: &a[Belli]&f You completed the prayer? Thank you, the soldiers will feel relieved to hear it.
column3: &a[Belli]&f ¿Has completado la oración? Gracias, los soldados se sentirán aliviados al escucharlo.

column2: I am not going to sugarcoat it, things look downright grim!
column3: No voy a azucararlo, ¡las cosas parecen francamente sombrías!

column2: The walls have fallen, the streets are teeming with the &cUndead&f and I just ran out of drinks.
column3: The walls have fallen, the streets are teeming with the &cUndead&f and I just ran out of drinks.

column2: At times like these, people turn their hope to some kind of divine intervention!
column3: At times like these, people turn their hope to some kind of divine intervention!

column2: There is a &dPath&f, lit by candles, that leads to a &dSanctuary in the Mountains&f.
column3: Hay un &dCamino&f, iluminado por velas, que lleva a un &dSantuario en las Montañas&f.

column2: Warriors go up this path and defeat the &cMonk&f which guards the sanctuary in order to be blessed by the war god in combat.
column3: Warriors go up this path and defeat the &cMonk&f which guards the sanctuary in order to be blessed by the war god in combat.

column2: It may just be a superstition, but would it hurt to give people hope?
column3: Puede que solo sea una superstición, pero ¿haría daño dar esperanza a la gente?

column2: The fact you made your way here shows you are a cut above the rest - go up the mountain and defeat the &cMonk&f.
column3: The fact you made your way here shows you are a cut above the rest - go up the mountain and defeat the &cMonk&f.

column2: All warriors will feel better knowing they are being watched over.
column3: Todos los guerreros se sentirán mejor sabiendo que están siendo protegidos.

column2: It's a war zone out there!
column3: ¡Es una zona de guerra por ahí!

column2: I never thought we\nwould survive this!
Ring the bell to let\nthe forces know we won!
column3: Toca la campana para que\nlas fuerzas sepan que ganamos.

column2: It is so good to see you!
&a[Belli] &fKill the &cAdmiral&f and some of the troops on the boats. Be careful about their water superiority! I recommend using &eGrappling Arrows&f to move around the ships.
column3: &a[Belli] &fMata al &cAlmirante&f y algunas de las tropas en los barcos. ¡Ten cuidado con su superioridad de agua! Te recomiendo usar &eFlechas de Agarre&f para moverte por los barcos.

column2: &7&oI should go slay the &cAdmiral&7&o and some of its troops on the boats just &dOutside of Gladius&7&o.
column3: &7&oDebería ir a matar al &cAlmirante&7&o y algunas de sus tropas en los barcos justo &dfuera de Gladius&7&o.

column2: &a[Belli]&f The admiral is no more? Why, I feel better already!
column3: &a[Belli]&f ¿El almirante ya no es más? ¡Por qué, ya me siento mejor!

column2: Have you seen them? The dozens of ships just outside of &dGladius&f? They are to blame for all of this.
column3: Have you seen them? The dozens of ships just outside of &dGladius&f? They are to blame for all of this.

column2: We never expected an invasion from the &dBlood Temple&f, much less one done by siege weapons mounted on boats!
column3: We never expected an invasion from the &dBlood Temple&f, much less one done by siege weapons mounted on boats!

column2: We must do something about it. Killing the &cAdmiral&f and some of the forces won't give us back what we lost, but it will sure make us feel better.
column3: We must do something about it. Killing the &cAdmiral&f and some of the forces won't give us back what we lost, but it will sure make us feel better.

column2: It's a war zone out there!
column3: ¡Es una zona de guerra por ahí!

column2: Don't forget to\nding, ding that bell!
&a[Belli] &fYou will find the ship in the waters to the south-west. Give them hell!
column3: &a[Belli] &fEncontrarás el barco en las aguas del sur-oeste. ¡Dales el infierno!

column2: &7&oI should go collect the &eDocuments&7&o and slay any &cMariners&7&o near the ship.
column3: &7&oDebería ir a recoger los &eDocumentos&7&o y matar los &cMarineros&7&o cerca del barco.

column2: &a[Belli]&f Back already? Excellent work! We really needed these &eDocuments&f.
Now that you took care of the &cMariner Forces&f I got another task for you.
column3: Ahora que te encargaste de las &cFuerzas Marineras&f, tengo otra tarea para ti.

column2: The &dSunken Ship&f should be reachable now.
column3: El &dBarco Hundido&f debería ser accesible ahora.

column2: You see some time ago one of our ships got sunk, unfortunately it was carrying &eImportant DDocuments&f.
column3: You see some time ago one of our ships got sunk, unfortunately it was carrying &eImportant DDocuments&f.

column2: I need you to reach the &dSunken Ship&f and kill any threats around and retrieve the &eDocuments&f.
column3: I need you to reach the &dSunken Ship&f and kill any threats around and retrieve the &eDocuments&f.

column2: Come back to me after you have completed the task.
column3: Vuelve a mí después de haber completado la tarea.

column2: &aFit to keep a soldier fed during a war.
column3: &aAdecuado para mantener a un soldado bien alimentado durante la guerra.

column2: &a[Cibus]&f The &dWarehouse&f is hard to miss! It's the extra large warehouse-looking building near the part where the wall fell! Grab some &eSupplies&f and get them back here!
column3: &a[Cibus]&f ¡El &dAlmacén&f es difícil de pasar por delante! ¡Es el edificio extra grande con aspecto de almacén cerca de la parte donde cayó el muro! ¡Recoge algunos &eSuministros&f y ponlos de vuelta aquí!

column2: &7&oI should go to the &dWarehouse&7&o and bring back &eSupplies&7&o.
column3: &7&oDebería ir al &dAlmacén&7&o y traer de vuelta &eSuministros&7&o.

column2: &a[Cibus]&f You brought the &eSupplies&f back? Fantastic! Meanwhile I came up with the perfect idea for the drinks - and it should be something that will lift the spirits of the soldiers!
column3: &a[Cibus]&f ¿Trajiste de vuelta los &eSuministros? ¡Fantástico! Mientras, llegué con la idea perfecta para las bebidas - ¡y debería ser algo que levante los espíritus de los soldados!

column2: &7&oSeems like the &aCibus&7&o has a plan, I should talk to them.
column3: &7&oParece que el &aCibus&7&o tiene un plan, debería hablar con él.

column2: &dGladius&f is a fortress equipped to last a long siege
column3: ¡&dGladius&f es una fortaleza equipada para durar un asedio largo

column2: without any issues, but that's assuming we have access to the &dWarehouse&f!
column3: sin problemas, ¡pero eso asumiendo que tenemos acceso al &dAlmacén&f!

column2: Unfortunately the &dWarehouse&f was one of the first places to fall, and now we are slowly starving to death!
column3: Unfortunately the &dWarehouse&f was one of the first places to fall, and now we are slowly starving to death!

column2: If you can clear a path to the &dWarehouse&f and get some &eSupplies&f that would greatly aid in the war effort!
column3: If you can clear a path to the &dWarehouse&f and get some &eSupplies&f that would greatly aid in the war effort!

column2: &a[Cibus]&f The &dTavern&f is right across the street, hard to miss! Just head to the &dBasement&f and get the &eGood Stuff&f!
column3: &a[Cibus]&f La &dTaberna&f está justo al otro lado de la calle, es difícil de pasar de lado. ¡Solo ve al &dSótano&f y consigue las &eCosas buenas&f!

column2: &7&oI should go to the &dBasement&7&o of the tavern and get "the &eGood Stuff&7&o".
column3: &7&oDebería ir al &dSótano&7&o de la taberna y obtener "las &eCosas Buenas&7&o".

column2: &a[Cibus]&f You defeated the &cBarkeep&f? I thank you for freeing my old man from this accursed undeath. Here, I'll have the first drink with you.
column3: &a[Cibus]&f ¿Has derrotado al &cCantinero&f? Te doy las gracias por liberar a mi viejo de esta maldita no-muerte. Venga, voy a tomar la primera bebida contigo.

column2: We have food, but what about drinks?
column3: Tenemos alimentos, pero ¿qué hay con las bebidas?

column2: Some would say it's foolish to get drunk in the middle of a war, but if now then when?
column3: Algunos dirían que es tonto emborracharse en medio de una guerra, pero si no ahora ¿cuándo?

column2: The &cBarkeep&f across the street kept all of the good stuff in the &dBasement&f.
column3: El &cTabernero&f de enfrente guardó todo lo bueno en el &dSótano&f.

column2: I think you know where I'm going with this!
column3: I think you know where I'm going with this!

column2: Go to the &dBasement&f of the tavern across the street and get the &eGood Stuff&f.
column3: Ve al &dSótano&f de la taberna de enfrente y consigue las &eCosas Buenas&f.

column2: If you find the &cBarkeep&f, I'd consider it a personal favor if you free him from this curse of undeath.
column3: If you find the &cBarkeep&f, I'd consider it a personal favor if you free him from this curse of undeath.

column2: We are pretty sure that he was in the &dBasement&f when the invasion happened so odds are he is still there, though probably no longer himself.
column3: We are pretty sure that he was in the &dBasement&f when the invasion happened so odds are he is still there, though probably no longer himself.

column2: &8The very symbol of the Gladius Fortress.
column3: &8El mismísimo símbolo de la Fortaleza Gladius.

column2: Made out of very tough black diamonds.
column3: Esta herramienta no pertenece a este mundo.

column2: This tool does not belong in this world.

column3: Hecho de diamantes negros muy resistentes.
Otorgado con la maldición del frío.

column2: What brings you under the hill?
column3: ¿Qué te lleva hacia debajo del barranco?

column2:
Have you tried our
delicious glow berries?
Did not expect anyone\nto come down here.
I am digging for black diamonds.
column3: Estoy cavando en busca de diamantes negros.

column2: Seems like it is really\nhard to find black diamonds\nin your world.
column3: Parece que es muy\ndifícil encontrar diamantes negros\nen tu mundo.

column2: My portable wormhole\ngenerator malfunctioned and I\nended up here.
column3: Mi generador portátil de\nagujeros de gusano falló y\nterminé aquí.

column2: I need the black diamonds\nto recharge my wormhole generator.
column3: Necesito los diamantes negros\npara recargar mi generador de agujeros de gusano.

column2: &8&oYou hear the sound of a nearby ice wall cracking and breaking...
column3: &8&oEscuchas el sonido de una pared de hielo que está cerca y se está agrietando y rompiendo...

column2: &a[Mekanikus]&f Oh, the Ice Village chain shipment. Yes, it is right in that chest over there.
column3: &a[Mekanikus]&f Oh, el envío de cadenas de la Aldea de Hielo. Sí, está justo en ese cofre de ahí.

column2: Sorry for not sending it over, but we were quite busy and had no time.
column3: Siento no haberlo enviado, pero estábamos bastante ocupados y no tuvimos tiempo.

column2: It's all paid for so feel free to just grab it.
column3: Ya está todo pagado, así que siéntete libre de cogerlo.

column2: &a[Philolaches Triferus]&f Go talk to Mekanikus. They are the ones that make the chains.
column3: &a[Philolaches Triferus]&f Ve a hablar con Mekanikus. Ellos son los que hacen las cadenas.

column2: &7&oI should go talk to &a&oMekanikus&7&o and bring back the &e&oShipment of Chains&7&o.
column3: &7&oDebería ir a hablar con &a&oMekanikus&7&o y traer de vuelta el &e&oEnvío de Cadenas&7&o.

column2: &a[Philolaches Triferus]&f Those are the chains! Thank you for getting these, we really needed them.
column3: &a[Philolaches Triferus]&f ¡Esas son las cadenas! Gracias por conseguirlas, realmente las necesitábamos.

column2: Hey, you came from &dPontis Mille&f right?
How would you like to help us out.
Here at the jail we tend to go through a lot of chains...
column3: Aquí en la cárcel solemos usar muchas cadenas...

column2: Especially the chains holding up the cages.
column3: Especialmente las cadenas que sujetan las jaulas.

column2: They rust a lot and then they break. That's how one of the prisoners escaped.
column3: Se oxidan mucho y luego se rompen. Así es como escapó uno de los prisioneros.

column2: The rusty chain snapped, the cage fell and he ran.
column3: La cadena oxidada se rompió, la jaula cayó y él corrió.

column2: We paid for a &eShipment of new chains&f, but it did not arrive yet. If you could go to &dPontis Mille&f and fetch our &eShipment of Chains&f then that would be great!
column3: We paid for a &eShipment of new chains&f, but it did not arrive yet. If you could go to &dPontis Mille&f and fetch our &eShipment of Chains&f then that would be great!

column2: &7&oI should go see what is happening at the &d&oIce Village Bell Tower&7&o.
column3: &7&oDebería ir a ver lo que sucede en el &d&oCampanario de la Aldea Helada&7&o.

column2: &a[Eleusium Festus]&f You found an undead banging their head on the bell...
column3: &a[Eleusium Festus]&f Has encontrado un no-muerto golpeando su cabeza en la campana...

column2: Well now I have heard it all...
column3: Bueno, ahora lo he oído todo...

column2: Do you see that? There, look at that bell tower in the village.
column3: ¿Ves eso? Allí, mira esa torre del campanario en el pueblo.

column2: You see it too, right? The feller there banging his head on the bell.
column3: Tú también lo ves, ¿verdad? El tipo de allí golpeándose la cabeza contra la campana.

column2: I am pretty sure that's what's going on, unless my vision is failing me.
column3: I am pretty sure that's what's going on, unless my vision is failing me.

column2: Could you go investigate and report back to me with your findings.
column3: ¿Podrías ir a investigar e informarme de tus hallazgos?

column2: &a[Romanus Superbus]&f He must be somewhere in the mountains.
column3: &a[Romanus Superbus]&f Debe estar en algún lugar en las montañas.

column2: &7&oI need to find the &c&oEscaped Prisoner&7&o and bring him back to the prison.
column3: &7&oDebería ir a encontrar el &c&oPrisionero Escapado&7&o y traerlo de vuelta a la prisión.

column2: &a[Romanus Superbus]&f Well, well, well. If it isn't our escaped sleeping beauty.
column3: &a[Romanus Superbus]&f Bueno, bueno, bueno, si no es nuestra escapada bella durmiente.

column2: Good work. A job well done deserves a good payment, here ya go.
column3: Buen trabajo. Un trabajo bien hecho merece un buen pago, aquí tienes.

column2: &aRomanus&7 hands you a heavy bag of coin.
column3: &aRomanus&7 te da una bolsa pesada de monedas.

column2: What timing! I was just looking for someone to go capture our &cEscaped Prisoner&f.
column3: What timing! I was just looking for someone to go capture our &cEscaped Prisoner&f.

column2: One of our prisoners managed to make the darn cage swing and the rusty chain that holds it cracked under the load.
column3: Uno de nuestros prisioneros consiguió hacer el girar la maldita jaula y la cadena oxidada que la mantiene se agrietó bajo la carga.

column2: He must have gotten pretty hurt during the escape so he cannot have gone that far.
column3: Debe haberse lastimado bastante durante la fuga, por lo que no puede haber ido tan lejos.

column2: I need you to bring him back &9alive&f, be careful though, he managed to snag one of our rusty swords before he fled.
column3: Necesito que lo traigas de vuelta &9con vida&f, ten cuidado sin embargo, se las arregló para agarrar una de nuestras espadas oxidadas antes de huir.
Un día frío para la pesca.

column2: Old age will not\nslow me down!
Being in a good\nmood is important.
column3: Estar en un buen estado\n de ánimo es importante.
¡No hay nada como una buena cerveza!
No pude imaginar\nvivir en algún lugar\nsin nieve.
No dejes que el\nfrío te agarre.

column2: I was sure I\nleft it here.
column3: Estaba seguro de que\nlo dejé aquí.
Podría ir por un\npoco de salmón.

column2: Keep that in mind\nnext time you swing\nyour sword.
column3: Ten esto en cuenta\nla próxima vez que gires\ntu espada.

column2: The shield can be\nmore than defense.
column3: El escudo puede ser\nmás que una defensa.

column2: &a[Alanus Isatis]&f You must have seen the &cRazorbacks&f on your way here so I assume you know where to find them.
column3: &a[Alanus Isatis]&f Debes haber visto a los &cJabalíes&f en tu camino aquí así que asumo que sabes dónde encontrarlos.

column2: &7&oI need to cull the &c&oRazorback&7&o population and retrieve &e&oAlanus' Dagger&7&o.
column3: &7&oNecesito sacrificar la población de &c&oJabalíes&7&o y recuperar la &e&oDaga de Alanus&7&o.

column2: &a[Alanus Isatis]&f Well done friend! That should help a lot.
column3: &a[Alanus Isatis]&f ¡Bien hecho amigo! Eso debería ayudar mucho.

column2: We can handle the rest. And you found my dagger too, glad to have it in my hands again.
column3: Podemos manejar el resto. Y también encontraste mi daga, contento de tenerla en mis manos de nuevo.

column2: The dagger is nothing special, but it was a handmade gift from my late father.
column3: La daga no es nada especial, pero era un regalo hecho a mano de mi difunto padre.

column2: Next time you're thirsty, the drinks are on me!
column3: ¡La próxima vez que tengas sed, las bebidas van por mi cuenta!

column2: Let me tell ya, I sure am glad you are here to help, ha ha.
column3: Déjame decirte, estoy muy contento de que estés aquí para ayudar, ja ja.

column2: Our mission here is to hunt &cRazorbacks&f and keep their numbers in check.
column3: Nuestra misión aquí es cazar &cJabalíes&f y mantener su número bajo control.

column2: It's not all about population control either.
column3: Tampoco se trata todo del control de la población.

column2: They provide us with valuable leather, tusks and meat.
column3: Nos proporcionan valioso cuero, colmillos y carne.

column2: Not sure this village would be around without them.
column3: No estoy seguro de si esta aldea estaría alrededor sin ellos.

column2: But this season their numbers have just exploded. We have been struggling with culling their numbers.
column3: Pero esta temporada su número acaba de explotar. Hemos estado luchando para sacrificar sus números.

column2: It's all about striking a balance, can't have their numbers be so high that they start becoming a danger again.
column3: Se trata de lograr un equilibrio, no puede ser que sus números sean tan altos que comiencen a convertirse en un peligro nuevamente.

column2: You need to go out there and slay a significant amount of them. Don't bother with hunting any of the &9Mature&f ones.
column3: Necesitas salir ahí afuera y matar una cantidad significativa de ellos. No te molestes en cazar ninguno de los &9Maduros&f.

column2: We only need you to cull the &cBabe&f and the &cJuvenile Razorbacks&f.
column3: Solo necesitamos que elimines los &cJabalíes Bebés&f y los &c Jabalíes Juveniles&f.

column2: I also have a personal favor to ask of you. When you're out there could you keep an eye out for my old &eDagger&f.
column3: También tengo un favor personal para pedirte. Cuando estés ahí fuera, podrías mantenerte atento por mi vieja &eDaga&f.

column2: I lost it couple of days ago during a hunt. Stuck it in a &cJuvenile Razorback&f and it just ran off with my dagger still attached...
column3: I lost it couple of days ago during a hunt. Stuck it in a &cJuvenile Razorback&f and it just ran off with my dagger still attached...

column2: Would mean a lot to me if you could retrieve it.
column3: Significaría mucho para mí si pudieras recuperarlo.

column2: &a[Severinus Martius]&f Ha ha! That should keep me warm for another couple of weeks!
column3: &a[Severinus Martius]&f ¡Ja ja! ¡Eso debería mantenerme caliente por un par de semanas más!

column2: Hey friend, you heading for &dCaerullium Village&f by any chance?
column3: Hola amigo, ¿vas hacia &dAldea Caerullium&f por casualidad?

column2: &a[Grania Cecilius]&f You can find the lighthouse to the East. Thanks!
column3: &a[Grania Cecilius]&f Puedes encontrar el faro al Este. ¡Gracias!

column2: &7&oI should go to the &d&oLighthouse&7&o and deliver these to the &a&oLighthouse Keeper&7&o.
column3: &7&oDebería ir al &d&oFaro&7&o y entregarle esto al &a&oFaro&7&o.

column2: &a[Severinus Martius]&f If you're heading over there then I would appreciate if you could deliver some of these to my good friend &aJeeves&f.
column3: &a[Severinus Martius]&f Si vas para allá, te agradecería que le entregaras algo de esto a mi buen amigo &aJeeves&f.

column2: &7&oSeems like the &a&oLighthouse Keeper&7&o has a quest for me.
column3: &7&oParece que el &a&oFaro&7&o tiene una misión para mí.

column2: We deliver the &aLighthouse Keeper&f some of our strong stuff every couple of weeks.
column3: We deliver the &aLighthouse Keeper&f some of our strong stuff every couple of weeks.

column2: It keeps him warm during the colder days.
column3: Lo mantiene caliente durante los días más fríos.

column2: It's a small gesture of thanks for all his hard work.
column3: Es un pequeño gesto de agradecimiento por todo su arduo trabajo.

column2: Any chance you could help out and bring over the next batch?
column3: ¿Hay alguna posibilidad de que puedas ayudar y traer el próximo lote?

column2: &a[Jeeves]&f Oh! A gift from my friend Severinus you say.
column3: &a[Jeeves]&f ¡Oh! Un regalo de mi amigo Severinus, dices.

column2: Well, thank you for bringing it over. Was nice seeing you again!
column3: Bueno, gracias por traerlo. ¡Fue agradable verte de nuevo!
