column2: &a[Severinus Martius]&f The portal is all the way at the top.
column3: &a[Severinus Martius]&f El portal está en la cima.

column2: &7&oI should go to &d&oCaerullium Village&7&o and deliver some of the good stuff to &a&oJeeves&7&o.
column3: &7&oDebería ir a &d&oAldea Caerullium&7&o y entregarle algo de lo bueno a &a&oJeeves&7&o.

column2: &a[Severinus Martius]&f Thank you for delivering some of the strong stuff to Jeeves. I know he likes a good drink here and there ha ha!
column3: &a[Severinus Martius]&f Gracias por entregarle algo de la bebida fuerte a Jeeves. ¡Sé que le gusta una buena bebida de vez en cuando, ja ja!

column2: Now, now it would be really rude of me to keep all of the good stuff to myself!
column3: ¡Ahora, ahora, sería muy grosero de mi parte quedarme con todo lo bueno para mí!

column2: If you would bother helping me out friend and delivering some of the good stuff to my friend &aJeeves&f at &dCaerullium Village&f.
column3: If you would bother helping me out friend and delivering some of the good stuff to my friend &aJeeves&f at &dCaerullium Village&f.

column2: You can get there quickly by taking the &9lighthouse portal&f.
column3: Puedes llegar rápidamente tomando el &9portal del faro&f.

column2: Sure are many Razorbacks\nout this season.
column3: Seguramente hay muchos Jabalíes\nafuera esta temporada.

column2: &9This bow is so freezing cold you
&9need to use gloves to handle it.
I should check up\non the cages.
Don't do the crime if\nyou can't do the time.
column3: No hagas el crimen si\nno puedes hacer el tiempo.

column2: How are we supposed to\ncomplete the trials now.
column3: ¿Cómo se supone que debemos\ncompletar las pruebas ahora?

column2: &a[Cornelia Ennodius]&f Are they gone? I was so scared. My parents sent you? Thank goodness.
column3: &a[Cornelia Ennodius]&f ¿Se han ido? Estaba tan asustada. ¿Mis padres te enviaron? Gracias a Dios.

column2: I woke up in the night, but the nightmares, they did not end. They were still there, so I ran and ran...
column3: Me desperté por la noche, pero las pesadillas no acababan. Todavía estaban allí, por lo que corrí y corrí...

column2: I couldn't escape. I, I...will be fine, I just need a minute...
column3: No pude escapar. Yo, yo... estaré bien, solo necesito un minuto...

column2: &a[Sestia Ennodius]&f The trail went cold here, she cannot be that far away...
column3: &a[Sestia Ennodius]&f El rastro se enfrió aquí, ella no puede estar tan lejos...

column2: &7&oI need to find the &a&oMissing Daughter&7&o before something happens to her.
column3: &7&oNecesito encontrar a la &a&oHija Perdida&7&o antes de que le suceda algo.

column2: &a[Sestia Ennodius]&f You found her! Quickly, where is she?
Thank you stranger, I will go to her at once!
column3: ¡Gracias, extraño, voy a ir a ella de inmediato!

column2: I was following her trail, this is where it ends.
column3: Estaba siguiendo su rastro, aquí es donde termina.

column2: Not sure where she would have gone from here.
column3: No estoy seguro de adónde habrá ido desde aquí.

column2: I fear that something bad might have happened.
column3: Me temo que podría haber ocurrido algo malo.

column2: Our &aGirl&f takes a lot after me and my special powers.
column3: Nuestra &aChica&f toma mucho de mí y mis poderes especiales.

column2: Except that hers are a lot more potent, she is capable of making powerful emotions manifest in the real world.
column3: Except that hers are a lot more potent, she is capable of making powerful emotions manifest in the real world.

column2: We are running out of time, we need to find her soon.
column3: Se nos acaba el tiempo, necesitamos encontrarla pronto.
&3pelaje más duro que se puede encontrar.

column2: &a[Domina Violet]&f They went East past the &9Trees&f.
column3: &a[Domina Violet]&f Fueron al este más allá de los &9Árboles&f.

column2: &7&oI need to make sure that the &c&oCustomers&7&o know not to mess with &a&oViolet&7&o. I also need to retrieve &e&oViolet's Property&7&o.
column3: &7&oNecesito asegurarme de que los &c&oClientes&7&o sepan que no deben meterse con &a&oViolet&7&o. También necesito recuperar &e&oLa Propiedad de Violet&7&o.

column2: &a[Domina Violet]&f I hope you taught them the value of pain.
column3: &a[Domina Violet]&f Espero que les hayas enseñado el valor del dolor.

column2: A small reward is in order for your hard work. I appreciate people that get it done.
column3: Una pequeña recompensa está en orden por tu arduo trabajo. Aprecio a la gente que terminan el trabajo.

column2: I had some naughty &cCustomers&f come visit some days ago.
column3: Tuve unos &cClientes&f traviesos que vinieron de visita hace unos días.

column2: They stole the most valuable of my &ePossessions&f.
column3: Robaron lo más valioso de mis &ePosesiones&f.

column2: You need to find them and make sure to teach them a lesson.
column3: Tienes que encontrarlos y asegurarte de darles una lección.

column2: Make sure they know that &aViolet&f does not forget to collect.
column3: Asegúrate de que sepan que &aViolet&f no se olvida de cobrar.

column2: &a[Romanus Superbus]&f Release him? Not guilty? Are you mad? You're lucky I don't throw you in a cage too for suggesting such nonsense.
column3: &a[Romanus Superbus]&f ¿Liberarlo? ¿No culpable? ¿Estás loco? Tienes suerte de que no te meta a ti también en una jaula por sugerir semejante tontería.

column2: &a[Luxuria Placidus]&f Who? Never heard of him.
column3: &a[Luxuria Placidus]&f ¿Quién? Nunca he oído hablar de él.

column2: &a[Glacies Princeps]&f What, absolutely not. I don't know how he convinced you to come here and beg for his release.
column3: &a[Glacies Princeps]&f ¿Qué? Absolutamente no. No sé cómo te convenció para que vinieras aquí a rogar por su liberación.

column2: That man you are trying to help was corrupted by the Ice Elemental. He went mad and slaughtered his entire family.
column3: Ese hombre al que intentas ayudar fue corrompido por el Elemental del Hielo, se volvió loco y mató a toda su familia.

column2: He will never be released. Is that understood.
&a[Adrius Calpornius]&f Go talk to them! Get me out!
&7&oI should go talk to the people on my list.
column3: &7&oDebería ir a hablar con la gente de mi lista.

column2: &a[Adrius Calpornius]&f WHAT?! LIES!!! I never would do such a horrible thing to my family...
column3: &a[Adrius Calpornius]&f ¡¿QUÉ?! ¡¡¡MENTIRAS!!! Nunca le haría semejante cosa horrible a mi familia...

column2: They are right here! Can't you see them, hear them. Here next to me, they want to be free too!!! RELEASE US!!!
column3: ¡Están justo aquí! ¿No puedes verlos, oírlos?. ¡¡¡Aquí junto a mí, quieren ser libres también!!! ¡¡¡LIBÉRANOS!!!

column2: &7Whatever sanity this poor man still had left, is gone now...
column3: &7Cualquier cordura que le quedara a este pobre hombre, se ha ido ahora...

column2: I do not belong here! Surely you can see that?
column3: ¡Yo no pertenezco aquí! ¿Seguramente lo pueden ver?

column2: I have done no wrong! Stranger will you hear my plea.
column3: ¡No he hecho nada malo! ¿Extraño, escucharías mi súplica?

column2: Would you help this poor soul who has been trapped here in this awful cage of no fault of his own?
column3: Would you help this poor soul who has been trapped here in this awful cage of no fault of his own?

column2: You must go talk to the &aJail Master&f or the &aVillage Leader&f.
column3: Debes ir a hablar con el &aMaestro de la Prisión&f o el &aLíder de la Aldea&f.

column2: Or any other &aFriendly Villager&f who would be willing to argue for my release!
column3: ¡O cualquier otro &aAldeano Amistoso&f que esté dispuesto a abogar por mi liberación!

column2: &a[Sestia Ennodius]&f I could sense you coming.
&a[Sparax Ennodius]&f My &aWife&f has already gone looking for her.
column3: &a[Sparax Ennodius]&f Mi &aEsposa&f ya ha ido a buscarla.

column2: I am sure she is somewhere outside the village. Go find her and talk to her.
column3: Estoy seguro de que ella está en algún lugar fuera de la aldea. Ve a encontrarla y habla con ella.

column2: &7&oI should go look for the &a&oWorried Mother&7&o.
&a[Sestia Ennodius]&f You were sent by my &aHusband&f to help with the search?
column3: &a[Sestia Ennodius]&f ¿Fuiste enviado por mi &aEsposo&f para ayudar con la búsqueda?

column2: Stranger! Would you help our family?
She has been gifted with special powers just like her &aMother&f.
column3: Ha sido dotada con poderes especiales al igual que su &aMadre&f.

column2: I fear that last night something terrible must have happened to make her run away in the middle of the night.
column3: I fear that last night something terrible must have happened to make her run away in the middle of the night.
salmón más grande en su vida.

column2: &a[Modestus Eulogius]&f It sounds like it coming somewhere from the hills behind me.
column3: &a[Modestus Eulogius]&f Parece que viene de alguna parte de las colinas detrás de mí.

column2: &7&oI should find the source of all the noise and make it stop.
column3: &7&oDebería encontrar la fuente de todo el ruido y hacer que pare.

column2: &a[Modestus Eulogius]&f Both me and my ears thank you!
column3: &a[Modestus Eulogius]&f ¡Tanto yo como mis oídos te damos las gracias!

column2: Shhh! Do you hear it? The annoying screeching. Ugh, I cannot take it anymore!
column3: ¡Shhh! ¿Lo oyes? El molesto chirrido. ¡Uf, no puedo más!

column2: Listen, I will pay good coin if you can find the source of that annoying screeching and make it stop.
column3: Listen, I will pay good coin if you can find the source of that annoying screeching and make it stop.

column2: &a[Theopropides Nero]&f You wanted to help so here is your chance!
column3: &a[Theopropides Nero]&f ¡Has querido ayudar así que esta es tu oportunidad!

column2: &7&oI must jump into the lake and kill 7 &c&oChilly Salmon&7&o and collect their bodies.
column3: &7&oDebería saltar al lago y matar 7 &c&oSalmones Fríos&7&o y recoger sus cuerpos.

column2: &a[Theopropides Nero]&f Oh! Look at them! Such big ones!.
This should keep us fed for a while! Thank you for the assistance, you're a good soul in my book!
column3: ¡Esto debería mantenernos alimentados durante un tiempo! ¡Gracias por la asistencia, eres un buen alma en mi libro!

column2: These &cFish&f, what is wrong with them!
I have been out here fishing for days now!
column3: ¡He estado aquí pescando durante días ahora!

column2: Not even a single bite. If only I was younger I would show them!
column3: Ni siquiera una sola mordedura. ¡Si tan solo fuera más joven, se los demostraría!

column2: Well it sure is good you're here now. Our village gets most of its food from these &cFish&f.
column3: Bueno, seguro que es bueno que estés aquí ahora. Nuestro pueblo obtiene la mayor parte de su alimento de esos &cPeces&f.

column2: And if we cannot catch any, well that is a big problem.
column3: Y si no podemos atrapar a ninguno, bueno eso es un gran problema.

column2: You will need to go down there and beat them senseless.
column3: Tendrás que bajar allí y golpearlos hasta dejarlos inconscientes.
&bEs una caña de pesca bien hecha.
Simplemente tratando de\ndisfrutar de la paz.

column2: &a[Eleusium Calenus]&f My wife sent you? Oh, are those treats? My favorite too! She's such a darling.
column3: &a[Eleusium Calenus]&f ¿Mi esposa te envió? ¡Oh, son golosinas? ¡Mis favoritas también! Es un encanto.

column2: She always takes care of me, even in these dark times, she still has a place for me in her heart.
column3: Ella siempre cuida de mí. Incluso en estos tiempos oscuros, ella todavía tiene un lugar para mí en su corazón.

column2: You tell her I am doing just fine and that I love her very much.
column3: Dile que estoy muy bien y que la quiero mucho.

column2: &a[Titia Calenus]&f He will be in one of the middle cages.
column3: &a[Titia Calenus]&f Estará en una de las jaulas del medio.

column2: Do not forget to tell him I love him.
column3: No te olvides de decirle que lo amo.

column2: &7&oI should deliver these treats to the &a&oHusband&7&o.
&a[Titia Calenus]&f Back so quick! Oh, did he really say that? He is such a sweetie.
column3: &a[Titia Calenus]&f ¡Volviste tan rápido! Oh, ¿realmente dijo eso? Él es tan dulce.

column2: If you don't mind, could I ask you to do something for me?
column3: Si no te importa, ¿podría pedirte que hicieras algo por mí?

column2: My dear &aHusband&f has been jailed and I know it's tough living a cage all day.
column3: Mi querido &aEsposo&f ha sido encarcelado y sé que es duro vivir una jaula todo el día.

column2: So I prepared some treats that I was gonna deliver to him.
column3: Así que preparé algunas golosinas que yo iba a entregarle.

column2: But I am quite busy right now and I was wondering if maybe you would like to go there and deliver them to him.
column3: Pero ahora mismo estoy bastante ocupada y me preguntaba si tal vez te gustaría ir allí y entregárselo.
No, eso es lo que pensé.
Botas de Cuero de la Reina

column2: &a[Luxuria Placidus]&f You will find the &cCreatures&f in any woods near the village.
column3: &a[Luxuria Placidus]&f Encontrarás las &cCriaturas&f en cualquier bosque cerca de la aldea.

column2: We will at least need 15 of the &eCrystals&f if we want to have enough to build a snowman.
column3: Necesitaremos al menos 15 de los &eCristales&f si queremos tener suficiente para construir un muñeco de nieve.

column2: &7&oI should go slay enough &c&oFrost Fur Ursus&7&o to gather 15 &e&oIce Crystals&7&o.
column3: &7&oDebería ir a matar suficientes &c&Ursus de Piel de Escarcha&7&o para recoger 15 &e&oCristales de Hielo&7&o.

column2: &a[Luxuria Placidus]&f You gathered enough crystals? Wonderful!
I can start making the snowman now, I cannot wait for the kids to see it!
column3: Puedo empezar a hacer el muñeco de nieve ahora, ¡no puedo esperar a que los niños lo vean!

column2: The kids around the village have been pretty bored lately and I've been thinking.
column3: Los niños de la aldea han estado bastante aburridos últimamente y he estado pensando.

column2: There are these &cMagical Creatures&f that inhabit the woods around this village.
column3: Hay estas &cCriaturas Mágicas&f que habitan los bosques alrededor de esta aldea.

column2: The creatures fur grows &eMagical Ice Crystals&e.
column3: El pelaje de las criaturas produce &eCristales de Hielo Mágicos&e.

column2: When you infuse snow with these &eCrystals&f it makes the snow shuffle around and expand and contract.
column3: When you infuse snow with these &eCrystals&f it makes the snow shuffle around and expand and contract.

column2: And if you build a snowman out of this infused snow it makes it look as if the snowman is moving.
column3: And if you build a snowman out of this infused snow it makes it look as if the snowman is moving.

column2: The kids would love it! So, want to help this old man cheer up some kids?
column3: The kids would love it! So, want to help this old man cheer up some kids?
Deja que nuestra chica esté\nsegura, por favor.

column2: &eYou see LL engraved in the handle
Hope you are enjoying the map!
&8[Centurion]&fAre you braving the Goblin Mines? Beware the Goblin King!
column3: &8[Centurion]&f¿Vas a adentrarte en las Minas Goblin? ¡Ten cuidado con el Rey Goblin!

column2: &8[Centurion]&fWe hope our scouting party made it past him. Meet up with them if you can.
column3: &8[Centurion]&fEsperamos que nuestro equipo de exploración haya pasado más allá de él. Reúnete con ellos si puedes.

column2: &8&oI should venture through the mines and defeat the Goblin King.
column3: &8&oI debe aventurarse a través de las minas y derrotar al Rey Goblin.

column2: &8[Scouting party]&fYou made it through? I almost wish you hadn't. You won't believe what lies ahead.
column3: &8[Fiesta de exploración]&f¿Lo has conseguido? Casi me gustaría que no lo hubieses. No creerás lo que queda por delante.

column2: &8&oSounds like the scouting party has bad news for me.
column3: &8&oSonidos como el grupo de exploradores me dan malas noticias.

column2: This day just keeps getting worse. First, we get ambushed by goblins.
column3: Este día sigue empeorando. En primer lugar, nos emboscan los goblins.

column2: The we retreat, only to find our army split. Some are dead, many are missing.
column3: Luego nos retiramos, solo para encontrar que nuestro ejército se dividió. Algunos están muertos, muchos otros están desaparecidos.

column2: Worst of all, we fear we might've woken the Goblin King.
column3: Lo peor de todo, tememos que hayamos despertado al Rey Goblin.

column2: Some, hopefully, made it through. We have to set up camp and recover for now.
column3: Algunos, esperemos, lo lograron. Tenemos que establecer un campo y recuperarnos por ahora.

column2: If you dare brave into the mines, you are on your own.
column3: Si te atreves a entrar en las minas, estás solo.

column2: We tried to sneak past them, and it did not go well.
column3: Intentamos escabullirlos más allá de ellos, y no salió bien.

column2: The only way forward is through bloodshed.
column3: La única forma de avanzar es a través del derramamiento de sangre.

column2: &a[Chief Piscis] &fOh so you were in the ship that beached a few hours ago?
column3: &a[Jefe Piscis] &f¿Oh, así que estabas en el barco que encalló hace unas horas?

column2: I apologize, we would've sent help but I am afraid we are drowning in our own issues right now!
column3: &7&oDebería informar al &aPrimer oficial &7&oPara ver si debería ayudar a estas persona!

column2: A nearby &dBandit Camp &fkeeps raiding our supplies, a mysterious &cSea Creature &fkeeps haunting our shores and a &dWolf Den &fis making foraging impossible!
column3: ¡Un &dCampamento de Bandidos &fcercano sigue asaltando nuestros suministros, una &cCriatura Marina &fmisteriosa sigue merodeando por nuestras costas y una &dguarida de lobos &fhace imposible buscar comida!

column2: If you help us out, I will tell you where you might be able to get the supplies you need to repair your ship.
column3: Si nos ayudan, te diré dónde podrías conseguir los suministros que necesitas para reparar tu nave.

column2: &7&oI should report to the &aFirst Mate &7&oto see if I should help these people!
column3: &7&o¡Debería informar al &aPrimer Oficial &7&opara ver si debo ayudar a esa gente!

column2: &a[Captain Squalus]&f Go to the nearby village and see if they will help us!
column3: &a[Capitán Squalus]&f ¡Ve a la aldea cercana y ve si nos ayudarán!

column2: Be careful on your way there, we don't know what lurks around these parts!
column3: ¡Ten cuidado en tu camino allí, no sabemos qué acecha alrededor de estas partes!

column2: Oh and you ever see any critters start spawning a bunch of particles, well that is your sign that something bad is about to happen!
column3: Oh and you ever see any critters start spawning a bunch of particles, well that is your sign that something bad is about to happen!

column2: &7&oI should investigate the nearby village and talk to their leader.
column3: &7&oDebería investigar la aldea cercana y hablar con su líder.

column2: &a[First Mate Iracundi]&f Darnation! We just can't catch a break today! Here, it's clearly dangerous to go alone, take this!
column3: &a[Primer compañero Iracundi]&f ¡Demonios! ¡No podemos coger un descanso hoy! ¡Ten, es claramente peligroso ir solo, toma esto!

column2: &7&oSeems like First Mate Iracundi has a request for me...
column3: &7&oParece que el Primer Compañero Iracundi tiene una solicitud para mí...

column2: You're finally awake? Good! We need your help.
column3: ¿Por fin estás despierto? ¡Bueno! Necesitamos tu ayuda.

column2: The ship beached during last night's storm.
column3: El barco arrasó durante la tormenta de la noche pasada.

column2: We see a &dLighthouse &fin the distance, so there must be a village there!
column3: ¡Vemos un &dFaro &fen la distancia, así que debe haber una aldea allí!

column2: Go talk to the &aVillage Leader &fand see if they can lend use some help!
column3: ¡Ve a hablar con el &aLíder de la Aldea &fy comprueba si pueden prestar algo de ayuda!

column2: The &aFirst Mate &fwent ahead of you, but hasn't returned yet.
column3: El &aPrimer Oficial &fse adelantó a ti, pero no ha regresado todavía.

column2: Follow his instructions if you see him!
&a[Shogun Navita] &f&dGladius&f calls for our aid?\n&7&oSeems like I should talk to the &aShogun&7&o.
column3: &a[Shogun Navita] &f¿&dGladius&f pide nuestra ayuda?\n&7&oParece que debería hablar con el &aShogun&7&o.

column2: &a[General Hasta] &fSafe travels, friend. Remember: Kill the &cGate Keeper&f and make sure our plea reaches &aShogun Navita's&f ears..
column3: &a[General Hasta] &fViajes seguros, recuerda: Mata al &cgGuardián de la Puerta&f y asegúrate de que nuestra petición llegue a los oídos de &aShogun Navita&f..

column2: &7&oI should slay the &cGate Keeper&7&o at the &dBridge&7&o and make my way to &aShogun Navita&7&o in &dPontis Mille&7&o.
column3: &7&oDebería matar al &cGuardián de la Puerta&7&o en el &dpuente&7&o y hacerme camino a &aShogun Navita&7&o en &dPontis Mille&7&o.

column2: &a[Shogun Navita]&f Truly the news you bring me are most disturbing, but I am afraid we already suspected something... unnatural... was going on.
column3: &a[Shogun Navita]&f Verdaderamente las noticias que me traes son las más inquietantes, pero me temo que ya sospechábamos que algo... antinatural... estaba pasando.

column2: &7&oSeems like &aShogun Navita&7&o wants to talk to me.
It is time to call &dPontis Mille&f for aid.
column3: Ya es hora de llamar a &dPontis Mille&f para recibir ayuda.

column2: Let them know of what happened here and tell them we are cashing in our favor.
column3: Háganles saber lo que sucedió aquí y díganles que estamos cobrando a nuestro favor.

column2: There is an &cAutomaton&f on the &dBridge&f that leads there. Defeat it and the bridge will lower.
column3: Hay un &cautómata&f en el &dpuente&f que conduce allí. Derrótalo y el puente bajará.

column2: &a[Navita]&f You can find the &aMajor&f on top of those stairs right ahead!
column3: &a[Navita]&f ¡Puedes encontrar al &aAlcalde&f en la parte superior de esas escaleras justo por delante!

column2: &7&oI should go talk to the &aMajor&f and see if he can help.
column3: &7&oDebería ir a hablar con el &aAlcalde&f y ver si puede ayudar.

column2: &a[Major Fortes Bellator]&f The &aShogun&f seeks to aid &dGladius&f? I thought he would never ask! But first, we must prepare.
column3: &a[Alcalde Fortes Bellator]&f ¿El &aShogun&f busca ayudar a &dGladius&f? ¡Pensé que nunca lo preguntaría! Pero primero, debemos prepararnos.

column2: &7&oSeems like &aFortes Bellator&7&o has work for me.
column3: &7&oParece que &aFortes Bellator&7&o tiene trabajo para mí.

column2: The tales of your travel are most surprising.
column3: Las historias de tu viaje son muy sorprendentes.

column2: That you made it alive to here is nothing short of a miracle.
column3: Que hayas llegado vivo hasta aquí no es nada menos que un milagro.
Las fuerzas que invaden &dGladius&f son insuperables.

column2: &dGladius&f will eventually crumble under their might...
column3: &dGladius&f eventualmente se derrumbará bajo su poder...

column2: Aid?... Ah, yes. Go see &aMajor Fortes Bellator&f.
column3: ¿Ayuda?... Ah, sí. Ve a ver a &aAlcalde Fortes Bellator&f.

column2: He will be able to assist you.
&a[Fortes Bellator]&fTread lightly, the &dGoblin Mines&f are a dangerous place. Perhaps you should aid the normal guard before assisting the &aRoyal Guard&f.
column3: &a[Fortes Bellator]&fAnda con cuidado, las &dMinas Goblin&f son un lugar peligroso. Quizás deberías ayudar a la guardia normal antes de asistir a la &aGuardia Real&f.

column2: The &dMines&f are north of the city. There are stairs leading to its entrance.
column3: Las &dMinas&f están al norte de la ciudad. Hay escaleras que conducen a su entrada.

column2: &7&oI should see what else I can aid &aFortes Bellator&7&o with, or I can head to the &dGoblin Mines'&7&o entrance.
column3: &7&oDebería ver en que más puedo ayudar a &aFortes Bellator&7&o, o dirigirme a la entrada de las &dMinas Goblin&7&o.

column2: &a[Centurion]&fIt is so good to see someone! Has &dPontis Mille&f sent you?
column3: &a[Centurion]&f¡Es muy bueno ver a alguien! ¿Te ha enviado &dPontis Mille&f?

column2: &7&oI should hear what the &aCenturion&7&o has to say
column3: &7&oDebería escuchar lo que tiene que decir &aCenturion&7&o

column2: I cannot believe what befell &dGladius&f. They hit it fast, and they hit it where it hurts most.
column3: I cannot believe what befell &dGladius&f. They hit it fast, and they hit it where it hurts most.

column2: It is our sworn duty to aid our allies. We have failed our duty, and we have failed our allies.
column3: It is our sworn duty to aid our allies. We have failed our duty, and we have failed our allies.

column2: The &cCounselor's&f ordered us to mobilize our troops in several zones before the invasion.
column3: The &cCounselor's&f ordered us to mobilize our troops in several zones before the invasion.

column2: You see, recently and unusual and devastating storm was spotted at the &dStorm Temple&f.
column3: You see, recently and unusual and devastating storm was spotted at the &dStorm Temple&f.

column2: The Royal Guard was ordered to quiet the storm, and the &aShogun&f refuses to belay that order.
column3: The Royal Guard was ordered to quiet the storm, and the &aShogun&f refuses to belay that order.

column2: Our own guards are in other places, and I fear we will need all that we have to take &dGladius&f back.
column3: Our own guards are in other places, and I fear we will need all that we have to take &dGladius&f back.

column2: The path to the &dStorm Temple&f is treacherous, as it requires going through the &dGoblin Mines&f.
column3: The path to the &dStorm Temple&f is treacherous, as it requires going through the &dGoblin Mines&f.

column2: Help our guard clear the mines and make a path to the &dStorm Temple&f!
column3: Help our guard clear the mines and make a path to the &dStorm Temple&f!

column2: &a[Centurion]&f Are you braving the &dGoblin Mines&f? Beware the &cGoblin King&f!
column3: &a[Centurion]&f ¿Vas a adentrarte en las &dMinas Goblin&f? ¡Ten cuidado con el &cRey Goblin&f!

column2: We hope our &aScouting Party&f made it past him. Meet up with them if you can.
column3: Esperamos que nuestro &aEquipo de Exploración&f haya pasado más allá de él. Reúnete con ellos si puedes.

column2: &7&oI should venture through the &dMines&7&o and defeat the &cGoblin King&7&o.
column3: &7&oDebería aventurarme a través de las &dMinas&7&o y derrotar al &cRey Goblin&7&o.

column2: &a[Scouting Party]&f You made it through? I almost wish you hadn't. You won't believe what lies ahead.
column3: &a[Equipo de Exploración]&f ¿Lo has conseguido? Casi me gustaría que no lo hubieses. No creerás lo que queda por delante.

column2: &7&oSounds like the scouting party has bad news for me.
column3: &7&oSuena como que el grupo de exploradores tiene malas noticias para mí.

column2: This day just keeps getting worse. First, we get ambushed by goblins.
column3: Este día sigue empeorando. En primer lugar, nos emboscan los goblins.

column2: Then we retreat, only to find our army split. Some are dead, many are missing.
column3: Luego nos retiramos, solo para encontrar que nuestro ejército se dividió. Algunos están muertos, muchos otros están desaparecidos.

column2: Worst of all, we fear we might've woken the &cGoblin King&f.
column3: Lo peor de todo, tememos que hayamos despertado al &cRey Goblin&f.

column2: Some, hopefully, made it through. We have to set up camp and recover for now.
column3: Algunos, esperemos, lo lograron. Tenemos que establecer un campo y recuperarnos por ahora.

column2: If you dare brave into the mines, you are on your own.
column3: Si te atreves a entrar en las minas, estás solo.

column2: We tried to sneak past them, and it did not go well.
column3: Intentamos escabullirlos más allá de ellos, y no salió bien.

column2: The only way forward is through bloodshed.
column3: La única forma de avanzar es a través del derramamiento de sangre.

column2: &a[Blepharo]&f We have weakened their forces a little, but still, this is no easy task.
column3: &a[Blepharo]&f Hemos debilitado sus fuerzas un poco, pero aun así, esta no es una tarea fácil.

column2: The Storm is no ordinary opponent. Do not underestimate it.
column3: La Tormenta no es un oponente ordinario. No la subestimes.

column2: &7&oI should go into the &dStorm Temple&f and slay the &cStorm&f.
column3: &7&oDebería ir al &dTemplo de Tormenta&f y matar a la &cTormenta&f.

column2: Defeated the &cStorm&f? I was told that was impossible! I mean...
column3: ¿Derrotaste a la &cTormenta&f? ¡Me dijeron que era imposible! Quiero decir...

column2: ... it is no use hiding it now. I knew about the &cStorm&f. I knew about the &dGladius&f invasion - I even facilitated it. I did it for my people - for &dPontis Mille&f.
column3: ... no sirve de nada esconderlo ahora. Sabía sobre la &cTormenta&f. Sabía de la invasión de &dGladius&f - incluso la facilité. Lo hice por mi gente - por &dPontis Mille&f.

column2: &cCounselor Machiavelli&f convinced me that the &cStorm&f was as unstoppable as Nature itself, and that the fall of &dGladius&f and &dPontis Mille&f was an inevitability that we could but delay through sacrifice.
column3: &cEl Consejero Machiavelli&f me convenció de que la &cTormenta&f era tan imparable como la naturaleza misma, y que la caída de &dGladius&f y &dPontis Mille&f era una inevitabilidad, que no podíamos retrasar a través del sacrificio.

column2: I see now that that snake poisoned my mind and corrupted my judgment. He must be dealt with posthaste.
column3: Veo ahora que esa serpiente envenenó mi mente y corrompió mi juicio. Debemos encargarnos de él a toda prisa.

column2: &8&oSeems like &aShogun Navita&7&o has a problem he wants me to deal with.
column3: &8&oParece que &aShogun Navita&7&o tiene un problema del que quiere que me encargue.

column2: It is hard to believe that you pushed through the &dGoblin Mines&f on your own.
column3: Es difícil creer que hayas logrado pasar por las &dMinas Goblin&f por tu cuenta.

column2: Perhaps with your fortitude you will be able to face the challenge ahead.
column3: Quizás con tu fortaleza podrás enfrentar el desafío que tienes por delante.

column2: We attempted to assault the &dStorm Temple&f, and reached its deepest confines at a great cost.
column3: We attempted to assault the &dStorm Temple&f, and reached its deepest confines at a great cost.

column2: What we found there... It defies understanding.
column3: Lo que encontramos allí... Desafía la comprensión.

column2: It may be hard to believe, but it sounds like the very storm itself has materialized as our opponent.
column3: It may be hard to believe, but it sounds like the very storm itself has materialized as our opponent.

column2: We do not even know if it can be defeated. We feared we were sent to our deaths.
column3: We do not even know if it can be defeated. We feared we were sent to our deaths.

column2: If you truly defeated the &cGoblin King&f, then perhaps you will find a way to slay this storm.
column3: Si realmente has derrotado al &cRey Goblin&f, entonces tal vez encuentres una manera de matar a esta tormenta.

column2: &a[Shogun Navita]&f &cCounselor Machiavelli&f has retreated to his quarters in the lower city by the market. Be careful, has has amassed a devoted following in his time, and will not go down without a fight.
column3: &a[Shogun Navita]&f El &cConsejero Machiavelli&f se ha retirado a sus cuarteles en la ciudad baja por el mercado. Ten cuidado, ha acumulado seguidores devotos en su tiempo, y no caerá sin una lucha.

column2: &7&oIt is time for &cCounselor Machiavelli&f to face righteous retribution.
column3: &7&oEs hora de que el &cConsejero Machiavelli&f se enfrente a una justa retribución.

column2: &dPontis Mille&f owes you a great debt, wanderer. Once we finish mobilizing the army we will be ready to right our wrongs and march to &dGladius'&f aid.
column3: &dPontis Mille&f te debe una gran deuda, viajero. Una vez que terminemos de movilizar al ejército, estaremos listos para corregir nuestros errores y marchar a la ayuda de &dGladius&f.

column2: &7<Shogun Navita focuses on the far speech stone>&a[Shogun Navita]&2 We feared you. We surrendered our allies to you. We dispersed our armies. No more.
column3: &7<Shogun Navita focuses on the far speech stone>&a[Shogun Navita]&2 We feared you. We surrendered our allies to you. We dispersed our armies. No more.

column2: &dPontis Mille&2 marches to war, and we shall not walk alone! You shall rue the day you crossed our path.
column3: ¡&dPontis Mille&2 marcha a la guerra, y no caminaremos solos! Lamentarás el día que te cruzaste en nuestro camino.

column2: &7<Ominous laughter can be heard through the far speech stone as &aShogun Navita &7smashes it on the ground>
column3: &7<Ominous laughter can be heard through the far speech stone as &aShogun Navita &7smashes it on the ground>

column2: &7&oSeems like the &aShogun&7&o has a plan. I should talk to him.
column3: &7&oParece que el &aShogun&7&o tiene un plan. Debería hablar con él.

column2: Once upon a time, &cCounselor Machiavelli&f, the wisest among us, foresaw the fall of &dPontis Mille&f.
column3: Érase una vez, el &cConsejero Machiavelli&f, el más sabio entre nosotros, previó la caída de &dPontis Mille&f.

column2: Faced with an unprecedented existential threat, he convinced me to keep quiet as to not incite panic.
column3: Ante una amenaza existencial sin precedentes, me convenció de callarme para no incitar al pánico.

column2: I took the only course of action I thought we had left - sacrificing our closest ally to buy us mere weeks.
column3: Tomé la única medida que pensaba que nos quedaba - sacrificar a nuestro aliado más cercano para comprarnos meras semanas.

column2: I spoke to the entity which resides in the &dBlood Temple&f. I made a deal with the devil.
column3: Hablé con la entidad que reside en el &dTemplo de Sangre&f. Hice un trato con el diablo.

column2: In exchange for revealing &dGladius'&f greatest weakness - their naval capabilities - I bought us time.
column3: In exchange for revealing &dGladius'&f greatest weakness - their naval capabilities - I bought us time.

column2: They demanded I send the army away, which I did by mobilizing it to face nearby conflicts.
column3: Exigieron que enviara al ejército lejos, y lo hice movilizándolo para hacer frente a los conflictos cercanos.

column2: I was blind, but now I see. &cCounselor Machiavelli&f was in their pocket the whole time.
column3: Estaba ciego, pero ahora veo. &cEl consejero Machiavelli&f estuvo en su bolsillo todo el tiempo.

column2: He guided us to our doom, and would've gotten away with it had you not appeared.
column3: Nos guio a nuestra perdición, y se habría salido con la suya si no hubieras aparecido.

column2: I ask you, please rid us of the treacherous &cCounselor&f.
column3: Te pido, por favor, desvíanos del &cConsejero&f traicionero.

column2: He has locked himself in his quarters, surrounded by those loyal to him and his... pets.
column3: Se ha encerrado en sus cuarteles, rodeados por aquellos leales a él y su... mascotas.

column2: Be careful. I knew not the reason why he isolated himself, but it is now clear he is expecting retribution.
column3: Ten cuidado. No sabía el por qué se aisló, pero ahora está claro que espera represalias.

column2: Bring me back the &eFar SSpeech Stone&f we used to communicate with the &dBlood Temple&f.
column3: Tráeme de vuelta la &ePiedra de Habla Lejana&f que usamos para comunicarnos con el &dTemplo de Sangre&f.

column2: I wish to deliver one last message through them.
column3: Deseo mandar un último mensaje a través de ellos.

column2: &a[Glacies]&f Welcome to our village traveler! Please tell me, what brings you here friend.
column3: &a[Glacies]&f ¡Bienvenido a nuestra aldea, viajero! Por favor, dime, ¿qué te trae por aquí, amigo?

column2: &a[Bromia Culleolus]&f Oh, the way to the village. Yes, just take  this road that leads to the mountain.
column3: &a[Bromia Culleolus]&f Oh, el camino al pueblo. Sí, simplemente toma este camino que lleva a la montaña.

column2: &a[Demenis Nolus]&f Heading to the village, eh. Just keep going East, follow the road and you should be there in no time!
column3: &a[Demenis Nolus]&f Vas hacia el pueblo, ¿eh? Sigue yendo hacia el Este, sigue el camino y deberías llegar en poco tiempo.

column2: &a[Callipho Classicius]&f Directions? Just head down this road that leads to the graveyards.
column3: &a[Callipho Classicius]&f ¿Indicaciones? Simplemente baja por este camino que lleva a los cementerios.

column2: &a[Shogun Navita]&f It will be a long journey. Make sure you prepare. Follow the roads that lead south.
column3: &a[Shogun Navita]&f Será un viaje largo. Asegúrate de prepararte. Sigue las carreteras que conducen al sur.

column2: &7&oI must go and locate the &d&oIce Village&7&o to the far south.
column3: &7&oDebo ir y localizar la &d&oAldea de Hielo&7&o en el sur lejano.

column2: &a[Glacies Princeps]&f The Shogun sent you, I see, it is good to hear that &aNavita&f is back to his old self.
column3: &a[Glacies Princeps]&f El Shogun te envió, ya veo, es bueno escuchar que &aNavita&f está de vuelta a su viejo yo.

column2: Before we can act against the &dBlood Temple&f, there are some issues that I would like dealt with first.
column3: Antes de que podamos actuar contra el &dTemplo de Sangre&f, hay algunas problemas que me gustaría tratar primero.

column2: We must send aid to &dGladius&f as soon as possible.
column3: Debemos enviar ayuda a &dGladius&f tan pronto como sea posible.

column2: Champion, there is a village of mighty warriors to the far south.
column3: Campeón, hay una aldea de guerreros poderosos al sur.

column2: You should travel there and inform them that &dPontis Mille&f would seek their aid in pushing back the invaders from the &dBlood Temple&f.
column3: You should travel there and inform them that &dPontis Mille&f would seek their aid in pushing back the invaders from the &dBlood Temple&f.

column2: Find &aGlacies Princeps&f and tell them I sent you.
column3: Encuentra a &aGlacies Princeps&f y diles que te envié yo.

column2: There many travelers on the roads, you should stop and ask them for direction.
column3: Hay muchos viajeros en los caminos, deberías detenerte y preguntarles por direcciones.

column2: &a[Alanus Isatis]&f Here to help with the &cRazorbacks&f?
&a[Domina Violet]&f I hope you are here to help!
column3: &a[Domina Violet]&f ¡Espero que estés aquí para ayudar!

column2: &a[Glacies Princeps]&f Once you are done helping them. Come back to me and we can talk.
column3: &a[Glacies Princeps]&f Una vez que hayas terminado de ayudarlos. Vuelve a mí y podemos hablar.

column2: &7&oI should go talk to the villagers on my list and help them out with any issues they might have.
column3: &7&oDebo ir a hablar con los aldeanos de mi lista y ayudarlos a resolver cualquier problema que puedan tener.

column2: &a[Romanus Superbus]&f &2Glacies&f sent you, about darn time! We have a prisoner on the loose!
column3: &a[Romanus Superbus]&f ¡&2Glacies&f te envió, ya era hora! ¡Tenemos un prisionero suelto!

column2: Before we further discuss anything about
column3: Antes de seguir discutiendo algo sobre

column2: There are issues that have popped around our village that need to be dealt with as soon as possible.
column3: Hay problemas que han surgido alrededor de nuestra aldea que deben tratarse lo antes posible.

column2: If these issues are not resolved then I would fail in my duties as a village leader.
column3: Si no se resuelven estos problemas, fallaría en mis deberes como líder de la aldea.

column2: There is no way for me to ignore the plea of my own people and put others first.
column3: No hay forma de que yo ignore la petición de mi propio pueblo y ponga a los demás en primer lugar.

column2: If you could aid us in resolving these issues then our attention would be all yours.
column3: Si pudieses ayudarnos a resolver estos problemas, entonces nuestra atención sería toda tuya.

column2: We have an escaped prisoner, wildlife problems and even our own villagers stealing from the village.
column3: Tenemos un prisionero escapado, problemas con la vida silvestre e incluso nuestros propios aldeanos roban de la aldea.

column2: I will tell you the names and the locations of the people that came with these issues to me.
column3: Te diré los nombres y las localizaciones de las personas que vinieron a mí con estos problemas.

column2: Go talk to them and make sure you help them with any complaints and issues they have.
column3: Ve a hablar con ellos y asegúrate de ayudarles con cualquier queja y problema que tengan.

column2: They will be able to tell you in more detail what needs to be done.
column3: Ellos podrán decirte con más detalle qué es lo que hay que hacer.

column2: &a[Glacies Princeps]&f You can find the start of the path to the trial at &aViolet's&f house.
column3: &a[Glacies Princeps]&f Puedes encontrar el inicio del camino a la prueba en la casa de &aViolet&f.

column2: Follow the &9Amethyst&f blocks, they will guide you to the peak.
column3: Sigue los bloques de &9Amatista&f, te guiarán hasta la cima.

column2: &7&oI should follow the &9&oAmethyst Blocks&7&o to the peak of the mountain and then slay the &c&oMinor Ice Elementals&7&o.
column3: &7&oDebería seguir los &9&obloques de Amatista&7&o hasta la cima de la montaña y luego matar a los &c&oElementales de Hielo Menores&7&o.

column2: &a[Glacies Princeps]&f You have done it? May their souls rest in peace now.
column3: &a[Glacies Princeps]&f ¿Lo has hecho? Que sus almas descansen en paz ahora.

column2: Let's speak again friend. There is more to be done.
column3: Hablemos de nuevo amigo. Queda más por hacer.

column2: Well you have certainly impressed me and most of the village.
column3: Bueno, sin duda me has impresionado y a la mayoría de la aldea.

column2: I owe you an explanation friend. You see for the longest time we used to draw power from the &cIce Elementals&f.
column3: I owe you an explanation friend. You see for the longest time we used to draw power from the &cIce Elementals&f.

column2: They would bless us with their power and in return any of us who would want to become a warrior or a hunter had to pass the &9Trial of Ice&f.
column3: Nos bendecían con su poder y a cambio cualquiera de nosotros que quiera convertirse en guerrero o cazador tenía que pasar la &9Prueba de Hielo.

column2: To pass the trial you had to climb the black mountain all the way to its eastern peak. And at the peak you would face the &cMinor Ice Elementals&f in combat.
column3: To pass the trial you had to climb the black mountain all the way to its eastern peak. And at the peak you would face the &cMinor Ice Elementals&f in combat.

column2: Should you succeed then your claim to become a warrior or a hunter was unquestionably your right.
column3: Si tenías éxito, entonces tu reclamo de convertirte en guerrero o cazador era incuestionablemente tu derecho.

column2: If you failed...then...your energy and your being belonged to the &cIce Elementals&f.
column3: If you failed...then...your energy and your being belonged to the &cIce Elementals&f.

column2: This is how it was for the longest time. Until the &dBlood Temples&f influence grew in power.
column3: Así fue durante el tiempo más largo. Hasta que la influencia de los &dTemplos de Sangre&f creció en poder.

column2: Ever since then the &cIce Elementals&f have been emboldened. Drawing power from them was now a risk.
column3: Ever since then the &cIce Elementals&f have been emboldened. Drawing power from them was now a risk.

column2: Several of our people got corrupted and we had to jail them for our own safety.
column3: Several of our people got corrupted and we had to jail them for our own safety.

column2: And doing the trial became impossible, what faced you at the peak was something no villager could overcome.
column3: Y hacer la prueba se volvió imposible, lo que te enfrentabas en la cima era algo que ningún aldeano podía superar.

column2: Those who have failed the trial are still there, their souls trapped in the husks of their decaying bodies.
column3: Aquellos que han fallado la prueba todavía están ahí, sus almas atrapadas en las cáscaras de sus cuerpos en descomposición.

column2: It is clear that our old traditions are no longer.
column3: Está claro que nuestras viejas tradiciones ya no existen.

column2: The &cIce Elementals&f must be dealt with...
column3: Los &cElementales de Hielo&f deben ser eliminados...

column2: I would ask you to be the last one to undertake &9The Trial of Ice&f. Climb to the peak and face the &cMinor Ice Elementals&f and release the souls of those who failed the trial.
column3: I would ask you to be the last one to undertake &9The Trial of Ice&f. Climb to the peak and face the &cMinor Ice Elementals&f and release the souls of those who failed the trial.

column2: &a[Glacies Princeps]&f You will find a path that leads into the temple at the summit of the village.
column3: &a[Glacies Princeps]&f Encontrarás un camino que lleva al templo en la cima de la aldea.

column2: &7&oI should go into the temple and slay the &c&oIce Elemental&7&o.
column3: &7&oDebería entrar en el templo y matar al &c&oIce Elemental&7&o.

column2: &a[Glacies Princeps]&f I could feel the energies flowing out, all the way from here.
column3: &a[Glacies Princeps]&f Pude sentir las energías fluyendo, desde aquí.

column2: You have done us a great favor friend. The &dIce Village&f will provide aid to you and your allies.
column3: Nos has hecho un gran favor, amigo. El &dPueblo de Hielo&f te brindará ayuda a ti y a tus aliados.

column2: There is another settlement that might need your help, let's speak.
column3: Hay otro asentamiento que podría necesitar tu ayuda, hablemos.

column2: &7&oI should hear what &a&oGlacies&7&o has to say.
column3: &7&oDebería escuchar lo que tiene que decir &a&oGlacies&7&o.

column2: It is time to free ourselves from this curse.
column3: Es hora de liberarnos de esta maldición.

column2: We should have never made ourselves dependent on an &cElementals&f power.
column3: Nunca debimos hacernos dependientes del poder de un &cElemental&f.

column2: We shall correct that mistake here and now.
column3: Corregiremos ese error aquí y ahora.

column2: What you have slain were just &cMinor Ice Elementals&f, the &cIce Elemental&f rests in a temple right across from our village.
column3: What you have slain were just &cMinor Ice Elementals&f, the &cIce Elemental&f rests in a temple right across from our village.

column2: It was the main source of our power...and foolishness.
column3: Era la principal fuente de nuestro poder... y de nuestra necedad.

column2: Go forth now and slay the &cIce Elemental&f.
column3: Ve ahora y mata al &cIce Elemental&f.

column2: &a[Chief Piscis]&fYou'll help us? Thank the seas! This was starting to feel like a sinking ship!
column3: &a[Chief Piscis]&f¿Nos ayudarás? ¡Gracias a los mares! ¡Esto empezaba a sentirse como un barco hundiéndose!

column2: &a[First Mate Iracundi]&f Fine, go help the locals, see what info you can gather and see if you can get them to help us in turn. I will be here, negotiating things.
column3: &a[Primer compañero Iracundi]&f Bien, ve a ayudar a los locales, ve qué información puedes recolectar y ve si puedes conseguir que nos ayuden a cambio. Estaré aquí, negociando cosas.

column2: Come back as soon as you have something!
&7&oI should talk to the &aVillage Leader&7&o to see about helping the locals.
column3: &7&oDebería hablar con el &aLíder de la Aldea&7&o para ver cómo ayudar a los locales.

column2: &a[Chief Piscis]&f Everyone in the village has an issue that needs dealing with, and I am no exception. My request is quite challenging, so maybe you want to get warmed up and get the lay of the land with some of the issues from the other villagers.
column3: &a[Jefe Piscis]&f Todo el mundo en la aldea tiene un problema que se necesita tratar, y no soy una excepción. Mi petición es bastante difícil, así que tal vez quieras calentarte y conocer el lugar con algunos de los problemas de los demás aldeanos.

column2: Talk to me when you are ready, and I will share with you the secrets kept by us to leaving this valley!
column3: ¡Habla conmigo cuando estés listo, y compartiré contigo los secretos guardados por nosotros para salir de este valle!

column2: &7&oI should talk to the locals and see who needs help, and come back to the leader when I feel ready to continue.
column3: &7&oDebería hablar con los locales y ver quién necesita ayuda, y volver al líder cuando me sienta preparado para continuar.

column2: So not only can they not help, but they want our help? Bah!
column3: ¿Así que no solo no pueden ayudar, sino que quieren nuestra ayuda?, ¡Bah!

column2: Well, we don't have much choice now, do we?
column3: Bueno, no tenemos muchas opciones ahora, ¿verdad?

column2: Go, help them, then make them help us!
column3: ¡Ve, ayúdales y haz que nos ayuden!
&a[Lutum Princeps]&f Esto más vale que sea importante.

column2: &a[Glacies Princeps]&f You will find &aTerravilla&f straight West of here.
column3: &a[Glacies Princeps]&f Encontrarás &aTerravilla&f directamente al Oeste de aquí.

column2: It is located on top of this ancient elemental ruin, you will know it when you see it.
column3: Se encuentra en la parte superior de esta antigua ruina elemental, lo conocerás cuando lo veas.

column2: Oh, I almost forgot. The person you want to talk to is &aOverseer Lutum&f.
column3: Oh, casi lo olvido. La persona con la que quieres hablar es &aSupervisor Lutum&f.

column2: &7&oI should go to &d&oTerravilla&7&o and talk to &a&oOverseer Lutum&7&o.
column3: &7&oDebería ir a &d&oTerravilla&7&o y hablar con &a&oSupervisor Lutum&7&o.

column2: &a[Lutum Princeps]&f Came all the way from the &dIce Village&f, eh. Good to see some help arrive.
column3: &a[Lutum Princeps]&f Viniste desde la &dAldea de Hielo&f, ¿eh? Me alegra ver que llega algo de ayuda.

column2: When I sent that request for aid I wasn't sure if we were gonna get any. I heard the situation over there wasn't that much better.
column3: Cuando envié esa solicitud de ayuda, no estaba seguro de si recibiríamos alguna. Escuché que la situación allá no era mucho mejor.

column2: We are in quite a pickle over here. We have plenty of work for you if you want it.
column3: Estamos en un buen lío por aquí. Tenemos mucho trabajo para ti si lo deseas.

column2: Some time ago we received a request for aid from a nearby settlement.
column3: Hace algún tiempo recibimos una solicitud de ayuda de un asentamiento cercano.

column2: Years ago a bunch of explorers settled on top of this ancient ruin.
column3: Hace años, un grupo de exploradores se asentó en la cima de esta antigua ruina.

column2: I think they call their little settlement &dTerravilla&f.
column3: Creo que llaman a su pequeño asentamiento &dTerravilla&f.

column2: Apparently there is a lot of treasure to be had there if you don't mind the risk of death.
column3: Apparently there is a lot of treasure to be had there if you don't mind the risk of death.

column2: But I hear that something has gone wrong there and they asked us if we could spare any help to send their way.
column3: But I hear that something has gone wrong there and they asked us if we could spare any help to send their way.

column2: To be honest, you are the strongest warrior I have ever seen.
column3: Para ser honesto, eres el guerrero más fuerte que he visto.

column2: You are the best help we could send. If you would like to, of course.
column3: Eres la mejor ayuda que podríamos enviar. Si quisieras, por supuesto.

column2: &a[Lutum Princeps]&f I am not sure where the &cRobbers&f are exactly. I just know that people have reported seeing them coming from the hills.
column3: &a[Lutum Princeps]&f No estoy seguro de dónde están exactamente los &cLadrones&f. Solo sé que la gente ha informado haberlos visto venir de las colinas.

column2: &7&oI should deal with the &c&oRobbers&7&o and help any villagers in need if I have the time.
column3: &7&oDebería encargarme de los &c&oLadrones&7&o y ayudar a los aldeanos necesitados si tengo tiempo.

column2: &a[Lutum Princeps]&f Well that is one issue resolved. Onto the next!
column3: &a[Lutum Princeps]&f Bueno, ese problema está resuelto. ¡Vamos al siguiente!

column2: Before we move on, I want you to have this blade.
column3: Antes de seguir adelante, quiero que tengas esta hoja.

column2: It might be old and dull but it's still as good as anything you can get your hands on today.
column3: Puede que sea viejo y polvo, pero sigue siendo tan bueno como cualquier cosa que puedas poner tus manos hoy.

column2: &7&oI should hear out what &a&oLutum&7&o has planned next.
column3: &7&oDebería escuchar lo que &a&oLutum&7&o ha planeado a continuación.

column2: Many years ago some explorers came across this ruin and as they investigated it more closely they discovered a large underground maze-like structure.
column3: Many years ago some explorers came across this ruin and as they investigated it more closely they discovered a large underground maze-like structure.

column2: In this structure there were a lot of ancient artifacts and treasures.
column3: En esta estructura había una gran cantidad de artefactos y tesoros antiguos.

column2: But also a lot of danger. Not like that stopped anyone from going down there.
column3: Pero también mucho peligro. Aunque eso no impidió que nadie bajara allí.

column2: And as the word spread, more and more people came here to make their fortunes.
column3: Y a medida que la noticia se extendió, más y más gente vino aquí para hacer fortuna.

column2: Before you know it, it turned into a small settlement.
column3: Antes de que te dieras cuenta, se convirtió en un pequeño asentamiento.

column2: Until lately everything was fine, but then awful things started happening.
column3: Hasta hace poco todo estaba bien, pero luego empezaron a ocurrir cosas terribles.

column2: Before I tell you more, we should start by dealing with the lesser issues first.
column3: Antes de contarte más, deberíamos empezar por resolver los problemas menores primero.

column2: A small band of &cRobbers&f has found a foothold in the hills surrounding &dTerravilla&f.
column3: A small band of &cRobbers&f has found a foothold in the hills surrounding &dTerravilla&f.

column2: We need them gone. Also, feel free to assist any villagers in &aTerravilla&f that might need help.
column3: We need them gone. Also, feel free to assist any villagers in &aTerravilla&f that might need help.

column2: &a[Lutum Princeps]&f The pub is at the ground level, right across. Don't let them overwhelm you.
column3: &a[Lutum Princeps]&f La taberna está en la planta baja, justo enfrente. No dejes que te abrumen.

column2: I will have a nice reward waiting here for you when you're back.
column3: Tendré una buena recompensa esperándote aquí cuando regreses.

column2: &7&oI need to go to the pub and deal with the &c&oBar Brawlers&7&o.
column3: &7&oNecesito ir a la taberna y encargarme de los &c&oPeleadores de Bar&7&o.

column2: &a[Lutum Princeps]&f I hear that the pub is a peaceful place again. Let's discuss the real issue now.
column3: &a[Lutum Princeps]&f Oigo que la taberna vuelve a ser un lugar tranquilo. Hablemos ahora del verdadero problema.

column2: Before we get to the big problem underground, I would like you to do one last thing here in town.
column3: Before we get to the big problem underground, I would like you to do one last thing here in town.

column2: There has been huge trouble in our little pub.
column3: Ha habido un gran problema en nuestra pequeña taberna.

column2: There are certain characters in town who keep going to the pub and causing a ruckus.
column3: Hay ciertos personajes en el pueblo que siguen yendo a la taberna y causando alboroto.

column2: Well I heard that this time all of them managed to gather at the pub at the same time.
column3: Well I heard that this time all of them managed to gather at the pub at the same time.

column2: And of course now there is a huge brawl happening over there.
column3: Y, por supuesto, ahora hay una gran pelea ocurriendo allí.

column2: This is a great opportunity for us to arrest all of them at once.
column3: Esta es una gran oportunidad para arrestarlos a todos a la vez.

column2: Go to the pub and knock them all out. We will handle the rest.
column3: Ve a la taberna y noquéalos a todos. Nosotros nos encargaremos del resto.

column2: &a[Lutum Princeps]&f You can get to the maze by walking down the spiral staircase in the middle of the ruins.
column3: &a[Lutum Princeps]&f Puedes llegar al laberinto bajando por la escalera de caracol en medio de las ruinas.

column2: Don't get lost in the maze, also make sure to watch out for the constructs. Good luck!
column3: No te pierdas en el laberinto, también asegúrate de estar atento a las construcciones. ¡Buena suerte!

column2: &7&oI should enter the &d&oRuins Maze&7&o and slay the &c&oEarth Elemental&7&o.
column3: &7&oDebería entrar en el &d&oLaberinto de las Ruinas&7&o y matar al &c&oElemental de Tierra&7&o.

column2: &a[Lutum Princeps]&f I cannot believe it, you're back. In one piece too!
column3: &a[Lutum Princeps]&f No puedo creerlo, has vuelto. ¡Y de una pieza!

column2: I guess you are tougher than you look. What you have done here is incredible it is clear we are in great debt to you. Is there anything Terravilla might be able to do for you.
column3: Supongo que eres más duro de lo que pareces. Lo que has hecho aquí es increíble, está claro que estamos en gran deuda con usted. ¿Hay algo que Terravilla pueda hacer por ti?

column2: &7&oI need to tell &a&oLutum&7&o about my quest and the &d&oBlood Temple&7&o.
column3: &7&oNecesito contarle a &a&oLutum&7&o sobre mi misión y el &d&oTemplo de Sangre&7&o.

column2: You see the real reason we asked for help is because of what happened at the ruins.
column3: You see the real reason we asked for help is because of what happened at the ruins.

column2: There were always dangerous things down there, but nothing a seasoned adventurer or explorer could not handle.
column3: There were always dangerous things down there, but nothing a seasoned adventurer or explorer could not handle.

column2: But then something awakened, these ancient constructs started rising out of the ground and the walls.
column3: But then something awakened, these ancient constructs started rising out of the ground and the walls.

column2: Then these quakes started happening, it was weird, because you could only feel them if you were down in the ruins.
column3: Then these quakes started happening, it was weird, because you could only feel them if you were down in the ruins.

column2: So we shut everything down, nobody was allowed access to the ruins anymore.
column3: Así que cerramos todo, a nadie se le permitió el acceso a las ruinas nunca más.

column2: A few days ago I gathered some of my best men and sent them down there to find the source of it all.
column3: A few days ago I gathered some of my best men and sent them down there to find the source of it all.

column2: They barely made it back. They found an &cEarth Elemental&f high above the pillars, on top some sort of platform.
column3: They barely made it back. They found an &cEarth Elemental&f high above the pillars, on top some sort of platform.

column2: It must have been there for ages, dormant.
column3: Debe haber estado allí durante siglos, inactivo.

column2: No clue why it decided to wake up now...
column3: Ni idea de por qué decidió despertar ahora...

column2: Your job would be to go down there, navigate through the maze and put the &cEarth Elemental&f into a slumber it will never wake up from!
column3: Your job would be to go down there, navigate through the maze and put the &cEarth Elemental&f into a slumber it will never wake up from!

column2: &a[Navita]&f You have returned! I hope you have good tidings.
column3: &a[Navita]&f ¡Has regresado! Espero que traigas buenas noticias.

column2: &a[Lutum Princeps]&f So you are heading off to &dPontis Mille&f, make sure to tell the &aShogun&f that &dTerravilla&f will be ready to assist.
column3: &a[Lutum Princeps]&f Así que te diriges a &dPontis Mille&f, asegúrate de decirle al &aShogun&f que &dTerravilla&f estará lista para ayudar.

column2: &7&oI should head to &d&oPontis Mille&7&o and speak with &a&oShogun Navita&7&o.
column3: &7&oDebería dirigirme a &d&oPontis Mille&7&o y hablar con el &a&oShogun Navita&7&o.

column2: &a[Navita]&f It is good to hear that the &dIce Village&f has decided to join our cause! But I did not expect that you would manage to convince &dTerravilla&f to pledge to our cause as well.
column3: &a[Navita]&f ¡Es bueno oír que la &dAldea de Hielo&f ha decidido unirse a nuestra causa! Pero no esperaba que lograras convencer a &dTerravilla&f para que también se comprometiera con nuestra causa.

column2: We had no idea what was going on... Yes, &dTerravilla&f will be able to pledge some of our forces to your cause.
column3: We had no idea what was going on... Yes, &dTerravilla&f will be able to pledge some of our forces to your cause.

column2: I wonder if the &cEarth Elemental&f awakening had anything to do with the &dBlood Temple&f.
column3: I wonder if the &cEarth Elemental&f awakening had anything to do with the &dBlood Temple&f.

column2: We will prepare our forces and wait for word from &dPontis Mille&f.
column3: Prepararemos nuestras fuerzas y esperaremos noticias de &dPontis Mille&f.
&a[Oficial del Puesto Avanzado]&f Te estaba esperando.

column2: &a[Navita]&f The outpost is to the South of the city. Not too long now before the additional forces from &dTerravilla&f and the &dIce Village&f arrive.
column3: &a[Navita]&f El puesto avanzado está al sur de la ciudad. No falta mucho para que lleguen las fuerzas adicionales de &dTerravilla&f y la &dAldea de Hielo&f.

column2: &7&oI should head to the &d&oOutpost&7&o and speak with the &a&oOutpost Officer&7&o.
column3: &7&oDebería dirigirme al &d&oPuesto Avanzado&7&o y hablar con el &a&oOficial del Puesto Avanzado&7&o.

column2: &a[Outpost Officer]&f We are almost ready for the assault! Let us talk once you have time.
column3: &a[Oficial del Puesto Avanzado]&f ¡Ya casi estamos listos para el asalto! Hablemos cuando tengas tiempo.

column2: It is so good to see you again friend!
While you were gone we were preparing our forces.
column3: Mientras no estabas, estábamos preparando nuestras fuerzas.

column2: We have made an &dOutpost&f between the &dBlood Temple&f and &dPontis Mille&f.
column3: We have made an &dOutpost&f between the &dBlood Temple&f and &dPontis Mille&f.

column2: You should go there and report to the &aOutpost Officer&f.
column3: Deberías ir allí e informar al &aOficial del Puesto Avanzado&f.

column2: They will let you know how we should proceed with the assault on the &dBlood Temple&f.
column3: Ellos te informarán sobre cómo debemos proceder con el asalto al &dTemplo de Sangre&f.

column2: &a[Officer]&f I hope you are ready for the final assault.
column3: &a[Oficial]&f Espero que estés listo para el asalto final.

column2: &a[Outpost Officer]&f Well this is it. I will see you again at the entrance. Give them no quarter!
column3: &a[Oficial del Puesto Avanzado]&f Bueno, esto es todo. Te veré de nuevo en la entrada. ¡No les des cuartel!

column2: &7&oI should fight my way to the &d&oBlood Temple&7&o entrance and speak with the &a&oOfficer&7&o.
column3: &7&oDebería abrirme paso hasta la entrada del &d&oTemplo de Sangre&7&o y hablar con el &a&oOficial&7&o.

column2: &a[Officer]&f Our scouts have come back with useful information.
column3: &a[Officer]&f Nuestros exploradores han regresado con información útil.

column2: Our allies from &dTerravilla&f and the &dIce Village&f have arrived.
column3: Nuestros aliados de &dTerravilla&f y la &dAldea de Hielo&f han llegado.

column2: We are ready to assault the &dBlood Temple&f.
column3: Estamos listos para asaltar el &dTemplo de Sangre&f.

column2: Our goal is to reach the entrance and secure it.
column3: Nuestro objetivo es alcanzar la entrada y asegurarla.

column2: Once that is done we can focus on the final assault.
column3: Una vez hecho eso, podemos concentrarnos en el asalto final.

column2: &a[Officer]&f After you have dealt with them, another one of our officers will wait for you at the other side of the barriers.
column3: &a[Oficial]&f Después de que te hayas encargado de ellos, otro de nuestros oficiales te esperará al otro lado de las barreras.

column2: &a[Officer]&f Our scouts have come back with useful information.
column3: &a[Officer]&f Nuestros exploradores han regresado con información útil.

column2: We have figured out that the way to the core of the temple is blocked by &9four barriers&f.
column3: We have figured out that the way to the core of the temple is blocked by &9four barriers&f.

column2: The &9barriers&f seem to be magically held in place by &cFour Guardians&f.
column3: The &9barriers&f seem to be magically held in place by &cFour Guardians&f.

column2: Our scouts report that the &cFour Guardians&f are. A &cGiant&f at the bottom of the temple. An &cAlchemist&f at the southern side of the temple. A &cCultist&f mage at the northern side of the temple. And finally some sort of &cObserver&f construct at the north-eastern side of the temple.
column3: Our scouts report that the &cFour Guardians&f are. A &cGiant&f at the bottom of the temple. An &cAlchemist&f at the southern side of the temple. A &cCultist&f mage at the northern side of the temple. And finally some sort of &cObserver&f construct at the north-eastern side of the temple.

column2: &a[Officer]&f Oh, I almost forgot, I have a message to you from &aMajor Fortes&f. "Go knock them dead!"
column3: &a[Oficial]&f Oh, casi lo olvido, tengo un mensaje para ti de parte del &aMayor Fortes&f. "¡Ve y mátalos a todos!"

column2: &7&oI need to go slay the &c&oFire Elemental&7&o.
column3: &7&oNecesito ir a matar al &c&oElemental de Fuego&7&o.

column2: &a[Officer]&f Is it done? That was quite the epic battle! I have never seen anyone fight like that.
column3: &a[Oficial]&f ¿Está hecho? ¡Esa fue una batalla épica! Nunca he visto a nadie luchar así.

column2: &a[Officer]&f We will escort you back to safety. It is time for celebration!
column3: &a[Oficial]&f Te escoltaremos de vuelta a un lugar seguro. ¡Es hora de celebrar!

column2: &7&oSeems like the &a&oOfficer&7&o has more to say.
column3: &7&oParece que el &a&oOficial&7&o tiene más que decir.

column2: It is hard to believe we made it to this point.
column3: Es difícil creer que llegamos a este punto.

column2: And I don't think it would have been possible without your help.
column3: Y no creo que hubiera sido posible sin tu ayuda.

column2: Without a doubt the best strategy here is for you to go join the rest of our troops in fighting the &cFire Elemental&f.
column3: Without a doubt the best strategy here is for you to go join the rest of our troops in fighting the &cFire Elemental&f.

column2: It doesn't sound like they are winning, please hurry!
column3: No parece que estén ganando, ¡por favor, date prisa!

column2: Fortes'&f forces will be making sure to intercept any reinforcements they try to send your way.
column3: Fortes'&f forces will be making sure to intercept any reinforcements they try to send your way.

column2: &a[Navita]&f Welcome, slayer of evils, protector of Primis!
column3: &a[Navita]&f ¡Bienvenido, asesino de males, protector de Primis!

column2: &a[Officer]&f Enough chatter. Let’s ensure you return safely to &aNavita&f.
column3: &a[Oficial]&f Basta de charla. Asegurémonos de que regreses sano y salvo a &aNavita&f.

column2: &7&oI need to make my way back to &d&oPontis Mille&f&o and talk to &a&oNavita&f&o.
column3: &7&oNecesito regresar a &d&oPontis Mille&f&o y hablar con &a&oNavita&f&o.

column2: &a[Navita]&fYou have returned victorious. Your deeds will be sung for generations to come.
column3: &a[Navita]&fHas regresado victorioso. Tus hazañas serán cantadas por generaciones.

column2: You have done the impossible, hero. The fire elemental’s rage has been quenched, and the blood elemental’s vile presence has been destroyed.
column3: You have done the impossible, hero. The fire elemental’s rage has been quenched, and the blood elemental’s vile presence has been destroyed.

column2: Your bravery and skill have saved countless lives.
column3: Tu valentía y habilidad han salvado incontables vidas.

column2: We will escort you back to &dPontis Mille&f. The ruler, &aNavita&f, awaits your return and has decreed a celebration in your honor.
column3: We will escort you back to &dPontis Mille&f. The ruler, &aNavita&f, awaits your return and has decreed a celebration in your honor.

column2: &a[Chief Piscis]&f The &dBandit Camp&f isn't too far away if you follow the road!
column3: &a[Jefe Piscis]&f ¡El &dCampamento de Bandidos&f no está demasiado lejos si sigues la carretera!

column2: Be careful on your way there, we don't know what they are up to but it can't be anything good!
column3: ¡Ten cuidado en tu camino hacia ahí, no sabemos lo que están haciendo, pero no puede ser nada bueno!

column2: Oh, and make sure you bring back my &eGrandfather's Heirloom&f!
column3: ¡Oh, y asegúrate de traer de vuelta la &eReliquia de mi Abuelo&f!

column2: &7&oI should go to the nearby &dBandit Camp&7&o and clear it out.
column3: &7&oDebería ir al &dCampamento de Bandidos&7&o cercano y despejarlo.

column2: &a[Chief Piscis]&f I see you're back! Do you bring good news?
column3: &a[Jefe Piscis]&f ¡Veo que estás de vuelta! ¿Traes buenas noticias?

column2: &7&oYou tell &aChief Piscis&7&o about the camp and turn the &eHeirloom&7&o in.
column3: &7&oTu cuenta al &aJefe Piscis&7&o sobre el campamento y devuelve la &eReliquia&7&o.

column2: What's this? Mages? Elementals? This is an ill omen. You must talk to the &aRuler of Gladius&f to report this incident at once!
column3: ¿Qué es esto? ¿Magos? ¿Elementales? ¡Esto es un mal augurio!. ¡Debes hablar con el &aGobernante de Gladius&f para informar de este incidente enseguida!

column2: Truly you have served us well! Here, for your efforts, I give you my &eGrandfather's Sword&f! May it serve you as well as it has served our family!
column3: ¡Realmente nos ha servido bien! ¡Ten, por tus esfuerzos, te doy la &eEspada de mi Abuelo&f! ¡Que te sirva tan bien como ha servido a nuestra familia!

column2: &7&oSeems like the &aChief Piscis&f is ready to tell me how to get out of here.
column3: &7&oParece que el &aJefe Piscis&f está listo para decirme como salir de aquí.

column2: A nearby &dBandit Camp&f has recently been sighted and is trying to take us under!
column3: A nearby &dBandit Camp&f has recently been sighted and is trying to take us under!

column2: They keep raiding our supplies and kidnapping our villagers!
column3: ¡Siguen asaltando nuestros suministros y secuestrando a nuestros aldeanos!
¡Incluso se llevaron la &eReliquia de mi Abuelo&f!

column2: We don't know what they want, but we need them gone!
column3: No sabemos qué quieren, ¡pero necesitamos que se vayan!

column2: Figure out what they are doing, deal with them and bring me back my &eGrandfather's Heirloom&f!
column3: Figure out what they are doing, deal with them and bring me back my &eGrandfather's Heirloom&f!

column2: &a[Captain Squalus]&f There you are! By the seas, I thought you were eaten by a were-badger!
column3: &a[Capitán Squalus]&f ¡Ahí estás! ¡Por los mares, pensé que te había comido un tejón-lobo!

column2: &7&oWell that was a celebration I will not forget any time soon.
column3: &7&oBueno, esa fue una celebración que no olvidaré pronto.

column2: &7&oBut it is time to say goodbye to &d&oPontis Mille&7&o and slowly make my way to our &d&oShip&7&o.
column3: &7&oPero es hora de decir adiós a &d&oPontis Mille&7&o y dirigirme lentamente a nuestro &d&oBarco&7&o.

column2: &a[Captain Squalus]&fThe ship’s as good as new, thanks to the folks from Pontis Mille. Their handiwork is impressive, and the crew’s been itching to set sail again.
column3: &a[Capitán Squalus]&fEl barco está como nuevo, gracias a la gente de Pontis Mille. Su trabajo es impresionante, y la tripulación está ansiosa por zarpar de nuevo.

column2: &a[Captain Squalus]&fThey also left a small gift for you. Here take it.
column3: &a[Capitán Squalus]&fTambién te dejaron un pequeño regalo. Aquí, tómalo.

column2: &a[Captain Squalus]&fThe sea’s calling, and with you back, we’re ready to answer. What say ye?
column3: &a[Capitán Squalus]&fEl mar llama, y contigo de vuelta, estamos listos para responder. ¿Qué dices?

column2: &7&oPrimis is safe, its dangers defeated, but the journey isn’t over. There are still new adventures to explore, mysteries to uncover, and challenges to face. Onwards!
column3: &7&oPrimis está a salvo, sus peligros derrotados, pero el viaje no ha terminado. Todavía hay nuevas aventuras que explorar, misterios que descubrir y desafíos que enfrentar. ¡Adelante!

column2: Tonight, we celebrate! But come, sit by my side. Tell me of your trials and triumphs. There is much to discuss.
column3: Tonight, we celebrate! But come, sit by my side. Tell me of your trials and triumphs. There is much to discuss.

column2: People of &dPontis Mille&f, we owe our lives and our peace to this hero! Let us rejoice in their honor and pledge our gratitude forever.
column3: People of &dPontis Mille&f, we owe our lives and our peace to this hero! Let us rejoice in their honor and pledge our gratitude forever.

column2: Hero, your deeds today have ensured the safety of our city, but I have news that may concern you. While you were battling the great evils, I dispatched a small troupe to the location of your beached &dShip&f. We carried supplies, tools, and goods to your crew and oversaw the ship’s repair.
column3: Hero, your deeds today have ensured the safety of our city, but I have news that may concern you. While you were battling the great evils, I dispatched a small troupe to the location of your beached &dShip&f. We carried supplies, tools, and goods to your crew and oversaw the ship’s repair.

column2: Your captain and crew have worked tirelessly, and I am pleased to inform you that your ship is seaworthy once more. It waits for you, ready to embark on its next voyage. This, too, is a gift of gratitude from &aPontis Mille&f.
column3: Your captain and crew have worked tirelessly, and I am pleased to inform you that your ship is seaworthy once more. It waits for you, ready to embark on its next voyage. This, too, is a gift of gratitude from &aPontis Mille&f.

column2: Enough talk for now! Let us quench our thirst with drink, satisfy our hunger with a feast, and delight our ears with the sweetness of music!
column3: Enough talk for now! Let us quench our thirst with drink, satisfy our hunger with a feast, and delight our ears with the sweetness of music!

column2: &a[Petrae]&f &2Chief Piscis&f sent you? Unfortunately the passage is closed, and the &cElemental&f guards it...
column3: &a[Petrae]&f ¿El &2Jefe Piscis&f te envió? Desafortunadamente, el pasaje está cerrado y el &cElemental&f lo protege...

column2: &a[Chief Piscis]&f The mountain pass is guarded by an extremely dangerous &cGolem&f, which you are probably not able to defeat right now!
column3: &a[Jefe Piscis]&f ¡El paso de la montaña está protegido por un &cGolem&f extremadamente peligroso, que probablemente no podrás derrotar ahora mismo!

column2: We know of a secret passage in the mountains. Follow the path of &9Blue Flowers &fand talk to the &aMountain Guide&f to get safe passage to Bridgeport!
column3: Conocemos un paso secreto en las montañas. ¡Sigue el camino de &9Flores Azules &fy habla con el &aGuía de Montaña&f para conseguir un pasaje seguro a Bridgeport!

column2: &7&oI should follow the &9&oBlue Flower &7&opath to the &aMountain Guide&7&o!
column3: &7&o¡Debería seguir el camino de &9&oFlores Azules &7&ohasta el &aGuía de Montaña&7&o!

column2: &7&oI should make sure to finish any business I got left before I leave.
column3: &7&oDebería asegurarme de terminar cualquier negocio que me quede antes de irme.

column2: &7&oHint: Make sure you track the quest to make finding your destination easier!
column3: &7&oConsejo: ¡Asegúrate de rastrear la misión para facilitar la búsqueda de tu destino!

column2: &a[Petrae]&f Are you sure you want to risk it? I can help you...
column3: &a[Petrae]&f ¿Estás seguro de que quieres arriesgarlo? Puedo ayudarte...

column2: &7&oSeems like &aPetrae&f has a request for me.
column3: &7&oParece que &aPetrae&f tiene una solicitud para mí.

column2: We must report our findings about the &dBandit Camp&f to &dGladius&f!
column3: ¡Debemos informar nuestros hallazgos sobre el &dCampamento Bandido&f a &dGladius&f!

column2: The mountain pass is guarded by an ancient, powerful &cGolem&f which must be avoided at all costs!
column3: The mountain pass is guarded by an ancient, powerful &cGolem&f which must be avoided at all costs!

column2: Follow the &9Blue Flowers&f along the path, they will lead you to a secret passage through the mountains!
column3: Follow the &9Blue Flowers&f along the path, they will lead you to a secret passage through the mountains!

column2: A mountain guide will be waiting for you at the end of the &9Blue Flower &fpath!
column3: ¡Un guía de montaña te estará esperando al final del camino de &9Flores Azules&f!

column2: &a[Petrae]&f You seek to defeat the &cCrystal Elemental&f? I can but wish you luck in your endeavor!
column3: &a[Petrae]&f ¿Buscas derrotar al &cElemental de Cristal&f? ¡Solamente te puedo desear suerte en tu esfuerzo!

column2: If you are successful in your attempt, meet my brother on the other side of the passage!
column3: If you are successful in your attempt, meet my brother on the other side of the passage!

column2: &7&oSeems like I must defeat the &cCrystal Elemental&7&o.
column3: &7&oParece que debo derrotar al &cElemental de Cristal&7&o.

column2: &a[Eartep]&f Wow! Who are you? I saw you defeat the &cCrystal Elemental&f, clearly there's greatness in your future!
column3: &a[Eartep]&f ¡Wow! ¿Quién eres? ¡Te vi derrotar al &cElemental de Cristal&f, claramente hay grandeza en tu futuro!

column2: My brother sent you? Let me tell you the path to &dGladius&f!
column3: ¿Te envió mi hermano? ¡Déjame decirte el camino a &dGladius&f!

column2: You need to pass through? Ill timing, my friend.

column3: Un &cElemental de Cristal &fha invadido nuestro paso

column2: If you really must make your way to Gladius,
column3: ¡Si realmente tienes que llegar a Gladius,

column2: you will have to defeat this &cElemental&f first!
column3: tendrás que derrotar a este &cElemental&f primero!

column2: &a[Filius] &fYou made it through the mountain! You don't see that every day.
column3: &a[Filius]&f ¡Lo lograste a través de la montaña! Eso no se ve todos los días.

column2: I'm afraid my father is missing, but I can tell you about the path to &dGladius&f. If you want to help us though, talk to my &aMother&f!
column3: Me temo que mi padre no está, pero puedo informarte sobre el camino a &dGladius&f. ¡Si quieres ayudarnos, sin embargo, habla con mi &aMadre&f!

column2: &7&oSeem like &aFilius&7&o can help me find the way to &dGladius&7&o.
column3: &7&oParece que &aFilius&7&o puede ayudarme a encontrar el camino a &dGladius&7&o.

column2: &a[Eartep]&f Just tell the &aProprietor of the Farmstead&f that I sent you, though I have heard that the &aProprietor&f hasn't been seen in a while.
