column2: &a[Posuere Hominem]&f You can find the start of the course at the &dEnd of that Tunnel&f.
column3: &a[Posuere Hominem]&f Puedes encontrar el inicio del recorrido en &dEl final del túnel&f.

column2: Just swim up to the first vine and keep climbing the vine until you reach the top.
column3: Just swim up to the first vine and keep climbing the vine until you reach the top.

column2: Don't forget to speak to my &aBrother&f at the end of the course for the reward!
column3: ¡No olvides hablar con mi &aHermano&f al final del recorrido para obtener la recompensa!

column2: &7&oI should head to the start of the course.
column3: &7&oI debe dirigirse al inicio del recorrido.

column2: &a[Idoneitatem Hominem]&f Well deserved! I hope you did not cheat! Try and beat my record if you can.
column3: &a[Idoneitatem Hominem]&f ¡Bien hecho! ¡Espero que no hayas hecho trampa! Intenta batir mi récord si puedes.

column2: So you think you have you what it takes.
column3: Así que crees que tienes lo que necesita.

column2: Are you fit enough, are you quick enough, are you strong enough?
column3: ¿Estás en forma suficiente, eres lo suficientemente rápido, ¿eres lo suficientemente fuerte?

column2: Platforms, vines, dangerous heights. All you could ever want!
column3: Plataformas, lianas, alturas peligrosas. ¡Todo lo que podrías desear!

column2: The ultimate challenge lies ahead! OK, OK.
column3: ¡El desafío definitivo te espera! OK, OK.

column2: Me and my &aBrother&f might have been bored a bit and made an entire acrobatics course.
column3: Me and my &aBrother&f might have been bored a bit and made an entire acrobatics course.

column2: The goal is to to get from platform to platform using &9Vines&f and &9Acrobatics&f and reach the end of the course.
column3: The goal is to to get from platform to platform using &9Vines&f and &9Acrobatics&f and reach the end of the course.

column2: Should you get through the course and reach the end. (Which is a sphere by the way.)
column3: Se debe completar el recorrido y llegar al final. (Que por cierto es una esfera).

column2: You will be rewarded with a very nice &eItem&f!
I heard there is great\ntreasure to be had!
column3: ¡He oído que hay un gran tesoro\nque se puede tener!

column2: Something wonderful awaits\nyou if you enter!
&a[King Nemian]&f If there is a &dNest&f I am sure it would be &9Surrounded by Cobwebs&f.
column3: &a[Rey Nemian]&f Si hay un &dNido&f, estoy seguro de que estaría &9Rodeado de Telarañas&f.

column2: &7&oI should find the &dSpiders Nest&7&o and clear it out.
column3: &7&oDebo encontrar el &dNido de Arañas&7&o y despejarlo.

column2: &a[King Nemian]&f Hah! I knew we could count on you!
Here are your fine boots, well deserved!
column3: ¡Aquí tienes tus buenas botas, bien merecidas!

column2: So they have a &dNest&f somewhere in the &dGrove&f.
column3: Así que tienen un &dNido&f en algún lugar del &dBosquecillo&f.

column2: That would explain why their population has skyrocketed.
column3: Eso explicaría por qué su población se ha disparado.

column2: We were used to some &cSpiders&f wandering into the &dGrove&f, but this is too much.
column3: Estábamos acostumbrados a que algunas &cArañas&f se pasearan por la &dCueva&f, pero esto es demasiado.

column2: It would be great if you could locate the &dNest&f and clear it out.
column3: Sería genial si pudieras localizar el &dNido&f y despejarlo.

column2: We will make you some fine &eSpider Leg Boots&f as a reward!
column3: ¡Te haremos unas buenas &eBotas de Pata de Araña&f como recompensa!

column2: &a[Luxuria Gorgonius]&f The &eHeirloom&f is quite valuable I am sure they would keep it &9Somewhere Extra Safe&f.
column3: &a[Luxuria Gorgonius]&f La &eReliquia Familiar&f es bastante valiosa. Estoy seguro de que la guardarían en &9algún lugar extra seguro&f.

column2: &a[Luxuria Gorgonius]&f Oh my gosh! You found it!
There are not enough thanks in the world for what you just did for me.
column3: No hay suficientes agradecimientos en el mundo por lo que acabas de hacer por mí.

column2: &7&oThis stew should keep med fed for a while.
column3: &7&oEste guiso me debería mantener alimentado durante un tiempo.

column2: Disaster has struck our little hole.
column3: El desastre ha golpeado nuestro pequeño agujero.

column2: Not too long ago our lovely home got raided by &cElf Bandits&f.
column3: No hace mucho tiempo que nuestra hermosa casa fue atacada por &cElfos Bandidos&f.

column2: Thankfully we weren't home at the time so nobody got hurt.
column3: Afortunadamente no estábamos en casa en ese momento así que nadie salió lastimado.

column2: We managed to replace most of our possessions.
column3: Hemos conseguido reemplazar la mayoría de nuestras posesiones.

column2: But they took my &eFamily Heirloom&f that was sitting on the shelf.
column3: Pero se llevaron mi &eReliquia Familiar&f que estaba en el estante.

column2: If you would be so kind to go try and get it back for me, I would be most thankful.
column3: Si fueras tan amable de tratar de recuperarlo, estaría muy agradecido.

column2: I make the best stews, I would be glad to share some with you as a reward.
column3: Hago los mejores guisos, estaría encantado de compartir algunos con ustedes como recompensa.

column2: My brother will come rescue me.
I assure you I will be just fine.
column3: Te aseguro que estaré muy bien.

column2: Ugh, there must be something to do.
column3: Ugh, tiene que haber algo que hacer.

column2: Maybe I should brew more drinks.
column3: Tal vez debería preparar más bebidas.

column2: My husband makes the best cakes.
column3: Mi marido hace los mejores pasteles.

column2: Have to make sure the light keeps them away.
column3: Tengo que asegurarme de que la luz los mantiene lejos.
¡No dejes que las arañas te muerdan!

column2: Oh, did not expect to see anyone here.
column3: Oh, no esperaba encontrar a alguien aquí.

column2: Just gotta be quick and they can't get ya.
column3: Solo tienes que ser rápido y no podrán alcanzarte.

column2: This is my favorite resting spot.
column3: Este es mi lugar favorito de descanso.

column2: Thought you could\nsteal from me elves...
column3: Pensé que podrías\nrobar de mis elfos...

column2: Gonna get back my\npossessions when\nthey go sleep.
column3: Voy a recuperar mis\nposesiones cuando\nse vayan a dormir.

column2: It's gonna be a good\nday I can feel it.
column3: Será un buen\ndía que pueda sentirlo.

column2: Not sure how the king\nexpects me to do\nall of this...
column3: No está seguro de cómo el rey\nespera que haga\ntodo esto...
Este papeleo\nno se hará a sí mismo.

column2: If you need anything\nspeak to the king.
column3: Si necesitas algo\nhabla con el rey.
No hay tiempo para charlar,\nmis disculpas.

column2: I am actually fishing for bugs.
Large aqua-bugs fall from the trees.
column3: Grandes insectos de agua caen de los árboles.

column2: I use tree sap as bait.
column3: Utilizo savia de árbol como cebo.

column2: The aqua-bugs cannot resist the bait!
column3: ¡Los insectos de agua no pueden resistir el cebo!

column2: Gotta catch'em before they head for the trees.
column3: Hay que capturarlos antes de que se dirijan a los árboles.

column2: They are quite tasty if you roast them.
column3: Son muy sabrosos si los asas.

column2: I could stand here for days.
Hope you like my little farm.
column3: Espero que te guste mi pequeña granja.

column2: So many wines to attend to.
column3: Tantos vinos a los que atender.

column2: Did you check out the berry farm?
column3: ¿Has echado un vistazo a la granja de bayas?

column2: Can't be inside all the time.
column3: No puede estar adentro de todo el tiempo.

column2: What brings you into our lovely hole?
column3: ¿Qué te trae a nuestro agujero encantador?

column2: Feel free to stay a while.
column3: Siéntete libre de quedarte un rato.

column2: What? Yes, I'm doing just fine.
I did not have too many, nope.
I am so cozy right now.
column3: Estoy tan acogido en este momento.

column2: We used to go outside more often.
Too many dangers outside these days.
column3: Demasiados peligros afuera en estos días.

column2: Welcome to the best hole in the grove!
column3: ¡Bienvenido al mejor agujero de la arboleda!

column2: Built this hole with my own hands!
column3: ¡Construí este agujero con mis propias manos!

column2: Life is all about taking it easy.
column3: La vida se trata de tomarlo con facilidad.

column2: Too many elves in our grove.
&a[Phygia Gorgonius]&f Time to kick those &cElves&f out for good!
column3: &a[Phygia Gorgonius]&f ¡Hora de echar a esos &cElfos&f para siempre!

column2: &a[King Nemian]&f The hole right next to this one one, can't  miss it!
column3: &a[Rey Nemian]&f ¡El agujero justo al lado de este, no puedes perderlo!

column2: If you are available there is plenty more work to do around here.
column3: Si estás disponible, hay mucho más trabajo que hacer por aquí.

column2: but I have assigned &aPhygia&f to handle those issues.
column3: pero he asignado a &aPhygia&f para manejar esos problemas.

column2: Go talk to &aPhygia Gorgonius&f in the hole next to this one.
column3: Ve a hablar con &aPhygia Gorgonius&f en el agujero al lado de este.

column2: They will be able to tell you more and what needs to be done.
column3: Ellos podrán decirte más y lo que hay que hacer.

column2: &a[King Nemian]&f When you exit the hole the &dLighthouse&f is straight forward and a bit to the left.
column3: &a[Rey Nemian]&f Cuando salgas del agujero el &dFaro&f es directo y un poco a la izquierda.

column2: &a[Alanus Secundas]&f I am so thankful! We were just starting to run out of food.
column3: &a[Alanus Secundas]&f ¡Estoy muy agradecido! Estábamos empezando a quedarnos sin comida.

column2: &7&oSeems like &aAlanus&7&o wants to talk to me.
Wanderer, could I ask a simple favor of you?
column3: Viajero, ¿te podría pedir un favor simple?

column2: There is a nearby &dLighthouse&f. We usually deliver food to the family that lives there.
column3: Hay un &dFaro&f cercano. Solemos entregar comida a la familia que vive ahí.

column2: But ever since the troubles began we could not leave our &dGrove&f.
column3: Pero desde que comenzaron los problemas, no pudimos abandonar nuestra &dArboleda&f.

column2: Would you be so kind to bring the family their latest batch of food.
column3: ¿Serías tan amable de traer a la familia su último lote de comida?

column2: It would be great if you could hurry, it has been a while since the last delivery.
column3: Sería genial si pudieras apresurarte, ha pasado un tiempo desde la última entrega.

column2: &8[Jeeves]&f They do not need the food anymore? I was just about to go shopping.
column3: &8[Jeeves]&f ¿Ya no necesitan la comida? Justo estaba a punto de ir de compras.

column2: &8[Jeeves]&f So kind of you to come here and let me know.
column3: &8[Jeeves]&f Qué amable de tu parte venir aquí y hacérmelo saber.

column2: &8[Alanus Secundas]&f When you exit the dwelling the Lighthouse is straight forward and a bit to the left.
column3: &8[Alanus Secundas]&f Cuando salgas de la vivienda el &dFaro&f es directo y un poco a la izquierda.

column2: &8[Alanus]&f You let him know? Good, good!
Uh, before you came. Jeeves the Traveling Merchant stopped by.
column3: Uh, antes de que vinieras. Jeeves el Mercader Ambulante se pasó por aquí.

column2: We asked him if he could go get some food for us.
column3: Le preguntamos si podía ir a buscar algo de comida para nosotros.

column2: Well, that is not necessary anymore so it would be great if you could climb to the top of the lighthouse and travel to Caeruleaum Village and tell Jeeves we do not need the food anymore.
column3: Well, that is not necessary anymore so it would be great if you could climb to the top of the lighthouse and travel to Caeruleaum Village and tell Jeeves we do not need the food anymore.

column2: Gotta make sure the\nlighthouse is working.
column3: Tengo que asegurarme de que\nel faro esté funcionando.
Me alegro de ver a alguien\nvenir a visitar.

column2: My turn to watch\nover the light.
column3: Mi turno para vigilar\nsobre la luz.

column2: Well, I am feeling a bit better.
column3: Bueno, me siento un poco mejor.

column2: You think you got what it takes?
Try and beat my record of 1m 47s.
column3: Trata y bate mi récord de 1m 47s.

column2: &8[King Nemian]&f You will find them lurking beneath the shadows of the trees.
column3: &8[Rey Nemian]&f Los encontraras acechando bajo las sombras de los árboles.

column2: &8&oI need to find Forest Crawlers and kill them.
column3: &8&oNecesito encontrar a los rastreadores del bosque y matarlos.

column2: &8[King Nemian]&fGood to see you return, and with plenty of legs too!
column3: &8[Rey Nemian]&f¡Es bueno verte regresar, y con muchas piernas!

column2: &8[King Nemian]&fYou think that their nest might be near? Let's talk more about this
column3: &8[Rey Nemian]&f¿Crees que su nido podría estar cerca? Hablemos más de esto

column2: Oh I am so happy that finally someone has arrived to help us out.
column3: Oh estoy tan contento de que finalmente alguien ha llegado para ayudarnos.

column2: We have a big arachnid problem going on in our little grove.
column3: Tenemos un gran problema arácnido en nuestro pequeño bosque.

column2: There are so many arachnids around these days that you cannot even take a nice evening walk without one of the nasty buggers jumping at you from the shadows.
column3: There are so many arachnids around these days that you cannot even take a nice evening walk without one of the nasty buggers jumping at you from the shadows.

column2: It is clear that their population numbers need a serious culling.
column3: Está claro que sus números de población necesitan una reducción seria.

column2: Oh! Please bring to me any arachnid legs that are still in good condition.
column3: ¡Oh! Por favor, tráeme cualquier pata de arácnido que aún esté en buenas condiciones.

column2: We use them to make small cranes and grabbers.
column3: Las usamos para hacer pequeñas grúas y pinzas.

column2: &1Boots made from spider legs and leather.
column3: &1Botas hechas con piernas de araña y cuero.

column2: &a[Phygia Gorgonius]&f I am sure you will find plenty of them if you find some place with shade and just look up, hard to miss their tree houses.
column3: &a[Phygia Gorgonius]&f Estoy segura de que encontrarás un montón de ellos si encuentras algún lugar con sombra y solo miras hacia arriba, es difícil pasar de vista sus casas de árboles.

column2: &7&oI should go take care of these &cElves&7&o before &aPhygia&7&o catches on fire from rage.
column3: &7&oDebería ir a encargarme de esos &cElfos&7&o antes de que &aPhygia&7&o se prenda fuego de la rabia.

column2: &a[Phygia Gorgonius]&f My friend! HAHA! So good to see you again!
column3: &a[Phygia Gorgonius]&f ¡Mi amigo! ¡JAJA! ¡Muy bueno verte de nuevo!

column2: I was watching from a distance. Seeing those fools fall to their death, nothing better!
column3: Estaba mirando desde la distancia. Ver a esos tontos caer a su muerte, ¡no hay nada mejor!

column2: &7&oThe elves wont be bothering &aPhygia&7&o ever again.
column3: &7&oLos elfos no volverán a molestar a &aPhygia&7&o jamás.

column2: I've had it up here with these gosh darn tree climbing &cElf Bandits&f in our &dGrove&f.
column3: Estoy harto de estos malditos &cElfos Bandidos&f trepadores de árboles en nuestro &dBosque&f.

column2: Not like the &cSpiders&f were enough, now these shadow loving poop nuts have decided to settle in our trees!
column3: Not like the &cSpiders&f were enough, now these shadow loving poop nuts have decided to settle in our trees!

column2: They love the dark you see, the light hurts them, makes them all foggy in the head.
column3: Aman la oscuridad que verás, la luz los lastima, los hace confusos en la cabeza.

column2: Of course a lot of darkness and shadow in our little &dGrove&f. So they moved right in!
column3: Por supuesto, mucha oscuridad y sombra en nuestro pequeño &dBosque&f. ¡Así que se mudaron directamente!

column2: Forced their way in with their superior numbers.
column3: Se abrieron paso a la fuerza con sus números superiores.

column2: Well they got something coming alright, one look at you and I can tell you can handle a couple of stone giants!
column3: Well they got something coming alright, one look at you and I can tell you can handle a couple of stone giants!

column2: I am sure some elves won't be much of an issue for you.
column3: Estoy seguro de que algunos elfos no serán un gran problema para ti.

column2: Go send them a message. The message is clear, THEIR NASTY BUTTS AIN'T WELCOME HERE!
column3: Ve a enviarles un mensaje. El mensaje es claro, ¡SUS TRASEROS ASQUEROSOS NO SON BIENVENIDOS AQUÍ!

column2: Every bridge path has at least one color!
column3: ¡Cada camino de puente tiene al menos un color!

column2: Pontis was built like a maze for defense.
column3: Pontis se construyó como un laberinto para defensa.

column2: The bridge ceilings show that path's color!
column3: ¡Los techos de los puentes muestran el color de ese camino!

column2: Every bridge path has at least one color!
column3: ¡Cada camino de puente tiene al menos un color!

column2: Pontis was built like a maze for defense.
column3: Pontis se construyó como un laberinto para defensa.

column2: The bridge ceilings show that path's color!
column3: ¡Los techos de los puentes muestran el color de ese camino!

column2: Do not worry,\nthe elite guard\nis on the case!
column3: ¡No te preocupes,\nel guardia élite\nestá en el castillo!

column2: Don't mind me, just keeping the peace.
column3: No me hagas caso, solamente manteniendo la paz.

column2: I've got my eye on you, adventurer.
column3: Tengo mi ojo en ti, aventurero.

column2: No questions, and no one gets hurt!
Ain't got no time for messing around.
column3: No tengo tiempo para estar jugando.

column2: Don't mind me, just keeping the peace.
column3: No me hagas caso, solamente manteniendo la paz.

column2: I've got my eye on you, adventurer.
column3: Tengo mi ojo en ti, aventurero.

column2: No questions, and no one gets hurt!
Ain't got no time for messing around.
column3: No tengo tiempo para estar jugando.

column2: wave=1:message=&8[Star Gazer] &fIn the beginning the Elementals were just Primal wisps, nothing more than a collection of violent energy given form.
column3: wave=1:message=&8[Star Gazer] &fIn the beginning the Elementals were just Primal wisps, nothing more than a collection of violent energy given form.

column2: wave=2:message=&8[Star Gazer] &fAs the wisps grew their energies took on the Primal forms of Earth, Water, Fire and Air.
column3: wave=2:message=&8[Star Gazer] &fAs the wisps grew their energies took on the Primal forms of Earth, Water, Fire and Air.

column2: wave=3:message=&8[Star Gazer] &fThis is when Humans appeared. At first there was harmony, but that was short-lived.
column3: wave=3:message=&8[Star Gazer] &fThis is when Humans appeared. At first there was harmony, but that was short-lived.

column2: wave=4:message=&8[Star Gazer] &fDissent grew between primal forces and humans, resulting in the formation of factions and, eventually, wars.
column3: wave=4:message=&8[Star Gazer] &fDissent grew between primal forces and humans, resulting in the formation of factions and, eventually, wars.

column2: wave=5:message=&8[Star Gazer] &fAs great wars waged, warfare evolved. The Primals developed into the elements as we know them today, and the humans adapted to these elements.
column3: wave=5:message=&8[Star Gazer] &fAs great wars waged, warfare evolved. The Primals developed into the elements as we know them today, and the humans adapted to these elements.

column2: wave=6:message=&8[Star Gazer] &fAs a stalemate slowly made itself evident, the conflicts between the elements and the humans came to a fragile armistice.
column3: wave=6:message=&8[Star Gazer] &fAs a stalemate slowly made itself evident, the conflicts between the elements and the humans came to a fragile armistice.

column2: wave=7:message=&8[Star Gazer] &fIn the dark, and slowly fading from Human memory, the elementals developed dark rituals through which the power of Life itself could be harnessed.
column3: wave=7:message=&8[Star Gazer] &fIn the dark, and slowly fading from Human memory, the elementals developed dark rituals through which the power of Life itself could be harnessed.

column2: wave=8:message=&8[Star Gazer] &fArmed with this new terrible power, the Elementals started recruiting in the shadows, taking those with a thirst for power to their side.
column3: wave=8:message=&8[Star Gazer] &fArmed with this new terrible power, the Elementals started recruiting in the shadows, taking those with a thirst for power to their side.

column2: wave=9:message=&8[Star Gazer] &fThose who chose to follow the Elementals were rewarded with terrible power should they succeed, and with a fate worse than death when they failed.
column3: wave=9:message=&8[Star Gazer] &fThose who chose to follow the Elementals were rewarded with terrible power should they succeed, and with a fate worse than death when they failed.

column2: wave=10:message=&8[Star Gazer] &fEmboldened by this, Elementals have now resumed the long-forgotten war, certain that this time they will overcome Humanity.
column3: wave=10:message=&8[Star Gazer] &fEmboldened by this, Elementals have now resumed the long-forgotten war, certain that this time they will overcome Humanity.

column2: I hope to see many stars.
&7An ornate shield with a cosmos motive.
column3: &7Un escudo ornamentado con un motivo de cosmos.

column2: &7A thousand tiny spiky stars stretch across the Chestplate.
column3: &7Mil minúsculas estrellas se esparcirán por la pechera.

column2: &7The leggings sparkle like the stars in the sky.
column3: &7Los pantalones brillan como las estrellas del cielo.

column2: &9If you hold it up all the
&aYou can sense a presence coming from the stone.
column3: &aPuedes sentir una presencia proveniente de la piedra.

column2: &a[Meliorem]&f Fortes sent you here to upgrade your gear?
column3: &a[Meliorem]&f ¿Fortes te envió aquí para mejorar tu equipo?

column2: &a[Meliorem]&f Talk to the assistant in the back and he will give you some free goodies.
column3: &a[Meliorem]&f Habla con el asistente de atrás y te dará algunas cosas gratis.

column2: &a[Fortes]&f You can find &aMeliorem&f down in the city streets near a &dWater Fountain&f.
column3: &a[Fortes]&f Puedes encontrar a &aMeliorem&f en las calles de la ciudad cerca de una &dFuente de Agua&f.

column2: &a[Fortes]&f Do not forget! Drag over you gear, the enchantment book and any lucky tickets you might have into the enchantment window and then click on Enchant when you are ready!
column3: &a[Fortes]&f ¡No lo olvides! Arrastra tu equipo, el libro de encantamientos y cualquier ticket de la suerte que puedas tener a la ventana de encantamiento y luego haz clic en Encantar cuando estés listo.

column2: &7&oI should find &a&oMeliorem the Enchanter&7&o and upgrade some of my gear.
column3: &7&oDebería encontrar a &a&oMeliorem el Encantador&7&o y mejorar algo de mi equipo.

column2: &a[Assistant]&f I can give you a free book and a ticket. Talk to &aMeliorem&f to enchant your gear!
column3: &a[Asistente]&f Puedo darte un libro gratis y un ticket. ¡Habla con &aMeliorem&f para encantar tu equipo!

column2: Hmm, your gear could use some upgrades.
column3: Hmm, tu equipo podría necesitar algunas mejoras.

column2: We have an enchanter in our city that could help you out with that.
column3: Tenemos un encantador en nuestra ciudad que podría ayudarte con eso.

column2: You see enchanting is a pretty straight forward process.
column3: Verás, encantar es un proceso bastante sencillo.

column2: All you need is some &eElite Gear&f and an &eEnchantment Book&f and if you have it with you, an optional &eLucky Ticket&f.
column3: All you need is some &eElite Gear&f and an &eEnchantment Book&f and if you have it with you, an optional &eLucky Ticket&f.

column2: You talk to the &aEnchanter&f and a window will open up where you can drag over your piece of &eElite Gear&f your &eEnchantment Book&f and any &eLucky Tickets&f you might have.
column3: You talk to the &aEnchanter&f and a window will open up where you can drag over your piece of &eElite Gear&f your &eEnchantment Book&f and any &eLucky Tickets&f you might have.

column2: The &eLucky Tickets&f are completely optional, they only improve the chance of the enchantment being a success.
column3: The &eLucky Tickets&f are completely optional, they only improve the chance of the enchantment being a success.

column2: After you have placed your items in the correct slots you can hit the Enchant button and hopefully you will have an enchanted piece of gear!
column3: After you have placed your items in the correct slots you can hit the Enchant button and hopefully you will have an enchanted piece of gear!

column2: Oh, and of course the enchanter will charge you a small fee for their service.
column3: Oh, y por supuesto, el encantador te cobrará una pequeña tarifa por su servicio.

column2: &a[Augustina Verrucosis]&f Oh, this is quite important! I will let the residents know.
column3: &a[Augustina Verrucosis]&f ¡Oh, esto es bastante importante! Se lo haré saber a los residentes.

column2: Thank you for delivering these important documents.
column3: Gracias por entregar estos documentos importantes.

column2: &a[Godefridus Novation]&f You will do it? Excellent!
You can follow the &9Yellow Path&f to get to the slums.
column3: Puedes seguir el &9Camino Amarillo&f para llegar a los tugurios.

column2: The &dFields Farm&f is right beyond the slums, just follow the path.
column3: La &dGranja de Campo&f está justo más allá de los tugurios, simplemente sigue el camino.

column2: Oh! And watch out for the field rats!
column3: ¡Oh! ¡Y cuidado con las ratas de campo!

column2: &7&oI should head for the &d&oSlums&7&o and then the &d&oFields Farm&7&o.
column3: &7&oDebería dirigirme a los &d&oTugurios&7&o y luego a la &d&oGranja de Campo&7&o.

column2: &a[Milonia Majus]&f Documents? Let me see them. Hmmm, looks official.
column3: &a[Milonia Majus]&f ¿Documentos? Déjame verlos. Hmmm, parece oficial.

column2: Thank you for coming all the way here to deliver them.
column3: Gracias por venir hasta aquí para entregarlos.

column2: &7&oSeems like &a&oMilonia&7&o could use my help with the rats...
column3: &7&oParece que a &a&oMilonia&7&o podría usar mi ayuda con las ratas...

column2: If I could bother you with some delivery tasks.
column3: Si pudiera molestarte con algunas tareas de entrega.

column2: I have here some important documents that need to be delivered to the &dSlums&f and to the &dFields Farm&f.
column3: I have here some important documents that need to be delivered to the &dSlums&f and to the &dFields Farm&f.

column2: The soldier that was supposed to come and get them has not arrived yet.
column3: El soldado que se suponía que vendría a buscarlos aún no ha llegado.

column2: And this is an urgent matter, we cannot afford to wait any longer.
column3: Y este es un asunto urgente, no podemos permitirnos esperar más.

column2: Unfortunately I have strict orders to not leave my post.
column3: Desafortunadamente tengo órdenes estrictas de no abandonar mi puesto.

column2: If you could do this for me it would help us out a lot.
column3: Si pudieras hacer esto por mí, nos ayudaría mucho.

column2: &dThose who hunt cannot be the prey.

column3: &dAquellos que cazan no pueden ser la presa.

column2: &a[Dordalus Nasica]&f I only saw the &cRockhounds&f steal the berries.
column3: &a[Dordalus Nasica]&f Solo vi a los &cSabuesos de Roca&f robar las bayas.

column2: &7&oI should go kill the &c&oRedwood Rockhounds&7&o and collect any &e&oStolen Berries&7&o they drop.
column3: &7&oDebería matar a los &c&oSabuesos de Secoya&7&o y recoger cualquier &e&oBaya Robada&7&o que dejen caer.

column2: &a[Dordalus Nasica]&f Oh my, you did it. Could I bother you with one more tiny favor.
column3: &a[Dordalus Nasica]&f Oh mi, lo hiciste. ¿Puedo molestarte con un pequeño favor más?

column2: &7&o Seems like &d&oMilonia&7&o has more work for me.
column3: &7&o Parece que &d&oMilonia&7&o tiene más trabajo para mí.

column2: Oh gosh, I have no idea what is wrong with these &cRockhounds&f.
column3: Oh por Dios, no tengo idea de qué les pasa a estos &cSabuesos de Piedra&f.

column2: They keep coming into the &dBerry Farm&f while I am away or sleeping.
column3: Ellos siguen entrando en la &dGranja de Bayas&f mientras estoy ausente o durmiendo.

column2: You would think they come here and eat the berries, but no!
column3: Uno pensaría que vienen aquí y se comen las bayas, ¡pero no!

column2: They load their mouths with them and carry them off somewhere deep into the forest.
column3: Se llenan la boca con ellas y se las llevan a algún lugar profundo del bosque.

column2: I mean they are &cHounds&f! Why are they even stealing berries.
column3: ¡Quiero decir que son &cHounds&f! ¿Por qué siquiera roban bayas?

column2: Well I guess it doesn''t matter, I have a favor to ask.
column3: Bueno, supongo que no importa, tengo un favor que pedir.

column2: Could you go clear the &9Area Behind the Berry Farm&f, and bring back my &eStolen Berries&f.
column3: Could you go clear the &9Area Behind the Berry Farm&f, and bring back my &eStolen Berries&f.

column2: I have a lot of pies to make and the berries that they stole were ripe and ready.
column3: Tengo muchos pasteles que hacer y las bayas que robaron estaban maduras y listas.

column2: The most dangerous\nweapon is the one\nbetween your ears.
column3: El arma\nmás peligrosa es el que está\nentre tus oídos.
Tres flechas\nson todo lo que necesito.

column2: Hope our camp\nprovides you respite\nfrom the wild.
column3: Espero que nuestro campamento\nte proporcione un respiro\nde la naturaleza.

column2: Don't mind me just\nfetching some water.
column3: No me hagas caso\nsólo estoy buscando un poco de agua.

column2: &a[Milonia Majus]&f Here take this device it will roughly guide you to the their location.
column3: &a[Milonia Majus]&f Toma este dispositivo, te guiará aproximadamente a su ubicación.

column2: &7&oI should go and challenge the &c&oThree Great Beasts&7&o.
column3: &7&oDebería ir y desafiar a las &c&oTres Grandes Bestias&7&o.

column2: &a[Milonia Majus]&f You have returned. And you have brought all three items I requested as proof.
column3: &a[Milonia Majus]&f Has vuelto. Y has traído los tres artículos que pedí como prueba.

column2: That must have been quite an adventure, reminds me of my younger days when I had more strength and agility.
column3: Debe haber sido toda una aventura, me recuerda mis días de juventud cuando tenía más fuerza y agilidad.

column2: Well enough about me, here is your reward as promised!
column3: Bueno, basta de mí, ¡aquí está tu recompensa como prometí!

column2: &7You hand back the beast tracking device.
column3: &7Devuelves el dispositivo de rastreo de bestias.

column2: &a[Milonia Majus]&fI had almost forgotten about that thing, thank you!
column3: &a[Milonia Majus]&f casi se me había olvidado de esa cosa, ¡gracias!
¡Hasta que nos encontremos de nuevo aventurero!

column2: So you found &aVolumnia&f. Thank the great hunters that she is alright.
column3: Así que encontraste &aVolumnia&f. Gracias a los grandes cazadores que ella está bien.

column2: Since you have helped &aVolumnia&f and proven yourself a kind soul.
column3: Ya que has ayudado a &aVolumnia&f y has demostrado ser un alma bondadosa.

column2: How about a friendly challenge. I would be willing to offer you some nice quality armor should you face the challenge and return victorious.
column3: How about a friendly challenge. I would be willing to offer you some nice quality armor should you face the challenge and return victorious.

column2: The challenge involves hunting &cThree Great Beasts&f scattered across Pontis.
column3: El desafío implica cazar &cThree Great Beasts&f dispersas por Pontis.

column2: The &cBeast Cod Furiosa&f who swims underneath a bridge where two mountains stand.
column3: La &cBeast Cod Furiosa&f que nada bajo un puente donde se alzan dos montañas.

column2: Crawler Megdun&f that slumbers on top of a sun covered grove.
column3: Crawler Megdun&f que duerme en la cima de una arboleda bañada por el sol.

column2: Dancing between two western peaks you will find the &cBeast Impaler Uladzimir.
column3: Bailando entre dos picos occidentales encontrarás a la &cBeast Impaler Uladzimir&f.

column2: As proof bring me the &eImpaler's Horn&f, the &eCod's Scale&f and the &eCrawler's Silk&f.
column3: Como prueba, tráeme el &eCuerno del Empalador&f, la Escama del &eBacalao&f y la &eSeda del Reptador&f.

column2: I hope she isn't in\ntrouble again.
column3: Espero que no esté en\nproblemas de nuevo.

column2: If only there were more\nhours in the day.
column3: Ojalá hubiera más\nhoras en el día.

column2: Speak to me when you\nhave found Volumnia.
column3: Habla conmigo cuando\nhayas encontrado a Volumnia.

column2: &a[Augustina Verrucosis]&f Their &dCamp&f should be somewhere North-West of here.
column3: &a[Augustina Verrucosis]&f Su &dCampamento&f debería estar en algún lugar al noroeste de aquí.

column2: &7&oI need to head for the &d&oHunters Camp&7&o.
&a[Scribonia Ingenvinus]&f Help the &dSlums&f with their &cMonster&f issue?
column3: &a[Scribonia Ingenvinus]&f ¿Ayudar a los &dTugurios&f con su problema de &cMonstruos&f?

column2: &7&oI should talk to &a&oScribonia&7&o and hear out what she has to say.
column3: &7&oDebería hablar con &a&oScribonia&7&o y escuchar lo que tiene que decir.

column2: I hope I am not bothering you. You look like a person that would listen to a plea.
column3: Espero no estar molestándote. Pareces una persona que escucharía una súplica.

column2: We do not have much to do here in the &dSlums&f, most of us like to wander the &dFields&f to pass the time.
column3: We do not have much to do here in the &dSlums&f, most of us like to wander the &dFields&f to pass the time.

column2: Unfortunately that has come to a stop after a bunch of &cMonsters&f started roaming around the &dFields&f.
column3: Unfortunately that has come to a stop after a bunch of &cMonsters&f started roaming around the &dFields&f.

column2: We heard that some hunters have made &dCamp&f near the &dFields&f.
column3: Escuchamos que algunos cazadores han hecho &dCamp&f cerca de los &dFields&f.

column2: If you could go there and talk to them and ask them to deal with these &cMonsters&f...
column3: Si pudieras ir allí y hablar con ellos y pedirles que se encarguen de estos &cMonsters&f...

column2: &dTruly a one in a million specimen.
column3: &dVerdaderamente una en un millón de especímenes.

column2: &a[Scribonia Ingenvinus]&f I knew you would say yes! I see you are already well equipped.
column3: &a[Scribonia Ingenvinus]&f ¡Sabía que dirías que sí! Veo que ya estás bien equipado.

column2: OK, this is what I want you to do.
column3: OK, esto es lo que quiero que hagas.

column2: We are worried about that large &cBeast&f aka. &cBig ol' Bubba&f so that is priority number one.
column3: Estamos preocupados por esa gran &cBestia&f alias. &cGran Viejo Bubba&f así que esa es la prioridad número uno.

column2: Second I need you to slay 5 &cLonghorns&f and 6 &cShorthorns&f.
Understood? Good. Report to me when you're done.
column3: ¿Comprendido? Bien. Repórtate a mí cuando hayas terminado.

column2: &7&oI should slay &c&oBig ol' Bubba&7&o and kill 5 &c&oLonghorns&7&o and 6 &c&oShorthorns&7&o.
column3: &7&oDebería matar al &c&oGran Viejo Bubba&7&o y matar a 5 &c&oCuernos-largos&7&o y 6 &c&oCuernos-cortos&7&o.

column2: &a[Scribonia Ingenvinus]&f I must say I am quite impressed.
column3: &a[Scribonia Ingenvinus]&f Debo decir que estoy bastante impresionado.

column2: Clearly you are way more than just 'capable'.
column3: Está claro que eres mucho más que 'capaz'.

column2: Thank you for the assistance, we will be able to handle the rest.
column3: Gracias por la asistencia, podremos manejar el resto.

column2: Until we meet again, great hunter.
column3: Hasta que nos volvamos a encontrar, gran cazador.

column2: Deal with the &cMonsters&f? Well I can tell you we have already been doing that.
column3: ¿Enfrentarse a los &cMonstruos&f? Bueno, puedo decirte que ya hemos estado haciendo eso.

column2: There is just too many of them and not enough of us.
column3: Simplemente hay demasiados de ellos y no suficientes de nosotros.

column2: We started hunting them as soon as we made our &dCamp&f here.
column3: Empezamos a cazarlos tan pronto como hicimos nuestro &dCampamento&f aquí.

column2: But their numbers just don't seem to be going down.
column3: Pero sus números simplemente no parecen estar bajando.

column2: And that's not even the worst of it.
column3: Y eso no es ni siquiera lo peor.

column2: We have discovered a lair and a big old &cBeast&f that comes with it!
column3: ¡Hemos descubierto una guarida y una gran &cBestia&f que viene con ella!

column2: Well since you have made it to our &dCamp&f in one piece, I assume you are quite capable yourself.
column3: Well since you have made it to our &dCamp&f in one piece, I assume you are quite capable yourself.

column2: How about joining the hunt? What say you?
column3: ¿Qué tal unirte a la caza? ¿Qué dices?
Esta cosa más le vale que se mantenga.

column2: Any more lifting and\nI'm gonna break.
The view from here\nis really nice.
column3: La vista desde aquí\nes muy agradable.

column2: Am I glad to see you!
How could I let this happen.
&a[Lena Lucan]&f Fresh bread! I cannot thank you enough!
column3: &a[Lena Lucan]&f ¡Pan fresco! ¡No puedo agradecerte lo suficiente!

column2: &a[Tranio Florens]&f Wow! The day just keeps getting better!
Thank you for the flour kind soul.
column3: Gracias por la harina, alma bondadosa.

column2: &7You hand the over the bread and the flour.
&a[Rufia Tertulus]&f I don't know what to say. My children will be so happy!
column3: &a[Rufia Tertulus]&f No sé qué decir. ¡Mis hijos estarán tan felices!

column2: &7The woman bows to you in deep appreciation.
column3: &7La mujer se inclina ante ti en profunda gratitud.

column2: &a[Fabia Praetextus]&f I guess fantasies do come true sometimes. I am eternally grateful to you kind sir.
column3: &a[Fabia Praetextus]&f Supongo que las fantasías a veces se hacen realidad. Estoy eternamente agradecida a usted, amable señor.

column2: &a[Daemones Maritialis]&f I wish there were more people like you in the world.
column3: &a[Daemones Maritialis]&f Desearía que hubiese más gente como tú en el mundo.

column2: The &dSlums&f are straight North of here, you can see the buildings in the distance.
column3: Los &dTugurios&f están justo al norte de aquí, puedes ver los edificios a la distancia.

column2: &7&oI should go to the &dSlums&7&o and hand out the food to those in need.
column3: &7&oDebería ir a los &dTugurios&7&o y repartir la comida a los necesitados.

column2: &a[Augustina Verrucosis]&f &2Daemones&f sent you here didn't he.
He has been coming by every week handing out any food he could spare to make sure we didn't starve...
column3: Ha estado viniendo todas las semanas repartiendo toda la comida que pudiera para asegurarse de que no nos muriéramos de hambre...

column2: Thank you stranger, my family won't forget this.
column3: Gracias, extraño, mi familia no olvidará esto.

column2: I can feel a good heart beating in that chest of yours.
column3: Puedo sentir un buen corazón latiendo en ese pecho tuyo.

column2: Not everyone is as fortunate as you and I.
column3: No todos son tan afortunados como tú y yo.

column2: There are some poor souls living in the &dPontis Mille Slums&f.
column3: Hay algunas pobres almas que viven en los &dTugurios de Pontis Mille&f.

column2: For a while now I have been working over time to produce surplus bread and flour.
column3: Hay algunas almas pobres viviendo en los &dPontis Mille Slums&f.

column2: Would you mind taking these sacks of wheat and these bread stacks.
column3: Would you mind taking these sacks of wheat and these bread stacks.

column2: Then travel with them to the &dSlums&f and hand them out to those in need?
column3: ¿Te importaría llevarte estos sacos de trigo y estas pilas de pan?

column2: I have been doing this for a while now but I injured my left foot, so I cannot do much walking right now.
column3: I have been doing this for a while now but I injured my left foot, so I cannot do much walking right now.

column2: &fEverything one would need" - "&fto treat serious injuries.
column3: &fTodo lo que uno necesita" - "&fpara tratar lesiones graves.

column2: &a[Dordalus Nasica]&f I think I saw the &cHound&f head into the &dRedwoods&f, North-West of the farm.
column3: &a[Dordalus Nasica]&f Creo que vi al &cSabueso&f dirigirse a las &dSecoyas&f, al noroeste de la granja.

column2: &7&oI should go slay the &c&oFruity Hound&7&o and see if the &e&oContest Berry&7&o is still in one piece.
column3: &7&oDebería ir a matar a el &c&oSabueso Afrutado&7&o y ver si la &e&oBaya de Concurso&7&o todavía está en una pieza.

column2: &a[Dordalus Nasica]&f YES! That is my darling! Fine and whole, not even any saliva on it!
column3: &a[Dorsalis Nasica]&f ¡SÍ! ¡Ese es mi amor! Fino y entero, ¡ni siquiera un poco de saliva en él!

column2: As a reward for your work you can have my second largest berry. Be careful not to eat it.
column3: Como recompensa por tu trabajo puedes tener mi segunda baya más grande. Ten cuidado de no comerlo.

column2: I know might be tempting to eat it, but believe me it's way more useful if you keep it around.
column3: Sé que puede ser tentador comerlo, pero créeme, es mucho más útil si lo conservas.

column2: Since you are my NUMBER ONE berry recovery agent, I have another task for you.
As you can see we grow some very large berries on our little &dBerry Farm&f here.
column3: As you can see we grow some very large berries on our little &dBerry Farm&f here.

column2: There was a &eSpecific Berry&f I was growing for a contest.
column3: There was a &eSpecific Berry&f I was growing for a contest.

column2: But as I was walking to the &dBerry Farm&f I saw a &cFruity Rockhound&f jump for the bush holding my prized berry.
column3: But as I was walking to the &dBerry Farm&f I saw a &cFruity Rockhound&f jump for the bush holding my prized berry.

column2: He snapped it off and carried it away.
column3: He snapped it off and carried it away.

column2: Its jaws were holding the berry by its stem so it should still be in one piece, I hope.
column3: Its jaws were holding the berry by its stem so it should still be in one piece, I hope.

column2: If you go slay the beast and bring back my dear &eContest Berry&f I will have a nice reward waiting for you.
column3: If you go slay the beast and bring back my dear &eContest Berry&f I will have a nice reward waiting for you.

column2: &a[Milonia Majus]&f I am sure that you already noticed that they like to squirm around the path area.
column3: &a[Milonia Majus]&f Estoy seguro de que ya notaste que les gusta retorcerse alrededor del área del camino.

column2: &7&oI should go kill the &cRats&7&o that hang around the path that leads to &dPontis Mille&7&o.
column3: &7&oDebería ir a matar a las &cRatas&7&o que andan por el camino que conduce a &dPontis Mille&7&o.

column2: &a[Milonia Majus]&f Thank you so much! We can get back to making delicious goods now.
column3: &a[Milonia Majus]&f ¡Muchas gracias! Podemos volver a hacer productos deliciosos ahora.

column2: Lately all these &cRats&f have been driving me crazy.
column3: Últimamente todas estas &cRatas&f me han estado volviendo loco.

column2: They keep going into our little farm and eating all our goods!
column3: ¡Siguen entrando en nuestra pequeña granja y comen todos nuestros bienes!

column2: Any chance you could go and lower their numbers a bit?
column3: ¿Hay alguna posibilidad de que puedas ir y bajar un poco sus números?

column2: Be careful, there are so many of them.
column3: Ten cuidado, hay muchos de ellos.

column2: Oh, I almost forgot to tell you.
column3: Oh, casi me olvido de decírtelo.

column2: If you see a large &cWell Fed Rat&f don't bother with it.
column3: Si ves una &cRata Bien Alimentada&f grande, no te molestes con ella.

column2: It has grown so large and fat it would take you days to slay it.
column3: Ha crecido tan grande y gordo que te llevaría días matarlo.
&el trabajo en forma a tu favor.

column2: Raw rat meat. No need to cook.
column3: Carne de rata cruda. No hay necesidad de cocinar.

column2: &a[Dinia Niraemius]&f Flour? Sure, one sack of flour coming up!
column3: &a[Adulescens Lupis]&f Oí que la granja tenía problemas de &cRat&f. ¡Tres sacos de harina en camino, sin problema!

column2: &a[Daemones Maritialis]&f The farm needs more flour eh? Here ya go, two sacks!
column3: &a[Dinia Niraemius]&f ¿Harina? ¡Claro, un saco de harina en camino!

column2: &a[Adulescens Lupis]&f I heard the farm was having &cRat&f problems. Three sacks of flour coming up, no problem!
column3: &a[Milonia Majus]&f ¡Muchas gracias! Ahora podemos volver a hacer productos deliciosos.

column2: &a[Milonia Majus]&f You will need to collect the flour from all three &dWindmills&f.
column3: &a[Milonia Majus]&f Deberás recolectar la harina de los tres &dMolinos de Viento&f.

column2: &7&oI need to visit the three &dWindmills&7&o and collect the flour they produce.
column3: &7&oNecesito visitar los tres &dMolinos de Viento&7&o y recoger la harina que producen.

column2: &a[Milonia Majus]&f This should last us for quite a while!
Hopefully our flour tab won't get too big, hehe.
column3: Esperemos que nuestra ficha de harina no sea demasiado grande, jeje.

column2: Wow, you're quite handy. If I could bother you with another task.
column3: Wow, eres bastante útil. ¿Si pudiera molestarte con otra tarea?

column2: The &cRats&f had completely ruined our current stock of flour.
column3: Las &cRatas&f han arruinado por completo nuestro stock actual de harina.

column2: So we need to a completely new batch of flour.
column3: Entonces necesitamos un lote completamente nuevo de harina.

column2: The &dWindmills&f should have plenty of it.
column3: Los &dMolinos de Viento&f deberían tener un montón de ella.

column2: Go collect the flour and drop it off back here with me.
column3: Ve a recoger la harina y déjala aquí conmigo.

column2: I will be paying good coin for this service!
column3: ¡Pagaré una buena moneda por este servicio!

column2: &a[Volumnia Zoilus]&f The &dHunters Camp&f is straight South, cannot miss it, look for tents.
column3: &a[Volumnia Zoilus]&f El &dCampamento de Cazadores&f está directamente al sur, no puedes pasarlo por delante, busca tiendas de campaña.

column2: &7&oI need to go collect the &e&oFirst Aid Equipment&7&o for &a&oVolumnia&7&o at the &d&oHunters Camp&7&o.
column3: &7&oNecesito ir a recoger el &e&oEquipo de Primeros Auxilios&7&o para &a&oVolumnia&7&o en el &d&oCampamento de Cazadores&7&o.

column2: &a[Volumnia Zoilus]&f Already back? Hand me the equipment.
Do not worry about me, I will have myself patched up in no time.
column3: No te preocupes por mí, me arreglaré en poco tiempo.

column2: Thank you for everything! You saved my life you know!
Am I glad to see you right now!
Dang &cNightmare Rat&f ambushed me while I was climbing down the well.
column3: Malditas &cRatas de Pesadilla&f me tendieron una emboscada mientras bajaba por el pozo.

column2: I injured my arm and legs when I fell.
column3: Me lastimé el brazo y las piernas cuando me caí.

column2: Argh, I still have some of its toxic spit left in my eyes.
column3: Argh, todavía tengo algo de su saliva tóxica en mis ojos.

column2: Thankfully I managed to crawl my way onto this little ledge before it could come finish me off.
column3: Thankfully I managed to crawl my way onto this little ledge before it could come finish me off.

column2: How embarrassing, not sure what hurts more right now, my body or my pride.
column3: How embarrassing, not sure what hurts more right now, my body or my pride.

column2: I have some &eFirst Aid Equipment&f in the chest at the &dHunters Camp&f.
column3: I have some &eFirst Aid Equipment&f in the chest at the &dHunters Camp&f.

column2: Would you mind getting it for me? Oh, and make sure not to tell anyone there a word about what you saw here.
column3: Would you mind getting it for me? Oh, and make sure not to tell anyone there a word about what you saw here.

column2: ...almost died in a well...this is a chapter of my life I will need to erase...
column3: ...casi muero en un pozo...este es un capítulo de mi vida que tendré que borrar...

column2: This one is the best Windmill around!
column3: ¡Este es el mejor molino de viento de los alrededores!
&aLa captura de peces ha sido fácil!

column2: &7&oI should check out the lower part of the city and see if I can find the &a&oElite Guards&7&o.
column3: &7&oDebería revisar la parte baja de la ciudad y ver si puedo encontrar a los &a&oGuardias de Élite&7&o.

column2: &7&oI should let the cat enjoy it's meal in peace.
column3: &7&oDebería dejar que el gato disfrute de su comida en paz.

column2: &7&oIt seems to have dropped something, hmm...
column3: &7&oParece que ha dejado caer algo, hmm...

column2: No cat food but I think I can help ya find something even better...
column3: No cat food but I think I can help ya find something even better...

column2: I heard a couple of &aGuards&f have been dealing with a rat infestation in the lower parts of the city.
column3: I heard a couple of &aGuards&f have been dealing with a rat infestation in the lower parts of the city.

column2: Go down there and maybe you can get some &cRats&f for your cat friend.
column3: Baja allí y quizás puedas conseguir algunas &cRatas&f para tu amigo gato.

column2: Someone needs to drop\noff these documents.
&a[Royal Guard]&f Do I look like someone who keeps track of cat food?...
column3: &a[Royal Guard]&f ¿Acaso parezco alguien que lleva la cuenta de la comida para gatos?...

column2: &a[Tyndarus Faustinius]&f Sorry, I have no idea.
column3: &a[Tyndarus Faustinius]&f Lo siento, no tengo ni idea.

column2: &a[Melaenis Gelasius]&f Cat food? Where the heck did you manage to find a cat here...
column3: &a[Melaenis Gelasius]&f ¿Comida para gatos? ¿Dónde diablos conseguiste encontrar un gato aquí...?

column2: No, I don't know where to get any cat food.
column3: No, no sé dónde conseguir comida para gatos.

column2: &a[Sulpicio Panthera]&f I wish I could help, sorry.
column3: &a[Sulpicio Panthera]&f Ojalá pudiera ayudar, lo siento.

column2: &a[Tyndarus Columbanus]&f We used to have cat food around here somewhere, but heck knows what happened to it...
column3: &a[Tyndarus Columbanus]&f Solíamos tener comida para gatos por aquí en alguna parte, pero quién diablos sabe qué le pasó...

column2: &7&oI should see if anybody in the city knows where to find some cat food.
column3: &7&oDebería ver si alguien en la ciudad sabe dónde encontrar comida para gatos.

column2: &a[Modestus Aper]&f Cat food? I don't know about that. But...
column3: &a[Modestus Aper]&f ¿Comida para gatos? No sé sobre eso. Pero...

column2: &7&o Are you hungry? Does the little one want some food?
column3: &7&o ¿Tienes hambre? ¿Quiere el pequeño algo de comida?

column2: &7&oLet's see if we can get you some food.
column3: &7&oVamos a ver si podemos conseguirte algo de comida.

column2: &a[Delphium Calpurnius]&f Last I heard my shipment of &eFishing Nets&f was supposed to be heading for &dGladius&f.
column3: &a[Delphium Calpurnius]&f La última vez que supe, mi envío de &eRedes de Pesca&f se suponía que se dirigía a &dGladius&f.

column2: &7&oI need to go look around &d&oGladius&7&o for &a&oDelphium's&7&o shipment of &e&oFishing Nets&7&o.
column3: &7&oNecesito ir a buscar por &d&oGladius&7&o el envío de &e&oRedes de Pesca&7&o de &a&oDelphium&7&o.

column2: &a[Delphium Calpurnius]&f Those are the &eFishing Nets&f! Thank you so much!
column3: &a[Delphium Calpurnius]&f ¡Esas son las &eRedes de Pesca&f! ¡Muchas gracias!

column2: &a[Delphium Calpurnius]&f I invested a lot of my savings into these! Not sure what I would have done if you hadn't found them.
column3: &a[Delphium Calpurnius]&f ¡Invertí gran parte de mis ahorros en estas! No estoy seguro de qué habría hecho si no las hubieras encontrado.

column2: I ordered some &eFishing Nets&f from &dGladius&f that haven''t arrived yet.
column3: Pedí unas &eRedes de Pesca&f a &dGladius&f que aún no han llegado.

column2: I wonder if something might have happened to the shipment.
column3: Me pregunto si algo le habrá pasado al envío.

column2: If you are willing, I would pay you a small reward if you could go see what happened to the shipment and get the &eFishing Nets&f for me.
column3: If you are willing, I would pay you a small reward if you could go see what happened to the shipment and get the &eFishing Nets&f for me.

column2: So Fortes has decided to take action.
column3: Así que Fortes ha decidido tomar medidas.

column2: Help me finish my task, and my forces will be ready.
column3: Ayúdame a terminar mi tarea, y mis fuerzas estarán listas.

column2: So Fortes has decided to act.
column3: Así que Fortes ha decidido actuar.

column2: If you could assist me with this task, then my forces will be ready.
column3: Si pudieras ayudarme con esta tarea, entonces mis fuerzas estarán listas.

column2: So Fortes sent you? I see.
column3: ¿Así que te envió Fortes? Ya veo.

column2: Your help would be much appreciated, aid me and my forces will be ready.
column3: Tu ayuda sería muy apreciada, ayúdame y mis fuerzas estarán listas.

column2: &a[Fortes]&f Follow the &9orange path&f from the main room to find &aGeneral Bromia&f.
column3: &a[Fortes]&f Sigue el &9camino naranja&f desde la sala principal para encontrar a la &aGeneral Bromia&f.

column2: &a[Fortes]&f At the end of the &9yellow path&f you will find the &aGeneral Rogerius&f.
column3: &8[Fortes]&fAl final del camino amarillo encontrarás al General Rogerius.

column2: &a[Fortes]&f At the end of the &9shorter purple&f path you will find the &aGeneral Cylindrus&f.
column3: &a[Fortes]&f Al final del &9camino morado más corto&f encontrarás al &aGeneral Cylindrus&f.

column2: &7&oI need to talk to the three &a&oGenerals&7&o.
&a[Fortes]&f You managed to contact them? Excellent!
&a[Fortes]&f Here is your reward. Don't spend it all in one place.
column3: &a[Fortes]&f Aquí tienes tu recompensa. No la gastes toda en un solo lugar.

column2: I am sorry that we cannot send aid to &dGladius&f right away.
column3: Lamento que no podamos enviar ayuda a &dGladius&f de inmediato.

column2: Ever since that new &cCounselor&f came, our ruler has not been himself.
column3: Desde que llegó ese nuevo &cCounselor&f, nuestro gobernante no ha sido el mismo.

column2: If you could reach out to the &aGenerals&f in the city and let them know that &dGladius&f needs help we might be able to to do something about it.
column3: If you could reach out to the &aGenerals&f in the city and let them know that &dGladius&f needs help we might be able to to do something about it.

column2: But not before we deal with the existing issues first.
column3: Pero no antes de que resolvamos los problemas existentes primero.

column2: I am sure that the &aGenerals&f will be happy to let you help them out with their issues.
column3: Estoy seguro de que &aGenerals&f estará encantado de dejarle ayudar con sus problemas.

column2: Go talk to them and then come back to let me know they got the message.
column3: Ve a hablar con ellos y luego vuelve para hacerme saber que recibieron el mensaje.

column2: I will reward you for your time.
&8[Hegio Remus]&f Another letter? Thank you for bringing it to me.
&8&oI should go talk to the Pontis Mille Lighthouse Keeper.
column3: &8&oDebería ir a hablar con el Farero de Pontis Mille.

column2: &8[Hegio Remus]&f Hey, do you have a second?
&8&oSeems like Hegio Remus needs me to talk to him.
column3: &8&oParece que Hegio Remus necesita que hable con él.

column2: Before you go anywhere, could you deliver this letter for me?
column3: Antes de ir a alguna parte, ¿podrías entregar esta carta por mí?

column2: You can find the gentleman it needs to go to on top of the Lighthouse.
column3: Puedes encontrar al caballero al que debe ir en la parte superior del Faro.

column2: Don't worry the Lighthouse is right behind me through that doorway.
column3: No te preocupes, el Faro está justo detrás de mí a través de esa puerta.

column2: &a[Jeeves]&f Oh, we meet again. It's good to see you.
column3: &a[Jeeves]&f Oh, nos encontramos de nuevo. Es bueno verte.

column2: You have something for me? Oh, wow...that is quite the shopping list.
column3: ¿Tienes algo para mí? Oh, vaya... esa es una lista de compras bastante grande.

column2: I will have the items sent back to &aHegio&f as soon as possible.
column3: Enviaré los artículos de vuelta a &aHegio&f lo antes posible.

column2: Thank you for stopping by. Hope we meet again.
column3: Gracias por pasar. Espero que nos volvamos a encontrar.

column2: &7&oI should let &aHegio&7&o know I delivered the note.
column3: &7&oDebería hacerle saber a &aHegio&7&o que entregué la nota.

column2: &7&oI should go talk to &aJeeves&f at &dCaeruleaum Village&7&o.
column3: &7&oDeberia ir a hablar con &aJeeves&f en &dVilla Caeruleaum&7&o.

column2: Here, you can have some of this &eRabbit Stew&f I keep in my back pocket.
column3: Toma, puedes tomar un poco de este &eEstofado de conejo&f que guardo en mi bolsillo trasero.

column2: Would you mind taking the portal and delivering a note to my good friend &aJeeves&f.
column3: ¿Te importaría tomar el portal y entregarle una nota a mi buen amigo &aJeeves&f?.

column2: It is so beautiful up here.
&a[Wounded Guard]&f Finally, the rescue is here!
&a[Hurt Guard]&f Am so I happy to see you!
&a[Centurion]&fTry to not get lost in the &9Maze&f.
May luck be on your side warrior!
column3: ¡Que la suerte esté de tu lado guerrero!

column2: &7&oI should venture through the &d&oMines&7&o and locate the &9&oMaze&7&o.
column3: &7&oDebería aventurarme a través de las &d&oMinas&7&o y localizar el &9&oLaberinto&7&o.

column2: &a[Centurion]&f They are alive, excellent, we will send some soldiers to get them out as soon as possible.
column3: &a[Centurion]&f Están vivos, excelente, enviaremos algunos soldados para sacarlos lo antes posible.

column2: I see you brought proof of the &cGoblins&f death, well done.
column3: Veo que trajiste pruebas de la muerte del &cGoblin&f, bien hecho.

column2: &7&oHopefully people keep out of the &9Maze&7&o in the future.
column3: &7&oEsperemos que la gente se mantenga fuera del &9Laberinto&7&o en el futuro.

column2: If I could bother you for a second.
column3: Si pudiera molestarte por un segundo.

column2: Since you will be going into the &dMines&f already, it would be great if you could help us resolve some issues.
column3: Since you will be going into the &dMines&f already, it would be great if you could help us resolve some issues.

column2: We are missing three &aGuards&f that were sent into the mines to hunt down a &cCursed Goblin&f.
column3: We are missing three &aGuards&f that were sent into the mines to hunt down a &cCursed Goblin&f.

column2: I fear that something might have happened to them.
column3: Temo que algo les haya pasado.

column2: This &cCursed Goblin&f is supposed to be hiding in some sort of &9Maze&f in the &dMines&f.
column3: This &cCursed Goblin&f is supposed to be hiding in some sort of &9Maze&f in the &dMines&f.

column2: Could you locate the &aMissing Guards&f and bring me proof of the &cGoblins&f death.
column3: Could you locate the &aMissing Guards&f and bring me proof of the &cGoblins&f death.

column2: &aThere are runes etched into the axe handle.
column3: &aHay runas grabadas en el mango del hacha.

column2: &aSeems like this axe was cursed at one point...
column3: &aParece que esta hacha estaba maldita en algún punto...

column2: Stars have so much to tell.
column3: Las estrellas tienen tanto que decir.

column2: May the moon light your way.
column3: Que la Luna ilumine tu camino.

column2: &7Boots made out of special soft bark.
Tread lightly and carry a big sword.
column3: Camina ligero y carga una espada grande.

column2: &a[Donatello]&f You can tell the General I am doing just fine!
column3: &a[Donatello]&f ¡Puedes decirle al General que estoy perfectamente bien!

column2: &a[Leonardo]&f The General should not worry, I am ok!
column3: &a[Leonardo]&f El General no debe preocuparse, ¡estoy bien!

column2: &a[Michelangelo]&f Tell that old man everything is in order!
column3: &a[Michelangelo]&f ¡Dile a ese viejo que todo está en orden!

column2: &a[Raphael]&f Tell Rogerius I am alive and doing fine!
column3: &a[Raphael]&f ¡Dile a Rogerius que estoy vivo y bien!

column2: &a[Rogerius]&fYou can get to the &dSewers&f by going to the fountain and then a bit south-east.
column3: &a[Rogerius]&fPuedes llegar a las &dCloacas&f yendo a la fuente y luego un poco al sureste.

column2: You know you are at the right spot when you see a big sewage pipe going into the wall.
column3: Sabes que estás en el lugar correcto cuando ves una gran tubería de aguas residuales que se mete en la pared.

column2: &7&oI need to find my way into the &dSewers&7&o and complete the tasks.
column3: &7&oNecesito encontrar mi camino a las &dCloacas&7&o y completar las tareas.

column2: &a[Rogerius]&f You have completed the all I have asked? If only I had 10 more men like you...
column3: &a[Rogerius]&f ¿Has completado todo lo que te he pedido? Si tan solo tuviera 10 hombres más como tú...

column2: If you are up to the task then I could use your help.
column3: Si estás a la altura de la tarea, entonces podría usar tu ayuda.

column2: The &dSewers&f under the city have become a lair for all sorts of trouble makers and critters.
column3: Las &dCloacas&f debajo de la ciudad se han convertido en una guarida para todo tipo de alborotadores y criaturas.

column2: The trouble makers call themselves &cNinjas&f...even though they are far from it.
column3: Los alborotadores se hacen llamar &cNinjas&f... aunque están lejos de serlo.

column2: They have a leader, I think he calls himself &cShreepper&f or something.
column3: Tienen un líder, creo que se hace llamar &cShreepper&f o algo así.

column2: Make sure to get rid of him, a snake without it's head is not a threat.
column3: Asegúrate de deshacerte de él, una serpiente sin cabeza no es una amenaza.

column2: If you could go down there and thin the numbers of critters and the trouble makers then that would allow me to assign my forces to more important tasks...
column3: If you could go down there and thin the numbers of critters and the trouble makers then that would allow me to assign my forces to more important tasks...

column2: We had also sent &a4 Agents&f down there, I have not heard from them yet.
column3: We had also sent &a4 Agents&f down there, I have not heard from them yet.

column2: It would mean a lot to me if you could check up on them to make sure they are OK.
column3: It would mean a lot to me if you could check up on them to make sure they are OK.

column2: I also seem to have misplaced my personal &eSewage Keys&f if you could retrieve those too, then that would be great.
column3: I also seem to have misplaced my personal &eSewage Keys&f if you could retrieve those too, then that would be great.
&2Te hace querer comer algo de pizza.

column2: &aA key ring with a lot of keys on it.
column3: &Un anillo de llave con muchas llaves en él.

column2: Now you too are a Ninja
column3: Ahora tú también eres un Ninja

column2: Now you too are a Ninja
column3: Ahora tú también eres un Ninja

column2: Full of small tiny razor blade
column3: Lleno de pequeñas hojas de afeitar

column2: Walk softly, and carry a big gun.
column3: Camina suavemente, y lleva un arma grande.

column2: It's not much but its our\nlittle part of town
column3: No es mucho más que nuestra\npequeña parte de la ciudad
Espero que estés teniendo\nun gran día.

column2: The smell of hay\nmakes me happy.
column3: El olor al heno\nme hace feliz.

column2: My favorite place to\nrelax after a hard day.
column3: Mi lugar favorito para\nrelajarme después de un día difícil.
Me pregunto qué traerá el mañana.

column2: Just close my eyes\nfor a second.
column3: Simplemente cierro mis ojos\npor un segundo.

column2: Gotta imagine I am\nat a better place.
column3: Tengo que imaginar que\nestoy en un lugar mejor.
Tal vez alguna fruta\npara los pequeños.

column2: &7[Fortes Bellator]&f You can find the &aStargazers&f at the &dObservatory&f.
column3: &7[Fortes Bellator]&f Puedes encontrar a los &aObservadores de Estrellas&f en el &dObservatorio&f.

column2: The &dObservatory&f is located past the &dLighthouse&f. It is a large tower, hard to miss.
column3: El &dObservatorio&f se encuentra pasado el &dFaro&f. Es una gran torre, difícil de pasar de lado.

column2: &7&oI should talk to the &aStargazers&7&o at the &dObservatory&7&o.
column3: &7&oDebería hablar con los &aObservadores de Estrellas&7&o en el &dObservatorio&7&o.

column2: &a[Virgo Dexippus]&f The &aMajor&f sent you? It must be important then.
column3: &a[Virgo Dexippus]&f ¿Te ha enviado el &aAlcalde&f? Debe ser importante entonces.

column2: You have done so much for this city and its people.
column3: Has hecho mucho por esta ciudad y su gente.

column2: Having assisted the three &aGenerals&f and helped the areas around &dPontis Mille&f has freed up a serious amount of our resources.
column3: Having assisted the three &aGenerals&f and helped the areas around &dPontis Mille&f has freed up a serious amount of our resources.

column2: We would be able to send our forces to aid &dGladius&f now.
column3: Ahora podríamos enviar nuestras fuerzas para ayudar a &dGladius&f.

column2: But before we take action there is one last thing I would like you to do.
column3: Pero antes de tomar medidas, hay una última cosa que me gustaría que hicieras.

column2: You should go speak with the &aStargazers&f.
column3: Deberías ir a hablar con los &aStargazers&f.

column2: It is in regards to our lost history and the &cElementals&f.
column3: Es con respecto a nuestra historia perdida y a los &cElementales&f.

column2: The &aStargazers&f will be able to tell you more once you talk to them.
column3: Los &aStargazers&f podrán contarte más una vez que hables con ellos.

column2: Here take this sealed note and show it to them.
column3: Aquí tienes esta nota sellada y muéstrasela a ellos.

column2: &a[Virgo Dexippus]&f Talk to &aStella&f and &9Click on the Sword&f to start listening.
column3: &a[Virgo Dexippus]&f Habla con &aStella&f y &9Haz Clic en la Espada&f para empezar a escuchar.

column2: &7&oI should talk to &aStella&7&o and start the &9Arena Challenge&7&o.
column3: &7&oDebería hablar con &aStella&7&o y comenzar el &9Desafío de Arena&7&o.

column2: &a[Virgo Dexippus]&f Do not share this information with anyone.
column3: &a[Virgo Dexippus]&f No compartas esta información con nadie.

column2: Hand me the note. Let me take a look...
We have been given permission to share important information with you regarding our past.
column3: We have been given permission to share important information with you regarding our past.

column2: You must have done something quite important, this information is usually only shared with the top brass.
column3: You must have done something quite important, this information is usually only shared with the top brass.

column2: &aStella&f will share with you what we have uncovered.
column3: &aStella&f compartirá contigo lo que hemos descubierto.

column2: &4[General Hasta] &fPontis Mille came to our aid after all!
column3: &4[General Hasta] &f¡Pontis Mille vino en nuestra ayuda después de todo!

column2: &a[Fortes Bellator]&f Bring your best gear, this won't be a cakewalk.
column3: &a[Fortes Bellator]&f Trae tu mejor equipo, esto no será un paseo.

column2: &7&oI should interact with the &a&oPontis Soldier&7&o at the &d&oGladius-Pontis entrance&7&o.
column3: &7&oDebería interactuar con el &a&oSoldado de Pontis&7&o en la &d&oentrada Gladius-Pontis&7&o.

column2: &a[Fortes Bellator]&f Now that was a battle for the history books!
column3: &a[Fortes Bellator]&f ¡Esa sí que fue una batalla para los libros de historia!

column2: &a[Fortes Bellator]&f We managed to find some &9important information&f on one of the enemy generals!
column3: &a[Fortes Bellator]&f ¡Logramos encontrar algo de &9información importante&f sobre uno de los generales enemigos!

column2: &a[Fortes Bellator]&f Apparently there is a secret passage that leads to the &dBlood Temple&f somewhere in the &dFields-Ice Village Mountains&f. The entrance is sealed off by a puzzle. The solution to the puzzle was written as: &oRed, Blue, Green, Orange. If color one cannot see, then deciphering of the names one should seek.&f We are not sure what it means, hopefully it will be of use to you. Until we meet again friend!
column3: &a[Fortes Bellator]&f Aparentemente hay un pasaje secreto que lleva al &dTemplo de Sangre&f en algún lugar de las &dMontañas de la Aldea de Hielo de los Campos&f. La entrada está sellada por un puzle. La solución al puzle estaba escrita como: &oRojo, Azul, Verde, Naranja. Si el color uno no puede ver, entonces el desciframiento de los nombres uno debe buscar.&f No estamos seguros de lo que significa, esperamos que te sea útil. ¡Hasta que nos volvamos a encontrar, amigo!

column2: &7&oI should try and solve the puzzle to get access to the hidden passage.
column3: &7&oDebería intentar resolver el puzle para obtener acceso al pasaje oculto.

column2: I assume everything has been revealed to you now?
column3: ¿Supongo que todo te ha sido revelado ahora?

column2: Good, good. While you were gonna we have finished preparing our troops.
column3: Bien, bien. Mientras ibas, hemos terminado de preparar nuestras tropas.

column2: We are now ready to march on &dGladius &fand retake the city.
column3: Ahora estamos listos para marchar sobre &dGladius &fy retomar la ciudad.

column2: It has pained me greatly to just standby and watch our ally suffer under siege.
column3: Me ha dolido mucho quedarme al margen y ver a nuestro aliado sufrir bajo asedio.

column2: But no more! After today &dGladius &fwill be free once again!
column3: ¡Pero no más! ¡Después de hoy &dGladius &fserá libre una vez más!

column2: When you are ready to march with us go talk to the &aPontis Soldier&f.
column3: When you are ready to march with us go talk to the &aPontis Soldier&f.

column2: You can find them near the &dGladius-Pontis gate&f.
column3: Puedes encontrarlos cerca de la &dpuerta Gladius-Pontis&f.

column2: Excellent, I knew we could count on him.
column3: Excelente, sabía que podíamos contar con él.

column2: &a[Bromia]&f The &dGroves&f are located North of the city.
column3: &a[Bromia]&f Las &dArboledas&f están ubicadas al Norte de la ciudad.

column2: There is a path through the mountain,, below the mines.
column3: Hay un camino a través de la montaña, debajo de las minas.

column2: &a[King Nemian]&f You have arrived just in time!
It is our duty to protect the &dGroves&f from any threats.
column3: Es nuestro deber proteger las &dArboledas&f de cualquier amenaza.

column2: &aKing Nemian&f of the &dGroves&f has sent a request for aid.
column3: &aRey Nemian&f de las &dArboledas&f ha enviado una solicitud de ayuda.

column2: Nasty critters have come to the &dGroves&f and other invaders are taking over the trees.
column3: Nasty critters have come to the &dGroves&f and other invaders are taking over the trees.

column2: If you could go over there and sort out these issues then my forces will be free to come to &dGladius'&f aid.
column3: If you could go over there and sort out these issues then my forces will be free to come to &dGladius'&f aid.

column2: &7&oI need to clear out the &dWerewolf Den&7&o.
&a[Magnus]&f By the great tree fairy, you've done it!!!
column3: &a[Magnus]&f ¡¡¡Por el gran hada del árbol, lo has conseguido!!!

column2: Feel free to rest at our camp, you are always welcome here.
column3: Siéntete libre de descansar en nuestro campamento, siempre eres bienvenido aquí.

column2: Not sure how a single person can accomplish what an entire battalion cannot.
column3: Not sure how a single person can accomplish what an entire battalion cannot.

column2: But if the &aGeneral&f has sent you, then who I am to complain.
column3: Pero si el &aGeneral&f te ha enviado, ¿quién soy yo para quejarme?

column2: We have located their &dDen&f, but the resistance is too strong.
column3: Hemos localizado su &dGuarida&f, pero la resistencia es demasiado fuerte.

column2: There was just no way to get through.
column3: Simplemente no había forma de pasar.

column2: But If you could  fight your way into the &dDen&f and clear it out then the &dRedwoods&f could be safe yet again.
column3: But If you could  fight your way into the &dDen&f and clear it out then the &dRedwoods&f could be safe yet again.

column2: Their &dDen&f is located under a &9Corrupted Redwood Tree&f.
column3: Su &dGuarida&f se encuentra bajo un &9Árbol de Secuoya Corrompido&f.

column2: Should be easy to spot it, it stands out among the healthy trees.
column3: Debería ser fácil de detectar, destaca entre los árboles sanos.

column2: &a[Gorenus Palis]&f My brother sent you looking for me?
column3: &a[Gorenus Palis]&f ¿Mi hermano te envió a buscarme?

column2: Oh, I messed up again...I got real lost this time.
column3: Oh, la volví a liar... Me perdí de verdad esta vez.

column2: I hope he isn't too mad.
column3: Espero que no esté demasiado enfadado.

column2: When you go back, please tell him I'm safe.
column3: Cuando vuelvas, por favor dile que estoy a salvo.

column2: &a[Rodenus Palis]&f So kind of you to offer your help.
column3: &a[Rodenus Palis]&f Muy amable de tu parte ofrecer tu ayuda.

column2: Please if you find him come tell me where he is right away.
column3: Por favor, si lo encuentras, ven y dime dónde está inmediatamente.
&7&oNecesito ir a buscar al hermano de &a&oRodenus&7&o.

column2: &a[Rodenus Palis]&f What! How the heck did he end up all the way there!
column3: &a[Rodenus Palis]&f ¿¡Qué!? ¿¡Cómo diablos terminó todo el camino hasta ahí!?

column2: Sigh, I better start going now then...
column3: Suspiro, será mejor que me vaya ahora entonces...

column2: Thank you for all your help. Here are the coins as promised.
column3: Gracias por toda tu ayuda. Aquí están las monedas como lo prometí.

column2: Me and my &aBrother&f were on our way back here from the village.
column3: Mi &aHermano&f y yo estábamos de camino de vuelta aquí desde la aldea.

column2: During our travels I had to do a little detour, so we got separated.
column3: Durante nuestros viajes tuve que hacer un pequeño desvío, así que nos separamos.

column2: We were supposed to meet up here. But no trace of him for quite some time now.
column3: We were supposed to meet up here. But no trace of him for quite some time now.

column2: He has a tendency to get lost...real lost.
column3: Tiene tendencia a perderse... de verdad.

column2: I am willing to pay a high reward to anyone who can find him.
column3: Estoy dispuesto a pagar una gran recompensa a cualquiera que pueda encontrarlo.

column2: &7It looks like someone took an iron ingot
column3: &7Parece que alguien tomó un lingote de hierro

column2: &7and pummeled it into the correct shape.
column3: &7y lo golpeó en la forma correcta.

column2: &7It looks like someone took an iron ingot
column3: &7Parece que alguien tomó un lingote de hierro

column2: &7and pummeled it into the correct shape.
column3: &7y lo golpeó en la forma correcta.

column3: &7Parece que alguien tomó un lingote de hierro

column2: &7and pummeled it into the correct shape.
column3: &7y lo golpeó en la forma correcta.
