column2: &7and pummeled it into the correct shape.
column3: &7y lo golpeó en la forma correcta.

column2: &7A nice and sharp stone at the end.
column3: &7Una bonita y afilada piedra al final.

column2: &7It''s just a stone club with a handle.
column3: &7Es solo un mazo de piedra con un mango.

column2: It will be all over soon.
It will be all over soon.
We have spotted barriers\nthat block the way\nto the core of the temple.
column3: Hemos avistado barreras\nque bloquean el camino\nal núcleo del templo.

column2: Killing the 4 guardians\nshould lower the barriers\nallowing you to pass.
column3: Matar a los 4 guardianes\ndebería bajar las barreras\npermitiéndote pasar.

column2: &a[Magnus]&f Who are you? Oh, you came from &dPontis Mille&f.
&a[Cylindrus]&fThe &dRedwoods&f can be reached by heading North.
column3: &a[Cylindrus]&fSe puede llegar a las &dSecoyas&f dirigiéndote hacia el Norte.

column2: Head North until you reach the &dRailway Stop&f, then head West.
column3: Dirígete hacia el Norte hasta llegar a la &dParada de Tren&f, luego dirígete hacia el Oeste.

column2: &7&oI need to head into the &dRedwoods&7&o and talk to &aMagnus&7&o.
column3: &7&oNecesito ir a las &dSecoyas&7&o y hablar con &aMagnus&7&o.

column2: &a[Magnus]&f The general has sent you to help?
column3: &a[Magnus]&f ¿El general te ha enviado a ayudar?
Hmm... será mejor que seas bueno.

column2: I could dedicate my forces to helping &dGladius&f if you could help us deal with the &cWerewolf&f crisis in the &dRedwoods&f.
column3: I could dedicate my forces to helping &dGladius&f if you could help us deal with the &cWerewolf&f crisis in the &dRedwoods&f.

column2: Our forces have been holding back the &cWerewolves&f for weeks now.
column3: Nuestras fuerzas han estado conteniendo a los &cHombres Lobo&f durante semanas.

column2: It would be great if you could assist us.
Go to the &dRedwoods&f and talk to &aMagnus Castorea&f.
column3: Ve a los &dRedwoods&f y habla con &aMagnus Castorea&f.

column2: They will let you know what needs to be done to end this crisis.
column3: Ellos te harán saber lo que hay que hacer para acabar con esta crisis.

column2: &8[Reynus]&f You can find the &cBandits&f right across the river.
column3: &8[Reynus]&f Puedes encontrar a los &cBandidos&f justo al otro lado del río.

column2: &7&oI need to go slay the correct &cBandit&7&o and collect the &eWatch&7&o.
column3: &7&oNecesito ir a matar al &cBandido&7&o correcto y recoger el &eReloj&7&o.

column2: &a[Reynus]&f I will make sure not to loose it again!
column3: &a[Reynus]&f ¡Me aseguraré de no volver a perderlo!

column2: My &ePocket-watch&f had fallen into the river when I was cutting down a tree.
column3: Mi &eReloj de Bolsillo&f se había caído al río cuando estaba cortando un árbol.

column2: It is a special watch you see. Filled with air and quite robust.
column3: Es un reloj especial verás. Lleno de aire y bastante robusto.

column2: Fully resilient to heavy logs being dropped on it, yep.
column3: Totalmente resiliente a los troncos pesados ​​que se dejan caer sobre él, sí.

column2: I saw one of those nasty &cBandits&f scoop it up and put it in their pocket.
column3: Vi a uno de esos asquerosos &cBandidos&f recogerlo y metérselo en el bolsillo.

column2: Pretty sure I saw them &9Carrying a Hatchet&f.
column3: Estoy seguro de que los vi &9Llevando un Hacha&f.

column2: If you could go to their camp and get it back for me. That would mean the world to me!
column3: Si pudieras ir a su campamento y recuperarlo para mí. ¡Eso significaría el mundo para mí!

column2: A nice reward for you too, when you get back!
column3: ¡Una buena recompensa para ti también, cuando vuelvas!

column2: I love the look of a healthy tree.
column3: Me encanta el aspecto de un árbol saludable.

column2:
Pretty sure I saw a wolf on two legs
 creeping around at night around here.
column3:
Pretty sure I saw a wolf on two legs
 creeping around at night around here.

column2: I wish they would leave us alone.
Hah! Try and reach me up here!
Not so loud, keep it down.
I am catching an extra break.
Don't tell em I am here.
column3: No les digas que estoy aquí.

column2: Operating the saw is kinda fun.
column3: Operar la sierra es un tanto divertido.

column2: Gotta make sure you don't get hurt.
column3: Tengo que asegurarme de que no te lastimes.

column2: Just relaxing after an honest day of work.
column3: Simplemente relajándome después de un día honesto de trabajo.

column2: The fastest axe in the west.
column3: El hacha más rápida en el oeste.

column2: No tree is a match for me!

column3: El hacha más rápida... ¡Mi parte inferior!
No te tomes en serio sus divagaciones.

column2: Mr. big-shot sure has a lot to say.
column3: El Sr. big-shot seguro tiene mucho que decir.

column2: My axe, your bark, they should meet.
column3: Mi hacha, tu corteza, deberían conocerse.

column2: Start off with a good chop.

For every tree we cut,
 we plant a new one!
column3:
For every tree we cut,
 we plant a new one!

column2: &a[Ligna Crispian]&f You will find them across the river.
column3: &a[Ligna Crispian]&f Los encontrarás al otro lado del río.

column2: &8&oI should go to the &dBandit Camp&f and clear it out.
column3: &8&oDebería ir al &dCampamento de Bandidos&f y despejarlo.

column2: &a[Ligna Crispian]&f Finally! Some peace, thank you!
Ever since these darn &cBandits&f settled across the river there has been no peace.
column3: Desde que estos malditos &cBandidos&f se asentaron al otro lado del río no ha habido paz.

column2: They keep ruining the trees, yesterday I caught one of them trying to set one of these giant trees on fire!
column3: They keep ruining the trees, yesterday I caught one of them trying to set one of these giant trees on fire!

column2: And not too long ago I got chased by a crazy person with a hatchet, I am quite sure it was one of the &cBandits&f.
column3: And not too long ago I got chased by a crazy person with a hatchet, I am quite sure it was one of the &cBandits&f.

column2: Not too mention they keep trying to rob anyone that has business with us good folk here at the &dSawmill&f.

column2: &e[Wallitz]&f I place my full trust in you to complete this mission, you have a strong will. Go to The Temple and destroy The Void Bell.
column3: &e[Wallitz]&f Pongo toda mi confianza en ti para completar esta misión, tienes una voluntad fuerte. Ve al Templo y destruye La Campana del Vacío.

column2: &7&oI have a really bad feeling about this.
column3: &7&oTengo un muy mal presentimiento sobre esto.

column2: &e[Wallitz]&f So it is done. As could be expected from our number one guild member! I heard that destroying The Void Bell released quite a shock-wave of energy. This was quite of an adventure, who knew we would end up going into the Nether.
column3: &e[Wallitz]&f Así que está hecho. ¡Como era de esperar de nuestro miembro número uno del gremio! Oí que destruir La Campana del Vacío liberó una considerable onda expansiva de energía. Esto fue toda una aventura, quién iba a decir que terminaríamos yendo al Nether.

column2: &e[Wallitz]&f Excuse me, but I must go and write an extensive report on what we have uncovered. Powerful artifacts forming in the Nether is not good news, I must make sure this discovery is shared with as many people as possible.
column3: &e[Wallitz]&f Disculpa, pero debo ir a escribir un informe extenso sobre lo que hemos descubierto. Los artefactos poderosos que se forman en el Nether no son buenas noticias, debo asegurarme de que este descubrimiento se comparta con la mayor cantidad de gente posible.

column2: &7&oThe ringing in your head is still there but it is growing weaker, with enough time it should go away completely.
column3: &7&oEl zumbido en tu cabeza todavía está ahí, pero se está debilitando, con suficiente tiempo debería desaparecer por completo.

column2: We have managed to get our eyes on what caused the corruption, it is a great artifact of power, the energy it emits is overwhelming.
column3: We have managed to get our eyes on what caused the corruption, it is a great artifact of power, the energy it emits is overwhelming.

column2: It is in some sort of temple, from what we can tell the temple was formed naturally…
column3: Está en una especie de templo, por lo que podemos decir, el templo se formó naturalmente...

column2: One of our scouts was affected by the artifact’s powers, the scout lost all self-control and started going towards the temple.
column3: One of our scouts was affected by the artifact’s powers, the scout lost all self-control and started going towards the temple.

column2: It took 3 of our members to stop the scout and drag him back.
column3: It took 3 of our members to stop the scout and drag him back.

column2: Later the scout described being overwhelmed by an urge to go in and interact with the artifact.
column3: Later the scout described being overwhelmed by an urge to go in and interact with the artifact.

column2: All of this is very concerning, the temple and the artifact are natural occurrences in the Nether it would seem.
column3: All of this is very concerning, the temple and the artifact are natural occurrences in the Nether it would seem.

column2: Are there more of these artifacts in the Nether I wonder?
column3: ¿Me pregunto si hay más de estos artefactos en el Nether?

column2: And if there are, then how many? I do not like any of this.
column3: Y si los hay, ¿cuántos? No me gusta nada de esto.

column2: Raw Nether energies pooling and slamming into each other and creating something new and sinister…
column3: Raw Nether energies pooling and slamming into each other and creating something new and sinister…

column2: The artifact itself looks like a bell so we have decided to name it The Void Bell.
column3: The artifact itself looks like a bell so we have decided to name it The Void Bell.

column2: From what we know the artifact has the following powers, mind domination, ability to resurrect the dead, grant eternal un-life, and that’s just the ones we can confirm.
column3: From what we know the artifact has the following powers, mind domination, ability to resurrect the dead, grant eternal un-life, and that’s just the ones we can confirm.

column2: Who knows what else it might be capable of.
column3: Quién sabe de qué más podría ser capaz.

column2: We do know that greater willpower can resist its mind dominating effects, at least for a while.
column3: We do know that greater willpower can resist its mind dominating effects, at least for a while.

column2: Even the strongest will would succumb to its mind domination sooner or later.
column3: Incluso la voluntad más fuerte sucumbiría a su dominación mental tarde o temprano.

column2: &e[Wallitz]&f Oh, and make sure you keep an eye out for any clues or other information that might confirm my suspicions.
column3: &e[Wallitz]&f Ah, y asegúrate de estar atento a cualquier pista u otra información que pueda confirmar mis sospechas.

column2: Just to be sure I will be sending in our smartest after you.
column3: Solo para asegurarme, enviaré a nuestro más inteligente después de ti.

column2: They will sweep the area and check the corpses to see what we are up against.
column3: Rastrearán la zona y examinarán los cadáveres para ver a qué nos enfrentamos.

column2: &7Interact with the nearby &fMiner Regulus &7teleporter to start the quest.
column3: &7Interactúa con el teletransportador cercano de &fMinero Regulus &7para iniciar la misión.

column2: &e[Wallitz]&f Excellent work! I wouldn’t expect anything but the finest work from one of our guild members! Our team is looking over the corpses of the undead and trying to make sense of all of this. Your reports aren’t making me feel any better about this since they only confirm my suspicions that there is more going on here. Check in with me soon for more work!
column3: &e[Wallitz]&f ¡Excelente trabajo! ¡No esperaría nada más que el mejor trabajo de uno de nuestros miembros del gremio! Nuestro equipo está examinando los cadáveres de los no muertos e intentando dar sentido a todo esto. Tus informes no me hacen sentir mejor al respecto, ya que solo confirman mis sospechas de que algo más está pasando aquí. ¡Vuelve a verme pronto para más trabajo!

column2: &7&oI should talk to &e&oWallitz&7&o when I can.
Good to see you around and in one piece!
column3: ¡Me alegra verte por aquí y de una pieza!

column2: We just had a distraught miner storm in, asking us for aid.
column3: Acaba de irrumpir un minero angustiado, pidiéndonos ayuda.

column2: Apparently, their entire village has been overrun by the undead and they have lost many villagers to the forces of evil.
column3: Apparently, their entire village has been overrun by the undead and they have lost many villagers to the forces of evil.

column2: And this doesn’t seem to be your regular bunch of evil brain dead undead either.
column3: Y este tampoco parece ser tu grupo habitual de no muertos malvados sin cerebro.

column2: I have this uneasy feeling this might be a major threat that we aren’t aware of yet.
column3: I have this uneasy feeling this might be a major threat that we aren’t aware of yet.

column2: Miner Regulus told us that some of the villagers were being taken alive and carried away into the mines in the mountains.
column3: Miner Regulus told us that some of the villagers were being taken alive and carried away into the mines in the mountains.

column2: Thankfully our ninety-nine-best guild member is available to help these poor folks.
column3: Thankfully our ninety-nine-best guild member is available to help these poor folks.

column2: That is you, by the way. Go to the village and cleanse it of its undead infestation.
column3: Ese eres tú, por cierto. Ve a la aldea y límpiala de su infestación de no muertos.

column2: &e[Wallitz]&f I do not need to tell you that fire resistance might be a good idea before heading out? Good luck!
column3: &e[Wallitz]&f ¿No necesito decirte que la resistencia al fuego podría ser una buena idea antes de salir? ¡Buena suerte!

column2: &7&oI should prepare for a challenging fight.
&7Interact with the nearby &fVillage Mother &7teleporter to start the quest.
column3: &7Interactúa con el teletransportador cercano de &fMadre de la Aldea &7para iniciar la misión.

column2: &e[Wallitz]&f What is that smokey smell? Oh, it’s our eighty-eight-best guild member! Glad to see that you made it back in one piece. Roasted but, still in one piece. I hope it wasn’t too difficult to put that flaming jello down.
column3: &e[Wallitz]&f ¿Qué es ese olor a humo? ¡Oh, es nuestro octogésimo octavo mejor miembro del gremio! Me alegra ver que regresaste de una pieza. Asado, pero aún de una pieza. Espero que no haya sido demasiado difícil acabar con esa gelatina llameante.

column2: &7&oThat was really draining but seems like there is more to do.
column3: &7&oEso fue realmente agotador, pero parece que hay más por hacer.

column2: Oh! You stopped by just in time!
I got some reports here, regarding those undead corpses from the village.
column3: Tengo algunos informes aquí, sobre esos cadáveres no muertos de la aldea.

column2: Wait, are they corpses or bodies if they’re undead?
column3: Espera, ¿son cadáveres o cuerpos si son no muertos?

column2: Anyway, the corpses had faint traces of Nether magic in them.
column3: En fin, los cadáveres tenían leves rastros de magia del Nether.

column2: Not good, not good at all. There shouldn’t be any Nether beings here at all.
column3: Not good, not good at all. There shouldn’t be any Nether beings here at all.

column2: From what you have told me and what information we could gather from that note.
column3: Por lo que me has contado y la información que pudimos reunir de esa nota.

column2: Our culprit is most likely something called Soulweaver Daine.
column3: Nuestro culpable es muy probablemente algo llamado Tejealmas Daine.

column2: We need to find whatever that creature is and slay it. Or this will only get worse.
column3: Necesitamos encontrar lo que sea esa criatura y matarla. O esto solo empeorará.

column2: This is now becoming a priority mission. I sent some scouts ahead of you.
column3: This is now becoming a priority mission. I sent some scouts ahead of you.

column2: They managed to find the mines. The mines are infested with all sorts of nasty creatures according to the reports.
column3: They managed to find the mines. The mines are infested with all sorts of nasty creatures according to the reports.

column2: Before we send you to the mines, I have a more important task. At the entrance to the mines, we sighted a powerful magma cube.
column3: Before we send you to the mines, I have a more important task. At the entrance to the mines, we sighted a powerful magma cube.

column2: Apparently, all it does is hop back and forth in this small cave.
column3: Aparentemente, todo lo que hace es saltar de un lado a otro en esta pequeña cueva.

column2: This must The Boiler that the note mentioned.
column3: Este debe ser El Caldero que mencionaba la nota.

column2: We cannot leave something like that alive.
column3: No podemos dejar algo así con vida.

column2: &e[Wallitz]&f Our scouts also reported seeing traces of spider-like beings down there, so you should expect attacks that can inflict poison and other nasty effects. I want to say good luck but I know you are our eighty-ninth-best guild member so I am sure you will get the job done!
column3: &e[Wallitz]&f Nuestros exploradores también informaron haber visto rastros de seres parecidos a arañas allí abajo, así que deberías esperar ataques que pueden infligir veneno y otros efectos desagradables. Quiero desearte buena suerte, pero sé que eres nuestro octogésimo noveno mejor miembro del gremio, ¡así que estoy seguro de que harás el trabajo!

column2: &7&oTime to head into the mines and see if I can locate the source of the trouble.
column3: &7&oEs hora de dirigirse a las minas y ver si puedo localizar la fuente del problema.

column2: &7Interact with the nearby &fProspector Voultar &7teleporter to start the quest.
column3: &7Interactúa con el teletransportador cercano de &fProspector Voultar &7para iniciar la misión.

column2: &e[Wallitz]&f What is that smokey smell? Oh, it’s our eighty-eight-best guild member! Glad to see that you made it back in one piece. Roasted but, still in one piece. I hope it wasn’t too difficult to put that flaming jello down.
column3: &e[Wallitz]&f ¿Qué es ese olor a humo? ¡Oh, es nuestro octogésimo octavo mejor miembro del gremio! Me alegra ver que regresaste de una pieza. Asado, pero aún de una pieza. Espero que no haya sido demasiado difícil acabar con esa gelatina llameante.

column2: &7&oI feel like this is not over yet.
column3: &7&oSiento que esto aún no ha terminado.

column2: With The Boiler out of the way, we can now focus on clearing out the mines of these evil creatures.
column3: With The Boiler out of the way, we can now focus on clearing out the mines of these evil creatures.

column2: You need to locate this Soulweaver Daine and make sure it is eliminated before it can cause more trouble.
column3: You need to locate this Soulweaver Daine and make sure it is eliminated before it can cause more trouble.

column2: And make sure you hurry up. This creature seems capable of creation so the more we wait the more time it has to create fresh undead.
column3: And make sure you hurry up. This creature seems capable of creation so the more we wait the more time it has to create fresh undead.

column2: The Mines is a dark place, so I recommend taking with you some potions of night vision.
column3: The Mines is a dark place, so I recommend taking with you some potions of night vision.

column2: &e[Wallitz]&f It looks ancient so hopefully it has weakened through the ages and won’t give you too much trouble.
column3: &e[Wallitz]&f Parece antiguo, así que con suerte se ha debilitado con el paso de los años y no te dará demasiados problemas.

column2: &7&oAn ancient guardian on a bridge, this should be fun...
column3: &7&oUn antiguo guardián en un puente, esto debería ser divertido...

column2: &7Interact with the nearby &fOld Dwarf Jotun &7teleporter to start the quest.
column3: &7Interactúa con el teletransportador cercano &fViejo Enano Jotun &7para iniciar la misión.

column2: &e[Wallitz]&f Managed to beat that old guardian, eh? Excellent work. Would not expect anything else from our fifty-sixth-best guild member!
column3: &e[Wallitz]&f Lograste vencer a ese viejo guardián, ¿eh? Excelente trabajo. ¡No esperaría menos de nuestro quincuagésimo sexto mejor miembro del gremio!

column2: &7&oLet's see if &e&oWallitz&7&o has more tasks for me.
column3: &7&oVeamos si &e&oWallitz&7&o tiene más tareas para mí.

column2: Ah, just in time. So, we looked at the remains of that weaver creature that was down in the mines.
column3: Ah, just in time. So, we looked at the remains of that weaver creature that was down in the mines.

column2: We are certain that it is a Nether being. How it made its way up here, I have no clue.
column3: We are certain that it is a Nether being. How it made its way up here, I have no clue.

column2: We had managed to open the gate that was blocking the way into that underground city you mentioned.
column3: We had managed to open the gate that was blocking the way into that underground city you mentioned.

column2: You need to go there and see what you can uncover...
column3: Necesitas ir allí y ver qué puedes descubrir...

column2: Oh, right! There is a guardian blocking the way into the city, and it doesn’t look friendly so you will need to deal with that first.
column3: Oh, right! There is a guardian blocking the way into the city, and it doesn’t look friendly so you will need to deal with that first.

column2: &e[Wallitz]&f Don’t bother trying to talk to the dwarves, we had a guild member try that already. It did not go so well…
column3: &e[Wallitz]&f No te molestes en intentar hablar con los enanos, ya tuvimos un miembro del gremio que lo intentó. No salió muy bien…

column2: &7Interact with the nearby &fDwarf Olav &7teleporter to start the quest.
column3: &7Interactúa con el teletransportador cercano &fEnano Olav &7para iniciar la misión.

column2: &e[Wallitz]&f Our forty-seventh-best guild member returns! I hear from our scouts that the dwarves were completely gone mentally. I wonder if their greed led them to some horrible fate?
column3: &e[Wallitz]&f ¡Regresa nuestro cuadragésimo séptimo mejor miembro del gremio! Escucho de nuestros exploradores que los enanos estaban completamente perdidos mentalmente. Me pregunto si su codicia los llevó a un destino horrible.

column2: &7&oI should speak to &e&oWallitz&7&o when I am ready to continue.
column3: &7&oDebería hablar con &e&oWallitz&7&o cuando esté listo para continuar.

column2: With the guardian gone our scouts were able to go ahead and gather some valuable information.
column3: With the guardian gone our scouts were able to go ahead and gather some valuable information.

column2: The city is ancient, way older than you, me and this guild.
column3: La ciudad es antigua, mucho más vieja que tú, yo y este gremio.

column2: A dwarven city, seems like they settled there a long time ago and were mining in the area.
column3: A dwarven city, seems like they settled there a long time ago and were mining in the area.

column2: Our scouts have sighted some of the dwarves, but something is wrong.
column3: Nuestros exploradores han avistado a algunos de los enanos, pero algo anda mal.

column2: They are just shambling about, but they do not appear undead either.
column3: Simplemente deambulan, pero tampoco parecen no-muertos.

column2: We are not sure what is going on. There is a palace at the end of the city, go down there and clear the way to the palace so our guild can examine the city in more detail.
column3: We are not sure what is going on. There is a palace at the end of the city, go down there and clear the way to the palace so our guild can examine the city in more detail.

column2: &e[Wallitz]&f How exciting! Your next mission is to secure the palace and ensure safe passage for our guild members to the next area.
column3: &e[Wallitz]&f ¡Qué emocionante! Tu próxima misión es asegurar el palacio y garantizar un paso seguro para los miembros de nuestro gremio a la siguiente área.

column2: &7&oI feel like this is gonna be a tough one...
column3: &7&oSiento que esta va a ser difícil...

column2: &7Interact with the nearby &fRoyal Guard Sven &7teleporter to start the quest.
column3: &7Interactúa con el teletransportador cercano &fGuardia Real Sven &7para iniciar la misión.

column2: &e[Wallitz]&f Has it been done? Excellent. We are not sure exactly what we should do with the city and the palace after all of this is over. Do you know any people that prefer staying deep underground in large dark caves? Anyway, the rest of the guild members are moving ahead and will scout the next area.
column3: &e[Wallitz]&f ¿Ya está hecho? Excelente. No estamos seguros exactamente qué deberíamos hacer con la ciudad y el palacio después de que todo esto termine. ¿Conoces a alguien que prefiera quedarse en lo profundo bajo tierra en grandes cuevas oscuras? De todos modos, el resto de los miembros del gremio están avanzando y explorarán la siguiente área.

column2: &7&oI wonder what the dwarves managed to find all the way in the depths...
column3: &7&oMe pregunto qué lograron encontrar los enanos en las profundidades...

column2: I have some interesting information to share with you.
column3: Tengo información interesante para compartir contigo.

column2: We have taken a closer look at the dwarves you were fighting.
column3: Hemos examinado más de cerca a los enanos contra los que estabas luchando.

column2: Judging by their armor they are as old as the city itself.
column3: A juzgar por su armadura, son tan antiguos como la propia ciudad.

column2: And as you have noticed they are under heavy corruption.
column3: Y como has notado, están bajo una fuerte corrupción.

column2: We have concluded that whatever gave them this eternal life also caused the corruption.
column3: Hemos concluido que lo que les dio esta vida eterna también causó la corrupción.

column2: The corruption was most likely caused by whatever was trying to mentally dominate them or change them.
column3: The corruption was most likely caused by whatever was trying to mentally dominate them or change them.

column2: Dwarves are quite tough mentally, living underground comes with its benefits, I guess.
column3: Dwarves are quite tough mentally, living underground comes with its benefits, I guess.

column2: We need to find the source of this corruption. Anything that is that powerful must be destroyed.
column3: We need to find the source of this corruption. Anything that is that powerful must be destroyed.

column2: The dwarves must have dug too deep and reached a Nether portal…
column3: Los enanos deben haber cavado demasiado profundo y alcanzado un portal al Nether…

column2: Well let’s not be too grim about this, you don’t get to visit the Nether every day.
column3: Well let’s not be too grim about this, you don’t get to visit the Nether every day.

column2: &e[Wallitz]&f There are various fiends around the quarry so watch your back.
column3: &e[Wallitz]&f Hay varios demonios alrededor de la cantera, así que ten cuidado.

column2: &7&oI should head to the quarry and use the lift.
column3: &7&oDebería ir a la cantera y usar el ascensor.

column2: &7Interact with the nearby &fDwarf Berge &7teleporter to start the quest.
column3: &7Interactúa con el teletransportador cercano &fEnano Berge &7para iniciar la misión.

column2: &e[Wallitz]&f Got the lift moving I see. I feel like stuff is about to get serious, some of those fiends you slayed were from the Nether.
column3: &e[Wallitz]&f Veo que pusiste el ascensor en marcha. Siento que las cosas se van a poner serias, algunos de esos demonios que mataste eran del Nether.

column2: Well, if it isn’t our thirty-sixth-best guild member.
column3: Bueno, si no es nuestro trigésimo sexto mejor miembro del gremio.

column2: The next area we are sending you to seems to be some kind of quarry?
column3: ¿La siguiente área a la que te enviamos parece ser una especie de cantera?

column2: I guess the dwarves just kept digging further down.
column3: Supongo que los enanos simplemente siguieron cavando más abajo.

column2: The madmen should have considered the dangers of digging that deep down...
column3: Los locos deberían haber considerado los peligros de cavar tan profundo...

column2: But, too late for that now. It would be of great help if you could go to the quarry and figure out how to get the lift moving.
column3: But, too late for that now. It would be of great help if you could go to the quarry and figure out how to get the lift moving.

column2: &e[Wallitz]&f Use the TNT to blow your way through the mines until you reach the Nether entrance and kill anything that might be a threat to the guild.

wave=1:message=&8[Gladius] &fToday's main event! A legendary fighter came all the way to the arena to test his might against the toughest monsters from all the land! But before that, here's a rookie fighting some zombies.
column3: wave=1:message=&8[Gladius] &fEl evento principal de hoy! ¡Un luchador legendario vino hasta la arena para probar su poder contra los monstruos más duros de toda la tierra! Pero antes de eso, aquí hay un novato luchando contra algunos zombis.

column2: wave=2:message=&8[Gladius] &fWould you look at that, they at least know how to wave their arms! That was just the warmup, let's start putting on some pressure!
column3: wave=2:message=&8[Gladius] &f¡Mira eso, al menos saben cómo agitar los brazos! Eso fue solo el calentamiento, ¡comencemos a poner algo de presión!

column2: wave=3:message=&8[Gladius] &fSo you think you know how to fight? Well this wave will put the &cheat &fon! Ha ha ha ha ha!
column3: wave=3:message=&8[Gladius] &f¿Así que crees que sabes pelear? ¡Pues esta ola pondrá el &ccalor&f! Ja ja ja ja ja!

column2: wave=4:message=&8[Gladius] &fAlright I guess they can take the heat! Ladies and gentlemen, strap on, we might be in for a show!
column3: wave=4:message=&8[Gladius] &fMuy bien, ¡supongo que pueden soportar el calor! Damas y caballeros, pónganse el cinturón, ¡podríamos estar en un espectáculo!

column2: wave=5:message=&8[Gladius] &fI found this &cweird creature &foutside, and I thought putting it in the arena would be funny!
column3: wave=5:message=&8[Gladius] &fEncontré esta &cextraña criatura &fafuera, ¡y pensé que ponerla en la arena sería divertido!

column2: wave=6:message=&8[Gladius] &fSeems like you can handle small groups of enemies just fine, &clet's try scaling that up!
column3: wave=6:message=&8[Gladius] &fParece que puedes manejar pequeños grupos de enemigos muy bien, &c¡intentemos escalar eso!

column2: wave=7:message=&8[Gladius] &fSo you think you can truly challenge the arena? We shall see...
column3: wave=7:message=&8[Gladius] &fEntonces, ¿crees que realmente puedes desafiar la arena? Veremos...

column2: wave=8:message=&8[Gladius] &fNot bad, but what if every enemy is a &cmelee &fenemy?
column3: wave=8:message=&8[Gladius] &fNo está mal, pero ¿y si todos los enemigos son enemigos &ccuerpo a cuerpo&f?

column2: wave=9:message=&8[Gladius] &fNice, nice, but what if they're all &cranged &finstead?
column3: wave=9:message=&8[Gladius] &fBien, bien, pero ¿y si en su lugar están todos &ca distancia&f?

column2: wave=10:message=&8[Gladius] &fCareful now, a &cbad doggo &fseems to have wandered into the arena! Where did it even come from?
column3: wave=10:message=&8[Gladius] &f¡Cuidado ahora, un &cbad doggo &fparece haber entrado en la arena! ¿De dónde vino?

column2: wave=11:message=&8[Gladius] &fAlright folks we got animal control to deal with the bad doggos, we're back in business!
column3: wave=11:message=&8[Gladius] &fMuy bien amigos, tenemos control de animales para lidiar con los perros malos, ¡we're back in business!

column2: wave=12:message=&8[Gladius] &fIt seems like the audience is clamoring for &cmore&f! Well, let's give it to them!
column3: wave=12:message=&8[Gladius] &f¡Parece que la audiencia está clamando por &cmás&f! Bueno, ¡vamos a dárselo!

column2: wave=13:message=&8[Gladius] &fSeems like the custodians got bored and gave the arena creatures &2poison&f! Let's see where this goes...
column3: wave=13:message=&8[Gladius] &f¡Parece que los guardianes se aburrieron y le dieron a las criaturas de la arena &2veneno&f! Veamos a dónde va esto...

column2: wave=14:message=&8[Gladius] &fWell that was... boring! Whoever gave those guys poison is fired! Come up with something better next time!
column3: wave=14:message=&8[Gladius] &fBueno, eso fue... ¡aburrido! ¡Quien les diera veneno a esos tipos está despedido! ¡Inventa algo mejor la próxima vez!

column2: wave=15:message=&8[Gladius] &fAnd here we have this year's prize-winning &4hog&f! It got first place for ugliness and meanness! Everyone give a round of applause for &4Mr. Oinkers&f!
column3: wave=15:message=&8[Gladius] &f¡Y aquí tenemos el &4cerdo&f premiado de este año! ¡Obtuvo el primer lugar en fealdad y maldad! ¡Todos aplaudan a &4Mr. Oinkers&f!

column2: wave=16:message=&8[Gladius] &fMr. Oinkers is now bacon! Here comes &cMr. Oinker's fans&f, flooding the arena to get their revenge!
column3: wave=16:message=&8[Gladius] &f¡Mr. Oinkers ahora es beicon! ¡Aquí vienen los &cfans de Mr. Oinker&f, inundando la arena para vengarse!

column2: wave=17:message=&8[Gladius] &fIt would seem as though our arena challenger thinks they have a shot! But can they deal with even more &cpowerful &ffoes?
column3: wave=17:message=&8[Gladius] &f¡Parecería que nuestro retador en la arena piensa que tiene una oportunidad! Pero, ¿pueden enfrentarse a enemigos aún más &cpoderosos&f?

column2: wave=18:message=&8[Gladius] &fThe &cfencing club &fand the &carchery club &fare having a contest! Let's see which one does better!
column3: wave=18:message=&8[Gladius] &f¡El &cclub de esgrima &fy el &cclub de tiro con arco &ftienen un concurso! ¡A ver cuál lo hace mejor!

column2: wave=19:message=&8[Gladius] &fThe fencing club didn't so so hot, let's see what the &carchery club&f has for us!
column3: wave=19:message=&8[Gladius] &fEl club de esgrima no lo hizo tan bien, ¡a ver qué nos depara con el club de tiro con arco!

column2: wave=20:message=&8[Gladius] &fSeems like the archery club didn't do so hot either! It seems like our challenger has begun attracting the attention of some of our top gladiators! Introducing &2Zoltan, the Pride of the Zombies&f!
column3: wave=20:message=&8[Gladius] &f¡Parece que al club de tiro con arco tampoco le fue tan bien! ¡Parece que nuestro retador ha comenzado a atraer la atención de algunos de nuestros mejores gladiadores! ¡Presentamos a &2Zoltan, el orgullo de los zombis&f!

column2: wave=21:message=&8[Gladius] &fUnbelievable! Seems like this rookie defeated Zoltan! Do we have a potential new champion in our hands?
column3: wave=21:message=&8[Gladius] &f¡Increíble! ¡Parece que este novato derrotó a Zoltan! ¿Tenemos un potencial nuevo campeón en nuestras manos?

column2: wave=22:message=&8[Gladius] &fSpectators are starting to place their bets! How far can today's contestant go?
column3: wave=22:message=&8[Gladius] &f¡Los espectadores comienzan a hacer sus apuestas! ¿Hasta dónde puede llegar el concursante de hoy?

column2: wave=23:message=&8[Gladius] &fDon't look away now, this wave's enemies all have &cwithering &fattacks!
column3: wave=23:message=&8[Gladius] &f¡No mires hacia otro lado ahora, todos los enemigos de esta ola tienen ataques &cwither&f!

column2: wave=24:message=&8[Gladius] &fSeems like some pretty big arena names are starting to arrive to stop this challenger! Stay tuned!
column3: wave=24:message=&8[Gladius] &f¡Parece que algunos nombres bastante importantes de la arena están comenzando a llegar para detener a este retador! ¡Manténganse al tanto!

column2: wave=25:message=&8[Gladius] &fHere comes &bAgdluak&f, the archer from the Great North! Beware of its &bfrost&f!
column3: wave=25:message=&8[Gladius] &f¡Aquí viene &bAgdluak&f, el arquero del Gran Norte! ¡Cuidado con su &bescarcha&f!

column2: wave=26:message=&8[Gladius] &fThat was a pretty cool fight! I am &cswarming &fwith excitement to see what's next!
column3: wave=26:message=&8[Gladius] &f¡Esa fue una pelea heladora! ¡Tengo un &chormigueo &fpor ver qué sigue!

column2: wave=27:message=&8[Gladius] &fI've been told the arena grows harder! &cZombies immune to arrows, skeletons that freeze their opponents &f- what will they think of next!?
column3: wave=27:message=&8[Gladius] &f¡Me han dicho que la arena se vuelve más dura! &cZombis inmunes a las flechas, esqueletos que congelan a sus oponentes &f- ¿¡en qué pensarán a continuación!?

column2: wave=28:message=&8[Gladius] &fIt's time to show off those &cfencing &fskills! Remember, it's all about the legwork!
column3: wave=28:message=&8[Gladius] &f¡Es hora de mostrar esas habilidades de &cesgrima&f! ¡Recuerde, la clave está en las piernas!

column2: wave=29:message=&8[Gladius] &fAnd now, let's have some &ctarget practice&f! The challenger is the target!
column3: wave=29:message=&8[Gladius] &f¡Y ahora, hagamos algo de &cpráctica de tiro&f! ¡El retador es el objetivo!

column2: wave=30:message=&8[Gladius] &fA true arena champion approaches! The &2Southern Viper &fonce again seeks to &cpoison &ftheir enemies to death with his &cthousand poisons&f!
column3: wave=30:message=&8[Gladius] &f¡Se acerca un verdadero campeón de la arena! ¡La &2Víbora del Sur &fbusca una vez más &cenvenenar &fa sus enemigos hasta la muerte con sus &cmil venenos&f!

column2: wave=31:message=&8[Gladius] &fThe Southern Viper has fallen! The crowd goes wild! What a day, ladies and gentlemen, what a day!
column3: wave=31:message=&8[Gladius] ¡La Víbora del Sur ha caído! ¡La multitud se vuelve loca! ¡Qué día, señoras y señores, qué día!

column2: wave=32:message=&8[Gladius] &fI have been told that the arena custodians are done messing around and are staring to let loose! Can our challenger survive this?
column3: wave=32:message=&8[Gladius] &f¡Me han dicho que los guardias de la arena han terminado de perder el tiempo y están empezando a soltarse! ¿Puede nuestro retador sobrevivir a esto?

column2: wave=33:message=&8[Gladius] &fSeems like some enemies got their hands on some of Southern Viper's &cpoisons&f! You do not want to get hit by those, ladies and gentlemen!
column3: wave=33:message=&8[Gladius] &f¡Parece que algunos enemigos se apoderaron de algunos de los &cvenenos &fde la Víbora del Su! ¡No querrán ser golpeados por eso, damas y caballeros!

column2: wave=34:message=&8[Gladius] &fBobby, make sure you put 1,000 Elite Coins on these contestants dying for me - no, no, 1,000 Elite Coins - wait was this thing on? I mean, onwards to the next wave!
column3: wave=34:message=&8[Gladius] &fBobby, asegúrate de apostar 1.000 Elite Coins en estos concursantes mueren - no, no, 1.000 Elite Coins - espera, ¿esto estaba encendido? Quiero decir, ¡hacia la próxima ola!

column2: wave=35:message=&8[Gladius] &fLadies and gentlemen, what a rare treat! It would seems as the very &aWood League Jester &fhas stepped up to fight! What delightful &2tricks &fdoes he have for us today?
column3: wave=35:message=&8[Gladius] &fDamas y caballeros, ¡qué delicia rara! ¡Parece que el mismísimo &aWood League Jester &fha dado un paso al frente para luchar! ¿Qué deliciosos &2trucos &ftiene para nosotros hoy?

column2: wave=36:message=&8[Gladius] &fWhat a lovely show ladies and gentlemen, give it up for &aThe Jester&f!
column3: wave=36:message=&8[Gladius] &f¡Qué hermoso espectáculo, damas y caballeros, den un fuerte aplauso para &aThe Jester&f!

column2: wave=37:message=&8[Gladius] &fBobby, how is my bet doing? What do you mean 10,000 Elite Coins, I told you to put 1,000 on there! Uh, pump them, &cpump the powers up&f!
column3: wave=37:message=&8[Gladius] &fBobby, ¿cómo va mi apuesta? ¿Qué quieres decir con 10,000 Elite Coins? ¡Te dije que apostaras 1,000! ¡Uh, mejóralos, &cméjora los poderes&f!

column2: wave=38:message=&8[Gladius] &fBobby you're killing me here! Uh, dump some &cswordsmen &fon there, I need to deal with something real quick...
column3: wave=38:message=&8[Gladius] &f¡Bobby, me estás matando! Uh, arroja algunos &cespadachines &fahí, necesito lidiar con algo muy rápido...

column2: wave=39:message=&8[Gladius] &fWhat do you mean no refunds? I didn't even want to - ahem, I mean, a legion of &carchers &fhave come from far to show off their skills!
column3: wave=39:message=&8[Gladius] &f¿A qué te refieres con que no hay reembolsos? Ni siquiera quería - ejem, quiero decir, ¡una legión de &carqueros &fha venido desde lejos para mostrar sus habilidades!

column2: wave=40:message=&8[Gladius] &fLadies an gentlemen, for, uh, random reasons, I have invited the strongest fighter I can summon! Meet &4Crucios, the Bearer of Curses&f!
column3: wave=40:message=&8[Gladius] &f¡Damas y caballeros, por, eh, razones aleatorias, he invitado al luchador más fuerte que puedo convocar! ¡Conoce a &4Crucios, el Portador de Maldiciones&f!

column2: wave=41:message=&8[Gladius] &fCrucios has been defeated!? What has the world come to?
column3: wave=41:message=&8[Gladius] &f¿¡Crucios ha sido derrotado!? ¿El mundo se ha vuelto loco?

column2: wave=42:message=&8[Gladius] &fA wealthy for now patron has decided to throw in free healthcare to arena enemies! Will they do better with &2healing&f?
column3: wave=42:message=&8[Gladius] &f¡Un, por ahora, rico inversor ha decidido brindar atención médica gratuita a los enemigos de la arena! ¿Lo harán mejor con la &2curación&f?

column2: wave=43:message=&8[Gladius] &f&cWither&f, &cpoison, &cfire&f throw in everything you have! Do you even know how much is on the line!?
column3: wave=43:message=&8[Gladius] &f¡&cWhiter&f, &cveneno&f, &cfuego&f, arroja todo lo que tengas! ¿¡Sabes cuánto hay en juego!?

column2: wave=44:message=&8[Gladius] &fThis is clearly not working, let me think of something...
column3: wave=44:message=&8[Gladius] &fEsto claramente no funciona, déjame pensar en algo...

column2: wave=45:message=&8[Gladius] &fHere is one of the top gladiators of the Wood League Arena! &cThousand Blades &fapproaches once again with his &cinnumerable projectiles&f! He better win!
column3: wave=45:message=&8[Gladius] &f¡Aquí está uno de los mejores gladiadores del Arena Liga de Madera! ¡&cThousand Blades &fse acerca una vez más con sus &cinnumerables proyectiles&f! ¡Será mejor que gane!

column2: wave=46:message=&8[Gladius] &fThousand Blades has fallen! It just seems like you can't get competent gladiators these days! That's fine, you'll see! You'll all see! &cRelease the swarm!
column3: wave=46:message=&8[Gladius] &f¡Thousand Blades ha caido! ¡Parece que no puedes conseguir gladiadores competentes en estos días! ¡Está bien, ya verás! ¡Todos veréis! &c¡Libera al enjambre!

column2: wave=47:message=&8[Gladius] &fIf swarms don't work, throw in &cmore powers&f! Throw in all of the powers!
column3: wave=47:message=&8[Gladius] &fSi los enjambres no funcionan, ¡&cagrega más poderes&f! ¡Agrega todos los poderes!

column2: wave=48:message=&8[Gladius] &fWe are starting to run out of options here! Are these all of the &cswordsmen &fwe have left?
column3: wave=48:message=&8[Gladius] &f¡Estamos empezando a quedarnos sin opciones aquí! ¿Son estos todos los &cespadachines &fque nos quedan?

column2: wave=49:message=&8[Gladius] &fAlright send all we have left, we have no other options! Move forth, &carchers&f!
column3: wave=49:message=&8[Gladius] &fMuy bien, envía todo lo que nos queda, ¡no tenemos otras opciones! ¡Adelante, &carqueros&f!

column2: wave=50:message=&8[Gladius] &fI guess this is it for me... I have no option but to declare - wait, who is that in the distance? Is that &4Uther, the Champion of the Wood League Arena&f? Ladies and gentlemen, match set and over, our contestant has no chance of winning here! They shall be &csmitten &fby our champion!
column3: wave=50:message=&8[Gladius] &fSupongo que esto es todo para mí... No tengo más opción que declarar - espera, ¿quién es ese en la distancia? ¿Ese es &4Uther, el Campeón de la Arena Liga de Madera&f? Damas y caballeros, juego, set y partido, ¡nuestro concursante no tiene ninguna posibilidad de ganar aquí! ¡Serán &cheridos &fpor nuestro campeón!

column2: wave=51:message=&8[Gladius the Destitute] &fUnbelievable, Uther has been defeated! We have a new arena champion! I would be incredibly excited if I wasn't so terribly in debt now!
column3: wave=51:message=&8[Gladius el Indigente] &f¡Increíble, Uther ha sido derrotado! ¡Tenemos un nuevo campeón de arena! ¡Estaría increíblemente emocionado si no estuviera tan terriblemente endeudado ahora!

column2: Nor is it to be thought...that man is either the oldest or the last of earth's masters, or that the common bulk of life and substance walks alone. The Old Ones were, the Old Ones are, and the Old Ones shall be. Not in the spaces we know, but between them, they walk serene and primal, undimensioned and to us unseen. Yog-Sothoth knows the gate. Yog-Sothoth is the gate. Yog-Sothoth is the key and guardian of the gate. Past, present, future, all are one in Yog-Sothoth. He knows where the Old Ones broke through of old, and where They shall break through again. He knows where They had trod earth's fields, and where They still tread them, and why no one can behold Them as They tread. By Their smell can men sometimes know Them near, but of Their semblance can no man know, saving only in the features of those They have begotten on mankind; and of those are there many sorts, differing in likeness from man's truest eidolon to that shape without sight or substance which is Them. They walk unseen and foul in lonely places where the Words have been spoken and the Rites howled through at their Seasons. The wind gibbers with Their voices, and the earth mutters with Their consciousness. They bend the forest and crush the city, yet may not forest or city behold the hand that smites. Kadath in the cold waste hath known Them, and what man knows Kadath? The ice desert of the South and the sunken isles of Ocean hold stones whereon Their seal is engraver, but who hath seen the deep frozen city or the sealed tower long garlanded with seaweed and barnacles? Great Cthulhu is Their cousin, yet can he spy Them only dimly. Iä! Shub-Niggurath! As a foulness shall ye know Them. Their hand is at your throats, yet ye see Them not; and Their habitation is even one with your guarded threshold. Yog-Sothoth is the key to the gate, whereby the spheres meet. Man rules now where They ruled once; They shall soon rule where man rules now. After summer is winter, after winter summer. They wait patient and potent, for here shall They reign again.
column3: Ni se debe pensar que el hombre es el más antiguo o el último de los maestros de la Tierra, o que la masa común de vida y sustancia camina sola. Los Antiguos eran, los Antiguos son, y los Antiguos serán. No en los espacios que conocemos, sino entre ellos, caminan serenos y primordiales, sin dimensiones y para nosotros invisibles. Yog-Sothoth conoce la puerta. Yog-Sothoth es la puerta. Yog-Sothoth es la llave y guardián de la puerta. Pasado, presente, futuro, todos son uno en Yog-Sothoth. Él sabe dónde los Antiguos rompieron a través de antaño, y donde romperán a través de nuevo. Él sabe dónde pisaron los campos de la tierra, y donde aún los pisan, y por qué nadie puede contemplarlos mientras pisan. Por su olor, a veces los hombres pueden saber que están cerca, pero de su apariencia no puede saberlo ningún hombre, excepto en los rasgos de aquellos que han engendrado en la humanidad; y de esos hay muchos tipos, diferenciándose en semejanza desde la verdadera eidolón del hombre hasta esa forma sin vista ni sustancia que son ellos. Caminan invisibles y repugnantes en lugares solitarios donde las Palabras han sido habladas y los Ritos aullados en sus Estaciones. El viento chilla con sus voces, y la tierra murmura con su conciencia. Doblan el bosque y aplastan la ciudad, pero ni el bosque ni la ciudad pueden contemplar la mano que golpea. Kadath en el frío desierto los ha conocido, ¿y quién conoce Kadath? El desierto de hielo del Sur y las islas hundidas del Océano tienen piedras en las que está grabado su sello, pero ¿quién ha visto la ciudad congelada o la torre sellada durante mucho tiempo adornada con algas marinas y percebes? El gran Cthulhu es su primo, sin embargo, sólo puede espiarlos débilmente. ¡Iä! ¡Shub-Niggurath! Como una inmundicia los conoceréis. Su mano está en vuestras gargantas, sin embargo, no los veis; y su morada es incluso una con vuestro umbral vigilado. Yog-Sothoth es la llave de la puerta, por la cual los esferas se encuentran. El hombre gobierna ahora donde una vez gobernaron ellos; pronto gobernarán donde ahora gobierna el hombre. Después del verano viene el invierno, después del invierno el verano. Esperan pacientes y poderosos, porque aquí reinarán de nuevo.
